Name: Ahsoka Tano
Key: '''Clone Wars''' | '''Star Wars: The Clone Wars (Season 7)''' | '''Star Wars: Rebels'''
Summary: Ahsoka Tano, was the Padawan of famed Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker during the Clone Wars. A talented young Togruta who was originally under the care of Jedi Master Plo Koon, she was later instructed by Jedi Grand Master Yoda to seek Skywalker's tutelage. Despite the Jedi Knight's initial misgivings about her, Ahsoka proved to be an excellent apprentice and a valuable ally who played a key role in numerous pivotal events of the Clone Wars.

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: America Chavez (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: America Chavez is a extra-dimensional being from the Utopian Parallel with the ability to travel the Multiverse using large, star-shaped portals. After manifesting her abilities, she became knowledgeable of different universes which she visited, also learning in the process that no alternate selves of her existed within the Multiverse. Chavez was later targeted by Scarlet Witch, who sought to acquire her powers, leading to her being relentlessly hunted down by inter-dimensional creatures and monsters. Believing she could defeat her enemies with the Book of Vishanti, she took up the help of Doctor Strange, until he betrayed her. Using a portal, she escaped to another universe, where she was rescued by another Doctor Strange. Chavez and Strange continued to elude Scarlet Witch through different universes and searched for the book, however, they were arrested by the Illuminati in the process; their quest fell futile when Scarlet Witch destroyed the book and abducted Chavez. Strange was able to rescue Chavez before the Scarlet Witch was able to absorb her powers. In the aftermath, Chavez joined the ranks of the Masters of the Mystic Arts.

Name: Angel of Valor
Summary: The Angel of Valor are the weakest and most numerous of the angels that serve the gods, they are used as foot soldiers of their deities. while following the orders of higher ranking angels or even clerics of their gods.

Name: Artus Cimber
Summary: Artus Cimber is the son of a thief and member of the Harpers who, upon exploring some old ruins, discovered the Ring of Winter, a relic of the Evil Goddess of Ice, Auril. Determined to never allow the ring to fall into the hands of evil, Artus has been on the run ever since, made immortal by the devious power of the ring. Artus is widely regarded as an immensely intelligent scholar and renowned adventurer aside from his status of guardian of the artifact.

Name: Ash Ketchum (I Choose You)
Key: '''Himself''' | '''Start of Adventure''' | '''Mid-Adventure Pokémon''' | '''End of M20/M21 Pikachu'''
Summary: nan

Name: Atropal
Summary: Atropals are stillborn godlings who have spontaneously risen as undead. A foul aura surrounds the Abomination, snuffing out weaker life and draining the souls of those near it. When one rises the Gods cringe and seal them in tombs for all time. But sometimes the barriers are broken and one is freed to wreak havoc on the multiverse.

Name: Auntie Ethel
Summary: Why are you so cruel? Please. It's you lot who come to me. All you do is want - to be prettier, to be richer, to be loved. People are their own worst enemies, petal. I just let them see it.

Name: B-1 Lancer
Summary: The Rockwell (Now part of Boeing) B-1 Lancer is a four engine, supersonic variable sweep swing strategic bomber developed in the 1960s originally to replace the aging B-52 Stratofortress. The bomber's original design has evolved into the current B-1B Lancer, a low-level penetration bomber with a long range while retaining supersonic capability.

Name: B-2 Spirit
Summary: The B-2 Spirit is a 2-seat stealth bomber developed by Northrop-Grumman. It is a heavy penetration strategic bomber sporting low observable stealth technology for piercing into high density air defenses. It is capable of carrying both conventional and nuclear payloads. There are currently 21 built.

Name: B-52 Stratofortress
Summary: The B-52 Stratofortress is a strategic bomber developed by Boeing. It is a long range jet powered aircraft and has been operated by the USAF since the 1950s and still continues to serve the USAF to this day with continuing upgrades and maintenance. The B-52 made its first flight on April 1952. It was also made to replace the earlier Convair B-36 peacemaker, especially in the role of carrying nuclear weapons for Cold War-era deterrence missions.

Name: Bailey Hoskins (Worst X-Man Ever)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Bailey Hoskins thought of himself as an unremarkable boy, part of no clique and having no notable hobbies, until the day his parents reveal to him that he may be a mutant. Excited at the prospects, he heads to Xavier's to find out about himself, and learns he only has the ability to blow himself up like a "human firework".

Name: Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser
Summary: The Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser was a large class of heavy cruisers in the United States Navy commissioned during or shortly after World War II. Fourteen Baltimores were completed, more than any other class of heavy cruiser, along with three ships of the Oregon City-class sub-class. Fast and heavily armed, the Baltimore cruisers were mainly used in World War II to protect the fast aircraft carriers in battle groups from air attack. Additionally, their 8"/55 (203mm) main guns and secondary 5"/38 (127mm) guns were regularly used to bombard land targets in support of amphibious landings. After the war, only six Baltimores and two Oregon City-class ships remained in service, while the rest were moved to the reserve fleet.

Name: Barbed Devil
Summary: Barbed Devils, also referred to as Hamatulas in their infernal tongue, serve as guardians of Baatorian vaults and elite warriors in devilish armies. The devils themselves are relatively low on the devil evolutionary scale, though this does not denote a lower form of power- indeed, their strength makes them the perfect servants of craftier devils.

Name: Barry (Pokémon)
Summary: Barry is the childhood friend of Lucas and the rival in Sinnoh. Always in a hurry, Barry is the reason that Lucas and him get Pokémon, as Barry convinces his friend to go search for the Red Gyarados, and in the process, they run into Professor Rowan, his starter Pokémon, and some wild Starlys. The duo's adventure begins when they use Rowan's Pokémon to defend themselves.

Name: Basilisk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Basilisks are reptilian magical creatures bestowed with the capability to turn enemies to stone. Their abilities are renowned enough that a seasoned adventurer will recognize the threat of remaining in the area when they begin seeing remarkably life-like statues of frightened wildlife.

Name: Bede (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fifth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Bede (Japanese: ビート Beet) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Marnie. He initially specializes in Psychic-type Pokémon, but is eventually scouted by Opal to succeed her as a Fairy-type Gym Leader, and thus changes his specialty type accordingly. As the Gym Leader of Ballonlea Stadium, he gives the Fairy Badge to Trainers who defeat him.

Name: Behir
Summary: Behirs are dragon-like creatures of electric origin that despise their brethren, to the point of driving them out of their territories if possible and, if not, leaving the area. They were created by Storm Dragons as weapons in a great war against the dragons, though nowadays are often kept as pets of powerful spellcasters and serve as signs of good omens for certain religions, notably in Chult.

Name: Bianca (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End and Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (BW2)'''
Summary: Bianca (ベル, Bel) is a Pokémon Trainer from the Unova region.

Name: Black King (Trolls' session)
Summary: Tier: At least 8-B, likely 8-A

Name: Black Pudding
Summary: Black Puddings are quasi-sentient globs of viscous black goop, most often found in poorly-lit dungeon halls where it might be dismissed as nothing more than a blot of shadow. In truth, it is a malevolent carnivore that strips and dissolves even the most durable materials, leaving behind only stone. It is a painful and not altogether quick way to perish.

Name: Bloodfire Ooze
Summary: Created from a dark ritual, a Bloodfire Ooze is an ooze that's made from people's blood with a bit of a demon added in. They are mindless beasts that seek out blood to absorb and use their fire abilities in battle, some Bloodfire Oozes are even more horrid when made by an extraplaner for they add a pseudonatural creature template which makes the Bloodfire a Blight Bloodfire

Name: Blue (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (First Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Second Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Third Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fourth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fifth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Sixth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Seventh Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Champion Battle)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Blue Oak was the rival in the first Generation of Pokémon. Characterized by his rude and crude personality, Blue embarked on his Pokémon journey at the same time as his rival, Red and was always one step ahead of him no matter where he went. Cocky, arrogant and even a little devious, Blue quickly found himself becoming the Pokémon Master of Kanto, only to be defeated by Red.

Name: Bone Naga
Summary: Bone Nagas are a member of the immortal species known as nagas. They were created by the mighty Creator Race Sarrukh, though they are ultimately an incomplete perversion of true nagas. During the ritual made to cement the naga's immortality, yuan-ti necromantic rituals rendered the creature undead, twisting them into servants of the yuan-ti instead, and with merely a fraction of the power their siblings possessed.

Name: Breachgnome
Summary: Specialized in fighting within cramped spaces, a well-positioned Breachgnome can hold off superior enemy forces for a long duration. They are trained to fight alone, although sometimes they work in small units that coordinate to block off several paths at once. They are seldom seen outside Gnome communities, though when are found outside they are often looking for Gnomes to help.

Name: Carmilla Carmine (Hazbin Hotel)
Summary: Carmilla Carmine is one of the many Overlords who appeared in Hazbin Hotel alongside Alastor and Vox. Carmilla specializes in the production of Hell's Angelic Weaponry, and she was the first ever Sinner to kill an Exorcist,[1] which would lead to Vaggie seeking Carmilla's help to fight off the Angelic Armies in the Finale. Not much is known of her past with her origins still being unknown.

Name: Cheren (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gym Battle)'''
Summary: Cheren, "The one who seeks the right path" is a main character in Pokémon Black/White and its sequel, Pokémon Black/White 2. Cheren, Bianca and Hilbert all went off on their Pokémon journey on the same day and thus their individual journeys intersected quite often, with Cheren occasionally finding himself duking it out with Hilbert and fighting by his side against Team Plasma. Though Cheren sometimes comes off as cold and distant, he's actually a good hearted and very honest person who seeks to do the right thing. He is also very smart and knowledgeable about Pokémon.

Name: Cloud Giant
Summary: Second tallest of the true Giants, the Cloud Giants are an aloof race, viewing all others barring Storm Giants as beneath them- fitting, given their proclivity to reside in castles which float on clouds. Alongside their impressive physical strength they have innate magical abilities, being able to levitate objects among other things.

Name: Colress
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 4)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon World Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Plasma Frigate)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Tree)'''
Summary: However, I disagree!

Name: Create-A-Bot
Summary: Create-A-Bot is the playable character in the 2007 games Transformers: Autobots and Transformers: Decepticons. He is a cybertronian that can turn into multiple forms.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: Dagger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tandy Bowen’s life started in privilege, but it was a life without the love of her parents, that made her decide to run away from home. While living on the streets she met Tyrone Johnson, but they were both kidnapped by scientists that wanted test subjects for their new experimental drugs. Although most of the test subjects died, Tandy and Tyrone survived, and as a side effect awakened powers. Now under the alias of Dagger, she becomes a personification of light that promises to rid the streets of all drugs in an attempt to stop what happened to her from happening to anyone else.

Name: Daku
Summary: Daku is the King of the Insect Enterrans and one of the Seven Enterran Generals. He resembles a Hercules Beetle-knight.

Name: Dao
Summary: Dao are the Genies of Earth. They are known by their greed and malicious nature towards intruders- their long, earthen galleries are pocked with the shine of gemstones revealed by their mining operations. Little does a Dao care for the hardship of others, often using its great wealth to support immense decadence- it is known they grind diamonds into dust and use it as a spice on their foods. The only race they are on friendly terms with are the Efreeti.

Name: Daren Timbide
Summary: Daren Timbide is a general in the Mintar armies and follower of Bane, the god of fear, malice, and bloodshed. Daren follows this ordeal in his conquests, slaughtering any enemy that presents themselves. However, Daren keeps his army in perpetual training rather than attacking- certain in the idea that he could slay any other given army on the continent, he merely bides his time in patient waiting for Bane's orders.

Name: Devourer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Devourers are massive undead that stalk the ethereal and astral planes, looking for travelers. The Devourer absorbs the souls of those it stalks, used to sustain their own unnatural life. They are also known for their grotesque features- they form a miniature of their latest victim's soul, trapped within their otherwise empty chest cavity.

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Djinni (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Djinni are elemental outsiders originating from the Plane of Air. Clothed in riches and in possession of good looks, Djinni are creatures of ease and relaxation, ruling small single-cloud kingdoms in the Plane of Air. Such freedoms afford them their mischief they constantly try to rile up, though they are not malevolent towards mortals. Of all of genie kind, Djinni are the most accepting of servitude, as they believe it is their fate - and, indeed, belief breeds tangible effect in a world of such magic.

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Efreeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Efreeti are immensely powerful fire-elemental genies. Often such genies take to the mortal planes to seek rulership over the desert peoples. Known for their haughtiness and cruelty, though often disguise this as their attempts at order, only admitting to an enlightened sense of self interest. Most of their followers are slaves they captured themselves, be it from the Elemental Plane of Fire or from the Prime. The Efreeti rule the famed City of Brass, a massive citadel for their kind and their nigh-infinite legions.

Name: Eidolon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Eidolon is a type of creature formed from souls, sent to protect a holy site. Once created, an eidolon stalks the holy vaults of the gods, protecting them from any would-be invaders. Oftentimes, an Eidolon will be left with a large, sacred statue to use as a tool for its possession- using the body allows it to wreak havoc upon enemies who might upset the deities and priests that created the mighty creature.

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Ezra Bridger
Summary: Ezra Bridger was a human male Jedi Padawan who, as an orphan on the Outer Rim planet of Lothal, became a rebel fighter and revolutionary leader in the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. He was born to Ephraim and Mira Bridger, two outspoken opponents of the Imperial regime on Lothal. As a boy, his parents were taken prisoner by the Empire, leaving Bridger to fend for himself on the streets of Lothal. He joined the rebel crew of the Ghost five years before the Battle of Yavin and, with his Force-sensitivity having been discovered, became the apprentice of Kanan Jarrus, a Jedi who survived Order 66. Bridger's abilities with the Force grew quickly, which aided in many of the crew's efforts against the Empire.

Name: F-117 Nighthawk
Summary: The F-117 Nighthawk is a single seat, twin engine attack aircraft developed by the secretive Skunk Works division of Lockheed and operated chiefly by the USAF. The aircraft is based on the earlier Have Blue technology demonstrator and was the first operational aircraft to be designed around stealth technology.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Felix Jaeger
Summary: Felix Jaeger is Gotrek's reluctant companion and "rememberer." Felix was a middle child of Gustav and Renata Jaeger, a wealthy Altdorf mercantile family. His three brothers became partners in the Jaeger & Sons firm, but Felix was the black sheep. At the university of Altdorf, he combined his interests in poetry and revolution to write verses advocating nonviolence for a seditious group called the Mock Beggars. This put him at odds with Wolfgang Krassner, a fellow student-revolutionary who believed violent revolution was necessary. The two duelled, and Jaeger killed the other man. For this he was arrested, but he avoided being hanged by the assistance of Zavant Konniger. He was nevertheless expelled from university.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Frost Worm
Summary: Frost Worms are enormous worms that spend their lives tunneling through snow, ice, and even solid stone and earth to search for prey in the frozen wastelands of Faerun and other realms it resides in. It is a hot topic of debate as to whether or not this creature is related to the Purple Worm or the Remorhaz- or even both. A battle between a Frost Worm and a Remorhaz may well lay waste to an entire landscape during the conflict.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Galena Tordrick
Summary: Galena Tordrick is a guardian of devilish cults and leader of a pair of Bone Devil police forces sent to attack those who perform misdeeds to her masters. Originally, she became a Hellfire Warlock to atone for her deeds in life- to use evil in the name of good- however, tasting the power of evil, she has turned fully to the side of Baator and now serves as an oppressor of good.

Name: Ghindul
Summary: Ghindul is one of two leaders of the Kir-lanan species, found at the Wailing Cliffs. His species came into existence during the Time of Troubles, comprised of the divine and negative energy released from the deaths of gods. Ghindul and his followers serve the shadow dragon Glouroth, and are in constant competition with another Kir-lanan sect led by Phaikkul.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Gray Render
Summary: Gray Renders are huge, lumbering monstrosities known for their well-documented strength on the level of giants, as well as their tendency to bond psychically to creatures. For whatever reason, be it from their artificial creation stories or their latent genetics, gray renders have a psychological need to bond to another living creature. Due to their chaotic nature, they make very risky pets, as they are known to claw apart trees on a whim and even destroy houses.

Name: Guardian Naga
Summary: Guardian Nagas are benevolent nagas of particular strength, originating from the time of the Sarrukh, an ancient Creator Race who ruled multiple empires from over 37,000 years ago across Faerun. They are serpent creatures with humanoid heads, most often found protecting areas of potent lore or magical significance, though can be found ruling over tribes of lesser beings such as Lizardfolk or Kobolds. Unlike their fellow nagas, guardian nagas are not of an inherently evil bent, and not prone to assaulting any intruder in their lairs- they attack only if forced, and prefer to give warnings before unleashing their arcane might.

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: Hezrou
Summary: Hezrou act as officers of demonic armies, enforcers of law among the rank and file soldiers. While not as clever as their more powerful brethren, such as the Balor, Hezrou are cunning combatants and direct their soldiers with extreme aggression. Far from cowardly, a Hezrou hungers for combat, and rushes to the front lines to cut swathes through their enemies.

Name: Hill Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Mouth of Grolantor''' | '''Barrowghast''' | '''Maw of Yeenoghu''' | '''Wereboar''' | '''Avalancher''' | '''Scion of Grolantor'''
Summary: Hill Giants are the lowest ranked of the True Giants, and fittingly are both the dumbest and shortest of them, but they're capable of surprisingly cunning actions in combat and they still possess great physical abilities.

Name: Hop (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Late Game/Beginning of Post Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End of Post Game/Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Hop (Japanese: ホップ Hop) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield and Leon's younger brother. He is your main rival throughout the games, eventually undergoing a period of self-doubt after a humiliating defeat at the hands of Bede, as he didn't want to be so weak as to drag down his older brother's name. After his defeat at the hands of the player in the Champion Cup, he eventually decides to work toward becoming a Pokémon Professor.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Hurricane (Real World)
Summary: Hurricanes are massive storm systems that form over the water and move toward land. Threats from hurricanes include high winds, heavy rainfall, storm surge, coastal and inland flooding, rip currents, and tornadoes. These large storms are called typhoons in the North Pacific Ocean and cyclones in other parts of the world.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Iceman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Iceman (Robert "Bobby" Drake) is a fictional character, a superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a founding member of the X-Men. A mutant, Iceman has the ability of cryokinesis where he can freeze anything around him and can also turn his body into ice. Although he is an Omega-level mutant, Drake has yet to tap into his full mutant potential. Over the years he has taken more interest in developing his abilities. One of the original X-Men, Iceman has had a frequent presence in X-Men (and Spider-Man)-related comics, video games, animated series, and movies.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city. Originally these creatures were made by Primus, and even the most wily and secretive of traders will enter into contracts with them- nothing is more straightforward and true than the ideals that forge the Inevitable's will. Inevitables care not for intent or purpose- only for the words written in their contracts. Lethal force is used to ensure such words are stood by.

Name: Iowa-class Battleship
Key: '''Pre-Refit (World War II/Korean War/Vietnam War-era)''' | '''Post-Refit (Persian Gulf War-era)'''
Summary: The Iowa-class battleships were a class of fast battleships designed and fielded by the United States Navy in 1939–1940 to escort their Fast Carrier Task Forces operating in the Pacific Theater during World War II. Four were completed, while two more were laid down but were not finished before the war's end and were ultimately scrapped. Like other third-generation American battleships, the Iowa class emphasized speed in addition to secondary and anti-aircraft batteries.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 9
Summary: This armor was created by Tony Stark before the events of the first Armor Wars storyline, although he was reluctant to use the new armor due to its high capabilities. Tony would later be forced to use the armor against the villain Firepower after the Silver Centurion Armor was destroyed. After defeating Firepower, Tony would continue to use this armor for more missions and battles.

Name: Kanan Jarrus
Summary: Kanan Jarrus (born Caleb Dume) is the protagonist of the Star Wars television show Star Wars Rebels, as well as a Jedi Padawan and a Rebel leader of the Ghost crew. He is the captain of the ship Ghost and also one of the few Jedi who survived both Order 66 and the ensuing Jedi Purge. Surviving both has turned him into a more bitter, cynical, and disillusioned individual that has not used his lightsaber in a long time. However, as the series progresses, Kanan will come to lead a motley crew of freedom fighters against the Empire and eventually take up the lightsaber once more as he transitions from a self-centered and jaded survivor to a heroic and selfless Jedi once more.

Name: Leonal
Summary: Leonals are lion-like celestials hailing from the plains of Elysium, and belong to the Guardinals, a type of angelic cross of abstract goodness and the animals of nature. As such, Leonal are incredible defenders of the natural world, as well as icons of the armies of Mystra, defending the proper usage of magic throughout the Planes.

Name: Lizardfolk
Summary: Lizardfolk are reptilian humanoids native to the world of Toril that tend to dwell in semi-aquatic environments (such as swamplands and coastlines). An exceedingly practical folk, they do not desire riches or knowledge that don't have use in normal day-to-day survival activities. Their people are hardy, and can adapt to most environments- so despite being dominated culturally by the likes of humans, dwarves, and elves, they rarely hold complaint for the lands leftover for their dominions.

Name: Lt. Surge
Summary: Lt. Surge "The Lightning American" is the leader of the Vermillion Gym and mainly uses Electric-type Pokémon. He is the third Gym Leader Red and Blue encounter in their adventures through Kanto. Characterized by his bold and brash composure, Lt. Surge is a war vet who served in the mysterious "Kanto War" of some years ago.

Name: Marid
Summary: Marids are aquatic genies hailing from the Elemental Plane of Water. While not evil, they are known to bend wishes to their liking. They are extremely rare on the Prime, more often being seen in the Elemental Plane of Water, inhabiting a vast coral palace in the mightiest reefs of the plane. All Marids declare themselves royalty and lords, though few have the power to enforce such expansive titles. Their ego is their greatest weakness, often lending them to weave legendary tales of their awesome might.

Name: Marnie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Marnie (Japanese: マリィ Mary) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Bede, and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon. She eventually replaces her older brother Piers as the Gym Leader of her hometown Spikemuth. As the Spikemuth Gym Leader, she gives the Dark Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Moff Gideon
Summary: Moff Gideon was an officer of the Imperial Security Bureau who contributed to the Great Purge against the Mandalorians until graduating to the rank of marshal and then Moff. After the Galactic Empire's downfall, he evaded execution for war crimes and became the leader of a powerful imperial fragment army while seeking a force-sensitive baby of the same species as Jedi master Yoda, causing him and his forces to conflict with The Mandalorian and his allies.

Name: Mr. Freeze (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Victor Fries was a cryogenics worker operating in Gotham City trying to find a way to cure his ill wife Nora. When he preserved her in cryostasis without authorization from GothCorp, the company tried to shut his research down, and in Victor's attempt to stop them he was caught in a dangerous chemical accident that left him unable to survive outside of very cold temperatures. Building a special suit to keep himself alive, he used it to become the supervillain Mr. Freeze.

Name: Mustard (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)'''
Summary: Mustard is a character in The Isle of Armor in Pokémon Sword and Shield. He is a former Champion of the Galar region and the mentor of Leon. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Dojo Master.

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Mystra (Midnight)
Key: '''Beginning of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''End of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''Avatar''' | '''Greater God'''
Summary: Before she was the God of magic, Mystra was known as the wizard Midnight. Born Ariel Manx, she was the second child of the merchant Theus. A hedonist, Ariel would spend her time with the local bards, sorcerers, fighters, and thieves where she would eventually earn her nickname Midnight due to her late night activities. Eventually she would develop a fascination with magic and left her home in the pursuit of a higher calling.

Name: N (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Black and White 2''' | '''Pokémon Team (Season Battles)'''
Summary: N is a character in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2. He was the puppet leader of Team Plasma in Pokémon Black and White and aspired to create separate worlds for humans and Pokémon. His full name is Natural Harmonia Gropius (ナチュラル・ハルモニア・グロピウス Natural Harmonia Gropius).

Name: Nessa (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hulbury Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Nessa is the Gym Leader of Hulbury's Gym, known officially as Hulbury Stadium. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon. She gives the Water Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Niffty
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Nightmare (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Nightmares are horse-like creatures originating from the Lower Planes, such as the Abyss, the Nine Hells, or Gehenna. They are the standard choice of mount for high-ranking fiends and undead alike, most often searching devil and demon lords, vampires, liches, and other evil-aligned creatures such as the shadar-kai. They are truly wicked beings and are best known for their flaming bodies and vicious tempers.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Ras Nsi
Summary: Ras Nsi was once a Chosen of Ubtao, a Primordial planar power residing in Chult. Some time long ago, however, he cast off his oaths and his power, and became an evil warlord, raising the dead to be his armies. When he did so, he lost control of his necromantic hordes, and in his defeat sought out the Yuan-Ti of Omu to take control.

Name: Rath Modar
Summary: Rath Modar is a Red Wizard of Thay and the primary conspirator against the lich Szass Tam in the campaign to retake Thay. During the crisis concerning the Cult of the Dragons, Rath offered his wizards' might to assist the cult in their goal of summoning Tiamat from the Nine Hells. It was his silent hope that Tiamat would, when she saw how useful he had been, offer to him an army of dragons to wipe out Szass Tam once and for all.

Name: Red (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Beginnings)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Early Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (End Game)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Red is the enigmatic and silent protagonist of Pokemon Red/Blue/Yellow and its remakes Pokémon FireRed/LeafGreen, as well as the hidden final boss of Pokémon Gold/Silver/Crystal and its remakes Pokemon HeartGold/SoulSilver.

Name: Remorhaz
Summary: Native to frozen lands, the Remorhaz spends all its days hunting prey. They are a millipede like creature that emits incredible heat from its body, using it burrow through ice without any issue.

Name: Retriever
Summary: Retrievers are the "gopher" units of any demonic fiefdom. Whenever a powerful lord or commander desires to search out lost artifacts, runaway slaves, or unruly underlings, the Retriever is sent out to find them and return them through any means possible. Most scholars can agree that the Retriever is built to mimic the structural design of the Bebilith, though the reason is unknown. Since they are constructs that are easily accessible to most demonic leaders, the Retrievers are also regularly entrusted with tasks that cannot be given to the demon's kin, for their ugly kind are not reliable.

Name: Rezmir the Black
Summary: Rezmir is a black half-dragon warrior placed in charge of a regional sect of the Cult of the Dragon, an organization dedicated to furthering Tiamat's goals across the plains. Around the time of Rezmir's leadership, the cult grew greatly in power and began to enact a plan to bring living dragons to great power, and eventually summon the Dragon Queen herself.

Name: Roc
Summary: A massive bird, the Roc is the supreme ruler of the skies in the mountains. They only go against large targets such as elephants, with the Roc being able to lift them with one leg. Sometimes Cloud and Storm Giants tame Rocs and use them as a deadly asset.

Name: Roper
Summary: The larva form, also known as a Piercer is an ambush predator in underground places that uses it camouflage in order to let itself drop upon prey whenever it senses someone below it. The adult form, also known as a Roper meanwhile is a far more active hunter, which while still using stealth, also employs tentacles it tosses at enemies in order to pull them to its maw.

Name: Silver (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cherrygrove City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Azalea Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Burned Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Goldenrod Tunnel)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)'''
Summary: Silver (Japanese: シルバー Silver) is one of the main characters and the rival of Pokémon Gold, Silver, Crystal and Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver. He is the son of Team Rocket Boss Giovanni that fought many times with Ethan, Kris or Lyra.

Name: Star-Lord (Classic)
Summary: Peter Quill, alias Star-Lord, was born during an unusual astronomical phenomenon when many of the planets aligned. Quill was raised by his single mother, Meredith. One day Peter saw an Ariguan spaceship land, and his mother was killed by the aliens. When he told the police his mother had been killed by aliens, no one believed him and he was put in a state orphanage. He ran off when he was fifteen and eventually became a trainee NASA astronaut. When the alien entity called the Master of the Sun visited the space station that Quill was stationed at and offered the mantle of Star-Lord to a worthy candidate, Quill volunteered, but was rejected in favour of another astronaut. Quill was outraged, stole a scoutship, and on returning to the space station took his colleague's place. Quill was then chosen to become Star-Lord, with the Master of the Sun first creating an illusion in which he was able to find and kill the aliens that murdered his mother to free him of his past. Equipped with a sentient vessel called "Ship", Quill commenced his role as Star-Lord.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Stone Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Stone Golem is the strongest of the common golems, often also being the prettiest looking due to being often assigned to guard museums.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Susztam Mar-Shinn
Summary: Susztam is the Head Student of the Inverted Tower, a Drow outpost of arcane learning located in Szith Mercane. As the Head Student, he maintains the greatest control over his magic, and one day hopes to usurp his master in becoming the position of his master- until then, he spends his days in the Inverted Tower, training and learning constantly. He is particularly known to be a master of illusory spells and makes use of them frequently[1]. The position of head student is one envied by his peers, and thus Susztam spends his days preparing for their inevitable betrayal[2]. During the takeover of Szith Mercane, Susztam has entered the service of Dorina T'sarran, occasionally acting as a strike-team killer on her behalf[3].

Name: Taillow
Summary: Tier: 8-A | At least 7-A

Name: Trienath Salazar
Summary: Trienath Salazar is a veteran Hellbreaker, a group of thieves adept at intruding into the depths of Baator and taking the diabolical treasure from within. Trienath is fleeing from the Pit Fiend Zaebos, a member of the Dark Eight of Avernus, and offers to help player characters if she finds them to be righteous.

Name: Umber Hulk
Key: '''Umber Hulk''' | '''Truly Horrid Umber Hulk''' | '''Vodyanoi''' | '''Shadow Hulk''' | '''Umber Ravager''' | '''Abyssal Hulk''' | '''Astral Hulk'''
Summary: Umber Hulks are ancient mutant creatures born countless eons ago, possibly before the onset of the Dawn War[1]. Hulking bug-eyed monstrosities, the Umber Hulks lurk in the Underdark, tunneling from cavern to cavern in search of food (and little else), often causing wars and conflicts over territory as they move. They are feared on a nearly mythological level to some due to their peculiar ability to incapacitate hostiles with a glance- and leave survivors with nary a memory of what occurred.

Name: Valentino (Hazbin Hotel)
Summary: Valentino is a one of the many Overlords in the show Hazbin Hotel. He resembles a moth with him having a set of wings[1] and having a squeak[2][1] whenever he is mad. In the show he runs Hell's adult film industry, and he is the abusive boss of Angel Dust[3]. He is one of the infamous "Vee" Overlords[4] along with Vox[4] and Velvette[4] who each control a part of Hell's entertainment with Vox controlling technology[2], and Velvette controlling social media[2]. Valentino's past is unknown with it being implied he died in the 1970s.

Name: Velasta and Velina T'sarran
Summary: Velasta and Velina T'sarran are a pair of Drow identical twins, nieces of Irae T'sarran who server under her daughter, Dorina, in Szith Mercane. Their duties there vary from humdrum to violent, but primarily include raiding on the surface and serving in the elite Hunter-Killer team alongside Susztam Mar-Shinn and Zedarr T'sarran[1]. While they are considered somewhat important to Irae's plans, if slain they are not outright given the time or resources for resurrection- instead they rise as revenants created by Irae.

Name: Velvette (Hazbin Hotel)
Summary: Velvette is the last member of the infamous Vees alongside Vox and Valentino who are both influential throughout Hell. Velvette's most infamous fact is her control over social media as she can control it and describes herself as the backbone of the Vees. Her past is unknown with her cause of death still a mystery but from what can be inferred, she died around the 2000s as she is always on social media which was one of the newest things in the early 2000s. Unlike Vox and Valentino, Velvette poses no threat to the main cast, and she only serves as an irritation for the other Overlords of Hell such as Carmilla Carmine and Zestial.

Name: Venom Ooze
Summary: Theorised to be off shoots of ochre jellies this ooze is atypical in that it doesn't remain mostly in one spot and instead seeks out prey actively, which it's able to capture with its great strength and potent poison. This ooze is most commonly found in the Underdark alone but have been known to be used by evil individuals or simply migrated to another environment due to their incredible resistance to the elements.

Name: Verdant Prince
Summary: Verdant Princes are powerful fey that roam the Prime Material, offering pacts with adventurers or even entire families. While often the pacts seem benign in nature (generally, the Prince won't even profit from the pact for many generations), each is in fact a malign curse on the pact-bearer, where when the Prince's plans come to fruition, that individual's descendants may well pay the full price of their ancestor's impudence.

Name: Viper (Mammon)
Summary: Viper is an illusionist from the anime Katekyo Hitman Reborn! where he serves as the illusionist of the Vongola's assassination squad, the Varia. He's the mist Arcobaleno, the 7 strongest people in the world in a generation that were turned into babies, and thus is known as the most skilled illusionist of his generation (even though he's already lost against other illusionists). Mammon is very greedy and tends to charge other people, including his allies, very high costs for his services.

Name: Vitreous Drinker
Summary: Vitreous Drinkers are undead servants of Vecna, known to wander the lands stealing their victims' eyesight. To do this, they collect certain arcane items to surprise and ambush targets, and uses its skills to, after the attack, see through their victims' eyes. As worshippers of the God of Secrets, they often target great sages, spies, and magi to gain their information.

Name: Vox
Summary: Vox is a major villain in the adult animated musical comedy series Hazbin Hotel[2], serving as a major villain in Season 1 and the main villain of Season 2. His powers are mostly based on electricity and technology as he owns Voxtek[1] which is a technology company that produces most of Hell's Technology[1]. Not much is known as his past life as a human but from what was confirmed, he was stated to have died somewhere in the 1950s making his stay in Hell shorter than Alastor's.

Name: W54 warhead
Summary: Tier: High 8-C to 8-B | High 8-C to 8-A | 8-A | 8-A

Name: Wally (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mauville City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Third and Fourth Battle)'''
Summary: Wally is one of the player's rivals in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire as well as their remakes, Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. He is a meek and sickly young boy who aspires to become a great Pokemon Trainer, having covered his entire room and filled multiple notebooks with information on strategy and raising Pokemon. Over the course of his journey, he gains confidence and a stronger constitution, eventually amassing a powerful Pokémon team and defeating every Gym Leader in the Hoenn region before the player does. He then goes on to battle the player right before they go on to challenge the Pokemon League. Although he lost, he refused to let go of his dream, becoming even stronger and regularly challenging the player at the Battle Resort.

Name: Water Weird
Summary: Made from water, the Water Weird is one of the possible Elemental Weirds. In their younger form they appear like a water serpent, shooting cold water at enemies and using their physiology to drown people who come close to them. Their adult self meanwhile is a powerful caster, being able to use various healing and water spells alongside regular Sorcerer spells.

Name: Wheep
Summary: An eyeless pathetic creature, the Wheep is a servant of other more powerful creatures which is often used as a bodyguard. It constantly emits a black vile from its eyes which makes tracking it down rather easy, although if they choose to, a Wheep is more than capable of using stealth to gain the edge in combat.

Name: Wingull
Summary: Wingull is a seagull Pokémon with wings that are made for soaring on updrafts. It carries food in its beak and makes its nest on the cliffsides. Fishermen take note of when Wingull are nearby, as it is a sign that the surrounding waters are filled with fish.

Name: Wolverine (Deadpool & Wolverine)
Summary: Logan: Scott used to beg me to wear it. So did Jean, Storm, Beast... All of them. They wanted me to be part of the team, but I wouldn't. Told them they all looked fuckin' ridiculous. I mean, I couldn't have 'em thinking I wanted to be there. And then one day while I was off on my own, the humans came. They went mutant hunting. Laura: I can guess the rest. Logan: No, no, let me say it, I... I need to say it. By the time I stumbled home, shit-faced from the bar, it was too late. They were dead.

Name: Yagnoloth
Summary: Yagnoloths are the minor lords of the yugoloth armies, controlling small swathes of the Lower Middle planes as command posts in the Blood War. They serve as basic negotiators for the yugoloth mercenary forces, and tend to bring in contracts for arcanaloths. They are most known for two distinctive traits- firstly, the physical trait of a single massively swelled arm, and secondly, the manipulative trait of always including a loophole in their contracts that voids the entire contract should the situation call for it.

Name: Yoda (Star Wars)
Summary: nan

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Ahsoka Tano
Key: '''Clone Wars''' | '''Star Wars: The Clone Wars (Season 7)''' | '''Star Wars: Rebels'''
Summary: Ahsoka Tano, was the Padawan of famed Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker during the Clone Wars. A talented young Togruta who was originally under the care of Jedi Master Plo Koon, she was later instructed by Jedi Grand Master Yoda to seek Skywalker's tutelage. Despite the Jedi Knight's initial misgivings about her, Ahsoka proved to be an excellent apprentice and a valuable ally who played a key role in numerous pivotal events of the Clone Wars.

Name: Alicia (Ejen Ali)
Summary: Alicia is a deuteragonist character in the Agent Ali series. She is a NEURO agent in M.A.T.A.. She is a friend, rival and fellow agent of Ali.

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: Angel of Valor
Summary: The Angel of Valor are the weakest and most numerous of the angels that serve the gods, they are used as foot soldiers of their deities. while following the orders of higher ranking angels or even clerics of their gods.

Name: Artus Cimber
Summary: Artus Cimber is the son of a thief and member of the Harpers who, upon exploring some old ruins, discovered the Ring of Winter, a relic of the Evil Goddess of Ice, Auril. Determined to never allow the ring to fall into the hands of evil, Artus has been on the run ever since, made immortal by the devious power of the ring. Artus is widely regarded as an immensely intelligent scholar and renowned adventurer aside from his status of guardian of the artifact.

Name: Atropal
Summary: Atropals are stillborn godlings who have spontaneously risen as undead. A foul aura surrounds the Abomination, snuffing out weaker life and draining the souls of those near it. When one rises the Gods cringe and seal them in tombs for all time. But sometimes the barriers are broken and one is freed to wreak havoc on the multiverse.

Name: Auntie Ethel
Summary: Why are you so cruel? Please. It's you lot who come to me. All you do is want - to be prettier, to be richer, to be loved. People are their own worst enemies, petal. I just let them see it.

Name: Badgerclops
Summary: Badgerclops is the deuteragonist of the Cartoon Network series, Mao Mao: Heroes of Pure Heart. In his childhood his spectacular creativity was dismissed by the people around him and he struggled to fit in. Eventually joining a group of cyborg criminals called the Thicket Thieves. It was with them that he met Mao Mao, who helped reinstate his moral standards and let him on board in his quest to becoming a legendary hero. From then on the two worked together, one day crashing into the Ruby Pure Heart and becoming the protectors of Pure Heart Valley alongside the fledgling Sweetypie, Adorabat. Now he serves the village while using his own more laid back, cautious, and sometimes theatric methods when compared to Mao Mao.

Name: Barbed Devil
Summary: Barbed Devils, also referred to as Hamatulas in their infernal tongue, serve as guardians of Baatorian vaults and elite warriors in devilish armies. The devils themselves are relatively low on the devil evolutionary scale, though this does not denote a lower form of power- indeed, their strength makes them the perfect servants of craftier devils.

Name: Basilisk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Basilisks are reptilian magical creatures bestowed with the capability to turn enemies to stone. Their abilities are renowned enough that a seasoned adventurer will recognize the threat of remaining in the area when they begin seeing remarkably life-like statues of frightened wildlife.

Name: Batman (Earth-43)
Key: '''Living Vampire (Red Rain)''' | '''Undead Vampire (Bloodstorm)''' | '''Evil Undead Vampire (Crimson Mist)''' | '''With Preparation'''
Summary: Batman, real name Bruce Wayne, is the protagonist of the Earth-43 trilogy of vampire stories: Red Rain, Bloodstorm, and Crimson Mist.

Name: Behir
Summary: Behirs are dragon-like creatures of electric origin that despise their brethren, to the point of driving them out of their territories if possible and, if not, leaving the area. They were created by Storm Dragons as weapons in a great war against the dragons, though nowadays are often kept as pets of powerful spellcasters and serve as signs of good omens for certain religions, notably in Chult.

Name: Black King (Trolls' session)
Summary: Tier: At least 8-B, likely 8-A

Name: Black Pudding
Summary: Black Puddings are quasi-sentient globs of viscous black goop, most often found in poorly-lit dungeon halls where it might be dismissed as nothing more than a blot of shadow. In truth, it is a malevolent carnivore that strips and dissolves even the most durable materials, leaving behind only stone. It is a painful and not altogether quick way to perish.

Name: Bloodfire Ooze
Summary: Created from a dark ritual, a Bloodfire Ooze is an ooze that's made from people's blood with a bit of a demon added in. They are mindless beasts that seek out blood to absorb and use their fire abilities in battle, some Bloodfire Oozes are even more horrid when made by an extraplaner for they add a pseudonatural creature template which makes the Bloodfire a Blight Bloodfire

Name: Bone Naga
Summary: Bone Nagas are a member of the immortal species known as nagas. They were created by the mighty Creator Race Sarrukh, though they are ultimately an incomplete perversion of true nagas. During the ritual made to cement the naga's immortality, yuan-ti necromantic rituals rendered the creature undead, twisting them into servants of the yuan-ti instead, and with merely a fraction of the power their siblings possessed.

Name: Breachgnome
Summary: Specialized in fighting within cramped spaces, a well-positioned Breachgnome can hold off superior enemy forces for a long duration. They are trained to fight alone, although sometimes they work in small units that coordinate to block off several paths at once. They are seldom seen outside Gnome communities, though when are found outside they are often looking for Gnomes to help.

Name: Cho'Gath
Summary: Tier: 8-B, Unknown maximum potential | At least High 6-C, Unknown maximum potential | Low 1-C

Name: Cloud Giant
Summary: Second tallest of the true Giants, the Cloud Giants are an aloof race, viewing all others barring Storm Giants as beneath them- fitting, given their proclivity to reside in castles which float on clouds. Alongside their impressive physical strength they have innate magical abilities, being able to levitate objects among other things.

Name: Collective Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Identical quintuplets from a Chinese farming family, Han, Chang, Lin, Sun, and Ho, the brothers Tao-Yu were taken into government custody for study after their mutant nature manifested. The brothers were trained to control their power, and became government agents as the Collective Man.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: Dao
Summary: Dao are the Genies of Earth. They are known by their greed and malicious nature towards intruders- their long, earthen galleries are pocked with the shine of gemstones revealed by their mining operations. Little does a Dao care for the hardship of others, often using its great wealth to support immense decadence- it is known they grind diamonds into dust and use it as a spice on their foods. The only race they are on friendly terms with are the Efreeti.

Name: Daren Timbide
Summary: Daren Timbide is a general in the Mintar armies and follower of Bane, the god of fear, malice, and bloodshed. Daren follows this ordeal in his conquests, slaughtering any enemy that presents themselves. However, Daren keeps his army in perpetual training rather than attacking- certain in the idea that he could slay any other given army on the continent, he merely bides his time in patient waiting for Bane's orders.

Name: Davy Crockett
Summary: The M-29 Davy Crockett was a nuclear gun developed by the United States during the Cold War.

Name: Devourer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Devourers are massive undead that stalk the ethereal and astral planes, looking for travelers. The Devourer absorbs the souls of those it stalks, used to sustain their own unnatural life. They are also known for their grotesque features- they form a miniature of their latest victim's soul, trapped within their otherwise empty chest cavity.

Name: Diablomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C, 8-B via Crazy Giggle, Up to 3-C, Possibly higher with Direct Absorption | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | Low 1-C, Up to 1-C | Low 1-C, 1-C via Direct Absorption | At least Low 1-C, Up to 1-C

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Djinni (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Djinni are elemental outsiders originating from the Plane of Air. Clothed in riches and in possession of good looks, Djinni are creatures of ease and relaxation, ruling small single-cloud kingdoms in the Plane of Air. Such freedoms afford them their mischief they constantly try to rile up, though they are not malevolent towards mortals. Of all of genie kind, Djinni are the most accepting of servitude, as they believe it is their fate - and, indeed, belief breeds tangible effect in a world of such magic.

Name: Doctor Octopus
Summary: Born in Schenectady, New York, Otto Octavius had a turbulent upbringing due to his abusive father Torbert berating him for being constantly bullied at school. Due to his mother's insistence that he could solve anything with his mind rather than with brute force, Otto focused more on his education, becoming a brilliant and respected nuclear physicist who devoted his entire life to developing a fusion-based energy source. His work eventually led him to Oscorp. By the time Octavius finally finished his fusion reactor for Oscorp, having lost his mother and the woman he loved during that time, he unveiled a harness of highly advanced mechanical arms controlled via a brain–computer interface to assist him with his research into atomic physics.

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Efreeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Efreeti are immensely powerful fire-elemental genies. Often such genies take to the mortal planes to seek rulership over the desert peoples. Known for their haughtiness and cruelty, though often disguise this as their attempts at order, only admitting to an enlightened sense of self interest. Most of their followers are slaves they captured themselves, be it from the Elemental Plane of Fire or from the Prime. The Efreeti rule the famed City of Brass, a massive citadel for their kind and their nigh-infinite legions.

Name: Eidolon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Eidolon is a type of creature formed from souls, sent to protect a holy site. Once created, an eidolon stalks the holy vaults of the gods, protecting them from any would-be invaders. Oftentimes, an Eidolon will be left with a large, sacred statue to use as a tool for its possession- using the body allows it to wreak havoc upon enemies who might upset the deities and priests that created the mighty creature.

Name: Father of All Bombs
Summary: The Aviation Thermobaric Bomb of Increased Power (ATBIP), or Авиационная вакуумная бомба повышенной мощности (АВБПМ), also colloquially known as "The Father of All Bombs" (Russian: Папа всех бомб) is a type of a thermobaric bomb created by Russia in 2007.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Firepower (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jack Taggert was a pilot selected for a battle suit created by the Project: Firepower of the United States Government in order to combat superheroes, as well as being used in riot control against civilians.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Frost Worm
Summary: Frost Worms are enormous worms that spend their lives tunneling through snow, ice, and even solid stone and earth to search for prey in the frozen wastelands of Faerun and other realms it resides in. It is a hot topic of debate as to whether or not this creature is related to the Purple Worm or the Remorhaz- or even both. A battle between a Frost Worm and a Remorhaz may well lay waste to an entire landscape during the conflict.

Name: Galena Tordrick
Summary: Galena Tordrick is a guardian of devilish cults and leader of a pair of Bone Devil police forces sent to attack those who perform misdeeds to her masters. Originally, she became a Hellfire Warlock to atone for her deeds in life- to use evil in the name of good- however, tasting the power of evil, she has turned fully to the side of Baator and now serves as an oppressor of good.

Name: Garcia Hotspur
Summary: Garcia Hotspur is the main protagonist of Shadows of the Damned.

Name: Ghindul
Summary: Ghindul is one of two leaders of the Kir-lanan species, found at the Wailing Cliffs. His species came into existence during the Time of Troubles, comprised of the divine and negative energy released from the deaths of gods. Ghindul and his followers serve the shadow dragon Glouroth, and are in constant competition with another Kir-lanan sect led by Phaikkul.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Gnar
Summary: Gnar is an excitable yordle whose playful antics can erupt into a toddler's outrage in an instant, transforming him into a massive beast bent on destruction. Frozen in True Ice for millennia, the curious creature broke free and now hops about a changed world he sees as exotic and wondrous. Delighted by danger, Gnar flings whatever he can at his enemies, be it his bonetooth boomerang... or an uprooted tree.

Name: Gray Render
Summary: Gray Renders are huge, lumbering monstrosities known for their well-documented strength on the level of giants, as well as their tendency to bond psychically to creatures. For whatever reason, be it from their artificial creation stories or their latent genetics, gray renders have a psychological need to bond to another living creature. Due to their chaotic nature, they make very risky pets, as they are known to claw apart trees on a whim and even destroy houses.

Name: Grendel (Marvel)
Summary: Grendel is one of a fleet of dragon-shaped symbiote conglomerates under the control of Knull. A progenitor Symbiote, Grendel traveled the cosmos devouring entire civilizations until it attacked Earth in the early medieval period, devouring several Norse soldiers before being blasted by Thor's divine lightning and trapped inside a glacier. As a result of this, pieces of Grendel fell to earth after its defeat and bonded to human hosts, founding a secret apocalyptic cult dedicated to the worship of Knull and the symbiotes.

Name: Guardian Naga
Summary: Guardian Nagas are benevolent nagas of particular strength, originating from the time of the Sarrukh, an ancient Creator Race who ruled multiple empires from over 37,000 years ago across Faerun. They are serpent creatures with humanoid heads, most often found protecting areas of potent lore or magical significance, though can be found ruling over tribes of lesser beings such as Lizardfolk or Kobolds. Unlike their fellow nagas, guardian nagas are not of an inherently evil bent, and not prone to assaulting any intruder in their lairs- they attack only if forced, and prefer to give warnings before unleashing their arcane might.

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: Hezrou
Summary: Hezrou act as officers of demonic armies, enforcers of law among the rank and file soldiers. While not as clever as their more powerful brethren, such as the Balor, Hezrou are cunning combatants and direct their soldiers with extreme aggression. Far from cowardly, a Hezrou hungers for combat, and rushes to the front lines to cut swathes through their enemies.

Name: Hill Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Mouth of Grolantor''' | '''Barrowghast''' | '''Maw of Yeenoghu''' | '''Wereboar''' | '''Avalancher''' | '''Scion of Grolantor'''
Summary: Hill Giants are the lowest ranked of the True Giants, and fittingly are both the dumbest and shortest of them, but they're capable of surprisingly cunning actions in combat and they still possess great physical abilities.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Hunter's Moon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in Luxor, Egypt, he was an excellent student throughout his life, eventually becoming a doctor. He grew to become a very rational and serious person who didn't believe in any higher entities, despite still attending prayer and studying the Qur'an and Hadith. As he was travelling at night, Badr was attacked and killed by a gang of vampires. Left to die with no one but Khonshu as witness, he offered to return Badr back to life as his fist, Badr accepted and became Hunter's Moon, a Fist of Khonshu.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Idunn
Summary: Idunn (イドゥン, Idenn in the Japanese version) is the final boss of Fire Emblem: Binding Blade. She is also the Demon Dragon who is known as the Dark Priestess.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city.
