Desperate to cure his physical deformities, Payne sought out the world's foremost cosmetic surgeons but to no anvil, until he learnt of the shapeshifting Matt Hagen. Using his blood, Preston would develop and brilliant serum that would seemingly allow him to remould the very thing he despised the most, however, instead it would drive him insane, turning him into the third bearer of the mantle of Clayface.

Name: Clefairy
Summary: Clefairy is a peculiar and friendly Pokémon often seen at night in mountains dancing to the moon.

Name: Cleveland-class Light Cruiser
Summary: The Cleveland-class light cruisers were built for the U.S. Navy during World War II, and were the most numerous class of light cruisers ever built. The ships were designed with the goal of increased cruising range, anti-aircraft armament, torpedo protection, etc., compared with earlier U.S. cruisers. Fifty-two ships of this class were originally planned, but nine of them were completed as the light aircraft carriers of the Independence class, and two of them were completed to a somewhat different design, called the Fargo class. The Fargo-class cruisers were a modified version of the previous Cleveland-class cruiser design; the main difference was a more compact pyramidal superstructure with single trunked funnel, intended to improve the arcs of fire of the anti-aircraft guns. In all, 13 Fargo-class ships were planned but only Fargo and Huntington were ever completed, the rest being cancelled at varying states of completion with the de-escalation of World War II. Of the 27 Cleveland-class cruisers that were commissioned, one (Galveston) was completed as a guided missile cruiser and five were later modified as Galveston and Providence-class guided missile cruisers. Following the naming convention at the time, all the ships completed as cruisers were named for US cities and towns.

Name: Cloud Giant
Summary: Second tallest of the true Giants, the Cloud Giants are an aloof race, viewing all others barring Storm Giants as beneath them- fitting, given their proclivity to reside in castles which float on clouds. Alongside their impressive physical strength they have innate magical abilities, being able to levitate objects among other things.

Name: Cockroach Hamilton (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dontrell Hamilton is a hitman residing in New York City, that uses a powerful custom shotgun he named "Josh", and is frequent foe to Luke Cage, using the alias of Cockroach

Name: Coelamon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B

Name: Collective Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Identical quintuplets from a Chinese farming family, Han, Chang, Lin, Sun, and Ho, the brothers Tao-Yu were taken into government custody for study after their mutant nature manifested. The brothers were trained to control their power, and became government agents as the Collective Man.

Name: Colleen Wing (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colleen Wing is a skilled martial artist who was trained by the mysterious Bakuto. She would later open up her own dojo in New York City. Colleen would eventually meet Danny Rand and help him adjust to the changes that had occurred in the city since his disappearance 15 years prior.

Name: Colress
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 4)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon World Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Plasma Frigate)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Tree)'''
Summary: However, I disagree!

Name: Condiment King (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Mitchell Mayo, once an average guy went inexplicably crazy and donned the identity of the Condiment King to cause crime. He was shown tormenting multiple policemen with his special designed sauce, until he was swiftly defeated by Batgirl and Robin. He was then taken to Arkham Asylum, where he eventually was able to work in the kitchen and fuel his obsession, as well as improve upon his formula. This was further aided by Poison Ivy, who taught him vast knowledge on roots, herbs, and spices. Years later, he would get out of Arkham and be "jokerized". Jokerization is stated to amplify the infected's personality, which actually made Mitchell a credible threat. This would almost cause the Birds of Prey to lose to him, as they though he was a joke. It is later stated due to the nature of Condiment King's obsession/portrayal as a joke, juries and parole boards don't take him seriously, thus allowing him to be set free on Gotham again and again. During Final Crisis Aftermath, Mitchell was one of Immortus' followers, The Army of the Endangered, and was cybernetically enhanced by the brilliant Professor Achilles Milo. He was the one to introduce the "Human Flame" to the group, which would be a mistake. Human Flame would rebel, and along with Seductress, kill every member of The Army of the Endangered, including Mitchell.

Name: Constantine Drakon (Post-Crisis)
Summary: As a child of ten, Constantine Drakon was often bullied by others for his diminutive stature, until he found his masterful skill in murder, and has become an unparalleled assassin-for-hire and a foe to Green Arrow

Name: Corvus Glaive (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Corvus Glaive was one of Thanos' children, and a member of the Black Order. After retrieving the Space Stone with Thanos and his siblings, Corvus Glaive and Proxima Midnight traveled to Scotland and ambushed Vision and Scarlet Witch. Corvus Glaive tried to take the Mind Stone, but Captain America, Falcon, and Black Widow arrived, and he was wounded by Black Widow. Corvus Glaive attempted to take the Mind Stone from Vision in Wakanda later. However, he was killed by Vision, who used his own weapon to stab him in the back.

Name: Couatl
Summary: In the beginning of civilization there were five creator races, and the mightiest of these were the Saruukh, who enslaved the other four. Eventually their empire spread so wide that it became too thin, and the vast majority of those in power were not sarrukh. And so the empire fell.

Name: Create-A-Bot
Summary: Create-A-Bot is the playable character in the 2007 games Transformers: Autobots and Transformers: Decepticons. He is a cybertronian that can turn into multiple forms.

Name: Crossbones (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Brock Rumlow was a HYDRA infiltrator who had been posing as a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent, and STRIKE's team field commander. Due to his training from S.H.I.E.L.D. and HYDRA, Rumlow had become a world-class combatant, with extensive experience in street fighting, martial arts, and military combat techniques.

Name: Crossbones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Captain America: I have this theory that no one is totally beyond redemption. That's why I'm so big on preserving life-- Even the lives of those who try to kill me. As long as a person's alive, there's hope he may redeem himself. So what I'm saying is... even though you've acted like lowlife scum every time we've met, there must be something good about you... Love for your mother, a childhood pet, a woman maybe? I'd really like to know what it is. Crossbones: You wanna know where I'm soft, huh, Cappy? Ha! Okay, why not? I'll tell you. I love... TO HATE! HAHAHAHAHAHA!

Name: Crush (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Xiomara Rojas is the daughter of Lobo and a former member of the Teen Titans. Abandoned at birth, Crush was raised by loving, but weak-willed drug addict parents, who were both murdered when she was a young girl. Lost and angry at the world, she took up the name Crush and started fighting in underground fighting promotions before she was recruited by Damian Wayne. Among her notable missions, Crush tracked down her parents' killer, a drug-dealer simply known as "Ezekiel", met and defeated her birth father, Lobo, and nearly started a romantic relationship with one of her team-mates, Djinn.

Name: Crypt Chanter
Summary: Corpse Chanters are malignant, ghostly undead known to haunt tombs, mausoleums, crypts, and similar places, filling their empty halls with their eerie music. Here, they disarm those that might disturb the dead, singing beautiful and terrifying songs to the interlopers, drawing them to their deaths.

Name: Ctenmiir
Summary: Once a great dwarven warrior, Ctenmiir fell in battle to a vampire and became one himself. After his vampire master died by the hand of Keraptis he swore loyalty to the later, with the wizard tasking him to protect the legendary weapon Whelm which Ctenmiir wielded before his death.

Name: CV90
Summary: The Combat Vehicle 90 (CV90) (Swedish: stridsfordon 90ⓘ, strf 90 or Stridsfordon 90) is a family of Swedish tracked armoured combat vehicles designed by the Swedish Defence Materiel Administration (FMV), Hägglund & Söner and Bofors during the mid-1980s to early 1990s, before entering service in Sweden in the mid-1990s. The CV90 platform design has continuously evolved from the Mk 0 to the current Mk IV with technological advances and changing battlefield requirements.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: D-Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dennis Dunphy was a high school athlete who was given super strength by the mysterious Power Broker, and he joined the new Unlimited Class Wrestling Federation (UCWF), where he could use his augmented strength against other similarly augmented wrestlers, and he became close friends with the Thing, under the ring name Demolition Dunphy.

Name: Dagger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tandy Bowen’s life started in privilege, but it was a life without the love of her parents, that made her decide to run away from home. While living on the streets she met Tyrone Johnson, but they were both kidnapped by scientists that wanted test subjects for their new experimental drugs. Although most of the test subjects died, Tandy and Tyrone survived, and as a side effect awakened powers. Now under the alias of Dagger, she becomes a personification of light that promises to rid the streets of all drugs in an attempt to stop what happened to her from happening to anyone else.

Name: Daken Akihiro
Summary: Akihiro, codename Daken is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Daken is the mutant son of Wolverine and his deceased wife Itsu. He possesses superhuman abilities similar to his father (e.g., healing factor, retractable claws), and was a member of the Dark Avengers under the name Wolverine until the conclusion of the 2010 storyline, "Siege". Daken was ranked sixth in Comics Alliance's "50 Sexiest Male Characters in Comics" list and is often recognized for his sex appeal

Name: Daku
Summary: Daku is the King of the Insect Enterrans and one of the Seven Enterran Generals. He resembles a Hercules Beetle-knight.

Name: Dao
Summary: Dao are the Genies of Earth. They are known by their greed and malicious nature towards intruders- their long, earthen galleries are pocked with the shine of gemstones revealed by their mining operations. Little does a Dao care for the hardship of others, often using its great wealth to support immense decadence- it is known they grind diamonds into dust and use it as a spice on their foods. The only race they are on friendly terms with are the Efreeti.

Name: Daredevil (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in the historically gritty or crime-ridden, working-class Irish-American neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen in New York City, Matthew "Matt" Michael Murdock is blinded by a radioactive substance that falls from a truck after he pushes a man to safety from the oncoming vehicle. While he no longer can see, the radioactive exposure heightens his remaining senses beyond normal human ability and gives him a "radar sense". His father, a boxer named Jack Murdock, supports him as he grows up, though Jack is later killed by gangsters after refusing to throw a fight. After donning a yellow and dark red costume (later all dark red), Matt seeks out revenge against his father's killers as the superhero Daredevil, fighting against his many enemies, including Bullseye and Kingpin.

Name: Daren Timbide
Summary: Daren Timbide is a general in the Mintar armies and follower of Bane, the god of fear, malice, and bloodshed. Daren follows this ordeal in his conquests, slaughtering any enemy that presents themselves. However, Daren keeps his army in perpetual training rather than attacking- certain in the idea that he could slay any other given army on the continent, he merely bides his time in patient waiting for Bane's orders.

Name: Darkdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Davy Crockett
Summary: The M-29 Davy Crockett was a nuclear gun developed by the United States during the Cold War.

Name: Deacon Frost (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Deacon Frost was once a scientist looking for the key to immortality, which he eventually found in the corpse of a recently killed vampire. Managing to extract his essence, Frost sought to inject in a woman's body to test its effects, but a fight broke out with her fiancee, who injected the substance in Frost's body, transforming him into what would become one of the most powerful vampires to blight the Earth.

Name: Deadpool (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Deadpool (Wade Winston Wilson) is a fictional character, a mercenary and anti-hero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer and artist Rob Liefeld and scripted by Fabian Nicieza, Deadpool first appeared in New Mutants #98 (Feb. 1991).

Name: Death (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Alice Wu-Gulliver: So.. you’re a- a green witch? Rio Vidal: Um… less a green witch, more, the Green Witch.

Name: Deathstroke (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Deathstroke (Slade Joseph Wilson) is a fictional supervillain appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. He is a mercenary and assassin who serves as the archenemy of the Teen Titans, specifically Dick Grayson. Over the years, writers have developed him as an adversary of other superheroes in the DC universe as well, such as Batman and Green Arrow.

Name: Deathstroke (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Slade Joseph Wilson, aka Deathstroke, joined the military at age sixteen, was an exceptional soldier and earned his fair share of medals. He volunteered for "Project X", which granted him enhanced reflexes, strength, mental capacity and rapid healing. After going AWOL in Bosnia, and winning his signature sword, he took on its name and began running covert black bag missions. It wasn't until after the death of his son that he became the world's deadliest assassin.

Name: Deep Gnome
Summary: Deep Gnomes, also known as Svirfneblin, are Gnomes primarily found underground in the Underdark. Their time in the underground has made so they naturally blend in and understand stone. They possess both great fighting skills and innate magical abilities, which they use greatly in combat.

Name: Defenders (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Defenders were a team of four street-based superheroes who banded together to save New York City from the Hand.

Name: Delver
Summary: Delvers are sub-subterranean creatures that use their acidic, corrosive slime to burrow through the earth, devouring stone for its minerals to sustain itself. They are predatory towards earthen creatures such as the common Xorn, though are largely docile outside of that (hostile specimens are recorded to have existed).

Name: Demogorgon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Aspect '''| '''Out of the Abyss '''| '''In the Abyss''' | '''Lesser God'''
Summary: Should feckless mortal seek to test His ire, Take heed of better foes than you now shamed- FRAZ-URB'LUU, who would take His name in vain: His wrath shall haunt your lands and wipe them clean. AZUVIDEXUS, who would dwell within His house: He'll vex the gods themselves to cast you out. ZUREGUREX, who would seek to claim His prize: Your storm-strewn dead shall not avail your flight. SHAMI-AMOURAE, who seeks His lust to build a throne: To the darkest wash of primal night be sent. ORCUS, who brings His armies forth to bear: Your troops shall end upon red fang and claw. GRAZ'ZT, who deigns to claim His vaunted crown: Your triple realm shall rot from deep within. OBOX-OB, who once ruled where He rules now: Your crown now rests upon the proper brow. For you are but His pawns and He your prince. And in the end but thralls to His demesne.

Name: Dervill the Treacherous
Summary: Dervill was a court wizard of Rhoona, serving his duke faithfully until the arrival of Xanathon in the city. With the rise of his temple's power, Dervill shifted his allegiance to that of Xanathon, believing him the probable winner of the upcoming conflict.

Name: Destrachan
Summary: Destrachans are dungeon dwelling creatures known for their immense control over sound- specifically, their ears are adjustable to various settings of sound. They look beastly and unintelligent, though this is not the case- in fact, they are crafty sadists, always looking for more prey in a very competitive food chain. Their roars are known to shatter stone walls, making them a powerful threat in the average dungeon.

Name: Detective Chimp (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Bobo T. Chimpanzee, the Detective Chimpanzee, used to be a normal circus animal, until an unlikely series of events led to him drinking from a magical fountain that augmented his mind to an incredible level of intelligence and gifted him immortality.

Name: Deva
Summary: Devas are messengers of the Good-aligned deities that they serve, generally taking the role of spreading goodness in the lesser planes in the name of their gods- either a subtle humanoid or an animal. When they need to they cast off their guise of mortality and appear in their true godly beauty.

Name: Devimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C, Low 1-C with Digital World's Darkness | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Devourer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Devourers are massive undead that stalk the ethereal and astral planes, looking for travelers. The Devourer absorbs the souls of those it stalks, used to sustain their own unnatural life. They are also known for their grotesque features- they form a miniature of their latest victim's soul, trapped within their otherwise empty chest cavity.

Name: Diablomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C, 8-B via Crazy Giggle, Up to 3-C, Possibly higher with Direct Absorption | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | Low 1-C, Up to 1-C | Low 1-C, 1-C via Direct Absorption | At least Low 1-C, Up to 1-C

Name: Diaboromon (Digimon Adventure)
Summary: Diaboromon is the main antogonist of Our war game and Diaboromon Strikes back. It hatched as a kuramon from a Digi-Egg that had formed on the Internet from a collection of viruses. It caused constant chaos in the Real World by eating data, and Digivolved rapidly with each sufficient amount of food. It was eventually defeated by Omegamon.

Name: Diamondback (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Willis Stryker, also known as Diamondback, is the half brother of Luke Cage and a deadly criminal equipped with advanced weaponry from Hammer Industries.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Dianamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Dire Bear
Summary: A regular bear is already a dangerous beast to stumble upon in the wild, thus a Dire Bear is an even worst meetup one can have in the forest due to it being a vastly stronger bear which can easily maul adventurers to death if they're not careful.

Name: Dire Boar
Summary: The Dire Boar is a giant variant of the regular boar, it's a rather vicious animal who when engages in combat attempts to tear its enemies into shreds with its tusks. The Dire Boar has 2 variants, the Thunderfury Boar which is a Fey Dire Boar and the Fhorge which is a variant found in the Outlands.

Name: Dire Elk
Summary: A bigger version of an elk, the Dire Elk is a rather aggressive and will try to gore its enemies with its massive antlers. It's incredibly rare, to the point where people believe that sighting is a foreshadowing of important events such as the birth of a king.

Name: Dire Rhinoceros
Summary: Larger and stronger than its regular counterpart, the Dire Rhinoceros is most often found in cold environments and is a formidable opponent for anyone who tries to challenge it.

Name: Dire Tiger
Summary: A far larger and stronger version of a tiger, the Dire Tiger is also a fearsome ambush predator which lives in dense jungles.

Name: Dire Tortoise
Summary: Large and slow, this tortoise travels in the desert eating any plants it can find and attacking anything it sees due to its bad temper

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Django Freeman
Summary: Tier: 10-A. 9-C with firearms. 8-C with preparation

Name: Djinni (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Djinni are elemental outsiders originating from the Plane of Air. Clothed in riches and in possession of good looks, Djinni are creatures of ease and relaxation, ruling small single-cloud kingdoms in the Plane of Air. Such freedoms afford them their mischief they constantly try to rile up, though they are not malevolent towards mortals. Of all of genie kind, Djinni are the most accepting of servitude, as they believe it is their fate - and, indeed, belief breeds tangible effect in a world of such magic.

Name: Doctor Octopus
Summary: Born in Schenectady, New York, Otto Octavius had a turbulent upbringing due to his abusive father Torbert berating him for being constantly bullied at school. Due to his mother's insistence that he could solve anything with his mind rather than with brute force, Otto focused more on his education, becoming a brilliant and respected nuclear physicist who devoted his entire life to developing a fusion-based energy source. His work eventually led him to Oscorp. By the time Octavius finally finished his fusion reactor for Oscorp, having lost his mother and the woman he loved during that time, he unveiled a harness of highly advanced mechanical arms controlled via a brain–computer interface to assist him with his research into atomic physics.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Domino (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Neena "Domino" Thurman is a character from Marvel Comics. She is best known as a member of the X-Force. Domino made her first full main story appearance in X-Force #8 as a unique individual from the Wild Pack group driven by the mutant Cable.

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Dorugoramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Dracula (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Vlad Dracula, formerly Vladimir Tepesch, is a villain from Marvel Comics originating in Tomb Of Dracula, based on the iconic character of the same name, and serves as the lord of the vampires.

Name: Dragon Turtle
Summary: Dragon Turtles are immense aquatic creatures with genetic ties to true dragons. Many cultures regarded Dragon Turtles as the most dangerous monsters of the sea, whilst others worshiped them as a sign of the gods. Despite not being the strongest of all sea monsters, they were held as posing a significantly higher threat due to their tendency to attack and rip apart ships passing through their territories. The turtles were obsessed with treasure and could often be bribed or given tribute to receive desired effects ranging from simply leaving ships alone to attacking others.

Name: Dryad (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Dryads are forest spirits and guardians of the plants within them, generally residing within the trees. Dryads are peaceful by nature (though not unwilling to fight), and are often considered to be exemplary messengers of the gods- including the likes of Corellon Larethian and Erevan Ilesere.

Name: Durandamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: Eduardo Lobo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Eduardo Lobo was an orphaned youth on the streets of Mexico, making ends meet alongside his brother Carlos, until one faithful night the love of his life was shot right before his eyes. This awakened a transformation within the young lad, and he discovered he was a mutant capable of transforming into a werewolf, similar to his brother. The two soon after took control of the local cartel in the late 1980s, with their empire reaching South Texas at its height.

Name: Efreeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Efreeti are immensely powerful fire-elemental genies. Often such genies take to the mortal planes to seek rulership over the desert peoples. Known for their haughtiness and cruelty, though often disguise this as their attempts at order, only admitting to an enlightened sense of self interest. Most of their followers are slaves they captured themselves, be it from the Elemental Plane of Fire or from the Prime. The Efreeti rule the famed City of Brass, a massive citadel for their kind and their nigh-infinite legions.

Name: Eidolon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Eidolon is a type of creature formed from souls, sent to protect a holy site. Once created, an eidolon stalks the holy vaults of the gods, protecting them from any would-be invaders. Oftentimes, an Eidolon will be left with a large, sacred statue to use as a tool for its possession- using the body allows it to wreak havoc upon enemies who might upset the deities and priests that created the mighty creature.

Name: Elecmon
Summary: Elecmon is a Mammal Digimon that retained Tsunomon's mammal-like elements and evolved. It's very curious and lively, and inherited its prank-loving personality from Tunomon. Also, Elecmon possesses nine tails, and during battle, it fans out its tail like the plumage of a peacock to intimidate its opponent.

Name: Electivire
Summary: Electivire is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Electabuzz, and the final form of the Gen II Elekid. It evolves when traded with an Electrizer.

Name: Electro (Francine Frye)
Summary: Francine Frye was a supervillain groupie living in New York, where she had relationships with many supervillains within the city, including one Max Dillon, Electro. One day when spending time with him, Electro's powers acted up, resulting in him accidentally killing her.

Name: Electro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: It's pitch black out there now. They're the faceless ones. They're the invisible nobodies. And me? I hurt. I'm scared. So afraid I'm gonna die. But it'll be worth it, won't it? When they look up and see me. The biggest. The brightest. The highest, the greatest. Oh it will be all worth it... when I... LIGHT THE NIGHT! Look at me, all of you! Look at Max Dillon! Look at ELECTRO!

Name: Elektra (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elektra Natchios is an assassin who was trained under Stick to join the Chaste. She fell in love with Matt Murdock during a mission for Stick to bring Murdock into the organization. She returned to his life after years of absence, putting her beliefs and methods at conflict with his own. Later, she was revealed to potentially be the Black Sky, the one who is supposed to lead the Hand. However, Elektra chose to help Murdock defeat the malevolent organization, and was killed in the final confrontation with Nobu Yoshioka. The Hand then retrieved Elektra's corpse from the grave and placed it in a stone chamber to be exposed to the Resurrection Elixir.

Name: Elephant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many options for a mount animal, the Elephant is a large herbivore people in Dungeons And Dragons can use. They are extremely large and rather smart for an animal, being able to avoid attacking objects that will harm them if touched.

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Elsa Bloodstone (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elsa Bloodstone is the daughter of the immortal monster hunter, Ulysses Bloodstone, who follows her father's footsteps to be a monster hunter herself. Armed with an arsenal of rifles, shotguns, pistols and other weapons, alongside being imbued by the power of the Bloodgem thanks to her choker, she hunts the various beasts and creatures of the Marvel Universe with expertise.

Name: Equinox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to two brilliant scientists, Terry Sorenson was granted the power of thermokinesis upon failing to save his father during a lab explosion.

Name: Erik Killmonger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Erik Stevens (born N'Jadaka) was a former American black-ops soldier of Wakandan origin through his father, Prince N'Jobu. His savagery while serving in the US black-ops earned him the nickname Erik Killmonger. Years after T'Chaka killed his father for betraying Wakanda, Killmonger then planned to forcibly dethrone T'Challa in order to accomplish his father's plan to use Wakanda's technology to conquer the world via imperialistic, supremacist, world-spanning, and likely genocidal warfare, to stop what he perceived to be the oppression of people of African descent by the world. Manipulating and then killing Ulysses Klaue to gain access to their city, Killmonger seemingly killed T'Challa during ritual combat and took the throne, but just before Killmonger unleashed his plan, the Black Panther had returned and challenged Killmonger, eventually killing him in their final battle.

Name: Ethereal Ooze
Summary: The Ethereal Ooze is an ooze found in the Ethereal plane, it uses its ability to freely travel to the Prime Material world to snatch unsuspecting prey into the Ethereal plane and eat them.

Name: Ezra Bridger
Summary: Ezra Bridger was a human male Jedi Padawan who, as an orphan on the Outer Rim planet of Lothal, became a rebel fighter and revolutionary leader in the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. He was born to Ephraim and Mira Bridger, two outspoken opponents of the Imperial regime on Lothal. As a boy, his parents were taken prisoner by the Empire, leaving Bridger to fend for himself on the streets of Lothal. He joined the rebel crew of the Ghost five years before the Battle of Yavin and, with his Force-sensitivity having been discovered, became the apprentice of Kanan Jarrus, a Jedi who survived Order 66. Bridger's abilities with the Force grew quickly, which aided in many of the crew's efforts against the Empire.

Name: F-117 Nighthawk
Summary: The F-117 Nighthawk is a single seat, twin engine attack aircraft developed by the secretive Skunk Works division of Lockheed and operated chiefly by the USAF. The aircraft is based on the earlier Have Blue technology demonstrator and was the first operational aircraft to be designed around stealth technology.

Name: F-14 Tomcat
Summary: The F-14 Tomcat is a supersonic, twin-engine, variable sweep wing, two-place fighter designed to attack and destroy enemy aircraft at night and in all weather conditions. Although now retired in the U.S. Navy, it remains in use, seeing service with the Iranian Air Force.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F-35 Lightning II
Summary: The F-35 Lightning II is family of single-seat, single-engine, all-weather stealth multi-role fighters developed and manufactured by Lockheed Martin for the Joint Strike Fighter program. The fifth-generation combat aircraft is designed to perform ground-attack and air-superiority missions.

Name: F-86 Sabre
Summary: The North American F-86 Sabre was a fighter used by the US and it's allies during the early Cold War period, and saw military service in the Korean War. It's closest Soviet equivalent is the MiG-15, and often saw combat against it during the Korean War. The aircraft was finally retired in 1994 in Bolivia, 47 years after it has made it's first flight and 45 years after it first entered service with the USAF.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Falcon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Samuel Thomas "Sam" Wilson, better known as the Falcon, was a former United States Air Force pararescue airman who left active duty when his wing-man Riley died in combat, choosing instead to begin helping any of his fellow veterans who were suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder at Veterans Affairs. During this time, Wilson met and soon became an ally of Captain America during the beginning of the HYDRA Uprising, assisting him in bringing down Alexander Pierce's schemes for Project Insight before then choosing to remain with Captain America. Falcon later joined the Avengers, and has been an active member ever since.

Name: Fancy Dan (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daniel Brito was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. Bullied at a young age due to his height, he took martial arts classes to better defend himself and earn respect, but the mocking only continued as he was branded Fancy Dan by his tormentors. He soon joined forces with Montana and Ox to form the mercenary collective the Enforcers, and have been a thorn in Spider-Man's side ever since.

Name: Father of All Bombs
Summary: The Aviation Thermobaric Bomb of Increased Power (ATBIP), or Авиационная вакуумная бомба повышенной мощности (АВБПМ), also colloquially known as "The Father of All Bombs" (Russian: Папа всех бомб) is a type of a thermobaric bomb created by Russia in 2007.

Name: Felix Jaeger
Summary: Felix Jaeger is Gotrek's reluctant companion and "rememberer." Felix was a middle child of Gustav and Renata Jaeger, a wealthy Altdorf mercantile family. His three brothers became partners in the Jaeger & Sons firm, but Felix was the black sheep. At the university of Altdorf, he combined his interests in poetry and revolution to write verses advocating nonviolence for a seditious group called the Mock Beggars. This put him at odds with Wolfgang Krassner, a fellow student-revolutionary who believed violent revolution was necessary. The two duelled, and Jaeger killed the other man. For this he was arrested, but he avoided being hanged by the assistance of Zavant Konniger. He was nevertheless expelled from university.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Firebrand (Gary Gilbert)
Summary: Gary Gilbert was the son of an unscrupulous businessman and abusive father, Simon Gilbert. In retaliation, Gilbert and his sister Roxanne became political activists against what they believed were unjust businesses. Gilbert was soon banished from his family home and his sister soon followed of her own volition. Gilbert became increasingly radical and believed only a violent revolution to overthrow the existing American government and capitalist system was necessary. Gilbert used his talents in physics and invention along with training classes offered by Stark Industries to create the weapons and costume of Firebrand, a hotheaded terrorist with the powers to match, and has been a recurring foe of Iron Man ever since.

Name: Firefly (Ted Carson) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Ted Carson was the boyfriend of famous movie star Cindy Cook. After breaking up, Ted's obsession would lead him to steal the technology and name of pyrotechnics expert: Garfield Lynns, to become Firefly and attempted to live a private life with Cindy after faking his death. Following his defeat at the hands of Nightwing and Batgirl, Ted would become a hired gun, recurring Batman foe and eventually groom a protégé. However, after being bailed out by Two-Face, Ted would reshape himself for good and joined Clayface's group of reformed villains.

Name: Firepower (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jack Taggert was a pilot selected for a battle suit created by the Project: Firepower of the United States Government in order to combat superheroes, as well as being used in riot control against civilians.

Name: Flag-Smasher (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Karli Morgenthau, is the leader of the group known as the Flag Smashers, an anarchist group that wishes to change things back to the way they were during the events of the Blip, a period of time when Thanos had wiped out half of all life in the universe that ended when the Avengers initiated the time heist to gather the Infinity Stones and undo the Blip.

Name: Flame Snake
Summary: Often used as guards the Flame Snake comes in 3 variants; Small, Lesser and Greater Flame Snake with each one being stronger then the former, the strongest of their kin being theorised to be banished demons cursed into being snakes.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Forest Gnome
Summary: Shy and reclusive, Forest Gnomes are the rarest of the Gnome types. They seldom get out of their woods, so their impact on the world at large is often minor. They are deeply connected to nature, being able to communicate with animals while also easily hiding in a forest environment.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Francine Langstrom (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Francine Langstrom is the wife of Kirk Langstrom, Man-Bat. While she is currently living a normal life, she used to be as addicted to the Man-Bat serum as him, threatening Gotham's inhabitants as a monstrous, giant vampire bat.

Name: Free Spirit (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cathy Webster was born and raised in Macomb, Illinois. She attended Hayden College and as a graduate student participated in an unsanctioned psychology experiment involving subliminal recordings at the Glasser Institute. She was subliminally programmed to hate all men, and her body subjected to "mutagenic radiation". The radiation enhanced her body to peak human conditioning similar to the Super Soldier Serum that enhanced Captain America. Cathy eventually overcame her brainwashing and discovered the woman in charge of the experiment was the criminal scientist Superia.

Name: Frost Worm
Summary: Frost Worms are enormous worms that spend their lives tunneling through snow, ice, and even solid stone and earth to search for prey in the frozen wastelands of Faerun and other realms it resides in. It is a hot topic of debate as to whether or not this creature is related to the Purple Worm or the Remorhaz- or even both. A battle between a Frost Worm and a Remorhaz may well lay waste to an entire landscape during the conflict.

Name: Gabumon (Yamato Ishida)
Summary: Yamato Ishida (Matt in the dub) and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure trilogy. Yamato is the secondary main character of 01 and Tri, next to Taichi Yagami. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship, this can be seen in his character rather early on in the series, as he's usually looking out for his friends best interest. Yamato is the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Galeb Duhr
Summary: Galeb Duhr is an intelligent elemental from the Plane of Earth, bearing the ability to invoke life in rocks and dirt. They were most often encountered on the Prime Material, hiding themselves as boulders unless someone invaded their territories (though they typically allied themselves with other defenders of nature, such as treants or pech). They spent their days endlessly tending to their boulders, much like a gardener might tend to their plants. They were often called upon by druids to protect groves and other places sacred to nature, and used their innate camouflage abilities to remain staunch in their sentinel duty, sitting still for years at a time.

Name: Galena Tordrick
Summary: Galena Tordrick is a guardian of devilish cults and leader of a pair of Bone Devil police forces sent to attack those who perform misdeeds to her masters. Originally, she became a Hellfire Warlock to atone for her deeds in life- to use evil in the name of good- however, tasting the power of evil, she has turned fully to the side of Baator and now serves as an oppressor of good.

Name: Gaomon (Thoma H. Norstein)
Summary: Thoma H. Norstein is a coolheaded child genius who has already graduated from university. His intelligence is highly valued, even within DATS. He executes his missions based on data and theories, so his personality frequently clashes with Masaru's, who relies more on emotions.

Name: Garcia Hotspur
Summary: Garcia Hotspur is the main protagonist of Shadows of the Damned.

Name: Gargantos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gargantos was an inter-dimensional being sent by Scarlet Witch to kidnap America Chavez in order to acquire her Multiversal abilities. Gargantos attacked Chavez in New York but was attacked by Wong and Doctor Strange, the latter of whom killed Gargantos by gouging its eye out with a lamppost.

Name: Gargoyle (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gargoyles are monstrosities of stone hailing from the planes of Earth. These prideful predators wait in dormancy, patiently watching for enemies to inflict pain upon. A gathering of Gargoyles oftentimes will resort to banter and bragging to pass the time.

Name: Ghindul
Summary: Ghindul is one of two leaders of the Kir-lanan species, found at the Wailing Cliffs. His species came into existence during the Time of Troubles, comprised of the divine and negative energy released from the deaths of gods. Ghindul and his followers serve the shadow dragon Glouroth, and are in constant competition with another Kir-lanan sect led by Phaikkul.

Name: Ghost (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ava Starr was the daughter of Elihas and Catherine Starr until they were both killed in an accidental quantum explosion. However, Ava was only left with the power to turn invisible and intangible, powers that led S.H.I.E.L.D. to recruit her as a special agent for dealing with extra-dangerous threats until she was adopted by Bill Foster. The two worked together to steal from Bill's nemesis, Hank Pym, and possibly find a solution to Ava's unstable body condition, with her working as "Ghost".

Name: Ghost (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ghost is an infamous and highly skilled corporate saboteur; he despises the huge, multinational companies that treat regular workers and people as dispensable pawns in their endeavours for greater turnover and profit margins; Ghost believes not only that all these organisations need to be destroyed, but that he is the one who can do it. This has resulted in him being extremely paranoid, seeing conspiracies almost everywhere and rarely, if ever, trusting anybody other than himself

Name: Ghost-Spider (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gwen Stacy was bitten by the radioactive spider rather than Peter Parker giving her the abilities of a spider. She goes by the name Spider-Woman and much like Spider-Man of Earth 616 used her newly found powers to for more personal gain rather than helping people by becoming a professional drummer. Peter Parker remained a weak individual that Gwen needed to save from bullying. This made him develop an inferiority complex causing him to create a serum to make himself more like Gwen after she has revealed to him her powers. This causes him to become Earth 65's version of the Lizard and Gwen is forced to fight him. Unfortunately due to the serum during the battle Peter dies and she vows to use her powers for good. Unfortunately, Gwen is blamed for Peter's death and a campaign against her (spearheaded by J. Jonah Jameson) is started.

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant Lizard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Giant Lizard''' | '''Footpad Lizard''' | '''Quicksilver Lizard''' | '''Subterranean Lizard''' | '''Giant Banded Lizard'''
Summary: Giant Lizards are monstrously large creatures bred in the Underdark by Drow as potential replacements to their typical spider mounts. They roam the subterranean parts of the world, commonly hunting in packs or being used as pack animals for their fearsome overlords[1].

Name: Giant Shark
Summary: A massive predator, the Giant Shark roams the seas, hunting whatever crosses its path be it whales or ships. This creature is not the same as a Megalodon, as it only reaches around half of their size.

Name: Giant Squid (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living in the deep sea, the Giant Squid is a creature most adventurers do not need to face, but some unlucky ones who travel the sea might have their sea stopped by one and sinked down to the depths if they do not scare it away fast enough.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Gibbon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Martin Blank, also known as Gibbon was a man who was born with simian traits akin to his villain namesake. This made him naturally agile and strong, however, it also make his appearance loathsome for others to behold. This lead to him mainly living as an outcast, being mocked by even the likes of Spider-Man. He was tragically killed by a Hunterbot in the Great Hunt.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Githzerai
Summary: In times long lost to the rampages of war, the Githzerai were once normal Githyanki who dissented from their brethren and formed a non-evil neutral faction. The Githzerai are ascetic monk-like folk who have settled in Limbo, a plane of chaos- a direct counter to their Lawful nature. They seek to battle the Slaadi, specifically to expand their knowledge in the face of direct adversity, building on the traits they learned from their slavery under the Mind Flayer empire.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Gnar
Summary: Gnar is an excitable yordle whose playful antics can erupt into a toddler's outrage in an instant, transforming him into a massive beast bent on destruction. Frozen in True Ice for millennia, the curious creature broke free and now hops about a changed world he sees as exotic and wondrous. Delighted by danger, Gnar flings whatever he can at his enemies, be it his bonetooth boomerang... or an uprooted tree.

Name: Gnoll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is His blessing.

Name: Goblimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 8-C

Name: Gokuwmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | Low 1-C

Name: Gordon Freeman
Summary: Dr. Gordon Freeman is the main protagonist of the Half-Life series. He is a theoretical physicist who is forced to defend himself and the Human race against hostile Aliens and other enemies following an experiment gone wrong. In the process, he becomes an almost legendary resistance hero, eventually becoming one of the leaders of an uprising against the alien invaders.

Name: Gorgon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gorgons are horrific bull-like creatures covered head-to-toe in iron plates protecting its true body. Their plates perpetually remain oiled thanks to secretions from their skin beneath, ensuring that it never rusts and remains as silent as possible. Gorgons, when they find prey, charge through them, oftentimes simply pulverizing weaker foes. The vapors that emit from the Gorgon are known to petrify enemies on contact, and not even those on other planes can escape its effects.

Name: Gorgon (Tomi Shishido)
Summary: Tomi Shishido, better known as The Gorgon is a mutant genius born in Kyoto, Japan. Even in infancy, his talents showed, as at just two weeks old, he spoke his first words. At thirteen years of age, Shishido had devised a mathematical formula that without question, proved the existence of God, but this revelation changed Shishido in a catastrophic manner. Believing that God's existence hindered mankind as man would be little more than subservient slaves if God existed, Shishido began to hate all gods, and began to desire to kill a god, along with all life on earth. During this time, Shishido learned he had the mutant power to turn people into stone with a glance, and the Japanese media dubbed him "Gorgon." Shortly after this, Gorgon formed the "Dawn of the White Light," a mutant death cult that subjected Japan to relentless terror attacks to complete their mission of ending all life. At eighteen years old, he searched for the Hand, drawing their attention by killing all of his loved ones, and committing suicide to prove his dedication to the organization. The Hand resurrected Gorgon promptly after this, and within a short time he became their leader, allowing him to continue his mission of ending all life.

Name: Gorilla Grodd (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Gorila Grodd is a telepathic gorilla and an enemy of the Flash. He was originally a normal ape who lived in an African city known as Gorilla City, until a radioactive meteor struck near his home and turned him into a genius with telekinetic powers.

Name: GranDracmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | Low 1-C | 1-C | 1-C

Name: GranKuwagamon
Key: '''Kokuwamon''' | '''Kokuwamon X''' | '''Kuwagamon File Island''' | '''Kuwagamon Folder Continent''' | '''Kuwagamon X''' | '''Okuwamon''' | '''Okuwamon X''' | '''GranKuwagamon'''
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Gravity (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Greg Willis was a boy from Wisconsin, who was granted the power of gravitikinesis after being sucked into a strange mini black hole. Deciding to use his powers for good, he moved to New York City and adopted the superhero persona Gravity.

Name: Gray Render
Summary: Gray Renders are huge, lumbering monstrosities known for their well-documented strength on the level of giants, as well as their tendency to bond psychically to creatures. For whatever reason, be it from their artificial creation stories or their latent genetics, gray renders have a psychological need to bond to another living creature. Due to their chaotic nature, they make very risky pets, as they are known to claw apart trees on a whim and even destroy houses.

Name: Green Arrow (Connor Hawke) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Connor Hawke, also known as the Green Arrow, is a superhero and former assassin known for his gentle, kind-hearted demeanor and unmatched strength. Originally from New Earth, Connor came in contact with a 'blue light' that transported him to Prime Earth, where he was recruited by the League of Assassins to be their champion. After defeating Damian in thee League of Lazarus, the two became good friends and fierce rivals.

Name: Green Arrow (Post-Crisis)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Grell
Summary: Grell are creatures that resemble floating brains with tentacles and a large beak protruding from the front. They are most famous for their voracious feeding habits- they bear little else in terms of dastardly plans outside of planning their next meal, going so far as to classify all things in life as "edible", "inedible", or "Great Eater" (those few things that might feed on a grell). While generally solitary, a rare few grell form great colonies led by philosophers, grell wizards that study the aberrant sciences of their native realm. The grell are non-hostile to other grell, and generally consider the choice of joining a colony as a matter of opinion.

Name: Grendel (Marvel)
Summary: Grendel is one of a fleet of dragon-shaped symbiote conglomerates under the control of Knull. A progenitor Symbiote, Grendel traveled the cosmos devouring entire civilizations until it attacked Earth in the early medieval period, devouring several Norse soldiers before being blasted by Thor's divine lightning and trapped inside a glacier. As a result of this, pieces of Grendel fell to earth after its defeat and bonded to human hosts, founding a secret apocalyptic cult dedicated to the worship of Knull and the symbiotes.

Name: Grey Gargoyle (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Paul Duval was a young chemist from Paris, who during a lab accident, discovered he was able to turn people to stone by the merest touch of his right hand. His criminal spree unchallenged in France, he traveled to America and wrest the secret of immortality from Thor, and has been a frequent foe of his, as the petrifying Grey Gargoyle.

Name: Grifter (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Cole Cash is a former U.S. Army Special Ops soldier who deserted and became a con artist. After the Daemonites attempted to possess his body, he ended up as one of the most wanted men alive. Hiding his face under a mask, he wages war on the Daemonites as Grifter. His firearms expertise makes him an incredible marksman and one of the most dangerous men in the world. Through Daemonite experimentation, he also gained telepathy and telekinesis.

Name: Grizzmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-B | 3-C

Name: Groot (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Groot is a hyper-intelligent, tree-like organism from the species Flora colossus native to the planet X. While he possesses human level intellect, Groot's robust and heavyweight physiology causes the organs of his acoustic generation to become stiff and inflexible, rendering the limits of his speech to the simple phrase, "I am Groot."

Name: Grung
Summary: One of the many amphibian humanoids in Dungeons and Dragons, the Grung are based on poisonous frogs. They emit a deadly poison from their skin, and also have a nasty bite and weapons to go alongside that.

Name: Guardian Naga
Summary: Guardian Nagas are benevolent nagas of particular strength, originating from the time of the Sarrukh, an ancient Creator Race who ruled multiple empires from over 37,000 years ago across Faerun. They are serpent creatures with humanoid heads, most often found protecting areas of potent lore or magical significance, though can be found ruling over tribes of lesser beings such as Lizardfolk or Kobolds. Unlike their fellow nagas, guardian nagas are not of an inherently evil bent, and not prone to assaulting any intruder in their lairs- they attack only if forced, and prefer to give warnings before unleashing their arcane might.

Name: Guido Mista
Summary: Guido Mista is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. He joins the Neopolitian gang Passione after his vigilantism almost gets him sent for twenty years in prison, but is saved by Bruno Bucciarati. He becomes involved in the week-long mission of protecting Trish Una and eventually to assassinate the Boss of Passione himself.

Name: Guilmon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 3-C, Up To 1-C with Digital Hazard | 1-C

Name: Gururumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C

Name: Gwenpool
Summary: Gwendolyn Poole was just a normal girl, living an unsatisfactory life and with a fierce passion for Marvel Comics, when one day she was mysterious transported within the exciting world of her beloved stories. Extremely galvanized at this prospect, Gwen donned a costume and took on the identity of Gwenpool, determined to have the most fun of her new life. Extremely erratic, reckless and borderline psychotic, Gwen viewed herself as the protagonist of the story and the world around her as a playground, uncaring for even the lives of others, for they were expendable fictional characters. However, things quickly escalated and slipped out of her hands, making her bitterly realize the harsh truth: she was not in control .

Name: Hagurumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B | At least High 4-C, possibly 4-A | 3-C

Name: Halagrad Doomhammer
Summary: Halagrad Doomhammer is a Soulguard, a direct counter and foil to the Faustian pacts of the devils of Baator. Considered meddlers and unwanted interruptions by the bulk of the religious community, they interfere with the devils' pact with the gods themselves, demanding safety for souls tainted by their fiendish ways. As such, Halagrad maintains immense knowledge on Baator- its politics and policies are known to the Soulguard, who must battle them on this front.

Name: Halfling (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The closest demihuman to humans, to the point where their name comes from being half as tall as human, Halflings are a naturally lucky race. Their society values comfort and security above all else, with them seldom venturing outside their home lands besides the dire of situations. This makes any Halfling adventurer the more fierce when going out to help their local community, with Halflings being naturally gifted in ranged combat and stealth.

Name: Hallows' Eve (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elizabeth Tyne went through a lot of hardship, an abusive father, kidnapped and prison, but she found love with Benjamin Reilly a clone of Spider-Man. She went through a lot of effort to help him become who he should be, including going to the dimension called Limbo. Tired of feeling useless she accepted a power that was given by Madelyne Pryor, now going by the name Hallows' Eve she tries to do everything she can to keep the relationship with Ben alive.

Name: Hammerhead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When left for dead in an alleyway after a brawl, a surgeon found Joseph and operated to fix him up, replacing his broken skull with a steel plate.

Name: Hannibal King (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Hannibal King used to be a relatively normal private investigator, until the day one job he was given brought him too close to a man far more dangerous than he could ever imagine: Deacon Frost, the same vampire who killed Blade's mother at the moment of his birth, bit Hannibal King, turning him into yet another member of the blood-drinking horde.

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Hatori
Summary: Often called Sand Crocodile the Hatori is a massive reptile that lives in the desert and hunts anything that isn't obviously stronger then itself like a dragon. Like a Wyern they're a distant relative of dragons, which is likely why they can reach their impressive size of 50 feet tall, with some Hatoris even reaching sizes of 200 feet tall.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: Clearly retirement doesn't suit you. Got tired of shooting golf? Hawkeye: Well, I played 18, shot 18... Just can't seem to miss.

Name: Hawkmon (Miyako Inoue)
Summary: Miyako Inoue and Hawkmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Miyako one of the many viewers watching the battle against Keramon in Our War Game.

Name: Heinrich Zemo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Baron Heinrich Zemo was born in 1900, the 12th Baron Zemo joined the Nazi Party early in its existence, quickly becoming one of the Nazis' top scientists and the most wanted Axis agent during World War II. Zemo was working on his invention known as Adhesive X when Captain America invaded his laboratories. In the course of destroying the only supply, the adhesive covered Zemo's cowled head, which became permanently affixed. As a result, Zemo was consumed with a violent, insane hatred for Captain America and mankind in general.

Name: Hellhound (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hell Hounds are a breed of extraplanar, fiery hound, often used as pets of infernal lords. Wild packs of Hell Hounds often roamed Baator, the Abyss, and even the Elemental Plane of Fire. As such, they could be found in the service of all manner of fiery outsiders, including Efreeti, Balors, and Pit Fiends.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: HerculesKabuterimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Hexeblaumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Hezrou
Summary: Hezrou act as officers of demonic armies, enforcers of law among the rank and file soldiers. While not as clever as their more powerful brethren, such as the Balor, Hezrou are cunning combatants and direct their soldiers with extreme aggression. Far from cowardly, a Hezrou hungers for combat, and rushes to the front lines to cut swathes through their enemies.

Name: HiAndromon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Hill Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Mouth of Grolantor''' | '''Barrowghast''' | '''Maw of Yeenoghu''' | '''Wereboar''' | '''Avalancher''' | '''Scion of Grolantor'''
Summary: Hill Giants are the lowest ranked of the True Giants, and fittingly are both the dumbest and shortest of them, but they're capable of surprisingly cunning actions in combat and they still possess great physical abilities.

Name: Hina Kurihara (Digimon Linkz)
Summary: Hina Kurihara is Linkz's navigator in Digimon Linkz. She is a tutorial program designed to help players navigate the Digital World. While Vorvomon and Jazamon are the partner of the protagonist of Digimon Linkz, in the Digimon Card Game Hina acts as their Tamer.

Name: Hobgoblin (Roderick Kingsley)
Summary: After Roderick Kingsley redesigned Norman Osborn's Goblin Formula and used it on himself, he took his old equipment and became the very first Hobgoblin, becoming a prominent Spider-Man villain.

Name: Honey Badger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gabrielle is one of at least ten clones of Wolverine, youngest of the Sisters, created by Alchemax Genetics, a division of Alchemax. The project was overseen by Robert Chandler, with security provided by Captain Mooney. The girls were created and trained to serve as bodyguards for humanitarian missions and other personnel. Much like Laura before them, they were often abused by their handlers, particularly Mooney, but the elder Sisters did their best to protect her from the worst of the abuse. She was incapable of feeling pain, the result of nanites implanted in her body that were slowly killing her. With six of her sisters dead due to fatalities on missions, or as a result of the nanites, she escaped along with Zelda, Bellona, and X23_3PAR. They were assisted in their escape by Kimura, who armed and equipped them before sending them after Alchemax for revenge for stealing property from The Facility.

Name: Hop (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Late Game/Beginning of Post Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End of Post Game/Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Hop (Japanese: ホップ Hop) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield and Leon's younger brother. He is your main rival throughout the games, eventually undergoing a period of self-doubt after a humiliating defeat at the hands of Bede, as he didn't want to be so weak as to drag down his older brother's name. After his defeat at the hands of the player in the Champion Cup, he eventually decides to work toward becoming a Pokémon Professor.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Human Robot (Post-Golden Age)
Summary: They don't know what you're capable of. Yes, you'll be a powerful killing machine, but that will be your choice. You can have free will. Know emotions. Feel anger... loyalty... respect. This crucial encoding can only be made with the displacement of my own life force. I am sorry to put you in this position, M-11, but there is no time to fix it otherwise. Some of my essence will be imparted into you. You'll be your own being. Let my final act give you life... my Human Robot

Name: Hunter's Moon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in Luxor, Egypt, he was an excellent student throughout his life, eventually becoming a doctor. He grew to become a very rational and serious person who didn't believe in any higher entities, despite still attending prayer and studying the Qur'an and Hadith. As he was travelling at night, Badr was attacked and killed by a gang of vampires. Left to die with no one but Khonshu as witness, he offered to return Badr back to life as his fist, Badr accepted and became Hunter's Moon, a Fist of Khonshu.

Name: Hurricane (Real World)
Summary: Hurricanes are massive storm systems that form over the water and move toward land. Threats from hurricanes include high winds, heavy rainfall, storm surge, coastal and inland flooding, rip currents, and tornadoes. These large storms are called typhoons in the North Pacific Ocean and cyclones in other parts of the world.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Hydroloth
Summary: Hydroloths are elite soldiers of the yugoloth mercenary armies, and maintain the respectable position of their marine forces. Hydroloths stalk the waterways of the Styx and its rivulets, and are adept at ambushing soldiers attempting to cross unwanted. Though cowardly, hydroloths are extremely ambitious, as they are the first evolutionary step of yugoloth to have awareness of their ability to ascend ranks. Thus, a hydroloth will scour the battlefield with terrible force, destroying all their enemies given the opportunity, in the hopes that their actions will be noticed by their superiors.

Name: I, Vampire (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: What manner of witchcraft has taken me? How did I get here? And how do I live? My mind is cleared, only hunger to fill it. But a hunger like one I have never felt... It boils and seethes, like an angry dog seethes. It overwhelms, my eyes filled with one need. What is happening to me, Lord? Please speak... I feel so strange, as if I'd never lived... As though the air I breathe, the light I see, Is the first I e'er have breathed or seen. And yet, I feel a dourness awash me. As though I've lost something more than sacred. Perchance a dream where reflections aren't cast. Where good people drink blood and hunger for death-- And when prey is near, I both lay and lie-- so easily, like to this I was born.

Name: Iceman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Iceman (Robert "Bobby" Drake) is a fictional character, a superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a founding member of the X-Men. A mutant, Iceman has the ability of cryokinesis where he can freeze anything around him and can also turn his body into ice. Although he is an Omega-level mutant, Drake has yet to tap into his full mutant potential. Over the years he has taken more interest in developing his abilities. One of the original X-Men, Iceman has had a frequent presence in X-Men (and Spider-Man)-related comics, video games, animated series, and movies.

Name: Idunn
Summary: Idunn (イドゥン, Idenn in the Japanese version) is the final boss of Fire Emblem: Binding Blade. She is also the Demon Dragon who is known as the Dark Priestess.

Name: Imhotep (Im: Great Priest Imhotep)
Summary: Imhotep is the main protagonist of the Im: Great Priest Imhotep manga franchise. A great priest from ancient times in Egypt from over 3000 years ago. He was the cause of Magai's existence on Earth. He was sealed away by command of the Gods for committing such a heinous crime. He was released 3,000 years later by command of the gods (the Ennead) and was tasked with exorcising all Magai.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city. Originally these creatures were made by Primus, and even the most wily and secretive of traders will enter into contracts with them- nothing is more straightforward and true than the ideals that forge the Inevitable's will. Inevitables care not for intent or purpose- only for the words written in their contracts. Lethal force is used to ensure such words are stood by.

Name: Iowa-class Battleship
Key: '''Pre-Refit (World War II/Korean War/Vietnam War-era)''' | '''Post-Refit (Persian Gulf War-era)'''
Summary: The Iowa-class battleships were a class of fast battleships designed and fielded by the United States Navy in 1939–1940 to escort their Fast Carrier Task Forces operating in the Pacific Theater during World War II. Four were completed, while two more were laid down but were not finished before the war's end and were ultimately scrapped. Like other third-generation American battleships, the Iowa class emphasized speed in addition to secondary and anti-aircraft batteries.

Name: Iron Fist (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Danny Rand was the child of owners of Rand Enterprises. After a plane crash where his parents died he was rescued by two monks who took him to K'un-Lun where he trained and later earned the title of Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 13
Summary: Model 13 was Tony Stark's attempt of creating something new and unique compared to his previous armors. Opposed to a single, integrated suit, Model 13's structure was based on a modular component system. The armor's capabilities, powers, and equipment would be reconfigured by swapping in and out sub-systems such as boots, gloves, helmets, weapons, or scanners. The varieties of equipment and abilities Model 13 would have would be heavily dependent on the mission Tony needed to accomplish.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 15
Summary: Tony Stark created this armor while in a mental breakdown due to the stress of attacks on Stark Enterprises and from being under Immortus' influence. This new suit would be used to betray and even kill fellow Avengers during the Crossing storyline event.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 4
Summary: Model 4, as known as Classic Armor, is the fourth Iron Man suit engineered by Anthony Stark.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 6
Summary: Made for underwater exploration Model 6 is a modified version of Model 4 which has been upgraded to handle pressure far better so it can go on extended dives into deep waters.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 7
Summary: One of Tony's speciality armors, Model 7 is an armor that sacrifices physical capabilities in exchange for being stealthier, and it was used on several occasions to gather intel by Stark.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 8
Summary: Model 8 or commonly known as the Silver Centurion Armor is one of Stark's most iconic suits. Appearing in the iconic storyline Armor Wars, this suit was made when he wanted to reinvent himself as Iron Man.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 9
