Summary: This armor was created by Tony Stark before the events of the first Armor Wars storyline, although he was reluctant to use the new armor due to its high capabilities. Tony would later be forced to use the armor against the villain Firepower after the Silver Centurion Armor was destroyed. After defeating Firepower, Tony would continue to use this armor for more missions and battles.

Name: Iron Monger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Obadiah Stane was the business partner of Tony Stark and a good friend of his father, Howard Stark. After Howard's death, Stane became interim CEO of Stark Industries until Tony took over officially shortly after. Stane's jealousy of the younger Stark led him to join forces with the Ten Rings to organize a failed attempt to assassinate him so Stane could become CEO once again. When this failed, Stane created the Iron Monger Armor and attempted to kill Stark himself, leading to his own death.

Name: Iron Monger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Obadiah Stane was a wealthy financer and businessman who took interest in acquiring Stark International, using his agents to assault it and Stark's allies.

Name: Ironheart
Summary: Riri Williams spent her childhood living in Chicago as a brilliant, yet reclusive child prodigy until her step-father and best friend were killed in a drive-by shooting at a picnic. Now having reason to put her intelligence to use, she secretly combined technology from an outdated Iron Man armor with spare materials from M.I.T. to craft her own power suit, but the rudimentary prototype was destroyed during her first outing as a vigilante.

Name: Ivern
Summary: Ivern Bramblefoot, known to many as the Green Father, is a peculiar half man, half tree who roams Runeterra's forests, cultivating life everywhere he goes. He knows the secrets of the natural world, and holds deep friendships with all things that grow, fly, and scuttle. Ivern wanders the wilderness, imparting strange wisdom to any he meets, enriching the forests, and occasionally entrusting loose-lipped butterflies with his secrets.

Name: J. Jonah Jameson
Summary: J. Jonah Jameson is the bossy and irascible editor-in-chief of the Daily Bugle. His dislike of superhumans, most particularly the Spider-Man (which stems from a combination of envy, distrust, and his son's accomplishments being overshadowed) leads him to tirelessly defame and vilify him at every opportunity with his newspaper, to the point where he has sometimes worked with supervillains to try and take him down.

Name: Jack Cooper (Titanfall 2)
Summary: As the main and playable protagonist of Titanfall 2, Rifleman Jack Cooper forms a bond with his Titan, BT-7274, in the game's campaign, where he and his new ally must complete their mission that could save multiple worlds in the frontier from destruction. He stands with the Militia against the IMS, the two strongest factions in the Frontier.

Name: Jack Flag (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jack Harrison and his brother, Drake, were members of Captain America's computer hotline network, and they created a citizen's patrol group in their hometown, Sandhaven, Arizona. Drake was attacked by a couple of criminals, and the attack left him unable to use his legs. After the attack, Jack and Drake discovered that the Serpent Society had infiltrated his hometown, and they had attempted to contact the local authorities, but the Serpent Society had paid them all off. Jack was unhappy with this information, so he began training in the martial arts and weight lifting so that he could fight the Serpent Society himself. He took on a disguise that he thought would make Captain America proud, and began to fight crime as Jack Flag.

Name: Jayce (Arcane)
Summary: Jayce Talis is a scientist and innovator, and, after years of success leading the city's scientific and consequently its economic progress, is currently the Head of the Council of Piltover.

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jessica Jones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Leaving her past as a crimefighting vigilante behind, Jessica Jones is a superpowered woman who works as a private investigator for her own agency, Alias Investigations, and apart from her grim job and dark past, is happily married to Luke Cage and a mother to their daughter, Danielle, however whenever trouble calls she isn't afraid to throw down to save the day.

Name: Jigglypuff
Summary: Tier: 8-C | At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Jinny Hex (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jinny Hex is a superhero from Texas and the great-great-granddaughter of Jonah Hex. Raised by a single mother in a rural town, Jinny was ignorant of her heritage until her mother, now on her deathbed, told her of the adventures of her distant relative and the treasure he left behind. After gaining the stash of treasure, Jinny traveled to Metropolis and ended up joining Young Justice and accompanied them on many adventures across the multiverse before she traveled back to Texas to face her deadbeat father in his quest to become king of the world.

Name: Jinx (Arcane)
Summary: Jinx, born as Powder, is a notorious Zaunite criminal and Vi's younger sister. When she was a little girl, her parents were killed in a failed uprising against Piltover, leading Vander, the upspoken leader of the undercity, to adopt both her and Vi as his own daughters. After a series of events forced Jinx and her sister apart in more ways than one, she was fundamentally and irrevocably changed, transforming her into the crazed killer she is today.

Name: Joe Kido (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Joe Kido and Gomamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Joe is one of the 8 chosen children of the Digimon Adventure 2020 continuity and is the crest bearer of of Sincerity. Despite his pessimistic attitude and appearing as a coward, Joe is actually quite kind and very brave.

Name: John Constantine (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: John Constantine, sometimes known as The Hellblazer, is an occult detective and scammer from Liverpool. Despite him having good intentions and typically wishing to protect the world, John's extreme methods have often put him at odds with other heroes: John is a very pragmatic man, and is willing to sacrifice others to save more, or even to protect himself, though it greatly hurts him to do so.

Name: Jubilee (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jubilation Lee was the daughter of two wealthy Chinese immigrants, but after her parents lost all their money in the stock market and were subsequently killed, Jubilation was sent to an orphanage that she would soon run away from. Living in a mall, Jubilation discovered her mutant powers when she was cornered in a back alley by security guards, creating blinding lights that allowed her to escape. One day, the M-Squad was called in to capture her, but she was saved by Psylocke, Storm, Rogue and Dazzler. Jubilation followed them through a portal to the X-Men base. Eventually she freed Wolverine from the Reavers and went on several adventures with him before finally joining the X-Men as Jubilee.

Name: JumboGamemon
Summary: A gigantic Cyborg Digimon that added beam cannons to its entire body until the strength of its Metal Body's shell was compromised.

Name: Justimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Jynx
Summary: Jynx is an Ice-Psychic type Pokémon originated from Kanto. It behaves with noises comparable to human speech, yet it can´t be understood by humans.

Name: Kaecilius (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kaecilius was a sorcerer and a former member of the Masters of the Mystic Arts. He became corrupted and opposed the Ancient One and his former brothers-in-arms when he felt his mentor had failed in her promise to help him find meaning to his wife and son's tragic deaths or found a way to bring them back together. Becoming angered by this, Kaecilius rebelled against his allies and formed the Zealots, aiming to find their meaning in the Mystic Arts that the Ancient One was hiding from them. He and his followers then stole a few pages of the Book of Cagliostro from Kamar-Taj's library as part of his scheme to summon Dormammu of the Dark Dimension to Earth. He is ultimately defeated when Dormammu accepts Doctor Strange's bargain to leave Earth and take the souls of Kaecilius and his minions with him in return for freedom from the time-loop that Strange created.

Name: Kaine Parker
Summary: Kaine was the Jackal's first attempt at cloning Peter Parker, but he was left deformed by a flaw in the cloning process and quickly became unstable.

Name: Kamen Rider Saber
Key: '''Beginning of Story (1-22)''' | '''Middle of Story (23-35)''' | '''Late Story (36-40)''' | '''End of Story (41-47)'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:KRSaber_Brave_Dragon_Sound.mp3

Name: Kanan Jarrus
Summary: Kanan Jarrus (born Caleb Dume) is the protagonist of the Star Wars television show Star Wars Rebels, as well as a Jedi Padawan and a Rebel leader of the Ghost crew. He is the captain of the ship Ghost and also one of the few Jedi who survived both Order 66 and the ensuing Jedi Purge. Surviving both has turned him into a more bitter, cynical, and disillusioned individual that has not used his lightsaber in a long time. However, as the series progresses, Kanan will come to lead a motley crew of freedom fighters against the Empire and eventually take up the lightsaber once more as he transitions from a self-centered and jaded survivor to a heroic and selfless Jedi once more.

Name: Karate Kid (Earth-Prime)
Summary: Val Armorr, the Karate Kid, is a founding member of the Legion of Super-Heroes, a group of teenagers inspired by the actions of superheroes from centuries ago, to rise up and stand against a society of quiet inaction and strict protocol.

Name: Karate Kid (Post-Zero Hour)
Summary: Val Armorr, the Karate Kid, is a superhero born in the 31st Century, an a member of the Legion of the Super-Heroes. While he doesn't have any superpowers, he is an unmatched master of martial arts.

Name: Karate Kid (Pre-Zero Hour)
Summary: The flat of the champion's foot connects- rending the doors from walls and floor, revealing bedrock-solid quartz molded in the image of glass... And seven human guard-dogs, chosen to challenge the invader's most prized skills... The taunt brings no reply... a silent tension waiting for the first attack. Begin the ballet of murder and watch masters of the art at work, the challenge lying not in the numbers of the attackers, but in their skill and silent determination... and devotion to the death of their foe. Yet this is no ordinary foe... nor even an ordinary master of the martial arts, for he has not the skills learned of a single art, but those of all... and from birth he has given his life over to their total mastery... until his every move shows that he is more than the master of the art from which he takes his name. His moves show the blood of the great black dragon in his veins... and the stern teachings of the sensei who made him a force for good. He is the complete fighting machine in human form... a true champion of combat... Val Armorr, the Karate Kid!

Name: Karl Mordo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Karl Mordo came to the Kamar-Taj to become one of the Masters of the Mystic Arts in order to avenge a tragedy in his life. Mordo was initially arrogant and disrespectful to others, but he eventually humbled and set aside his thirst for revenge. He was noted for being rigid and unwilling to compromise his beliefs of the natural order that he gained. Mordo became a Master and assisted the Ancient One in recruiting and training others in the ways of magic.

Name: Kasimir Velikov
Summary: Kasimir Velikov is a dusk elf living among the Vistani of Barovia. Among the last of his kind, his people were slaughtered when he orchestrated for his sister to be stoned to death after hearing her plans to wed Strahd von Zarovich. After the deed was done and his sister lay dead, Rahadin slaughtered the women of the Dusk Elves, dooming them to damnation, and cut off Kasimir's ears. Now, the vagrant Kasimir seeks solely to resurrect his sister, to somehow undo the wrongs he has done. To do this he will sacrifice everything and further damn himself in the process.

Name: Katana (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Tatsu Yamashiro, known as Katana, is a Japanese superhero skilled in swordsmanship. She has been a member of the Suicide Squad, the Outsiders, the Justice League of America, and the Birds of Prey. Her signature weapon, the "Soultaker" sword, is believed to trap the souls of those it slays—including her own husband.

Name: Kate Bishop (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Clint: This life you wanna live. To really help people. I mean, try to help people, anyway. Comes a lot of sacrifices. And some things you'll lose... forever. Kate: Well, there's also things you gain, like trick arrows and a cool costume.

Name: KGBeast (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Bred and raised by the Soviet Union's secret KGB cell; the Hammer, Anatoli Knyazev was made to be the very best there was. However, after the collapse of the Soviet Union, Knyazev switched professions to a hired killer known as the Beast and infamously put a bullet in Nightwing's skull. This would go on until his untimely self-demise at the hands of Task Force Z and ironically later would get resurrected to be put on the same team that led to his death in the first place.

Name: Kha'Zix
Summary: A vicious Void predator, Kha'Zix infiltrated Valoran to devour the land's most promising creatures. With each kill he absorbs his prey's strength, evolving to grow more powerful. Kha'Zix hungers most to conquer and consume Rengar, the one beast he considers his equal.

Name: Kimura (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kimura was X-23's handler in the Facility that created and assigned her missions. Throughout Kimura's time as X-23's handler, she abused her, finding any excuse to bully her, regardless of whether she had succeeded or failed in her missions.

Name: King Dodongo
Summary: Infernal Dinosaur: King Dodongo is the boss of Dodongo's Cavern, the second dungeon in The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time.

Name: King Shark (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Nanaue is the offspring of the self-proclaimed Hawaiian shark deity Kamo. After Kamo was captured on a tropical island by Amanda Waller, she also took one of his offspring with her before destroying the island, assuming that the child would be easier to control than the father. The child was Nanaue, who was raised by Waller in laboratory conditions and grew at an extremely fast rate. He was eventually dubbed King Shark and joined Amanda's team Taskforce X, better known as the Suicide Squad.

Name: Kingpin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Kingpin (real name Wilson Fisk) is a major fictional Marvel Comics supervillain that originated in the Spider-Man comics and media. He has since then gone on to be a major enemy of Daredevil as well as a recurring villain for both Spider-Man and the Punisher. In recent years, he has been revised as being more of Daredevil's enemy rather than Spider-Man's and has appeared in more mature, realistic and adult-themed comic appearances. He is portrayed as one of the most feared and powerful crime lords in the Marvel Universe, typically holding the position of New York City's crime overlord.

Name: Knell Beetle
Summary: Being an off shoot of giant beetles they're a mutated form of giant beetles due to magic and sonic energies, being mindless hunters who only seek to breed they make great use of their innate magical abilities and deadly claws in combat.

Name: Knightmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | Low 1-C

Name: Kog'Maw
Summary: Belched forth from a rotting Void incursion deep in the wastelands of Icathia, Kog’Maw is an inquisitive yet putrid creature with a caustic, gaping mouth. This particular Void-spawn needs to gnaw and drool on anything within reach to truly understand it. Though not inherently evil, Kog’Maw’s beguiling naiveté is dangerous, as it often precedes a feeding frenzy—not for sustenance, but to satisfy its unending curiosity.

Name: Koushiro Izumi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Koushiro Izumi and Tentomon are two of the main protagonists from Digimon Adventure 2020. Koushiro is the brains of the Chosen Children, constantly analyzing the world around him. However, his social skills are lacking due to his preference for computers over people.

Name: Kraven the Hunter
Summary: Sergei Kravinoff was born the scion of disgraced russian nobility, forcefully driven out of their homeland following the revolution and sent looking for refuge in the US. After years of abuse at his father's hands and the trauma of witnessing his mother's slow descent into madness and subsequent death, Sergei grew utterly dissatisfied with modern society and left looking for the peace that only a primeval world could give him. For decades he roamed the worlds' wildest lands, hunting any beast imaginable and earning fame as the matchless Kraven the Hunter. A fateful meeting with Aja Orisha allowed Sergei to be initiated to the mystical arts and acquire supernatural skills, although at great expenses due to his troubled mind.

Name: Kraven the Hunter (Last Son)
Summary: nan

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Kuo-Toa
Summary: Kuo-Toa are a species of fish-human hybrids that once dominated the surface world, ruling the islands and seas alike. However, they were driven away from their homes, deep into the Underdark, the evil world beneath the world.

Name: Lady Quallem
Summary: Lady Quallem was, in life, a fairly low-ranking noble of some standing in Daggerfall[1]. After her death, she was entombed below alongside her son, an arcanist of small capability, and history largely forgot about her from that point on. However, in the depths below the town, she became a ghost after finding she was unable to move on from this life. Now she haunts her tomb, protecting it against the mass amounts of grave robbers that might seek to loot it.

Name: Lascivious (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Davida DeVito was professional wrestler/mercenary under the alias Titania, being the member of all-female team known as the Grapplers. After a life of crime, she was killed by the Scourge of the Underworld.

Name: Lash (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Inhumans are a people born with latent powers that can only be unlocked through the process of Terrigenesis, a metamorphosis most commonly caused by coming into contact with Terrigen Mist. In his Inhuman city, Lash was one of the few in his generation selected to be worthy of undergoing this change. Thus, he gained the ability to absorb energy and subsequently emit it from his hands. However, after the detonation of the Terrigen Bomb, Terrigen Mist was unleashed upon the world everywhere, with new Inhumans being born every day. Lash, believing that not everybody should receive this gift, set out to correct the mistake, putting him in conflict with the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Legendary Tiger
Summary: Unknown how, the Legendary Tiger is a tiger with incredible power far beyond what a regular one has. One theory is that they act as a guardian of nature, but even outside that the Legendary Tiger is one of the strongest natural predators in nature.

Name: Leonal
Summary: Leonals are lion-like celestials hailing from the plains of Elysium, and belong to the Guardinals, a type of angelic cross of abstract goodness and the animals of nature. As such, Leonal are incredible defenders of the natural world, as well as icons of the armies of Mystra, defending the proper usage of magic throughout the Planes.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Lex Luthor, since his first appearance, has been the most consistent adversary of Superman. His origins have varied somewhat, from the son of an abusive household to the childhood friend of a young Clark Kent, but upon reaching the city of Metropolis, he used his genius intellect and scientific knowledge to become a highly corrupt businessman, and eventually the head of his own corporation, secure in his position as one of the most powerful men in the world.

Name: Lightmaster
Summary: Edward Lansky, known otherwise by the alias Lightmaster is a former Chancellor at New York University. After becoming disillusioned with those that run the university, he devised a nefarious plan to take control of the university, centered around kidnapping and murder.

Name: Lilina
Summary: Lilina is the daughter of Hector and the princess of Ostia, the largest nation in the Lycian Alliance. After Bern's generals manage to slay her father, she is entrusted to her best friend and fellow noble Roy for her protection, but she nevertheless heads to the battlefield herself to help end the war.

Name: Living Brain (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Living Brain is a robot with a hard drive stored in its body to allow it to store unlimited amount of data and has the potential to contain more knowledge than any other brain on earth, human or mechanical. Created by Dr. Petty, the machine was exploited during an exhibition which caused him to malfunction, and began wrecking havok until being stopped by Spider-Man.

Name: Living Laser
Summary: Arthur Parks, better known as The Living Laser is a Marvel character who first appeared at Avengers (1968) issue #34.

Name: Lizardfolk
Summary: Lizardfolk are reptilian humanoids native to the world of Toril that tend to dwell in semi-aquatic environments (such as swamplands and coastlines). An exceedingly practical folk, they do not desire riches or knowledge that don't have use in normal day-to-day survival activities. Their people are hardy, and can adapt to most environments- so despite being dominated culturally by the likes of humans, dwarves, and elves, they rarely hold complaint for the lands leftover for their dominions.

Name: LoaderLiomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B, occasionally High 8-C with Shippo Binta | High 8-C, occasionally 6-C with Critical Bite | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Locathah
Summary: One of D&D's aquatic races, the Locathah is a playable race of fish people. They are resilient, adept in using weapons, and possess natural athleticism alongside sharp senses. However they are bound to water, being only able to be above ground for 4 hours before needing to be covered in water as to not suffocate to death.

Name: Locus (Red vs Blue)
Summary: Locus is a dangerous mercenary and Felix's companion. During Season 11, Felix originally states that Locus intends to kidnap the Reds and Blues for the Federal Army of Chorus and prevent them from escaping the planet Chorus. However, his true affiliation is with the Space Pirates who take command under their superior named Control.

Name: Lt. Surge
Summary: Lt. Surge "The Lightning American" is the leader of the Vermillion Gym and mainly uses Electric-type Pokémon. He is the third Gym Leader Red and Blue encounter in their adventures through Kanto. Characterized by his bold and brash composure, Lt. Surge is a war vet who served in the mysterious "Kanto War" of some years ago.

Name: Lucario
Summary: nan

Name: Lucia von Bardas (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lucia von Bardas was a puppet Prime Minister of Latveria installed by the US during Doctor Doom's absense. Von Bardas however, secretly began using her position to fund supervillains in America. Angered by this, Nick Fury launched a secret assassination plot against her, signalling S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Daisy Johnson used her seismic powers to take down Castle Doom, apparently killing the Latverian leader. Von Bardas however resurfaced, and led a campaign to assassinate all the heroes involved in her avoided demise. Despite failing, she has remained a dastardly foe ever since.

Name: Luke Cage (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Luke Cage (real name Carl Lucas) is a former policeman from Savannah, Georgia, who was wrongfully convicted into Seagate Prison, where he met and fell in love with therapist Reva Connors. During his time in prison, he underwent an experiment to save his life that ended up giving him superhuman strength and a seemingly unbreakable skin. After he escaped from his prison, he changed his name and moved to New York City, marrying Connors and living there until her death seemingly due to a random bus crash.

Name: Luke Cage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Luke Cage, also known as Power Man (real name Carl Lucas), is a superhero from Marvel Comics. He first appeared in Luke Cage, Hero for Hire #1 (June 1972).

Name: M.O.D.O.K. Superior
Summary: M.O.D.O.K. Superior is the result of a failsafe program carried out by the original M.O.D.O.K. to ensure the continuation of his legacy in the eventuality of his downfall against the coalition of the Hulks. He is one of many cloned brains, but unlike the others he has been allowed to retain his free will. Upon surfacing as the new M.O.D.O.K., he vowed to not follow the faulty tracks of his predecessor and live his life free of any artificial conditioning, a trait most exemplified in his much more human and varied characterization.

Name: Magmortar
Summary: Magmortar is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Magmar, and the final form of the Gen II Magby. It evolves when traded with a Magmarizer. It releases flames of over 3600 degrees Fahrenheit from its arms, quite literally putting the mortar in Magmortar.

Name: Magnum Force (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Moses Magnum was fascinated with weapons as a youth. When Italy invaded Ethiopia, he joined the invaders against his own people. He eventually became the world's foremost independent weapons manufacturer. When Magnum's Deterrence Research Corporation (DRC) was hired to develop a toxic biochemical gas, he tested it on kidnapped innocents. The Punisher and Spider-Man shut down this operation, though Magnum narrowly escaped death.

Name: Malkarion the Blackguard
Summary: Malkarion was a lieutenant of the black dragon Despayr and former cleric of the god Tyr before switching to the side of Shar. He was a Dark creature- a being somewhat made of the nonexistent shadowstuff of the Plane of Shadow. Generally, Malkarion's tasks in service to Despayr was to organize the cult on the Plane of Shadow and allow the dragon to concentrate. He was known to have rich tastes, and went so far as to be eccentric to the point of keeping a Gorgon as a mount (though he was regularly petrified by it).

Name: Mammoth (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An ancient ancestor of the modern day elephant , the Mammoth is massive herbivore from the ice age. Mammoths live in cold plains in in big herds, where their general size makes so besides humanoids nobody bothers trying to hunt them.

Name: Man Mountain Marko (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Michael Marko was a street thug who had unknowingly decided to mug Peter Parker, believing him to be a timid teenager. Peter was distracted by his Aunt May's illness, just knocking Marko away like he was nothing. This humiliation had determined Marko for his path to strength, beginning with bodybuilding, but then body enhancements by genetic engineering, all the while he spiraled into the crime world, under the name Man Mountain Marko.

Name: Man-Ape (Marvel Comics)
Summary: M'Baku was born and raised in the Jabari Village within the nation of Wakanda, Africa. He was one of the greatest warriors of the African nation Wakanda, second only to T'Challa, the Black Panther himself. While the Panther, King of Wakanda, was on leave from his royal duties to serve the Avengers in America, the ambitious M'Baku plotted to usurp the throne. The Wakandan culture evolved from a hunter-warrior society and was traditionally ruled by its greatest warrior. The Black Panther outlawed the rival White Gorilla cult from Wakanda while the Panther cult was dominant. M'Baku flouted T'Challa's edicts and revived the White Gorilla cult, personally stalking and killing one of the rare white gorillas living in the jungles near Wakanda. Bathing in the gorilla's blood and eating the gorilla's flesh mystically conferred its great strength upon M'Baku, as he became Man-Ape, leader of the Jabari and a frequent foe to Wakandan peace.

Name: Man-Bat (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Studying methods to cure deafness by experimenting on bats, brilliant biologist Kirk Langstrom accidentally unveiled a formula that would go on to create one of Batman's most tragic foes, Man-Bat.

Name: Man-Thing (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ted Sallis was a scientist working for the United States Army on a super soldier serum known as SO-2, in the Florida Everglades.

Name: Mandarin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Mandarin was born the child of Mongolian and British aristocrats, both of whom died shortly after his birth. He was raised by his aunt, who was bitter about not being the inheritor of the family fortune and decided to twist his mind, raising him to be vain and bloodthirsty.

Name: Manticore (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Manticores were savage, man-eating magical beasts not dissimilar from the likes of Griffons and Chimeras, in that it was primarily a combination of three other creatures- a lion, a dragon, and a human. Its tail was from some unknown creature or possibly none at all, though it was an extremely deadly tool as it could rapidly fire out spikes as large as a sword.

Name: Mao Mao
Summary: Mao Mao (full name Mao Mao Mao) is the primary protagonist and titular character of the Cartoon Network series, Mao Mao: Heroes of Pure Heart. Originally, he and his friend, Badgerclops were but a band of rogue heroes trying to defeat the villainous Sky Pirates led by Orangusnake. Until Mao Mao and Badgerclops crashed into the Ruby Pure Heart: a barrier shielding Pure Heart Valley from the forces of evil. Feeling guilty for his actions, Mao Mao stayed in the village to protect its citizens from dangerous monsters and invaders. Later finding out the Ruby Pure Heart is a mystical artifact wanted by those seeking glory and recruiting a young girl wishing to be a hero like him named Adorabat. Now defender of the valley, he fights to uphold justice and one day become a legend known and beloved by all.

Name: Maokai
Summary: Tier: 8-B | 7-A | High 6-A

Name: Marid
Summary: Marids are aquatic genies hailing from the Elemental Plane of Water. While not evil, they are known to bend wishes to their liking. They are extremely rare on the Prime, more often being seen in the Elemental Plane of Water, inhabiting a vast coral palace in the mightiest reefs of the plane. All Marids declare themselves royalty and lords, though few have the power to enforce such expansive titles. Their ego is their greatest weakness, often lending them to weave legendary tales of their awesome might.

Name: Marnie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Marnie (Japanese: マリィ Mary) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Bede, and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon. She eventually replaces her older brother Piers as the Gym Leader of her hometown Spikemuth. As the Spikemuth Gym Leader, she gives the Dark Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Mary, Queen of Blood (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Mary Seward, also known as Mary, Queen of Blood, is the lover and enemy of I, Vampire. While he wished to live peacefully with humanity, she wanted to dominate them. After much fighting, Mary eventually came to agree with Andrew when he sacrificed himself to cure all vampires, and joined the effort to save him, even giving her life in the final battle against Cain to stop him.

Name: Mechanica
Summary: Mechanica is a playable fighter in ARMS. She was born without extendable ARMS, so she uses a powered suit to compete in the ARMS Grand Prix.

Name: Medusa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Medusas are creations of powerful Demon Lords or Archdevils, mortals who begged to become beautiful, to become loved. In return, after years of status and acting as a demigod among mortals, they are reduced to medusas, horrifying to behold. They live forever, secluded, turning any who might see them to stone.

Name: Megatherium (Dungeons And Dragons)
Summary: The Megatherium or more commonly known Ground Sloth is a massive mammal which lived in ancient times.

Name: Meltan
Summary: Melmetal is the evolutionary form of Meltan.

Name: Meramon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Merfolk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Merfolk are humanoid creatures bound to the sea and were half-human, half-fish, created in such a manner by the god Eadro (also known as the Deliverer, the Bather of Gills, and the Lord of the Sunlit Shallows). Aesthetically, they bore more similarities with fey-like creatures such as elves or eladrin than with humans. As with most humanoids they are neutral and can choose their own alignments based on taste. The primary historical threats to their people are merrow (murderous aquatic humanoids), and the consistent Seros wars, terrible conflicts that often decimate the entirety of their population.

Name: Messerschmitt Bf 109
Summary: The Messerschmitt Bf 109 G-6/R3 is a single-engined, single-seat monoplane fighter and a German World War II fighter aircraft that was the backbone of the Luftwaffe's fighter force. The Bf 109 first saw operational service in 1937 during the Spanish Civil War and was still in service at the dawn of the jet age at the end of World War II in 1945. It was one of the most advanced fighters of the era, including such features as all-metal monocoque construction, a closed canopy, and retractable landing gear. It was powered by a liquid-cooled, inverted-V12 aero engine. From the end of 1941, the Bf 109 was steadily being supplemented by the Focke-Wulf Fw 190. It was commonly called the Me 109, most often by Allied aircrew and among the German aces, even though this was not the official German designation.

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Mettle (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ken Mack was a member of the founding class of Avengers Academy, Hank Pym's hero school. Originally just your normal Hawaiian surfer, a hit to the face tore off part of his skin, revealing a skull of living iridium. Looking for someone who could return him to normal, he found Norman Osborn, who instead accelerated the transformation. After Osborn was revealed as a villain and arrested, Mettle was taken in by the Avengers alongside several others Osborn had experimented on and was trained to be a hero as the iridium juggernaut Mettle.

Name: Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21
Summary: The Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21 (Russian: Микоян и Гуревич МиГ-21; NATO reporting name: Fishbed) is a supersonic jet fighter and interceptor aircraft, designed by the Mikoyan-Gurevich Design Bureau in the Soviet Union.

Name: Mimi Tachikawa (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Mimi Tachikawa and her partner Palmon are members of the DigiDestined and thus major characters in Digimon Adventure 2020. Mimi is the Crest Bearer of Purity.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Mindless Ones (Marvel)
Summary: The Mindless Ones were created by Plokta as a way of slowing the expanding empires of rivals, they were virtually unstoppable engines of destruction; when a rival was deemed to be becoming too powerful, Plokta would let the Mindless Ones loose in the rival's realm, tying up the rival's resources trying to contain them.

Name: Mira (Toilet in Wonderland)
Summary: Mira is the main protagonist of Toilet in Wonderland. In the beginning of the game, she wakes up in a dream world that was created by her constipation. Her constipation level starts off at 100%, and as she collects laxatives and discovers the game's various magic toilets, that level will drop. If the level is dropped to 0%, the true ending will be unlocked.

Name: MirageGaogamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Misango
Summary: Misango is a playable character in ARMS. Like the other ARMS fighters, he was gifted with the mutation of ARMS, allowing his limbs to be extendable.

Name: Mister Fantastic
Summary: Reed Richards, better known as Mister Fantastic, is the leader of the Fantastic Four and the head of the Future Foundation. A nearly unparalleled scientist, he invited his colleagues Susan Storm, Johnny Storm, and Ben Grimm to test an experimental spacecraft of his own design as the government threatened to withdraw funding. Although their launch was successful, the ship's shielding was inadequate to protect the team from a sudden burst of cosmic radiation caused by a solar flare as they tried to enter hyperspace. This radiation mutated Richards, allowing him to stretch and elongate his body at will into nearly any shape he could imagine, with his friends suffering mutations of their own. Convinced that he ought to use his newfound powers for the good of humanity, he created the Fantastic Four, one of the world's first superhero teams.

Name: Mister Negative (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Martin Li, a gangster from China, found himself fused with an extra-dimensional demon from the Darkforce Dimension. The two entities, now sharing one body, call themselves Mister Negative.

Name: Mister Sinister
Summary: Mister Sinister, or just Sinister, is a fictional supervillain appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character first appeared in Uncanny X-Men #221 (Sept. 1987) and was created by writer Chris Claremont and artist Marc Silvestri.

Name: MOAB
Summary: The GBU-43/B Massive Ordnance Air Blast (commonly known as the Mother of All Bombs) is a large-yield conventional (non-nuclear) bomb, developed for the United States military by Albert L. Weimorts, Jr. of the Air Force Research Laboratory. At the time of development, it was touted as the most powerful non-nuclear weapon ever designed. The bomb was designed to be delivered by a C-130 Hercules, primarily the MC-130E Combat Talon I or MC-130H Combat Talon II variants.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Moff Gideon
Summary: Moff Gideon was an officer of the Imperial Security Bureau who contributed to the Great Purge against the Mandalorians until graduating to the rank of marshal and then Moff. After the Galactic Empire's downfall, he evaded execution for war crimes and became the leader of a powerful imperial fragment army while seeking a force-sensitive baby of the same species as Jedi master Yoda, causing him and his forces to conflict with The Mandalorian and his allies.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Comics)
Summary: While on a mission in Sudan, mercenary Marc Spector was left for dead in the desert by Raul Bushman, a ruthless African general, but was afterwards resurrected by the ancient Egyptian moon god known as Khonshu in exchange for being his avatar on Earth. Marc would later return to New York City and become the vigilante known as Moon Knight. Marc Spector possesses multiple personalities, such as the millionaire entrepreneur Steven Grant and cab driver Jake Lockley, and suffers from dissociative identity disorder, which causes great mental stress and instability that has made him an unstable and volatile person.

Name: Morbius the Living Vampire (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Michael Morbius was a brilliant scientist born in Greece who became a Nobel Prize winning biochemist. He suffered from a debilitating blood disease and developed an experimental treatment involving vampire bats and electroshocks. Its side effects turned him into a pseudo-vampire who needed to consume blood in order to survive and gained typical vampire characteristics such as an aversion to sunlight, and the powers of flight, enhanced strength, speed, and healing (a healing factor). His overall appearance changed as well: he gained fangs, his nose flattened to appear more bat-like, and his skin became extremely pale. Additionally, the victims of his bite would turn into living vampires themselves. He became a recurring foe as well as unwilling ally of Spider-Man, and went on to be a crime fighter himself, as Morbius, The Living Vampire.

Name: Morlun (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Morlun is a vampiric being, an inhabitant of Earth-001, and is a recurring foe of Spider-Man.

Name: Mostodon
Summary: A distant relative of the elephant the Mostodon stands tall at 10 feet with tusks which can grow anywhere between 12 to 15 feet, this tusks allow the Mostodon to combat its enemies directly without being in range of their melee attacks.

Name: Mother Panic (DC Comics)
Summary: After killing her father in self-defense after she overheard him threatening to sell her mother to a criminal organization, Violet Paige was sent to an experimental boarding school, Gather House. Treated in an inhuman manner, forced through rigid training and being experimented upon with cybernetic implants, Violet eventually murdered one of her abusers, Mother Panic, and destroyed Gather House, before taking Panic's name for herself and swearing to exact revenge upon those that hurt her.

Name: Motormouth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Young orphan Harley Davis was abandoned on the streets of London's East End, and rough-housed her way to the cusp of adulthood, at which point her foul-mouthed demeanor had earned her the nickname Motormouth.

Name: Mr. Freeze (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Victor Fries was a cryogenics worker operating in Gotham City trying to find a way to cure his ill wife Nora. When he preserved her in cryostasis without authorization from GothCorp, the company tried to shut his research down, and in Victor's attempt to stop them he was caught in a dangerous chemical accident that left him unable to survive outside of very cold temperatures. Building a special suit to keep himself alive, he used it to become the supervillain Mr. Freeze.

Name: Mr. Mime
Summary: nan

Name: Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)
Summary: Kamala Khan was a normal teenager until she was imbued with the mist from the Terrigen Bomb. The mist activated her latent inhuman DNA, resulting in her gaining polymorphic abilities. As she wished to became a hero like her idol Carol Danvers, she took her name and became the hero Ms. Marvel. She started to tread her own path as a hero, and gained recognition by many other heroes, becoming an Avenger, and even making her own super hero team, the "Champions". After being killed while helping Spider-Man, and resurrected in Krakoa, she finally found out her mutant heritage.

Name: Mustard (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)'''
Summary: Mustard is a character in The Isle of Armor in Pokémon Sword and Shield. He is a former Champion of the Galar region and the mentor of Leon. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Dojo Master.

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Mystra (Midnight)
Key: '''Beginning of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''End of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''Avatar''' | '''Greater God'''
Summary: Before she was the God of magic, Mystra was known as the wizard Midnight. Born Ariel Manx, she was the second child of the merchant Theus. A hedonist, Ariel would spend her time with the local bards, sorcerers, fighters, and thieves where she would eventually earn her nickname Midnight due to her late night activities. Eventually she would develop a fascination with magic and left her home in the pursuit of a higher calling.

Name: N (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Black and White 2''' | '''Pokémon Team (Season Battles)'''
Summary: N is a character in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2. He was the puppet leader of Team Plasma in Pokémon Black and White and aspired to create separate worlds for humans and Pokémon. His full name is Natural Harmonia Gropius (ナチュラル・ハルモニア・グロピウス Natural Harmonia Gropius).

Name: Namor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Namor, born Ch'ah Toh Almehen, also known as K'uk'ulkan, is a Talokanil Mutant who rules over the underwater kingdom of Talokan. Determined to protect his people from the surface world, Namor felt threatened when the United States came close to his country while searching for vibranium. Namor came into contact with Wakanda and proposed a military alliance, so no one would ever threaten them, but the Golden Tribe resisted waging war against the world. In response, Namor led his people against Wakanda, claiming the life of Ramonda. He was ultimately defeated by the new Black Panther and forced to yield, still expecting that eventually, Wakanda would ask for his help.

Name: Natsuko Aki (Re)
Summary: Natsuko Aki is a police inspector in the Re:Cutie Honey continuity. Initially hostile towards Cutie Honey on account of her destructive battles and believing they do more harm, rather than good, she eventually begins to warm up to her, becoming one of her most trusted, devoted, and valuable allies.

Name: Nessa (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hulbury Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Nessa is the Gym Leader of Hulbury's Gym, known officially as Hulbury Stadium. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon. She gives the Water Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Nico Minoru
Summary: Nico Minoru is the sole daughter of Robert and Tina Minoru, who hail from a powerful mystic bloodline. As a 16 year old attending an annual "charity event" under the organization known as Pride, Nico and her friends discovered their parents were actually super-villains, and the yearly event was a pretense for Pride to sacrifice children to the deities of Gibborim. After witnessing the sacrifice, they chose to run away from home while Nico adopted the alias: Sister Grimm. Nico would come to learn of the family treasure known as the Staff of One as their parents pursued them. Following the chaotic betrayal of her then boyfriend Alex Wilder, the parents were forced to die saving their kids, rendering Nico and her friends lonesome allies, who branded themselves as Runaways. She would serve as the leader of the Runaways, a member of the heroine team A-Force, and even an instructor at the Strange Academy.

Name: Nidalee
Summary: Raised in the deepest jungle, Nidalee is a master tracker who can shapeshift into a ferocious cougar at will. Neither wholly woman nor beast, she viciously defends her territory from any and all trespassers, with carefully placed traps and deft spear throws. She cripples her quarry before pouncing on them in feline form—the lucky few who survive tell tales of a wild woman with razor-sharp instincts, and even sharper claws...

Name: Niffty
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Night Hag
Summary: Night Hags are witch creatures originating from the Feywild, a corrupt, evil creature with a stark contrast to the many good-aligned beings of the plane. Night Hags in particular hold special ties to the Abyss, Night Hags fittingly have a specific goal in mind: turning the righteous to villainy. Their kind has long since made their bases in Hades, but spread freely throughout the Lower Planes.

Name: Nightmare (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Nightmares are horse-like creatures originating from the Lower Planes, such as the Abyss, the Nine Hells, or Gehenna. They are the standard choice of mount for high-ranking fiends and undead alike, most often searching devil and demon lords, vampires, liches, and other evil-aligned creatures such as the shadar-kai. They are truly wicked beings and are best known for their flaming bodies and vicious tempers.

Name: Nipper Plant
Summary: Nipper Plants are enemies introduced in Super Mario Bros 3. They are small Piranha Plants with white heads and short green stems with two leaves on either side. They attack by jumping when Mario is near, and some of them attack by shooting fireballs.

Name: Norman Osborn
Summary: Norman Osborn is the corrupt founder and head of Oscorp, a multi-billion dollar multinational corporation. After he took the experimental "Goblin Formula" to enhance his intelligence, his already unstable mind fractured further, leading to him becoming the original Green Goblin. In this role, he has been Spider-Man's greatest and most persistent archenemy, responsible for the death of Gwen Stacy. While his primary opponent and obsession is Spider-Man, his goals have branched out further in the past, and, at one time, he was the director of H.A.M.M.E.R., a replacement for S.H.I.E.L.D., and the leader of an Avengers populated by "reformed" supervillains, as the "Iron Patriot".

Name: Northstar
Summary: Northstar (Jean-Paul Beaubier) is a fictional character, a superhero who appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is the twin brother of Aurora. Through his mutation, Northstar gains superhuman powers, which he uses for the betterment of society. Although originally a member of Alpha Flight, a fictional team of Canadian superhumans, Northstar is later portrayed as a member of the X-Men. He is one of the first openly gay superheroes in American comic books, and the first openly gay character to come out in a book published by Marvel Comics. He married his partner, Kyle Jinadu, in Astonishing X-Men #51, published June 27, 2012.

Name: Nuke (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Frank Simpson was an American soldier deployed to Vietnam. He was an exemplary soldier, but at some point he was captured and tortured, which broke his mind, and then his body was nearly destroyed. The United States Government, seeing both Frank's potential and that he could be controlled, put him through another experimental Super Soldier project. They replaced a large amount of his body with cybernetics, and replaced the outside of his skin with hard plastics. They also devised a pill based system to control him. Red pills made him aggressive, White pills made him calm down, and blue pills kept him calm.

Name: Nycaloth
Summary: Nycaloths are powerful and intelligent greater yugoloths native to all of the Lower Planes, though mainly found in Gehenna. Their role in yugoloth society often takes up that of scouts and observers, traveling the Abyss and the Nine Hells, scouring for information on the tanar'ri and baatezu. In combat, nycaloths are elite airborne shock troops of the yugoloth legions and are feared by even greater devils and demons for their combat wit. Unlike other yugoloths, nycaloths are noted to be extremely loyal to their superiors, provided they are treated well. However, above all else the nycaloth is easily angered- it is said that they are prone to destroy entire companies of lesser yugoloths in fits of rage.

Name: Oblex
Summary: An Oblex is a collection of sentient slime created by the Illithids through various experiments in the Underdark. Akin to its creators, The Oblex shares a diet for the minds of others and is devoted entirely to absorbing the substance, using its wits to stalk intelligent prey before proceeding to engulf its prey's head, draining out their memories and personality while leaving the prey clueless and perplexed afterward, if not dead. These memories are presumably represented by the head of its victim.

Name: Obould Many-Arrows
Key: '''Orc Chief''' | '''King of the Citadel of Many-Arrows''' | '''Exarch of Gruumsh'''
Summary: Obould Many-Arrows is widely regarded as the most iconic orc in the Forgotten Realms, and a recurring opponent of Drizzt Do'Urden and Bruenor Battlehammer, among others. A cunning and intelligent creature even by human standards, Obould established himself as an Orcish power when he wiped out and took in several other orcish tribes, establishing a kingdom in the Spine of the World. Eventually, Obould signed a peace treaty (much to the dismay of his followers) with elf, human, and dwarf, cementing the existence of his kingdom as a major power in Faerun.

Name: Ogremon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C, up to Low 1-C | At least 6-C, up to Low 1-C

Name: Ohio-class Submarine
Summary: The Ohio class of nuclear-powered submarines is the sole class of ballistic missile submarines (SSBN) currently in service with the United States Navy. Fourteen of the eighteen boats are SSBNs, which, along with U.S. Air Force strategic bombers and intercontinental ballistic missiles, constitute the nuclear-deterrent triad of the U.S. The remaining four have been converted from their initial roles as SSBNs to cruise missile submarines (SSGNs). The Ohio-class boats, each displacing 18,750 tons submerged, are the third largest submarines in the world, behind the 48,000-ton Typhoon class and 24,000-ton Borei class of the Russian Navy. The Ohio class replaced the Benjamin Franklin- and Lafayette-class SSBNs.

Name: Old Man Logan
Summary: Old Man Logan is an alternate-universe version of Wolverine. His story takes place in a universe which used to be identical to Earth-616.

Name: Orangusnake
Summary: "Lord" Orangusnake is one of the primary antagonists of the Cartoon Network series, Mao Mao: Heroes of Pure Heart. Underhanded and fierce all in one, he leads the treacherous Sky Pirates with the goal of seizing the legendary Ruby Pure Heart and then conquering the world. However he wasn’t always so powerful; originally being two lone criminals. A snake named Coby and an orangutan named Tanner who merged to become much more powerful and intimidating than they ever would be alone. Combined, they serve as the most dangerous and recurring threat to Pure Heart Valley and its sheriffs. Never backing down despite their numerous losses, determined to make Mao Mao truly fear them.

Name: Orcus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Aspect''' | '''Out of the Abyss''' | '''In the Abyss''' | '''Lesser God''' | '''Tenebrous, with the Last Word''' | '''With the Last Word and Wand of Orcus'''
Summary: Orcus is the powerful demon lord of the undead. He began, like many demon lords, as a wicked mortal- a powerful spellcaster. He slowly climbed the ranks of demonhood after his demise until he became Orcus, demon lord of the damned. He would eventually achieve godhood, although this was temporary as he was soon after slaughtered. Orcus has a terrible habit of returning from the dead and squabbling with his fellow demons. It is said that he is one of (if not the most) powerful demon lord, with massive physical strength coming from his massive frame (standing 15 ft tall and weighing 6,000 lbs).

Name: Orphan-Maker (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Nanny: Murdering brute -- he's just a baby! Gambit: Coulda fooled me.

Name: Otyugh
Summary: Look out to the base of the wall there... look hard, and look for an enemy. An eye! An eye... coming up from the ground like a worm! But- but- what is it, out there? Only your father can tell you that, Erammon. And if I were you, I'd make sure he was in a good mood when I asked him.

Name: Ouryumon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least 5-B, possibly 1-C

Name: Outriders (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Outriders are an alien species that serve as warriors for Thanos and the Black Order. They appeared in Avengers: Infinity War, where they were deployed in dropships to take the Mind Stone from Vision, fighting against the Avengers and the military of Wakanda in an attempt to reach him, but their horde was quickly destroyed when Thor, Groot and Rocket Raccoon arrived on the battlefield.

Name: Overdrive (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Beverley was once a boy who dreamed to become a superhero like his hero Spider-Man. However, after failing to obtain superpowers in any way and proving himself to be inept at martial arts, he resigned himself to become a motorist like his father. However, after an accident left him seriously injured, he was approached by Mr. Negative, who sought his talents as a driver and promised to enhance his abilities through a swarm of nanobacteria that would allow him to transform any vehicle he came into contact with, as well as heal his injuries.

Name: Owlbear
Summary: Owlbears are a chimeric, magical combination of owls and bears (as the name implies), and are known to be terrible predators. They are famed for their ill tempers and ferocity- a fight with an owlbear is a fight to the death. Once they were natives to the Feywild, however they have since migrated to other worlds.

Name: P-47 Thunderbolt
Summary: The P-47 Thunderbolt was an escort fighter designed in 1941. Early on in the war it carried out escort missions and bombing missions on key targets. Heavy example of its use for a bomber fighter was in Italy. Constant improvement to the planes design continued but it eventually lost its need as an escort fighter to the P-51D due to increasing demands for range and low altitude speed, however the P-47 remained in service until past the end of the war. the P-47 was retired from service by all nations in 1966, with the last built P-47 was shipped out in October 1945.

Name: Papa Midnite (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: A powerful Vodou bokor who has created his own criminal empire, Papa Midnite is one of John Constantine's most noteworthy antagonists, having been at different times his ally or sworn enemy.

Name: Paul Rabin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Paul Rabin is the son of the Emissary who encountered Peter Parker and Mary Jane Watson after they entered his reality while fighting their own Emissary. After MJ used a device to send Peter back home, Paul spent nearly four years with her due to time dilation before Peter's return. During that time, Paul and MJ had found and adopted two kids to raise as their own. Apparently married, MJ refused to leave Paul, and they continued their family life in Earth-616.

Name: Pikachu
Summary: nan

Name: Plastic Man (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Eel O'Brien was small time gangster who was in the middle of a heist with his friends. As he was unlocking the safe, a guard caught wind of their crime and tried to stop him. One of his friends shot the guard and the guard shot back, but missed and hit the container of a chemical gas that spread towards Eel. It burned his skin, severely injuring him. While escaping in car, his friends betrayed him and chucked him out of the car, leaving him to die, however the gas didn't kill him and instead gave him the powers of elasticity, turning him into Plastic Man.

Name: Plesiosaurus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A massive aquatic dinosaur, the plesiosaurus is a powerful beast that sailors might deal with in their voyages.

Name: Poison Ivy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Poison Ivy is an enemy of Batman. She is depicted as one of the world's most prominent eco-terrorists. She is obsessed with plants, botany, and environmentalism. She uses toxins from plants and her own bloodstream for her criminal activities, which are usually aimed at protecting the natural environment. Fellow villain Harley Quinn is her recurring partner-in-crime and possibly her only human friend.

Name: Popeye (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An incredible fighter, Popeye is an amazing sailor who can even fight dragons once he eats spinach.

Name: Proxima Midnight (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Proxima Midnight was one of Thanos' children and a member of the Black Order. After retrieving the Space Stone with Thanos and her siblings, she and Corvus Glaive ambushed Vision and Scarlet Witch in Scotland, only to be defeated by Captain America, Black Widow and Falcon. Later, she and Cull Obsidian led the Outriders to invade Wakanda. She confronted Scarlet Witch, and was about to kill her, when Black Widow and Okoye interfered. As she was about to kill the two, Scarlet Witch used her telekinesis to throw Proxima Midnight into the path of a large war machine, crushing her.

Name: Punchline (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Alexis Kaye was a cold-hearted and psychopathic young woman who idolized The Joker, though crafted a very strong public image of someone who merely believed that Joker had good intentions at heart. After a killing-gone-wrong, The Joker reached out to her and the two began a relationship shortly thereafter. Now with the identity Punchline, she serves as a villain to the Batman Family, especially Nightwing, Clownhunter, and Bluebird.

Name: Punisher (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lt. Frank Castle returned home from duty only to see his wife and children murdered in front of him in cold blood by the Mafia. Unable to find justice by any fair means for them, Castle vowed to spend the rest of his life avenging them. Now equipped with state-of-the-art weapons, decades of combat experience, guerrilla and urban warfare techniques, as well as detective-like skills, he wages a one-man war against crime as the Punisher, a murderous vigilante that takes no prisoners, and comes at odds with both heroes and villains for his methods.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Quaggoth
Summary: One of many races which inhabit the underdark, the Quaggoth is a savage creature which tears enemies apart with their claws and weapons. They often become Drow slaves in order to fight surface world elves.

Name: Quicksilver (FOX)
Summary: Quicksilver, born Peter Maximoff, is a mutant who has the ability to move at superhuman speed.

Name: Quicksilver (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Pietro Maximoff was a native of the Eastern European country of Sokovia who grew up with his fraternal twin sister, Wanda. The country, which was embroiled in constant war and strife, became the base of operations for a HYDRA cell operated by Wolfgang von Strucker, who recruited Pietro and Wanda to take part in a series of tests involving the Scepter, giving the twins superpowers. While his sister received a number of mental abilities, Pietro acquired the ability to move at supersonic speeds and other physical features. When HYDRA fell, the twins joined the A.I. Ultron to continue their quest for revenge on Tony Stark, but eventually switched sides and helped the Avengers when they discovered Ultron's true intentions. Pietro then fought in the Battle of Sokovia alongside all of the other Avengers, but later sacrificed his own life to protect Hawkeye and a civilian boy named Costel, much to his sister's grief.

Name: Quicksilver (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Quicksilver (Pietro Maximoff) is a fictional superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character first appears in X-Men #4 (March 1964) and was created by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby. He is the twin brother of the Scarlet Witch.

Name: Radioactive Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Chen Lu was originally a Chinese nuclear physicist working on a way to defeat Thor, who had stopped his country's military strike on India. His plan was to expose himself to radiation, making him strong enough to defeat the Asgardian, and this granted him immense strength and various abilities. A frequent foe to Thor, Dr. Lu has been a member of the Thunderbolts and the Masters of Evil with an undying loyalty to his nation, as Radioactive Man.

Name: Rage Drake
Summary: The Rage Drake is a a primitive creature that's more akin to a cruel animal than an actual dragon. They also lack any sort of special magical abilities and thus they rely on stealth and brute force.

Name: Ragman (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Rory Regan is an ex-US soldier who now seemingly lives a quiet life as owner of the book/antique shop Rags 'n Tatters, but in reality lives a second life as the vigilante Ragman, who uses a demonic cloak to fight evil.

Name: Rahadin
Summary: Rahadin is the dusk elf servant of Strahd, and his long-time immortal brother-in-arms. He was banished from the Dusk Elf kingdoms for refusing to bow down to the king. He is credited as Strahd's most powerful general and having slaughtered thousands of men in the name of his count.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Ras Nsi
Summary: Ras Nsi was once a Chosen of Ubtao, a Primordial planar power residing in Chult. Some time long ago, however, he cast off his oaths and his power, and became an evil warlord, raising the dead to be his armies. When he did so, he lost control of his necromantic hordes, and in his defeat sought out the Yuan-Ti of Omu to take control.

Name: Rath Modar
Summary: Rath Modar is a Red Wizard of Thay and the primary conspirator against the lich Szass Tam in the campaign to retake Thay. During the crisis concerning the Cult of the Dragons, Rath offered his wizards' might to assist the cult in their goal of summoning Tiamat from the Nine Hells. It was his silent hope that Tiamat would, when she saw how useful he had been, offer to him an army of dragons to wipe out Szass Tam once and for all.

Name: Ravager (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Rose Wilson is a fictional character in the DC Comics universe. She is a member of the Teen Titans and the illegitimate daughter of Deathstroke.

Name: Ravemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Reader (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Not much is known about the Reader except that he was born in the Inhuman settlement of Orollan, and was forcibly blinded when the elders of the village saw and feared his powers, however he learnt to still be able to use them despite his blindness, and strives to protect others using his gifts.

Name: Reaper (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Pantu Hurageb was a member of the Mutant Liberation Front under the alias of Reaper, where he clashed repeatedly with the New Mutants and X-Force, often finding himself pitted against Shatterstar, losing his limbs in their confrontations. He has also temporarily been a reluctant hero as a member of the Exiles, when he was unwittingly transported to the Ultraverse.

Name: Red (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Beginnings)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Early Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (End Game)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Red is the enigmatic and silent protagonist of Pokemon Red/Blue/Yellow and its remakes Pokémon FireRed/LeafGreen, as well as the hidden final boss of Pokémon Gold/Silver/Crystal and its remakes Pokemon HeartGold/SoulSilver.

Name: Red Dragon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Wyrmling to Young''' | '''Juvenile to Mature Adult''' | '''Old to Ancient''' | '''Wyrms and Great Wyrms'''
Summary: And belching fire, and began to lunge down

Name: Red Goblin (Normie Osborn)
Summary: Grandson of Norman Osborn, Norman Harold Osborn, more commonly referred to as Normie, is also Red Goblin. Attaining his current symbiote Rascal through Venom giving him it, Normie is bonded to it. Together they escaped Norman, deciding to join the Avengers Academy instead, being ashamed of his heritage.

Name: Red Guardian (Alexi Shostakov)
Summary: Alexi Shostakov was an ex-pilot and Natasha Romanova's husband, who after faking his own death, was transformed into the superhuman Red Guardian, protector of the Soviet Union.

Name: Red Guardian (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Red Skull (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Johann Schmidt was the commanding officer of HYDRA, a special weapons division of the Nazi Schutzstaffel and the modern-day incarnation of the ancient HYDRA society. A brilliant scientist in his own right, he fought his way through the ranks of Nazi elite to become a confidant of Adolf Hitler himself. However, his ambition to become the superior man led him to test the Super Soldier serum on himself which transformed him into the horrifying Red Skull.

Name: Red Skull (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When Johann Schmidt was born, his mother Martha died while giving birth to him, leading to his father Hermann attempting to kill him and eventually killing himself. Left an orphan on the streets of early Nazi Germany, Johann turned to a life of theft until he began working as a bellhop in his late teens. During this time he ended up rescuing Germany's then-leader Adolf Hitler from an assassination attempt, who was so impressed with the hatred of mankind he could see within Schmidt that he began to personally train him into a "perfect soldier". Upon his training's completion, he had become the Red Skull, and turned into the archenemy of Captain America.

Name: Red Tool
Summary: Red Tool is a Gotham City vigilante who's infatuated with Harley Quinn. At first he grossed her out, but with time they became good friends.

Name: Rek'Sai
Summary: The largest and fiercest of her species, Rek'Sai is a merciless predator that tunnels through the earth to ambush and devour her prey. Her insatiable hunger has laid waste to entire regions of the once-great Shuriman empire. Merchants, traders and armed caravans will go hundreds of miles out of their way to avoid these vast areas, though cunning bandits have been known to lure the unwary into her killing grounds. Once Rek'Sai detects you, your fate is sealed. There is no hope of escape; she is death from below the sand.

Name: Remorhaz
Summary: Native to frozen lands, the Remorhaz spends all its days hunting prey. They are a millipede like creature that emits incredible heat from its body, using it burrow through ice without any issue.

Name: Rengar
Summary: Rengar is a ferocious vastayan trophy hunter who lives for the thrill of tracking down and killing dangerous creatures. He scours the world for the most fearsome beasts he can find, especially seeking any trace of Kha'Zix, the void creature who scratched out his eye. Rengar stalks his prey neither for food nor glory, but for the sheer beauty of the pursuit.

Name: Retriever
Summary: Retrievers are the "gopher" units of any demonic fiefdom. Whenever a powerful lord or commander desires to search out lost artifacts, runaway slaves, or unruly underlings, the Retriever is sent out to find them and return them through any means possible. Most scholars can agree that the Retriever is built to mimic the structural design of the Bebilith, though the reason is unknown. Since they are constructs that are easily accessible to most demonic leaders, the Retrievers are also regularly entrusted with tasks that cannot be given to the demon's kin, for their ugly kind are not reliable.

Name: Rezmir the Black
Summary: Rezmir is a black half-dragon warrior placed in charge of a regional sect of the Cult of the Dragon, an organization dedicated to furthering Tiamat's goals across the plains. Around the time of Rezmir's leadership, the cult grew greatly in power and began to enact a plan to bring living dragons to great power, and eventually summon the Dragon Queen herself.

Name: Rhino (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Aleksei Sytsevich was an ordinary member of the Russian mob up, until the day he accepted to undergo experimental treatments that would augment his physical capabilities. He was then equipped with an armored suit which warranted him the codename Rhino. Aleksei became a superpowered thug for hire, and clashed with many superheroes, notably Spider-Man and the Hulk.

Name: Rictavio
Summary: Rictavio, also known by his former name of Rudolph van Richten, is a legendary vampire hunter posing as a bard/circus ringleader in Barovia. He is also the former mentor of Ezmerelda d'Avenir. After having slain his son following his turning into a vampire spawn, and having witnessed his wife die to yet another vampire, Rictavio has spent his life hunting the undead ruthlessly. Now, as he nears the end of his life, he aims to slay the greatest vampire of all time- Strahd von Zarovich.

Name: Risque (Marvel Comics)
Summary: After her Cuban father, and Seminole mother divorced when she was twelve, Gloria Muñoz moved out with her mother and lived with her until she was 16. Having discovered her mutant powers, she left to live on her own and spent some time in Miami. During this time, Sledge helped her out of some trouble, and she promised to aid him in the future, a favor which was eventually repaid when she was tasked with bringing him the mutant Warpath.

Name: Robin (Damian Wayne)
Summary: Damian Wayne is the biological son of Bruce Wayne and Talia al Ghul. His existence was hidden from his father up to when he was about ten years old, during which time he was trained by the League of Assassins in a variety of disciplines to make him an extremely efficient killer. Damian was then sent to his father to disrupt his work as a vigilante (a task he completed with ease thanks to his blood relations and lack of social skills), but later grew to prefer his role as the son of Bruce Wayne and his time as Robin over his position as the al Ghul heir.

Name: Roc
Summary: A massive bird, the Roc is the supreme ruler of the skies in the mountains. They only go against large targets such as elephants, with the Roc being able to lift them with one leg. Sometimes Cloud and Storm Giants tame Rocs and use them as a deadly asset.

Name: Rock Gnome
Summary: The most common of the Gnomes, the Rock Gnomes are found all across the surface world. They are inventive and rather intelligent, using it to construct various devices for fun. They are also considered superb gunsmiths.

Name: Rogue (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anna Marie is a mutant who ran from home because of her aunt's controlling nature. As a runaway, already going by the name Rogue, she is found by Mystique who adopted her. She founds out in the worst way that she is a mutant by almost killing her first boyfriend, realizing that she couldn't have a normal life anymore she joins Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. On one of her missions she fights Ms. Marvel and by mistake permanently absorbs her powers almost killing her in the process. Didn't take long to realize that Carol Danvers memories were affecting her to the point of controlling her, so she asks Charles Xavier for help, after a long time of training and living her life as if she was cursed, she finally managed to control her powers and have a love life with Gambit.

Name: Roper
Summary: The larva form, also known as a Piercer is an ambush predator in underground places that uses it camouflage in order to let itself drop upon prey whenever it senses someone below it. The adult form, also known as a Roper meanwhile is a far more active hunter, which while still using stealth, also employs tentacles it tosses at enemies in order to pull them to its maw.

Name: Roserade
Summary: Roserade is a fully evolved, third stage, Grass and Poison type Pokémon originating from Gen IV. It evolves from the Baby Pokémon Budew with high friendship into Roselia, and from Roselia into Roserade with a Shiny Stone.

Name: Russian (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Russian, real name Ivan Vassilovitch Dragovsky is a supervillain in Marvel Comics. He is an opponent of the antihero known as The Punisher - originally a fairly traditional Punisher foe (having little in the way of superhuman powers) he evolved into a more powerful comic book super villain following his resurrection by a paramilitary group.

Name: Rylkar
Summary: Rylkar are rats that have evolved during heir time in the Underdark. They are known to enter an area, consume everything within it, and reproduce using all resources exponentially- thus leaving a rat-infested barrens. Rylkars bear a strong tie to flame, and view it as raw energy, something they can use to reproduce their thousands of young.

Name: Ryouga
Summary: Ryouga (Japanese: リョウガ) is the main character of the Pokémon RéBURST manga. Hot-blooded, naive, and not particularly worldly, he is able to gain the powers of a Pokémon with the aid of a Burst Heart. The one thing he hates most is the word "impossible", mentioning it riles him up into accomplishing what he was deemed incapable of doing.

Name: Sabretooth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: 8-C physically, Low 1-C with Adamantium claws

Name: Sahuagin
