Summary: Utterly vile and ruthless, the Sahuagin, also known as Sea Devils, terrorize the sea and beaches alike. They hold incredible hate for sea elves, going of their way to destroy nearby communities of them.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Salamander (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Native to the Realm of Fire, the Salamander are a hierarchical race which roams the land. The weaker Salamanders are often enslaved by other races, while the Noble are among some of the strongest inhabitants of the realm.

Name: Sanctuary II
Summary: The Sanctuary II was a massive warship commanded by Thanos. It was likely named after Thanos' previous base of operations, Sanctuary.

Name: Sandman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in a modest family, young William Baker was abandoned by his father and left in poverty with his alcoholic mother. He soon learned that this world rewards the strong, so he turned to violence first and to crime then, going by the alias of "Flint Marko".

Name: Sangonomiya Kokomi
Summary: Sangonomiya Kokomi (珊さん瑚ご宮のみや心ここ海み, Sangonomiya Kokomi?), is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact. The young Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island and a descendant of the Sangonomiya Clan, Kokomi is in charge of most of Watatsumi's affairs, shouldering heavy responsibilities alone in hopes of giving Watatsumi Island's people the hopes and happiness that they desire.

Name: Sarah Kerrigan
Key: '''Ghost Operative''' | '''Queen of Blades''' | '''Primal Queen of Blades''' | '''Xel'Naga'''
Summary: Sarah Kerrigan is a Terran Psionic and the Queen of Blades. Originally an agent of the Dominion, she was an incredible sniper. Eventually, she was betrayed by her commanding officer, Emperor Arcturus Mengsk, and left for dead. She was not killed, however, and was instead infected by the Zerg Overmind. Her psionic potential vastly increased, she wielded devastating power and was a terror to all who encountered her, effortlessly tearing through entire armies.

Name: Saxton Hale
Summary: Reader, if you thought the first two pages of my comic contained too much bare-knuckle excitement, then get ready to have your eyes break from widening in surprise and your comic-holding hands fall off your very arms when you get a look at the rest of this action-packed ish, starring me... SAXTON HAAAALE!

Name: Scarecrow (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Jonathan Crane was abused by both peers and family alike as a child due to his unusually slender appearance. With this making him grow resentful to all around him, he soon developed an obsession with fear and phobias, getting revenge on everyone who ridiculed him through lethal frights. As an adult, Jonathan becomes a psychologist for Arkham Asylum, where he performs fear-inducing experiments onto the inmates, and he eventually combines a scarecrow suit based off of an incident in his childhood with a special chemical gas he developed to become the criminal Scarecrow.

Name: Scarlet Spider
Summary: Benjamin "Ben" Reilly, also known as Scarlet Spider, is a clone of the original Spider-Man created by the Jackal.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wanda Maximoff is a Romani Transian sorceress and twin sister of the speedster Quicksilver. Once believed to have been mutant children of Magneto, the twins are in truth orphans enhanced by the High Evolutionary at Mount Wundagore. Wanda became a conduit of chaos magic, allowing her to shift probabilities and warp reality itself in the form of "hexes". After being saved from an angry mob by Magneto, the Scarlet Witch and her brother joined the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants to fight for Magneto's mutant supremacy cause. Disagreeing with Magneto's ruthless approach, the twins left him and joined the super-heroic Avengers instead, as the Scarlet Witch.

Name: Schwerer Gustav
Summary: The Schwerer Gustav is the heaviest gun ever built, weighing in at nearly 1350 tonnes. It was designed explicitly to destroy the main forts of the Maginot Line; the strongest fortifications in existence at the time.

Name: Scientist Supreme (Andrew Forson)
Summary: Andrew Forson is an A.I.M. scientist who has served as its Scientist Supreme in the past. A manipulative yet driven personality, he led A.I.M. initially as it went public, and was able to use his charisma and leadership to form the new High Council of A.I.M. He was eventually ousted from his position by Sunspot, and has remained a prominent leader within the now-fractured organization.

Name: Scorpion (Marvel Comics)
Summary: MacDonald Gargan is a former detective hired by J. Jonah Jameson to investigate Peter Parker who was subjected to a painful experiment that gave him superhuman abilities and drove him insane, leading to him becoming Scorpion, one of Spider-Man's many persistent foes.

Name: Selene (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born 17,000 years ago, prior to retcons Selene was noted as being the first mutant. She is a special kind of mutant known as an External. Living for many years, Selene has the power of psychic vampirism which she uses to empower herself and give herself a youthful body, effectively making her immortal so long as she feeds.

Name: Sevika
Summary: Sevika is one of the two secondary antagonists (alongside Marcus) of Season 1 of Arcane. She is Silco's top enforcer in his criminal empire, serving as the muscle for many of his operations. After getting caught in one of Jinx's explosions, she lost her left arm, which was replaced by Shimmer-powered cybernetics.

Name: Shadow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An enemy of the living that lurks in the darkness, the Shadow is a menacing foe to face in combat. As their name implies, they're animated shadows of dead people. Their origins are shrouded in mystery however one thing is for certain, that being that their touch is deadly. Their touch siphons life and strength from those unlucky enough to be hit by it, and if one dies from this their shadow becomes a new Shadow monster.

Name: Shang-Chi (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to the fearsome Fu Manchu, Shang-Chi was trained to be a living weapon to serve under Si-Fan, becoming one of the greatest martial artists in the world. However, during his first assignment, he came to know of his father's true identity as an international criminal mastermind, and defected soon afterwards. He has fought against the tyranny of his father ever since, and continues to fight for the safety of those around him.

Name: ShineGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode | 1-C

Name: Shocker
Summary: Herman Schultz was a bold criminal who attempted to make a living off of stealing. When he ended up getting caught he began building a suit and vibro-shock units in prison, afterward using them to become the Shocker.

Name: Shocker (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Herman Schultz is a former salvage worker who had become a professional criminal and one of the key members of Adrian Toomes' Crew who had sold alien-human hybrid weaponry created by the Tinkerer. As Toomes had murdered his former crewmate Jackson Brice, who had used a modified gauntlet occasionally under the alias of Shocker, Toomes passed the gauntlet down to Schultz and then appointed him as the new Shocker. With his new title and power of the gauntlet, Schultz continued to aid Toomes with fighting Spider-Man's attempts to stop all their black market arms deals, eventually resulting in the Shocker being defeated during a fight and arrested. (Marvel Cinematic Universe Wiki)

Name: ShogunGekomon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Shredstorm
Summary: Shredstorms are a swarm of thousands of tiny electrified constructs that take the form of bladed disks. Due to machinations of arcane nature taken at the time of the construct's creation, Shredstorms are bound together, with each of the shuriken-like constructs magically being attracted to others. They are designed as siege-breakers, and are used to overwhelm enemy defensive positions as well as tear defenders to ribbons.

Name: Shruikan
Summary: Shruikan was a black male Dragon, forcibly bonded to Galbatorix. He was the only dragon other than Glaedr to survive the Fall of the Dragon Riders to modern times. Galbatorix used Magic to artificially speed up Shruikan's growth, making him gigantic in size.

Name: Shuri
Summary: Shuri is the princess of Wakanda and king T'Challa's younger sister. Having longed to one day become the Black Panther much like her brother, she finally took the mantle on when T'Challa was put into a coma by the Cabal, though the Heart Shaped Herb initially rejected giving her power. When she saved her entire nation from Morlun in her brother's absence, the herb recognized her honor, finally giving her its strength and making her an offical secondary Black Panther alongside the king.

Name: Shuri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Shuri is the princess of Wakanda and sister of its king, T'Challa, the Black Panther. Leader of the Wakandan Design Group, she is responsible for the invention of Wakanda's most recent technology and her brother's costume, later helping him retake the Wakandan throne from Erik Killmonger.

Name: Shy Guy
Summary: Shy Guys are common enemies in the Mario and Yoshi franchises. They are recognizable by their masks, which they wear due to their shyness. Shy Guys made their first appearance in Yume Kōjō: Doki Doki Panic, a non-Mario game; they were later carried over to the Mario universe when Super Mario Bros. 2 was created.

Name: Silencer (DC Comics)
Summary: Raised since her youth by Talia Al Ghul to be part of her elite, superpowered assassin organization Leviathan, Silencer was for many years one of her most dangerous agents, performing nearly impossible missions thanks to her ability to completely negate sound in certain areas. Her prowess was such that she was eventually allowed to retire, after which she formed her own family and sought to live a normal life with a husband and child, taking the name of Honor Guest.

Name: Silk
Summary: nan

Name: Silver (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cherrygrove City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Azalea Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Burned Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Goldenrod Tunnel)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)'''
Summary: Silver (Japanese: シルバー Silver) is one of the main characters and the rival of Pokémon Gold, Silver, Crystal and Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver. He is the son of Team Rocket Boss Giovanni that fought many times with Ethan, Kris or Lyra.

Name: Silver Sable (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of a famed Nazi hunter Ernst Sablinova, Silvija asked to train under her father to avenge her mother's death, soon exceeding her father's expectations to be one of the best assassins across the globe, and succeeded him as the Head of Sable International, leader of the Wild Pack and monarch of Symkaria.

Name: Silver Samurai (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Keniuchio Harada (Silver Samurai) is the mutant, illegitimate son of the former Japanese crimelord Shingen Harada, head of the Clan Yashida. As a youth, Harada mastered the attendant disciplines of the medieval samurai and sought employment as a warrior for hire. He first worked for the criminal Mandrill and clashed with the blind hero Daredevil.

Name: Sinister Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Stephen Vincent Strange, also known as Sinister Strange, is a minor antagonist in the 2022 Marvel Cinematic Universe film Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness. He is a variant of Earth-199999's Doctor Strange, who was unable to live a life without his love, Christine Palmer.

Name: Sister Dagger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: One of the many daughters of the sorcerer and crimelord Zheng Zu, Zheng Esme was raised in the House of the Deadly Dagger outside of Paris, France, eventually becoming its Champion, Sister Dagger. When Sister Hammer named herself as the new Supreme Commander of the Five Weapons Society over its rightful successor, Shang-Chi, Sister Dagger and Brother Sabre approached their half-brother to usurp Hammer. Shang-Chi reluctantly joined them to free his remaining family from his father's cult.

Name: Skullbuster (Cylla Markham)
Summary: When pilot Cylla Markham was nearly dead after a supervillain shot down her aeroplane, she was found by Donald Pierce, who offered to give her cybernetic enhancements in exchange of her loyalties to the Reavers. Outfitted with metallic claws, she became the group's all-new Skullbuster.

Name: Sleipmon (Species)
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Snorlax
Summary: nan

Name: Snow Goblin
Summary: Standing between 3 to 4 feet tall, Snow Goblins are a Goblinoid creature that inhabits cold lands. Their voices can be heard from miles away and are used as hunting signals. The females are usually larger and more aggressive then males.

Name: Snow Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Made from snow this golems are found in both Icewind where they appear in their weaker forms and while their stronger variant exist in Ravenloft where they act like guardians for various places and appear like statues

Name: Solarmon
Summary: Solarmon is a Machine Digimon that appears to be a rare species of Machine-species Digimon. Among researchers, it is said to be a mutation of Hagurumon, but the truth is a mystery. Due to its "Computer Kernel" generating heat, its body has become hot enough to cause burns.

Name: Solomon Grundy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Solomon Grundy is a fictional character, usually depicted as a supervillain in DC Comics and an antihero in the DC animated series. He was originally depicted as a murder victim brought back to life as a corporeal revenant or zombie, though subsequent versions of the character have occasionally depicted a different origin. He is named after the 19th-century nursery rhyme Solomon Grundy.

Name: Sora Takenouchi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Sora Takenouchi and Piyomon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Sora bears the crest of love, Piyomon is her partner Digimon. She is a "Chick" type Digimon who specializes in fire based attacks.

Name: Speed Demon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Sanders is a fictional character in Marvel Comics. He was just a regular chemist when he received abilities from the Grandmaster. Equipped with his new abilities he used them to become a criminal and master thief. Using his chemical knowledge he was able to amplify his powers becoming the supervillain, Speed Demon.

Name: Spider-Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Peter: May, their chance of getting help is way better back where they came from. Sending them home, that's the best we can do for them. May: For them or for yourself? Look around you, this is what we do, we help people.

Name: Spider-Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Peter Benjamin Parker, more well-known as Spider-Man, was once just a nerdy teenager in High School. But after he was bitten by a radioactive spider at a science exhibition, he gained the proportionate strength, speed, and agility of a spider alongside a special precognitive ability known as the "Spider Sense" to warn him of incoming danger. However, after using his powers to in a wrestling match to earn money yet not prevent a burglary going on backstage that he had witnessed first-hand, he later returned home to find out that his Uncle Ben was murdered by someone who broke into their house.

Name: Spider-Man (Reign)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Peter Parker's time with Mary Jane had given her cancer, which she died from. Parker had retired from superheroics and was working as a florist, while a merciless and oppressive police force, named "The Reign", take power, imprisoning every superhuman they can find.

Name: Spider-Man 2099
Summary: In the year 2099, Miguel O'Hara, the head of the genetics department for the Alchemax Corporation, becomes the legendary hero known as Spider-Man.

Name: Spider-Woman
Summary: Jessica Drew lived with her parents in the nation of Transia. At the age of 7, she suffered from uranium poisoning because of her father's work. Her father Jonathan with Dr. Herbert Wyndham, managed to save her life using a spider-derived serum. Jessica spent decades in stasis until she was finally awakened, realized she was cured. Wanting a new life, she left her house but ended up being caught by Hydra. They brainwashed her and trained her to become their operative. On one of her missions, she was tasked with killing Nick Fury but was caught by him and told the truth about the organization she was working with. The truth made her quit and start again, trying to find her path in life. She started going by the superhero name Spider-Woman and saving people, sometimes working for S.H.I.E.L.D.

Name: Spidercide
Summary: Much like Scarlet Spider and Kaine Parker, Spidercide is a clone of Peter Parker created by the Jackal. Unlike his “brothers”, he had been given additional abilities so he could defeat them.

Name: Spirit Naga
Summary: Spirit Nagas are witch-like nagas hailing from the time of the sarrukh. Irrevocably evil, these creatures are typically found in solitude, guarding some long-forgotten ruin of an ancient civilization, or ruling over a cult of lesser beings who worship the naga like a goddess. These creatures can be found in numerous locales, and are even found in the Orient as spirits. Their appearance varies heavily, with many simply bearing a human head on a serpentine body. It is said to be easy to identify a spirit naga by scent, as their favorite meals include rotten flesh, giving them a terrible odor.

Name: Spock
Summary: Tier: 9-C physically. At least 8-C with phaser. | 9-B. At least 8-C with phaser.

Name: Sports Maxx
Summary: nan

Name: Star-Lord (Classic)
Summary: Peter Quill, alias Star-Lord, was born during an unusual astronomical phenomenon when many of the planets aligned. Quill was raised by his single mother, Meredith. One day Peter saw an Ariguan spaceship land, and his mother was killed by the aliens. When he told the police his mother had been killed by aliens, no one believed him and he was put in a state orphanage. He ran off when he was fifteen and eventually became a trainee NASA astronaut. When the alien entity called the Master of the Sun visited the space station that Quill was stationed at and offered the mantle of Star-Lord to a worthy candidate, Quill volunteered, but was rejected in favour of another astronaut. Quill was outraged, stole a scoutship, and on returning to the space station took his colleague's place. Quill was then chosen to become Star-Lord, with the Master of the Sun first creating an illusion in which he was able to find and kill the aliens that murdered his mother to free him of his past. Equipped with a sentient vessel called "Ship", Quill commenced his role as Star-Lord.

Name: Star-Lord (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ego: Stop! Listen- Listen to me! You are a god. If you kill me, you'll be just like everybody else! Star-Lord: What's so wrong with that?

Name: Stature (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of Scott Lang, Cassie Lang developed growth powers as a result of repeated exposure to Pym Particles, which were interlinked to her emotional state. After the demise of her father, Cassie carried his legacy by becoming a member of the Young Avengers under the alias of Stature.

Name: Stegosaurus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is the same creature as it is in real life but exists in Dungeons and Dragons.

Name: Stegron (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Vincent Stegron was working as an assistant to Dr. Curtis Connors on a project for S.H.I.E.L.D. that used dinosaur tissue supplied by Ka-Zar from the Savage Land. Becoming obsessed with the Lizard experiments and growing tired of the ills of human civilization, he decided to steal the dinosaur extract. He fled to the Savage Land and ingested the Connors Formula with the Stegosaurus DNA, turning himself into a Dinosaur Man.

Name: Stick (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Stick is a member of the Chaste, an ancient, powerful organisation that was created to fight the Hand and stop them from the mysterious Black Sky upon the world. Stick was born blind, but learned to hone his other senses to superhuman degrees. He became an extremely skilled martial artist who would go on to train Matt Murdock and Elektra Natchios, and later aid them in fighting the Hand.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Stone Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Stone Golem is the strongest of the common golems, often also being the prettiest looking due to being often assigned to guard museums.

Name: Storm (Marvel Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Sudowoodo
Summary: Tier: 8-C | 7-B

Name: Sugar Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A former inhabitant of Earth-295, the grotesque monstrosity calling himself Sugar Man made his way into Earth-616 and established himself as a criminal mastermind working behind the scenes in Genosha, and frequently clashes with the X-Men.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Super Shotgun
Summary: Essentially this weapon is a traditional (some might say outright old) double barrel shotgun that found its way to Mars and was used to fight off the demon invasion by none other than Doomguy himself. This shotgun is potentially three times more powerful than the typical shots fired from the Combat Shotgun.

Name: Superboy (Jonathan Samuel Kent) (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jonathan Samuel "Jon" Kent is the biological son of Superman and Lois Lane. Born with the help of Thomas Wayne in the Flashpoint timeline, Jon grew up oblivious to his heritage and the fact that he and his parents were from an entirely different version of Earth than the one he lives in. However, various circumstances led him to discover his family's past and awaken his latent Kryptonian powers. As a result, his father decided to officially begin teaching Jon about his abilities, allowing him to become Superboy.

Name: Supreme Intelligence (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Supreme Intelligence is an organic, computer construct, with the intelligence of the greatest minds of the Kree race. Was created by the Kree with the goal of creating a Cosmic Cube, although after gaining he's own will refused to do so as that could destroy the Kree race. He's intelligence eventually granted itself the position of ruler, and so using all he's power made Kree a powerful force in the universe.

Name: Susztam Mar-Shinn
Summary: Susztam is the Head Student of the Inverted Tower, a Drow outpost of arcane learning located in Szith Mercane. As the Head Student, he maintains the greatest control over his magic, and one day hopes to usurp his master in becoming the position of his master- until then, he spends his days in the Inverted Tower, training and learning constantly. He is particularly known to be a master of illusory spells and makes use of them frequently[1]. The position of head student is one envied by his peers, and thus Susztam spends his days preparing for their inevitable betrayal[2]. During the takeover of Szith Mercane, Susztam has entered the service of Dorina T'sarran, occasionally acting as a strike-team killer on her behalf[3].

Name: Taichi Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from the 2020 Reboot of Digimon Adventure. After being forcefully sucked into a Digital Space, Taichi meets Agumon alongside Yamato and Gabumon and defeats Algomon. Afterwards, Taichi and Co end up being sent to the Digital World where they go on an adventure to save the Holy Digimon while learning the secrets behind the Holy War between the forces of Light and Darkness.

Name: Taillow
Summary: Tier: 8-A | At least 7-A

Name: Takeru Takaishi (Adventure 2020)
Key: '''Takeru Takaishi''' | '''Patamon''' | '''Pegasusmon''' | '''Angemon''' | '''HolyAngemon''' / '''Holyangemon Priest Mode''' | '''Goddramon''' | '''Seraphimon and BlackSeraphimon''' | '''DanDevimon Shadow'''
Summary: Takeru and Patamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Takeru is the crest bearer of Hope and the younger brother of Yamato Ishida.

Name: Takuto and Shiki
Key: '''Start of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game and Post Game''' | '''During Voltobautamon rematch'''
Summary: Takuto and Shiki are the male and female protagonists of Digimon World: Next Order. They are a high school-senior ramping down the extracurricular activities and preparing for college exams. Addicted to Digimon games as a kid, even earning a second-place finish in the national championships as a fifth-grader. In present, they once again take the Digivice, which suddenly shines with light and transports them into the Digital World. Landing in a sealed dimension, they meet their partners, WarGreymon and MetalGarurumon, only to be suddenly attacked by a Machinedramon.

Name: Talis Kasterel
Summary: Talis the White was a high-ranking member of the reformed Cult of the Dragon, and a lieutenant of Rezmir the Black. Initially, she was a favorite candidate as the White Wyrmspeaker, but Severin Silrajin instead gave the position to a dwarven ally, Varramzord. At some point, it is believed she betrayed the cult due to this slight against her, though she is believed to have died in the fighting regardless.

Name: Talons (DC Comics)
Summary: The Talons are an order of assassins serving the Court of Owls, a shadowy cabal that subtly manipulates and influences Gotham City. Talon prospects would be recruited from Haly's Circus and put through an intense training regimen in order to turn them into the perfect killers for the Court. For centuries, these Talons would act as enforcers, being sent to silently dispatch enemies of the Court or those who posed a security risk. Augmented with regenerative capabilities due to biological modifications and armed with peak level weapons and training, Talons are a foe that spell doom to almost anyone unfortunate enough to face one down.

Name: Tashlyn Yafeera
Summary: The Master of Arm and Mercenaries, Tashlyn Yafeera acts as the provider of weapons and training for the sellwork of the Black Network.

Name: Taskmaster (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Antonia Dreykov, also known as Taskmaster, is the daughter of General Dreykov, who possesses uncanny photographic reflexes that allow her to mimic the fighting techniques of other individuals. Having been gravely injured during an assassination attempt on her father, Antonia had her mind and body controlled by a chip, turning her into Taskmaster, the Red Room's premiere commander.

Name: Taskmaster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tony Masters is a man who can mimic and copy physical actions. He considered a career as a crime fighter but decided to become a professional criminal. After using his skills to complete a series of jobs, he used the capital to start an academy to train aspiring professional criminals around the world. Eventually, his operations were discovered and shut down by the Avengers. Since then Taskmaster has worked as a spy, a mercenary and still acts as a teacher to certain individuals, all for the sake of profit.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: The Batman Who Laughs
Summary: On Earth -22, the Joker's insane rampage across Gotham City caused Batman to finally snap, breaking his long-held creed to never take a life, snapping the Clown Prince of Crime's neck to end the threat he posed once and for all. Unbeknownst to him, this released a special strain of Joker Venom that Batman inhaled, slowly twisting his moral fiber until he was no different from the Joker himself.

Name: The Fly (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Fly (formerly the Human Fly) once used to be Richard "Rick" Deacon, born in Newark, New Jersey, a small-time criminal who was shot by the police and left for dead after an unsuccessful kidnapping attempt, which was foiled by Spider-Man. Stumbling into the laboratory of Dr. Harlan Stillwell (whose brother Farley Stillwell created the Scorpion for J. Jonah Jameson), Deacon coerces the scientist into saving his life.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The Inspector
Summary: From the 1965 cartoon series, stars the inspector. The Inspector is a police detective from France who is always trying to bring justice, thus getting into situations where he must find out a way to solve the problem.

Name: The Joker (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: The Lizard (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Curtis Connors was a military surgeon turned herpetologist who lost his right arm during the war and sought to restore it by performing genetic research on the regenerative capabilities of reptiles. The serum that should have been the cure has instead turned him into the Lizard, a crazed but cunning monster who plans to return the planet to reptiles, which he believes being their righftul owners. Spider-Man always managed to foil his plans and reverse him back to a human, but every attempt at erasing the Lizard forever proved uneffective, and it remained a looming threat which could manifest anytime.

Name: The Nazgûl (Shadow of War)
Summary: The Nazgûl were known as Sauron's closest servants and often traveled on black horses or their fellbeasts, wearing black cloaks and hauberks of silver mail. They are described as being strongest when The Dark Lord has possession of the One Ring. The power of the Nazgûl also grows when all nine are together and when night falls upon Middle-Earth.

Name: The Player (Parry!!)
Summary: The Player is an unofficial name for the playable character in Parry!!. Not much is known about them outside of the fact that they go around killing waves of enemies and conquering various planets or "zones".

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: The Recruit (Transformers)
Summary: The Recruit is a rookie who arrived on Earth during the to help either the Autobots or the Decepticons to destroy the opposing force on earth. Unlike his predecessor, he can scan various weapons & power-ups that can help him during his missions.

Name: The Robin King
Summary: Bruce Wayne was born into the wealthy Wayne family of Gotham City. However, he had been a violent child ever since he was a baby, which the butler Alfred Pennyworth knew but ignored out of attachment and the belief that he'll grow up to have a calmer personality. The child would make an excuse whenever he was caught, and Alfred helped hide his violent attacks even from his parents but one day decided he had enough. Unfortunately for him, that very same day Bruce killed his parents when they took him to the movie theater. They were stopped by a mugger as they were returning home, but he stabbed him before using his gun to kill his shocked parents. When the police arrived, he lied that the mugger had shot them.

Name: The Turtle (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: The first villain Barry Allen has ever defeated, The Turtle is the direct opposite of Flash in their power. He is the avatar of the Still Force which lets him slow down objects and people to a screeching halt. In a possible future Turtle rules over Central City with an iron fist, with him having plans to slow down the whole multiverse.

Name: Thrust SSC
Summary: Thrust Supersonic Car is a British jet car developed by Richard Noble, Glynne Bowsher, Ron Ayers, and Jeremy Bliss.

Name: Thunderbolts (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The New Avengers, previously named the Thunderbolts by Alexei Shostakov, are a team of extraordinary individuals, with either superpowers or other special characteristics. They were assembled in 2027 as a result of being targeted by Valentina Allegra de Fontaine and working together to stop the Void from taking over New York City. Following their victory, de Fontaine manipulated the situation to declare the team as the newly formed iteration of the Avengers, which was met with a mixed reception from the public.

Name: Thwimp
Summary: The Thwimp are an enemy in the Mario Bros. franchise and are the Child of Thwomps[2], they jump small distances in attempts to take town Mario and his friends.

Name: Tig Rafelson (DC Comics)
Summary: Tig Rafelson is a young vampire hunter who ran into Andrew Bennett, ambushing him as he searched for his wife and enemy Mary Seward. While she came close to defeating him, he convinced her to temporarily side with him. While nominally on Andrew's side, Tig would often be a wrench in his plans, even killing him at one point, and after his return, he turned her into his vampire minion while under an evil curse. Tig finally found her death at the hands of Cain, who briefly used her body to resurrect his wife Lilith, but was quickly defeated alongside her by Andrew and Mary.

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Tigra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 8-C, at most High 8-C

Name: Titanium Man
Summary: Boris Bullski was a high ranking official in the Soviet government and a popular member in the Communist Party. In order to prove the USSR's superiority over the U.S, he created the Titanium Man armor to rival Tony Stark's Iron Man armor.

Name: Togepi
Summary: Tier: 8-C | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Tombstone (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lonnie Lincoln was born an albino and thus, subject to both racism and mockery for his albinism. He responded by bullying and extorting his classmates, including his only friend, Joe Robertson. Lonnie eventually went further into bad behavior and became a thug for mob bosses or a mob boss himself, depending on what was more convenient for him at the time. This was when he earned the moniker Tombstone.

Name: Tornado
Summary: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air, in contact with the ground, either pendant from a cumuliform cloud or underneath a cumuliform cloud, and often (but not always) visible as a funnel cloud. Tornadoes come in many shapes and sizes, but they are typically in the form of a visible condensation funnel originating from the base of a huge storm cloud, whose narrow end touches the earth and is often encircled by a basal cloud of debris and dust. Most tornadoes have wind speeds less than 110 miles per hour (180 km/h), are about 250 feet (80 m) across, and travel a few miles (several kilometers) before dissipating. The most extreme tornadoes can attain wind speeds of more than 300 miles per hour (480 km/h), are more than two miles (3 km) in diameter, and stay on the ground for dozens of miles (more than 100 km).

Name: Toxie Doxie (Marvel Comics)
Summary: You get to understand there are haves and have-nots in this world, you know? And that the have-nots don't really have the same right to life as the people who worked hard to be selected for greatness. And when the have-nots accidentally enter a position of power, where they can prevent Darwinian victors from exercising their talents... That's just wrong.

Name: Treant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living tree; the "'Treant"' serves as the forest's guardian. They are generally peaceful but will attack any evil creature or those who carelessly use fire. Treants come in many varieties, with some having creatures like Rot Grub on their bodies to combat pests.

Name: Trienath Salazar
Summary: Trienath Salazar is a veteran Hellbreaker, a group of thieves adept at intruding into the depths of Baator and taking the diabolical treasure from within. Trienath is fleeing from the Pit Fiend Zaebos, a member of the Dark Eight of Avernus, and offers to help player characters if she finds them to be righteous.

Name: Tsukaimon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | High 8-C | High 8-C | High 8-C

Name: Tu-95
Summary: The Tupolev Tu-95 is a 4-engine turboprop strategic bomber and missile platform developed by Tupolev, with it being an upscaled version of the previous Tu-4, which is a reverse engineering of the B-29. The bomber is the first intercontinental bomber developed by the USSR, with it's closest US Counterpart being the B-52 Stratofortress. Much like the B-52, it has gone through various upgrades and maintenance, remaining in service to this day.

Name: Twintelle
Summary: Twintelle ​is a playable character from ARMS. She is a movie star and uses the ARMS in her hair to fight in the Grand Prix amongst other ARMS fighters.

Name: Tybalt the Cursed
Summary: Tybalt the Cursed is the iconic Hellbred, a race of souls cast into Hell that repented their evil deeds in life the very moment they touched upon Baator, transforming them into the damned species they now represent. As a Hellbred, Tybalt possesses superhuman powers to work towards redemption, but this is a truly horrid life- for only the most hopeless and suicidal ventures lead to retribution. The life of a Hellbred is one of hurling oneself into impossible odds, seeking either death or the minuscule chance of success.

Name: Tyrogue
Summary: Tyrogue (Japanese: バルキー Balkie) is a Fighting-type Baby Pokémon originally introduced in Gen II. Known for its boundless enthusiasm for training and getting stronger, this Pokémon can evolve into several different forms depending on what aspect of its physical attributes it focuses on training.

Name: U.S. Agent (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jonathan F. "John" Walker is a former Captain of the United States Army's 75th Ranger Regiment and a founding member of the New Avengers. Due to his successful operations around the world, Walker was chosen to succeed Steve Rogers as the second Captain America. However, his aspirations of living up to Rogers' legacy attracted the ire of Sam Wilson and Bucky Barnes in their pursuit of the Flag Smashers, during which he took the Super Soldier Serum after failing to apprehend Karli Morgenthau. When his partner and best friend Lemar Hoskins was killed in action, Walker brutally murdered a surrendering foreign national in public, leading to him being stripped of his mantle and discharged from the United States Army with total loss of rank. Walker confronted Morgenthau again in New York City but chose to abandon his revenge to join Wilson and Barnes in thwarting her attack on the GRC. Despite his discharge, Walker was recruited by government agent Valentina Allegra de Fontaine to continue serving America in secret as U.S. Agent.

Name: U.S. Agent (Marvel Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Ultron (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ultron is the titular main antagonist of the 2015 epic Marvel superhero sequel hit, Avengers: Age of Ultron. He is a self-teaching, self-aware artificial intelligence dormant peacekeeping program created by Tony Stark. Possessing an eight-foot-tall advanced robotic body, Ultron was created by Stark with the purpose of protecting Earth from threats, but eventually deemed humanity itself as the greatest threat to Earth and attempted to create a technological singularity by committing genocide against them.

Name: Ulysses Klaue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a black-market arms dealer and smuggler as well as a gangster who had operated out of South Africa. He was a former acquaintance of Tony Stark from his weapons-dealing days, and was an associate of N'Jobu when he attempted to expose Wakanda to the rest of the world. In 2015, during an encounter with Ultron, Klaue sold his entire stockpile of the Vibranium to the A.I. before losing his arm in an argument with Ultron, and fled when the Avengers arrived.

Name: Umber Hulk
Key: '''Umber Hulk''' | '''Truly Horrid Umber Hulk''' | '''Vodyanoi''' | '''Shadow Hulk''' | '''Umber Ravager''' | '''Abyssal Hulk''' | '''Astral Hulk'''
Summary: Umber Hulks are ancient mutant creatures born countless eons ago, possibly before the onset of the Dawn War[1]. Hulking bug-eyed monstrosities, the Umber Hulks lurk in the Underdark, tunneling from cavern to cavern in search of food (and little else), often causing wars and conflicts over territory as they move. They are feared on a nearly mythological level to some due to their peculiar ability to incapacitate hostiles with a glance- and leave survivors with nary a memory of what occurred.

Name: V-mon (Daisuke Motomiya)
Summary: Daisuke "Davis" Motomiya and his partner Veemon are two of the protagonists of Digimon Adventure 02. The de facto leader of the DigiDestined, their hot-blooded and reckless natures mean they have a lot of room for improvement, but they nevertheless step up to the plate and take the reins of their adventures with enthusiasm.

Name: Valentino (Hazbin Hotel)
Summary: Valentino is a one of the many Overlords in the show Hazbin Hotel. He resembles a moth with him having a set of wings[1] and having a squeak[2][1] whenever he is mad. In the show he runs Hell's adult film industry, and he is the abusive boss of Angel Dust[3]. He is one of the infamous "Vee" Overlords[4] along with Vox[4] and Velvette[4] who each control a part of Hell's entertainment with Vox controlling technology[2], and Velvette controlling social media[2]. Valentino's past is unknown with it being implied he died in the 1970s.

Name: Vel'Koz
Summary: Tier: 8-B | 7-A | High 6-C

Name: Velasta and Velina T'sarran
Summary: Velasta and Velina T'sarran are a pair of Drow identical twins, nieces of Irae T'sarran who server under her daughter, Dorina, in Szith Mercane. Their duties there vary from humdrum to violent, but primarily include raiding on the surface and serving in the elite Hunter-Killer team alongside Susztam Mar-Shinn and Zedarr T'sarran[1]. While they are considered somewhat important to Irae's plans, if slain they are not outright given the time or resources for resurrection- instead they rise as revenants created by Irae.

Name: Velvette (Hazbin Hotel)
Summary: Velvette is the last member of the infamous Vees alongside Vox and Valentino who are both influential throughout Hell. Velvette's most infamous fact is her control over social media as she can control it and describes herself as the backbone of the Vees. Her past is unknown with her cause of death still a mystery but from what can be inferred, she died around the 2000s as she is always on social media which was one of the newest things in the early 2000s. Unlike Vox and Valentino, Velvette poses no threat to the main cast, and she only serves as an irritation for the other Overlords of Hell such as Carmilla Carmine and Zestial.

Name: Venom (Edward Brock)
Summary: Eddie Brock was a journalist who tried to expose the identity of a serial killer only for the real killer to be caught by Spider-Man, thus he ended up accusing the wrong man. Disgraced, he came into contact with an alien Symbiote, rejected by Spider-Man. The Symbiote bonded with him and they became Venom.

Name: Venom Ooze
Summary: Theorised to be off shoots of ochre jellies this ooze is atypical in that it doesn't remain mostly in one spot and instead seeks out prey actively, which it's able to capture with its great strength and potent poison. This ooze is most commonly found in the Underdark alone but have been known to be used by evil individuals or simply migrated to another environment due to their incredible resistance to the elements.

Name: Venom Symbiote (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The symbiote that would be later known as the Venom Symbiote was the 998th of its lineage and was spawned at some point during the reign of the dark elder god Knull. Beyond this, much of the symbiote's history prior to its arrival on Battleworld is unclear -- in part due to the symbiote's memories having been erased, modified, or otherwise altered numerous times.

Name: Verdant Prince
Summary: Verdant Princes are powerful fey that roam the Prime Material, offering pacts with adventurers or even entire families. While often the pacts seem benign in nature (generally, the Prince won't even profit from the pact for many generations), each is in fact a malign curse on the pact-bearer, where when the Prince's plans come to fruition, that individual's descendants may well pay the full price of their ancestor's impudence.

Name: Vermin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Edward Whelan was once a young scientist working under Baron Zemo. Upon questioning his plan to create mutated soldiers, Edward was taken and subjected the same experiments, which were meant to bring out the darkest parts of a one's inner self and change their appearance accordingly. Edward's childhood trauma of being abused by his father resurfaced, and the sense of guilt and shame he felt at the time gave birth to an entirely new personality, bearing the name of the most ugly and vile creature Edward thought to be like: Vermin.

Name: Vespiquen
Summary: Vespiquen is a Bug/Flying type Pokémon, based on a queen bee. It rules over an entire hive of Combee, controlling and protecting it. It evolves from exclusively female Combee at level 21.

Name: Vi (Arcane)
Summary: Vi, born as Violet, is a Zaunite vigilante and Jinx's older sister. A hotheaded and fearless woman who excels at fighting and likes to solve her problems with her fists, she wields a pair of powerful hextech gauntlets that can punch through buildings-and people-with little trouble.

Name: Viper (Mammon)
Summary: Viper is an illusionist from the anime Katekyo Hitman Reborn! where he serves as the illusionist of the Vongola's assassination squad, the Varia. He's the mist Arcobaleno, the 7 strongest people in the world in a generation that were turned into babies, and thus is known as the most skilled illusionist of his generation (even though he's already lost against other illusionists). Mammon is very greedy and tends to charge other people, including his allies, very high costs for his services.

Name: Viserion
Summary: Viserion is one of the dragons born in the Dothraki Sea, along with Drogon and Rhaegal. He is named after Daenerys Targaryen's brother, Viserys Targaryen. He is distinguishable by his cream and gold colored scales, and red-orange wings. Eventually, after being killed, became a Wight and was enslaved by the Night King.

Name: Vitreous Drinker
Summary: Vitreous Drinkers are undead servants of Vecna, known to wander the lands stealing their victims' eyesight. To do this, they collect certain arcane items to surprise and ambush targets, and uses its skills to, after the attack, see through their victims' eyes. As worshippers of the God of Secrets, they often target great sages, spies, and magi to gain their information.

Name: Volcanicdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | Low 1-C | 1-C

Name: Vox
Summary: Vox is a major villain in the adult animated musical comedy series Hazbin Hotel[2], serving as a major villain in Season 1 and the main villain of Season 2. His powers are mostly based on electricity and technology as he owns Voxtek[1] which is a technology company that produces most of Hell's Technology[1]. Not much is known as his past life as a human but from what was confirmed, he was stated to have died somewhere in the 1950s making his stay in Hell shorter than Alastor's.

Name: Vrock
Summary: Vrocks are twisted and malicious demons of the skies, tending towards positions as bodyguards for much more powerful demons, or merely aerial assault troops in the Blood War. Oftentimes a group of Vrock demons will work together to create devastation across the battlefield.

Name: Vulture (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Vulture is a supervillain and one of Spider-Man's most die-hard enemies. Before becoming a criminal, Adrian Toomes was a capable engineer who had made a breakthrough when he invented a new kind of magnetic harness. It was an overwhelming joy after a life of hardships. But everything crumbled when he learned his business partner had been stealing a large sum of his profits before finally ousting him from the company they founded. Adrian was sad and angry, so he used what he knew to make a flying suit and become the Vulture.

Name: W54 warhead
Summary: Tier: High 8-C to 8-B | High 8-C to 8-A | 8-A | 8-A

Name: Wally (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mauville City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Third and Fourth Battle)'''
Summary: Wally is one of the player's rivals in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire as well as their remakes, Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. He is a meek and sickly young boy who aspires to become a great Pokemon Trainer, having covered his entire room and filled multiple notebooks with information on strategy and raising Pokemon. Over the course of his journey, he gains confidence and a stronger constitution, eventually amassing a powerful Pokémon team and defeating every Gym Leader in the Hoenn region before the player does. He then goes on to battle the player right before they go on to challenge the Pokemon League. Although he lost, he refused to let go of his dream, becoming even stronger and regularly challenging the player at the Battle Resort.

Name: War Machine (Marvel Comics)
Summary: War Machine (James Rupert "Rhodey" Rhodes) is a fictional character, a superhero appearing in comic books set in the Marvel Comics universe.

Name: War Machine Armor Model 1
Summary: The Iron Man Armor Model 11 was created by Tony Stark, who added immense weapon artillery into the suit. He then later modified and gave the armor to Rhodey, who would fight in this armor as War Machine.

Name: War Machine Armor Model 2
Summary: After Parnell Jacobs found the War Machine Model 1, he brought it to Stuart Clarke, who in turn brought it to Sunset Bain, who rebuilt the armor with her own technology.

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Warpath (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Warpath is James Proudstar, an Apache Indian and mutant. He joined Emma Frost's school for mutants, and later sought vengeance against the X-Men, believing they were responsible for the death of his brother, John Proudstar. Warpath eventually got over the death of his brother and joined the X-Men family, first as a New Mutant, then as a member of X-Force.

Name: Water Weird
Summary: Made from water, the Water Weird is one of the possible Elemental Weirds. In their younger form they appear like a water serpent, shooting cold water at enemies and using their physiology to drown people who come close to them. Their adult self meanwhile is a powerful caster, being able to use various healing and water spells alongside regular Sorcerer spells.

Name: Web-Weaver (Marvel Comics)
Summary: As a high school student, Cooper Coen had a crush on classmate Peter Parker. While on a field trip, Cooper saved Peter from being bitten by a radioactive spider, resulting in Cooper being bitten instead and gaining super-human abilities. Cooper's already rocky relationship with his homophobic parents was strained further by his need to hide his secret identity, ultimately resulting in them kicking him out of his home. Cooper came to live with his aunts, Laurie and Mel Coen. The two encouraged Cooper to follow his passions and put him in New York's best fashion school, which later led to him receiving a job at the premier fashion house, Van Dyne. He then became a superhero under the alias of Web-Weaver.

Name: Wheep
Summary: An eyeless pathetic creature, the Wheep is a servant of other more powerful creatures which is often used as a bodyguard. It constantly emits a black vile from its eyes which makes tracking it down rather easy, although if they choose to, a Wheep is more than capable of using stealth to gain the edge in combat.

Name: Whiplash (Anton Vanko)
Summary: Anton Vanko lost his father, his town and his hand, after a devastating attack on Vostok by someone wearing a stolen battlesuit of Iron Man Armor. Presuming Tony Stark himself was responsible for the attack, he sought vengeance by modifying one of his armors, and has been a persistent threat to him ever since, as the all-new Whiplash.

Name: Whiplash (Marco Scarlotti)
Summary: Marco Scarlotti was a Maggia enforcer who cared deeply about supporting his family financially, and has been a persistent foe for Iron Man as the first Whiplash.

Name: Whiplash (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ivan Antonovich Vanko was a Russian physicist and the son of the disgraced scientist Anton Vanko. When Vanko's father died penniless due to the actions of Howard Stark, Vanko swore to seek revenge by targeting Howard's son, Tony Stark. Recreating an Arc Reactor based on his father's design and designing an armor similar to Iron Man's, Vanko attacked Stark in Monaco, following the events after he was incarcerated. After he was broken out by Justin Hammer, who had recruited him, Vanko hijacked the Hammer Drones, as well as the Mark I War Machine Armor, in an attempt to assassinate Stark and destroy his legacy.

Name: Whirlwind (Marvel Comics)
Summary: David Cannon was a mutant born with the ability to spin at inhuman speeds, allowing him to create tornadoes as he went along. Turning to a life of crime, Cannon took on the alias of the Human Top, and then Whirlwind, and has been a frequent foe to the Wasp ever since.

Name: White Rabbit (Marvel Comics)
Summary: White Rabbit: We don't need them! We're the Terrible Two! We're evil personified! The vilest villains on the face of the-- Walrus: They hung up on you, didn't they? White Rabbit: Uh-huh. After they were done laughing.

Name: Whizzer (Post-Golden Age)
Summary: Robert Frank was born to Dr. Emil Frank, a health practitioner. In the year 1941, Robert, an adult, was an assistant for his father's practice. One day, Emil was performing surgery on mobster Gabe Granno, when Granno's rival Neal Jennings burst in and forced Emil's scalpel down, fatally wounding Granno. Jennings then threatened to accuse Emil of murdering Granno if he did not flee the country. Fearing persecution, Emil and Robert left America and partook in a medical expedition in Cameroon. There, Robert contracted a rare tropical virus and was near death. Trying to save his son via blood transfusion from his own body, Emil became delirious and irrational. Determined to save the life of his son, Emil witnessed a mongoose fighting off a killing a cobra, only to be fatally wounded itself. Believing local folklore about the recuperative properties of the mongoose, Emil used the animal in a transfusion, reviving his son. Emil soon died from a combination of the blood transfusions and shock. Robert meanwhile found that he was endowed with super-human speed. Although initially believed that the mongoose blood was the source of his super-human powers, later reports suggest that the mongoose blood was actually a catalyst that triggered latent mutant abilities within Robert.

Name: Wiccan (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Billy Maximoff was one of the twins that Wanda Maximoff had given birth to in the Westview Anomaly. It was discovered by Wanda that she created them using her own magic, and their lives were tethered to the hex. As S.W.O.R.D entered Westview to interrogate the Maximoff Family, he and his brother used their powers to handle the military. In the end, Wanda eventually had to give up her family, saying her goodbyes to them before she destroyed the hex.

Name: Wights
Summary: A Wight is a reanimated corpse, either human or animal, raised from death by the Night King or the White Walkers with the use of necromancy. Wights were often referred to collectively as the Army of the Dead. Anyone who falls against the White Walkers must be burned, or else the dead will rise again as their slaves. Fear of their own dead becoming wights leads the free folk to burn them.

Name: Wingull
Summary: Wingull is a seagull Pokémon with wings that are made for soaring on updrafts. It carries food in its beak and makes its nest on the cliffsides. Fishermen take note of when Wingull are nearby, as it is a sign that the surrounding waters are filled with fish.

Name: Winter Soldier (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Winter Soldier (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Bucky Barnes, once believed dead near the end of World War II only to have been found and brainwashed by the Soviets for the next 50 years, Captain America's former sidekick now continues to defend his country from the shadows against those who would threaten it as legendary spy and assassin, The Winter Soldier.

Name: Wisemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Wobbuffet
Summary: Wobbuffet is a Psychic-type Pokémon from the second generation. It is quite special compared to others like it due to lacking any direct attacks. Instead, it endures attacks and then counters. This means that it is never the first one to attack.

Name: Wolfsbane (Marvel Comics)
Summary: At the start of her life, Rahne Sinclair was raised under the abusive teachings of a fundamentalist preacher in her Scottish homeland. Although she would carry her religion with her dearly throughout her life, the development of her lycanthropic mutant powers and subsequent tutelage with the New Mutants showed Rahne a deeper world of purpose and passion, as Wolfsbane.

Name: Wolverine (Deadpool & Wolverine)
Summary: Logan: Scott used to beg me to wear it. So did Jean, Storm, Beast... All of them. They wanted me to be part of the team, but I wouldn't. Told them they all looked fuckin' ridiculous. I mean, I couldn't have 'em thinking I wanted to be there. And then one day while I was off on my own, the humans came. They went mutant hunting. Laura: I can guess the rest. Logan: No, no, let me say it, I... I need to say it. By the time I stumbled home, shit-faced from the bar, it was too late. They were dead.

Name: Wolverine (Laura Kinney)
Summary: X-23 is a fictional comic book superheroine appearing in books published by Marvel Comics, most commonly in association with the X-Men. She was originally created by writer Craig Kyle for the X-Men: Evolution animated series before debuting in the NYX comic series in 2004. Since then, she has appeared in two six-issue miniseries written by Craig Kyle and Christopher Yost, regular runs in New X-Men, X-Force, Avengers Academy, and her own self-titled comic series written by Marjorie Liu.

Name: Wolverine (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Howlett, also referred to as Logan and is best known as Wolverine, is a recurring member of the X-Men and arguably the group's most famous member. Known for his rough-and-tumble, brutish personality, he is nevertheless a good-hearted man who fights for man and mutant alike. His mutant ability allows him to protrude claws of bone out of his knuckles and incredible regenerative abilities that allow him to recover from even the most lethal wounds and slows his aging, remaining in his physical prime despite being born in the 1880s.

Name: Wong (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Strange: Is that everyone? Wong: You wanted more!?

Name: Wood Elf
Summary: One of the major sub races of elves, the Wood Elves who are also known as Sylvan Elves live deep in the forests. They are so attuned with nature that they are able to make use of any small cover to hide away, and they are naturally faster on their feet.

Name: Wormmon (Ken Ichijouji)
Summary: Ken Ichijouji and Wormmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Ken as the Digimon Kaiser was the first major enemy of the Chosen Children. Being cruel, cold and sadistic person who enjoyed nothing more than causing pain to others and seeing them suffer. This persona was fueled by a corrupting Dark Seed that was planted in the back of his neck from defeating of Millenniummon.

Name: Xandala
Summary: Xandala is a half-elf sorceress and descendant of the ancient dragons of Chult, now seeking to stake a political claim in the region through raw force. Specifically, Xandala seeks the Ring of Winter, an artifact possessed by Artus Cimber. In doing this she encounters a group of adventurers looking to free the region from Acererak and convinces them to assist her in finding Artus, claiming to be his daughter. She is accompanied by a pseudodragon named Summerwise, who tries to prevent the young sorceress from falling to evil.

Name: Yagnoloth
Summary: Yagnoloths are the minor lords of the yugoloth armies, controlling small swathes of the Lower Middle planes as command posts in the Blood War. They serve as basic negotiators for the yugoloth mercenary forces, and tend to bring in contracts for arcanaloths. They are most known for two distinctive traits- firstly, the physical trait of a single massively swelled arm, and secondly, the manipulative trait of always including a loophole in their contracts that voids the entire contract should the situation call for it.

Name: Yamato Ishida (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Yamato Ishida and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure 2020. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship and the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Yeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Yeti is a distant relative of both primates and bears that lives in the high mountain peaks. Unlike their cousins the Yeti possesses the ability to absorb the heat of their area and have a gaze that can induce terror into those that are unprepared for it, but the former ability comes with a weakness to any great source of it as they'd absorb it too which would raise their internal body tempature to dangerous levels.

Name: Yoda (Star Wars)
Summary: nan

Name: Yorick Mori
Summary: The last survivor of a long-forgotten religious order, Yorick is both blessed and cursed with power over the dead. Trapped on the Shadow Isles, his only companions are the rotting corpses and shrieking spirits that he gathers to him. Yorick's monstrous actions belie his noble purpose: to free his home from the curse of the Ruination.

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Zatanna (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: You want to know why I perform as a stage magician? Why my father did before me? Here's the real trick, Bruce. The secret behind it all. The more you let magic consume your life, the less connected to the real world you become. You become a ghost of yourself. You become less and less of a person. It just eats away at you, Bruce. Every day, the knowledge consumes you. Suddenly, you know that none of the laws of nature really matter. You can change all of it with a few backwards words. YTIVARG ON EROM. THGIN SEMOCEB YAD. NIAR SEMOCEB SREWOLF. And then you can put it all right back. KCAB OT LAMRON. Do you know how hard it is to talk to someone in the real world when you know that, Bruce? How hard it is to anchor yourself to the real? So maybe you force it. You keep a schedule, make yourself deal with the real people, day in, day out, so you don't forget their perspective matters as much as your own. So you stay something like a human.

Name: Zephiel (Fire Emblem)
Summary: Zephiel (ゼフィール Zefīru, Zefhyr in the Japanese versions) is the main antagonist of Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade and a minor non-playable character in its prequel, Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: AeroVeedramon
Summary: A small, blue-colored, Dragon Digimon child. Although it is small and powerless, it has the potential to evolve to every Dragon Digimon. For that reason, it is a Digimon that is considered exceedingly valuable by tamers and researchers of Dragon Digimon. It is cherished due to its personality of friendliness and overflowing curiosity, characteristic of Baby Digimon. Just like other Baby Digimon, it spits acidic bubbles to attack, but as usual, their power is nonexistent.

Name: Agent Venom
Summary: Eugene "Flash" Thompson is Peter Parker’s former classmate, childhood bully, and Spider-Man’s biggest fan. Joining the military after graduating from high school, he lost his legs while saving a fellow soldier in Iraq. He is subsequently enlisted into Project Rebirth 2.0, where he bonds with the Venom symbiote that had formerly been bonded to Eddie Brock and Mac Gargan (better known as the Scorpion). Forming a close relationship with the symbiote, he utilizes its powers for good and has been part of the Secret Avengers, the Thunderbolts, and the Guardians of the Galaxy on separate occasions.

Name: Agumon (Masaru Daimon)
Summary: Masaru Damon/Marcus Damon and Agumon are the main characters from Digimon Data Squad.

Name: Agumon (Taichi Yagami)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from Digimon Adventure, Digimon Adventure 02 and Digimon Adventure Tri. The original "Goggle-Boy" duo, Tai and Agumon serve as the de facto leaders of the DigiDestined, fighting side-by-side through thick and thin. Taichi is the older brother of Hikari Yagami.

Name: Ai Apaec (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ai Apaec the Decapitator was a god worshiped by the Moche people of Peru in South America. Prone to cruel torture and bloodletting, he was eventually captured by US government officials and into custody in the United States of America. He was eventually rescued by Norman Osborn and then later reinstated as a part of his Dark Avengers under the guise of Spider-Man

Name: Algomon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, up to 1-C

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: Alraumon
Summary: Alraumon is a Plant Digimon that accomplished an evolution just like Palmon. It seems that, at noon, it opens up its arms and the flower on its head to perform photosynthesis. The aroma emitted from the flower on its head is definitely inherited from Palmon, so as usual it is intensely foul.

Name: Ami Han (White Fox)
Summary: Ami Han was born in South Korea as a Kumiho, a mystical Korean yokai, she was raised by her mother who taught her how to hunt and turn into a Kumiho, advising her to hide her true form from others, until she was killed by Samjokgu, three-legged dogs who hunted down the Kumihos until their near-extinction, Ami is now know as the last Kumiho. While helping a friend she was found by an agent of NIS (National Intelligence Service) to join them. As an adult she became the leader of NIS and is now known as White Fox.

Name: Angel of Valor
Summary: The Angel of Valor are the weakest and most numerous of the angels that serve the gods, they are used as foot soldiers of their deities. while following the orders of higher ranking angels or even clerics of their gods.

Name: Angewomon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | Low 1-C

Name: Ant-Man (Eric O'Grady)
Summary: Eric O'Grady was a low level S.H.I.E.L.D. agent working in the reconnaissance department of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier. Him and his best friend Chris McCarthy were tasked with guarding Dr. Henry Pym's lab by a higher ranking agent, Mitch Carson. When Pym went to leave the lab, Eric and Chris panicked and Eric attacked Pym, knocking him unconscious. Inside the lab, they found the most recent version of Ant-Man's Suit, which Chris put on and promptly activated, shrinking down. Thinking him gone, Eric panicked again and ran off, only to run into each other as a Hydra siege infiltrated the Helicarrier. While trying to find a safe place to hide, Chris was killed, and Eric took the Ant-Man's Suit off his body. Surviving the Helicarrier crash, Eric kept the suit and operated as Ant-Man.

Name: Ant-Man (Scott Lang)
Summary: Scott Lang was born and raised in Coral Gables, Florida. He later became an electronic engineer and met and married Peggy Rae. Together they had a daughter Cassandra "Cassie" Lang. Although he was an electronics expert he could not support his family doing repair work, so he turned his talents to burglary. Apprehended, he served his prison sentence and was paroled for good behavior. During his time in prison, however, Peggy divorced him. Lang had furthered his studies of electronics while in prison and was soon hired by Stark International to work in its design department.

Name: Apollomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Archnemon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Armadimon (Iori Hida)
Summary: Iori Hida and his partner Armadillomon are two of the DigiDestined in Digimon Adventure 02. Iori was a one of passengers on the plane that was saved by Kabuterimon and Garudamon in the Digimon Adventure.

Name: Artus Cimber
Summary: Artus Cimber is the son of a thief and member of the Harpers who, upon exploring some old ruins, discovered the Ring of Winter, a relic of the Evil Goddess of Ice, Auril. Determined to never allow the ring to fall into the hands of evil, Artus has been on the run ever since, made immortal by the devious power of the ring. Artus is widely regarded as an immensely intelligent scholar and renowned adventurer aside from his status of guardian of the artifact.

Name: Atropal
Summary: Atropals are stillborn godlings who have spontaneously risen as undead. A foul aura surrounds the Abomination, snuffing out weaker life and draining the souls of those near it. When one rises the Gods cringe and seal them in tombs for all time. But sometimes the barriers are broken and one is freed to wreak havoc on the multiverse.

Name: Auntie Ethel
Summary: Why are you so cruel? Please. It's you lot who come to me. All you do is want - to be prettier, to be richer, to be loved. People are their own worst enemies, petal. I just let them see it.

Name: BanchoLilimon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, possibly higher

Name: Barbed Devil
Summary: Barbed Devils, also referred to as Hamatulas in their infernal tongue, serve as guardians of Baatorian vaults and elite warriors in devilish armies. The devils themselves are relatively low on the devil evolutionary scale, though this does not denote a lower form of power- indeed, their strength makes them the perfect servants of craftier devils.

Name: Basilisk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Basilisks are reptilian magical creatures bestowed with the capability to turn enemies to stone. Their abilities are renowned enough that a seasoned adventurer will recognize the threat of remaining in the area when they begin seeing remarkably life-like statues of frightened wildlife.

Name: Behir
Summary: Behirs are dragon-like creatures of electric origin that despise their brethren, to the point of driving them out of their territories if possible and, if not, leaving the area. They were created by Storm Dragons as weapons in a great war against the dragons, though nowadays are often kept as pets of powerful spellcasters and serve as signs of good omens for certain religions, notably in Chult.

Name: Big Wheel (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Weele: I don't care what you create, Tinkerer-- as long as I can crush him but good. I'm sick of his taunting laugh-- of his always chiding me, calling me the Big Wheel, always pushing me to the wall. I want him, and I want him fast. Tinkerer: Then you shall have him, Mr. Weele. Hmmm, Big Wheel he calls you. How interesting.

Name: Black Cat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Cat (Felicia Hardy) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer Marv Wolfman and artist Keith Pollard, she first appeared in The Amazing Spider-Man #194 (July 1979). Felicia Hardy is the daughter of a world-renowned cat burglar. After suffering a traumatic event as a college freshman, she trained herself in various fighting styles and acrobatics and, after deciding to follow in her father's footsteps, adopted her costumed identity as the Black Cat.

Name: Black Goliath (Marvel Comics)
Summary: William Barrett Foster was born in the Watts ghetto of Los Angeles, California and spent his childhood there. His higher than mean-average intelligence and the influence of several good people enabled him to leave that ghetto and enroll in the California Institute of Technology, where he acquired a Ph.D. degree in biochemistry.

Name: Black Pudding
Summary: Black Puddings are quasi-sentient globs of viscous black goop, most often found in poorly-lit dungeon halls where it might be dismissed as nothing more than a blot of shadow. In truth, it is a malevolent carnivore that strips and dissolves even the most durable materials, leaving behind only stone. It is a painful and not altogether quick way to perish.

Name: Black Widow (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Former KGB agent Natasha Romanova, known as Black Widow, is one of the greatest spies on Earth and is one of the best agents S.H.I.E.L.D. has ever had. She's a long-time member of the Avengers and was a founding member and the only leader of the short-lived Los Angeles-based superteam: The Champions.

Name: BlackWarGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, Likely 1-C

Name: Blade (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Blade, real name Eric Brooks, is a vampire hunter, as well as a half-vampire hybrid himself, known to the blood-drinking undead as a "Dhampir" or "Daywalker", as he possesses all the strengths of a vampire without any of their weaknesses. The reason for his unique condition is that as his mother was giving birth to him, the vampire Deacon Frost, posing as a doctor, bit her, turning her into a vampire before immediately killing her. The vampiric corruption reached Eric through the umbilical chord, and turned him into a unique being with a vengeance against the vampiric kind, who would all eventually come to fear him.

Name: Blizzard (Gregor Shapanka)
Summary: Dr. Gregor Shapanka, Ph.D., an employee of Stark Industries, was conducting private research into a means for achieving physical immortality, who got fired for attempting to steal from Anthony Stark's vault.

Name: Bloodfire Ooze
Summary: Created from a dark ritual, a Bloodfire Ooze is an ooze that's made from people's blood with a bit of a demon added in. They are mindless beasts that seek out blood to absorb and use their fire abilities in battle, some Bloodfire Oozes are even more horrid when made by an extraplaner for they add a pseudonatural creature template which makes the Bloodfire a Blight Bloodfire

Name: Bone Naga
Summary: Bone Nagas are a member of the immortal species known as nagas. They were created by the mighty Creator Race Sarrukh, though they are ultimately an incomplete perversion of true nagas. During the ritual made to cement the naga's immortality, yuan-ti necromantic rituals rendered the creature undead, twisting them into servants of the yuan-ti instead, and with merely a fraction of the power their siblings possessed.

Name: Boomerang (Marvel Comics)
Summary: After moving from Australia to America, Fred Myers developed a passion for baseball and had potential to be one of the world's greatest pitchers. His career was cut short when he was suspended for taking bribes. The Secret Empire saw potential in Fred, and gave him the gear necessary to utilize his talents. After the Secret Empire crumbled, Boomerang found work with crime lords like Hammerhead and the Kingpin, and has been a part of groups like the Sinister Syndicate, the Masters Of Evil, The Thunderbolts, and even led the New Sinister Six.

Name: Breachgnome
Summary: Specialized in fighting within cramped spaces, a well-positioned Breachgnome can hold off superior enemy forces for a long duration. They are trained to fight alone, although sometimes they work in small units that coordinate to block off several paths at once. They are seldom seen outside Gnome communities, though when are found outside they are often looking for Gnomes to help.

Name: Bryweludramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: BX-series droid commando
Summary: BX-series droid commandos, also known as commando droids, were a type of advanced battle droid used by the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. They were created as an improvement over the standard B1 battle droids and had great agility and far superior computer processing power. They were feared for their accuracy with blasters and fighting skill as well as the fact that they did not go down easily.
