Name: Carnage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Following a deeply troubling childhood which culminated in him burning down an orphanage, Cletus Kasady became a sociopathic serial killer and was eventually convicted for eleven consecutive life sentences. Incarcerated at Ryker's Island Prison, Cletus eventually became cellmates with Eddie Brock, who had been separated from the Venom symbiote. When the alien returned to rescued Eddie, it left behind its asexually-produced offspring. The newborn symbiote bonded to Cletus and amalgmated with his blood, transforming him into the monstrous Carnage.

Name: Cerberumon
Summary: Cerberumon is a Demon Beast Digimon called the "Watchdog of Hell". The claws on its feet are hard enough to easily tear through Chrome Digizoid alloys, if they have a low purity. Also, its body is protected by a hard living shell, which has the ability to instantly repair any damage it incurs. The armor on its shoulders each possess sentience, and are able to instantly sense an attack coming from any direction, then report it to Cerberumon's central body.

Name: Cherrymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Chocomon (Wallace)
Summary: Chocomon is an antagonist in Digimon Adventure 02: Digimon Hurricane Landing!! Transcendent Evolution!! The Golden Digimentals. He is one of Wallace's partner Digimon, being the twin brother of Terriermon. He was driven insane by a virus, forcing the Chosen Children to fight him to prevent him from doing irreparable damage.

Name: Clash (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clash, the Superstar of Sound, is the alter-ego of Clayton Cole, a socially-inept, genius, multi-talented teenager. After seeing Masked Marvel, our beloved Peter Parker, crashing into Crusher Hogan’s match, he became a fan of what later became Spider-Man, who was, at the time, merely performing shows and stunts for money.

Name: Cleveland-class Light Cruiser
Summary: The Cleveland-class light cruisers were built for the U.S. Navy during World War II, and were the most numerous class of light cruisers ever built. The ships were designed with the goal of increased cruising range, anti-aircraft armament, torpedo protection, etc., compared with earlier U.S. cruisers. Fifty-two ships of this class were originally planned, but nine of them were completed as the light aircraft carriers of the Independence class, and two of them were completed to a somewhat different design, called the Fargo class. The Fargo-class cruisers were a modified version of the previous Cleveland-class cruiser design; the main difference was a more compact pyramidal superstructure with single trunked funnel, intended to improve the arcs of fire of the anti-aircraft guns. In all, 13 Fargo-class ships were planned but only Fargo and Huntington were ever completed, the rest being cancelled at varying states of completion with the de-escalation of World War II. Of the 27 Cleveland-class cruisers that were commissioned, one (Galveston) was completed as a guided missile cruiser and five were later modified as Galveston and Providence-class guided missile cruisers. Following the naming convention at the time, all the ships completed as cruisers were named for US cities and towns.

Name: Cloud Giant
Summary: Second tallest of the true Giants, the Cloud Giants are an aloof race, viewing all others barring Storm Giants as beneath them- fitting, given their proclivity to reside in castles which float on clouds. Alongside their impressive physical strength they have innate magical abilities, being able to levitate objects among other things.

Name: Cockroach Hamilton (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dontrell Hamilton is a hitman residing in New York City, that uses a powerful custom shotgun he named "Josh", and is frequent foe to Luke Cage, using the alias of Cockroach

Name: Coelamon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B

Name: Crossbones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Captain America: I have this theory that no one is totally beyond redemption. That's why I'm so big on preserving life-- Even the lives of those who try to kill me. As long as a person's alive, there's hope he may redeem himself. So what I'm saying is... even though you've acted like lowlife scum every time we've met, there must be something good about you... Love for your mother, a childhood pet, a woman maybe? I'd really like to know what it is. Crossbones: You wanna know where I'm soft, huh, Cappy? Ha! Okay, why not? I'll tell you. I love... TO HATE! HAHAHAHAHAHA!

Name: Crush (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Xiomara Rojas is the daughter of Lobo and a former member of the Teen Titans. Abandoned at birth, Crush was raised by loving, but weak-willed drug addict parents, who were both murdered when she was a young girl. Lost and angry at the world, she took up the name Crush and started fighting in underground fighting promotions before she was recruited by Damian Wayne. Among her notable missions, Crush tracked down her parents' killer, a drug-dealer simply known as "Ezekiel", met and defeated her birth father, Lobo, and nearly started a romantic relationship with one of her team-mates, Djinn.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: Dao
Summary: Dao are the Genies of Earth. They are known by their greed and malicious nature towards intruders- their long, earthen galleries are pocked with the shine of gemstones revealed by their mining operations. Little does a Dao care for the hardship of others, often using its great wealth to support immense decadence- it is known they grind diamonds into dust and use it as a spice on their foods. The only race they are on friendly terms with are the Efreeti.

Name: Daredevil (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in the historically gritty or crime-ridden, working-class Irish-American neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen in New York City, Matthew "Matt" Michael Murdock is blinded by a radioactive substance that falls from a truck after he pushes a man to safety from the oncoming vehicle. While he no longer can see, the radioactive exposure heightens his remaining senses beyond normal human ability and gives him a "radar sense". His father, a boxer named Jack Murdock, supports him as he grows up, though Jack is later killed by gangsters after refusing to throw a fight. After donning a yellow and dark red costume (later all dark red), Matt seeks out revenge against his father's killers as the superhero Daredevil, fighting against his many enemies, including Bullseye and Kingpin.

Name: Daren Timbide
Summary: Daren Timbide is a general in the Mintar armies and follower of Bane, the god of fear, malice, and bloodshed. Daren follows this ordeal in his conquests, slaughtering any enemy that presents themselves. However, Daren keeps his army in perpetual training rather than attacking- certain in the idea that he could slay any other given army on the continent, he merely bides his time in patient waiting for Bane's orders.

Name: Darkdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Davy Crockett
Summary: The M-29 Davy Crockett was a nuclear gun developed by the United States during the Cold War.

Name: Deacon Frost (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Deacon Frost was once a scientist looking for the key to immortality, which he eventually found in the corpse of a recently killed vampire. Managing to extract his essence, Frost sought to inject in a woman's body to test its effects, but a fight broke out with her fiancee, who injected the substance in Frost's body, transforming him into what would become one of the most powerful vampires to blight the Earth.

Name: Deadpool (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Deadpool (Wade Winston Wilson) is a fictional character, a mercenary and anti-hero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer and artist Rob Liefeld and scripted by Fabian Nicieza, Deadpool first appeared in New Mutants #98 (Feb. 1991).

Name: Demogorgon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Aspect '''| '''Out of the Abyss '''| '''In the Abyss''' | '''Lesser God'''
Summary: Should feckless mortal seek to test His ire, Take heed of better foes than you now shamed- FRAZ-URB'LUU, who would take His name in vain: His wrath shall haunt your lands and wipe them clean. AZUVIDEXUS, who would dwell within His house: He'll vex the gods themselves to cast you out. ZUREGUREX, who would seek to claim His prize: Your storm-strewn dead shall not avail your flight. SHAMI-AMOURAE, who seeks His lust to build a throne: To the darkest wash of primal night be sent. ORCUS, who brings His armies forth to bear: Your troops shall end upon red fang and claw. GRAZ'ZT, who deigns to claim His vaunted crown: Your triple realm shall rot from deep within. OBOX-OB, who once ruled where He rules now: Your crown now rests upon the proper brow. For you are but His pawns and He your prince. And in the end but thralls to His demesne.

Name: Devimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C, Low 1-C with Digital World's Darkness | Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Devourer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Devourers are massive undead that stalk the ethereal and astral planes, looking for travelers. The Devourer absorbs the souls of those it stalks, used to sustain their own unnatural life. They are also known for their grotesque features- they form a miniature of their latest victim's soul, trapped within their otherwise empty chest cavity.

Name: Diablomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C, 8-B via Crazy Giggle, Up to 3-C, Possibly higher with Direct Absorption | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | Low 1-C, Up to 1-C | Low 1-C, 1-C via Direct Absorption | At least Low 1-C, Up to 1-C

Name: Diaboromon (Digimon Adventure)
Summary: Diaboromon is the main antogonist of Our war game and Diaboromon Strikes back. It hatched as a kuramon from a Digi-Egg that had formed on the Internet from a collection of viruses. It caused constant chaos in the Real World by eating data, and Digivolved rapidly with each sufficient amount of food. It was eventually defeated by Omegamon.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Dianamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Djinni (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Djinni are elemental outsiders originating from the Plane of Air. Clothed in riches and in possession of good looks, Djinni are creatures of ease and relaxation, ruling small single-cloud kingdoms in the Plane of Air. Such freedoms afford them their mischief they constantly try to rile up, though they are not malevolent towards mortals. Of all of genie kind, Djinni are the most accepting of servitude, as they believe it is their fate - and, indeed, belief breeds tangible effect in a world of such magic.

Name: Doctor Octopus
Summary: Born in Schenectady, New York, Otto Octavius had a turbulent upbringing due to his abusive father Torbert berating him for being constantly bullied at school. Due to his mother's insistence that he could solve anything with his mind rather than with brute force, Otto focused more on his education, becoming a brilliant and respected nuclear physicist who devoted his entire life to developing a fusion-based energy source. His work eventually led him to Oscorp. By the time Octavius finally finished his fusion reactor for Oscorp, having lost his mother and the woman he loved during that time, he unveiled a harness of highly advanced mechanical arms controlled via a brain–computer interface to assist him with his research into atomic physics.

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Dorugoramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Dracula (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Vlad Dracula, formerly Vladimir Tepesch, is a villain from Marvel Comics originating in Tomb Of Dracula, based on the iconic character of the same name, and serves as the lord of the vampires.

Name: Durandamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: Eduardo Lobo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Eduardo Lobo was an orphaned youth on the streets of Mexico, making ends meet alongside his brother Carlos, until one faithful night the love of his life was shot right before his eyes. This awakened a transformation within the young lad, and he discovered he was a mutant capable of transforming into a werewolf, similar to his brother. The two soon after took control of the local cartel in the late 1980s, with their empire reaching South Texas at its height.

Name: Efreeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Efreeti are immensely powerful fire-elemental genies. Often such genies take to the mortal planes to seek rulership over the desert peoples. Known for their haughtiness and cruelty, though often disguise this as their attempts at order, only admitting to an enlightened sense of self interest. Most of their followers are slaves they captured themselves, be it from the Elemental Plane of Fire or from the Prime. The Efreeti rule the famed City of Brass, a massive citadel for their kind and their nigh-infinite legions.

Name: Eidolon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Eidolon is a type of creature formed from souls, sent to protect a holy site. Once created, an eidolon stalks the holy vaults of the gods, protecting them from any would-be invaders. Oftentimes, an Eidolon will be left with a large, sacred statue to use as a tool for its possession- using the body allows it to wreak havoc upon enemies who might upset the deities and priests that created the mighty creature.

Name: Elecmon
Summary: Elecmon is a Mammal Digimon that retained Tsunomon's mammal-like elements and evolved. It's very curious and lively, and inherited its prank-loving personality from Tunomon. Also, Elecmon possesses nine tails, and during battle, it fans out its tail like the plumage of a peacock to intimidate its opponent.

Name: Electro (Francine Frye)
Summary: Francine Frye was a supervillain groupie living in New York, where she had relationships with many supervillains within the city, including one Max Dillon, Electro. One day when spending time with him, Electro's powers acted up, resulting in him accidentally killing her.

Name: Electro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: It's pitch black out there now. They're the faceless ones. They're the invisible nobodies. And me? I hurt. I'm scared. So afraid I'm gonna die. But it'll be worth it, won't it? When they look up and see me. The biggest. The brightest. The highest, the greatest. Oh it will be all worth it... when I... LIGHT THE NIGHT! Look at me, all of you! Look at Max Dillon! Look at ELECTRO!

Name: Elsa Bloodstone (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elsa Bloodstone is the daughter of the immortal monster hunter, Ulysses Bloodstone, who follows her father's footsteps to be a monster hunter herself. Armed with an arsenal of rifles, shotguns, pistols and other weapons, alongside being imbued by the power of the Bloodgem thanks to her choker, she hunts the various beasts and creatures of the Marvel Universe with expertise.

Name: Equinox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to two brilliant scientists, Terry Sorenson was granted the power of thermokinesis upon failing to save his father during a lab explosion.

Name: Fancy Dan (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daniel Brito was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. Bullied at a young age due to his height, he took martial arts classes to better defend himself and earn respect, but the mocking only continued as he was branded Fancy Dan by his tormentors. He soon joined forces with Montana and Ox to form the mercenary collective the Enforcers, and have been a thorn in Spider-Man's side ever since.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Frost Worm
Summary: Frost Worms are enormous worms that spend their lives tunneling through snow, ice, and even solid stone and earth to search for prey in the frozen wastelands of Faerun and other realms it resides in. It is a hot topic of debate as to whether or not this creature is related to the Purple Worm or the Remorhaz- or even both. A battle between a Frost Worm and a Remorhaz may well lay waste to an entire landscape during the conflict.

Name: Gabumon (Yamato Ishida)
Summary: Yamato Ishida (Matt in the dub) and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure trilogy. Yamato is the secondary main character of 01 and Tri, next to Taichi Yagami. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship, this can be seen in his character rather early on in the series, as he's usually looking out for his friends best interest. Yamato is the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Galena Tordrick
Summary: Galena Tordrick is a guardian of devilish cults and leader of a pair of Bone Devil police forces sent to attack those who perform misdeeds to her masters. Originally, she became a Hellfire Warlock to atone for her deeds in life- to use evil in the name of good- however, tasting the power of evil, she has turned fully to the side of Baator and now serves as an oppressor of good.

Name: Gaomon (Thoma H. Norstein)
Summary: Thoma H. Norstein is a coolheaded child genius who has already graduated from university. His intelligence is highly valued, even within DATS. He executes his missions based on data and theories, so his personality frequently clashes with Masaru's, who relies more on emotions.

Name: Ghindul
Summary: Ghindul is one of two leaders of the Kir-lanan species, found at the Wailing Cliffs. His species came into existence during the Time of Troubles, comprised of the divine and negative energy released from the deaths of gods. Ghindul and his followers serve the shadow dragon Glouroth, and are in constant competition with another Kir-lanan sect led by Phaikkul.

Name: Ghost (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ghost is an infamous and highly skilled corporate saboteur; he despises the huge, multinational companies that treat regular workers and people as dispensable pawns in their endeavours for greater turnover and profit margins; Ghost believes not only that all these organisations need to be destroyed, but that he is the one who can do it. This has resulted in him being extremely paranoid, seeing conspiracies almost everywhere and rarely, if ever, trusting anybody other than himself

Name: Ghost-Spider (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gwen Stacy was bitten by the radioactive spider rather than Peter Parker giving her the abilities of a spider. She goes by the name Spider-Woman and much like Spider-Man of Earth 616 used her newly found powers to for more personal gain rather than helping people by becoming a professional drummer. Peter Parker remained a weak individual that Gwen needed to save from bullying. This made him develop an inferiority complex causing him to create a serum to make himself more like Gwen after she has revealed to him her powers. This causes him to become Earth 65's version of the Lizard and Gwen is forced to fight him. Unfortunately due to the serum during the battle Peter dies and she vows to use her powers for good. Unfortunately, Gwen is blamed for Peter's death and a campaign against her (spearheaded by J. Jonah Jameson) is started.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Gibbon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Martin Blank, also known as Gibbon was a man who was born with simian traits akin to his villain namesake. This made him naturally agile and strong, however, it also make his appearance loathsome for others to behold. This lead to him mainly living as an outcast, being mocked by even the likes of Spider-Man. He was tragically killed by a Hunterbot in the Great Hunt.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Gravity (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Greg Willis was a boy from Wisconsin, who was granted the power of gravitikinesis after being sucked into a strange mini black hole. Deciding to use his powers for good, he moved to New York City and adopted the superhero persona Gravity.

Name: Gray Render
Summary: Gray Renders are huge, lumbering monstrosities known for their well-documented strength on the level of giants, as well as their tendency to bond psychically to creatures. For whatever reason, be it from their artificial creation stories or their latent genetics, gray renders have a psychological need to bond to another living creature. Due to their chaotic nature, they make very risky pets, as they are known to claw apart trees on a whim and even destroy houses.

Name: Grizzmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-B | 3-C

Name: Guardian Naga
Summary: Guardian Nagas are benevolent nagas of particular strength, originating from the time of the Sarrukh, an ancient Creator Race who ruled multiple empires from over 37,000 years ago across Faerun. They are serpent creatures with humanoid heads, most often found protecting areas of potent lore or magical significance, though can be found ruling over tribes of lesser beings such as Lizardfolk or Kobolds. Unlike their fellow nagas, guardian nagas are not of an inherently evil bent, and not prone to assaulting any intruder in their lairs- they attack only if forced, and prefer to give warnings before unleashing their arcane might.

Name: Guilmon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 3-C, Up To 1-C with Digital Hazard | 1-C

Name: Gururumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C

Name: Hagurumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | 6-B | At least High 4-C, possibly 4-A | 3-C

Name: Hallows' Eve (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elizabeth Tyne went through a lot of hardship, an abusive father, kidnapped and prison, but she found love with Benjamin Reilly a clone of Spider-Man. She went through a lot of effort to help him become who he should be, including going to the dimension called Limbo. Tired of feeling useless she accepted a power that was given by Madelyne Pryor, now going by the name Hallows' Eve she tries to do everything she can to keep the relationship with Ben alive.

Name: Hammerhead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When left for dead in an alleyway after a brawl, a surgeon found Joseph and operated to fix him up, replacing his broken skull with a steel plate.

Name: Hannibal King (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Hannibal King used to be a relatively normal private investigator, until the day one job he was given brought him too close to a man far more dangerous than he could ever imagine: Deacon Frost, the same vampire who killed Blade's mother at the moment of his birth, bit Hannibal King, turning him into yet another member of the blood-drinking horde.

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Hawkmon (Miyako Inoue)
Summary: Miyako Inoue and Hawkmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Miyako one of the many viewers watching the battle against Keramon in Our War Game.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: HerculesKabuterimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Hexeblaumon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C

Name: Hezrou
Summary: Hezrou act as officers of demonic armies, enforcers of law among the rank and file soldiers. While not as clever as their more powerful brethren, such as the Balor, Hezrou are cunning combatants and direct their soldiers with extreme aggression. Far from cowardly, a Hezrou hungers for combat, and rushes to the front lines to cut swathes through their enemies.

Name: HiAndromon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Hill Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Mouth of Grolantor''' | '''Barrowghast''' | '''Maw of Yeenoghu''' | '''Wereboar''' | '''Avalancher''' | '''Scion of Grolantor'''
Summary: Hill Giants are the lowest ranked of the True Giants, and fittingly are both the dumbest and shortest of them, but they're capable of surprisingly cunning actions in combat and they still possess great physical abilities.

Name: Hina Kurihara (Digimon Linkz)
Summary: Hina Kurihara is Linkz's navigator in Digimon Linkz. She is a tutorial program designed to help players navigate the Digital World. While Vorvomon and Jazamon are the partner of the protagonist of Digimon Linkz, in the Digimon Card Game Hina acts as their Tamer.

Name: Hobgoblin (Roderick Kingsley)
Summary: After Roderick Kingsley redesigned Norman Osborn's Goblin Formula and used it on himself, he took his old equipment and became the very first Hobgoblin, becoming a prominent Spider-Man villain.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Human Robot (Post-Golden Age)
Summary: They don't know what you're capable of. Yes, you'll be a powerful killing machine, but that will be your choice. You can have free will. Know emotions. Feel anger... loyalty... respect. This crucial encoding can only be made with the displacement of my own life force. I am sorry to put you in this position, M-11, but there is no time to fix it otherwise. Some of my essence will be imparted into you. You'll be your own being. Let my final act give you life... my Human Robot

Name: Hunter's Moon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in Luxor, Egypt, he was an excellent student throughout his life, eventually becoming a doctor. He grew to become a very rational and serious person who didn't believe in any higher entities, despite still attending prayer and studying the Qur'an and Hadith. As he was travelling at night, Badr was attacked and killed by a gang of vampires. Left to die with no one but Khonshu as witness, he offered to return Badr back to life as his fist, Badr accepted and became Hunter's Moon, a Fist of Khonshu.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city. Originally these creatures were made by Primus, and even the most wily and secretive of traders will enter into contracts with them- nothing is more straightforward and true than the ideals that forge the Inevitable's will. Inevitables care not for intent or purpose- only for the words written in their contracts. Lethal force is used to ensure such words are stood by.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 4
Summary: Model 4, as known as Classic Armor, is the fourth Iron Man suit engineered by Anthony Stark.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 6
Summary: Made for underwater exploration Model 6 is a modified version of Model 4 which has been upgraded to handle pressure far better so it can go on extended dives into deep waters.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 7
Summary: One of Tony's speciality armors, Model 7 is an armor that sacrifices physical capabilities in exchange for being stealthier, and it was used on several occasions to gather intel by Stark.

Name: Iron Monger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Obadiah Stane was the business partner of Tony Stark and a good friend of his father, Howard Stark. After Howard's death, Stane became interim CEO of Stark Industries until Tony took over officially shortly after. Stane's jealousy of the younger Stark led him to join forces with the Ten Rings to organize a failed attempt to assassinate him so Stane could become CEO once again. When this failed, Stane created the Iron Monger Armor and attempted to kill Stark himself, leading to his own death.

Name: Ironheart
Summary: Riri Williams spent her childhood living in Chicago as a brilliant, yet reclusive child prodigy until her step-father and best friend were killed in a drive-by shooting at a picnic. Now having reason to put her intelligence to use, she secretly combined technology from an outdated Iron Man armor with spare materials from M.I.T. to craft her own power suit, but the rudimentary prototype was destroyed during her first outing as a vigilante.

Name: J. Jonah Jameson
Summary: J. Jonah Jameson is the bossy and irascible editor-in-chief of the Daily Bugle. His dislike of superhumans, most particularly the Spider-Man (which stems from a combination of envy, distrust, and his son's accomplishments being overshadowed) leads him to tirelessly defame and vilify him at every opportunity with his newspaper, to the point where he has sometimes worked with supervillains to try and take him down.

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jessica Jones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Leaving her past as a crimefighting vigilante behind, Jessica Jones is a superpowered woman who works as a private investigator for her own agency, Alias Investigations, and apart from her grim job and dark past, is happily married to Luke Cage and a mother to their daughter, Danielle, however whenever trouble calls she isn't afraid to throw down to save the day.

Name: Joe Kido (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Joe Kido and Gomamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Joe is one of the 8 chosen children of the Digimon Adventure 2020 continuity and is the crest bearer of of Sincerity. Despite his pessimistic attitude and appearing as a coward, Joe is actually quite kind and very brave.

Name: JumboGamemon
Summary: A gigantic Cyborg Digimon that added beam cannons to its entire body until the strength of its Metal Body's shell was compromised.

Name: Justimon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Kaine Parker
Summary: Kaine was the Jackal's first attempt at cloning Peter Parker, but he was left deformed by a flaw in the cloning process and quickly became unstable.

Name: Kamen Rider Saber
Key: '''Beginning of Story (1-22)''' | '''Middle of Story (23-35)''' | '''Late Story (36-40)''' | '''End of Story (41-47)'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:KRSaber_Brave_Dragon_Sound.mp3

Name: Karate Kid (Earth-Prime)
Summary: Val Armorr, the Karate Kid, is a founding member of the Legion of Super-Heroes, a group of teenagers inspired by the actions of superheroes from centuries ago, to rise up and stand against a society of quiet inaction and strict protocol.

Name: Knightmon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | Low 1-C

Name: Koushiro Izumi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Koushiro Izumi and Tentomon are two of the main protagonists from Digimon Adventure 2020. Koushiro is the brains of the Chosen Children, constantly analyzing the world around him. However, his social skills are lacking due to his preference for computers over people.

Name: Kraven the Hunter
Summary: Sergei Kravinoff was born the scion of disgraced russian nobility, forcefully driven out of their homeland following the revolution and sent looking for refuge in the US. After years of abuse at his father's hands and the trauma of witnessing his mother's slow descent into madness and subsequent death, Sergei grew utterly dissatisfied with modern society and left looking for the peace that only a primeval world could give him. For decades he roamed the worlds' wildest lands, hunting any beast imaginable and earning fame as the matchless Kraven the Hunter. A fateful meeting with Aja Orisha allowed Sergei to be initiated to the mystical arts and acquire supernatural skills, although at great expenses due to his troubled mind.

Name: Kraven the Hunter (Last Son)
Summary: nan

Name: Lascivious (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Davida DeVito was professional wrestler/mercenary under the alias Titania, being the member of all-female team known as the Grapplers. After a life of crime, she was killed by the Scourge of the Underworld.

Name: Lash (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Inhumans are a people born with latent powers that can only be unlocked through the process of Terrigenesis, a metamorphosis most commonly caused by coming into contact with Terrigen Mist. In his Inhuman city, Lash was one of the few in his generation selected to be worthy of undergoing this change. Thus, he gained the ability to absorb energy and subsequently emit it from his hands. However, after the detonation of the Terrigen Bomb, Terrigen Mist was unleashed upon the world everywhere, with new Inhumans being born every day. Lash, believing that not everybody should receive this gift, set out to correct the mistake, putting him in conflict with the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Leonal
Summary: Leonals are lion-like celestials hailing from the plains of Elysium, and belong to the Guardinals, a type of angelic cross of abstract goodness and the animals of nature. As such, Leonal are incredible defenders of the natural world, as well as icons of the armies of Mystra, defending the proper usage of magic throughout the Planes.

Name: Lightmaster
Summary: Edward Lansky, known otherwise by the alias Lightmaster is a former Chancellor at New York University. After becoming disillusioned with those that run the university, he devised a nefarious plan to take control of the university, centered around kidnapping and murder.

Name: Lilina
Summary: Lilina is the daughter of Hector and the princess of Ostia, the largest nation in the Lycian Alliance. After Bern's generals manage to slay her father, she is entrusted to her best friend and fellow noble Roy for her protection, but she nevertheless heads to the battlefield herself to help end the war.

Name: Living Brain (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Living Brain is a robot with a hard drive stored in its body to allow it to store unlimited amount of data and has the potential to contain more knowledge than any other brain on earth, human or mechanical. Created by Dr. Petty, the machine was exploited during an exhibition which caused him to malfunction, and began wrecking havok until being stopped by Spider-Man.

Name: Living Laser
Summary: Arthur Parks, better known as The Living Laser is a Marvel character who first appeared at Avengers (1968) issue #34.

Name: Lizardfolk
Summary: Lizardfolk are reptilian humanoids native to the world of Toril that tend to dwell in semi-aquatic environments (such as swamplands and coastlines). An exceedingly practical folk, they do not desire riches or knowledge that don't have use in normal day-to-day survival activities. Their people are hardy, and can adapt to most environments- so despite being dominated culturally by the likes of humans, dwarves, and elves, they rarely hold complaint for the lands leftover for their dominions.

Name: LoaderLiomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B, occasionally High 8-C with Shippo Binta | High 8-C, occasionally 6-C with Critical Bite | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Lucia von Bardas (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lucia von Bardas was a puppet Prime Minister of Latveria installed by the US during Doctor Doom's absense. Von Bardas however, secretly began using her position to fund supervillains in America. Angered by this, Nick Fury launched a secret assassination plot against her, signalling S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Daisy Johnson used her seismic powers to take down Castle Doom, apparently killing the Latverian leader. Von Bardas however resurfaced, and led a campaign to assassinate all the heroes involved in her avoided demise. Despite failing, she has remained a dastardly foe ever since.

Name: Luke Cage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Luke Cage, also known as Power Man (real name Carl Lucas), is a superhero from Marvel Comics. He first appeared in Luke Cage, Hero for Hire #1 (June 1972).

Name: Magnum Force (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Moses Magnum was fascinated with weapons as a youth. When Italy invaded Ethiopia, he joined the invaders against his own people. He eventually became the world's foremost independent weapons manufacturer. When Magnum's Deterrence Research Corporation (DRC) was hired to develop a toxic biochemical gas, he tested it on kidnapped innocents. The Punisher and Spider-Man shut down this operation, though Magnum narrowly escaped death.

Name: Man Mountain Marko (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Michael Marko was a street thug who had unknowingly decided to mug Peter Parker, believing him to be a timid teenager. Peter was distracted by his Aunt May's illness, just knocking Marko away like he was nothing. This humiliation had determined Marko for his path to strength, beginning with bodybuilding, but then body enhancements by genetic engineering, all the while he spiraled into the crime world, under the name Man Mountain Marko.

Name: Man-Ape (Marvel Comics)
Summary: M'Baku was born and raised in the Jabari Village within the nation of Wakanda, Africa. He was one of the greatest warriors of the African nation Wakanda, second only to T'Challa, the Black Panther himself. While the Panther, King of Wakanda, was on leave from his royal duties to serve the Avengers in America, the ambitious M'Baku plotted to usurp the throne. The Wakandan culture evolved from a hunter-warrior society and was traditionally ruled by its greatest warrior. The Black Panther outlawed the rival White Gorilla cult from Wakanda while the Panther cult was dominant. M'Baku flouted T'Challa's edicts and revived the White Gorilla cult, personally stalking and killing one of the rare white gorillas living in the jungles near Wakanda. Bathing in the gorilla's blood and eating the gorilla's flesh mystically conferred its great strength upon M'Baku, as he became Man-Ape, leader of the Jabari and a frequent foe to Wakandan peace.

Name: Man-Thing (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ted Sallis was a scientist working for the United States Army on a super soldier serum known as SO-2, in the Florida Everglades.

Name: Mandarin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Mandarin was born the child of Mongolian and British aristocrats, both of whom died shortly after his birth. He was raised by his aunt, who was bitter about not being the inheritor of the family fortune and decided to twist his mind, raising him to be vain and bloodthirsty.

Name: Marid
Summary: Marids are aquatic genies hailing from the Elemental Plane of Water. While not evil, they are known to bend wishes to their liking. They are extremely rare on the Prime, more often being seen in the Elemental Plane of Water, inhabiting a vast coral palace in the mightiest reefs of the plane. All Marids declare themselves royalty and lords, though few have the power to enforce such expansive titles. Their ego is their greatest weakness, often lending them to weave legendary tales of their awesome might.

Name: Meramon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Mettle (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ken Mack was a member of the founding class of Avengers Academy, Hank Pym's hero school. Originally just your normal Hawaiian surfer, a hit to the face tore off part of his skin, revealing a skull of living iridium. Looking for someone who could return him to normal, he found Norman Osborn, who instead accelerated the transformation. After Osborn was revealed as a villain and arrested, Mettle was taken in by the Avengers alongside several others Osborn had experimented on and was trained to be a hero as the iridium juggernaut Mettle.

Name: Mimi Tachikawa (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Mimi Tachikawa and her partner Palmon are members of the DigiDestined and thus major characters in Digimon Adventure 2020. Mimi is the Crest Bearer of Purity.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Mindless Ones (Marvel)
Summary: The Mindless Ones were created by Plokta as a way of slowing the expanding empires of rivals, they were virtually unstoppable engines of destruction; when a rival was deemed to be becoming too powerful, Plokta would let the Mindless Ones loose in the rival's realm, tying up the rival's resources trying to contain them.

Name: MirageGaogamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Mister Negative (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Martin Li, a gangster from China, found himself fused with an extra-dimensional demon from the Darkforce Dimension. The two entities, now sharing one body, call themselves Mister Negative.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Comics)
Summary: While on a mission in Sudan, mercenary Marc Spector was left for dead in the desert by Raul Bushman, a ruthless African general, but was afterwards resurrected by the ancient Egyptian moon god known as Khonshu in exchange for being his avatar on Earth. Marc would later return to New York City and become the vigilante known as Moon Knight. Marc Spector possesses multiple personalities, such as the millionaire entrepreneur Steven Grant and cab driver Jake Lockley, and suffers from dissociative identity disorder, which causes great mental stress and instability that has made him an unstable and volatile person.

Name: Morbius the Living Vampire (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Michael Morbius was a brilliant scientist born in Greece who became a Nobel Prize winning biochemist. He suffered from a debilitating blood disease and developed an experimental treatment involving vampire bats and electroshocks. Its side effects turned him into a pseudo-vampire who needed to consume blood in order to survive and gained typical vampire characteristics such as an aversion to sunlight, and the powers of flight, enhanced strength, speed, and healing (a healing factor). His overall appearance changed as well: he gained fangs, his nose flattened to appear more bat-like, and his skin became extremely pale. Additionally, the victims of his bite would turn into living vampires themselves. He became a recurring foe as well as unwilling ally of Spider-Man, and went on to be a crime fighter himself, as Morbius, The Living Vampire.

Name: Morlun (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Morlun is a vampiric being, an inhabitant of Earth-001, and is a recurring foe of Spider-Man.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)
Summary: Kamala Khan was a normal teenager until she was imbued with the mist from the Terrigen Bomb. The mist activated her latent inhuman DNA, resulting in her gaining polymorphic abilities. As she wished to became a hero like her idol Carol Danvers, she took her name and became the hero Ms. Marvel. She started to tread her own path as a hero, and gained recognition by many other heroes, becoming an Avenger, and even making her own super hero team, the "Champions". After being killed while helping Spider-Man, and resurrected in Krakoa, she finally found out her mutant heritage.

Name: Mystra (Midnight)
Key: '''Beginning of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''End of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''Avatar''' | '''Greater God'''
Summary: Before she was the God of magic, Mystra was known as the wizard Midnight. Born Ariel Manx, she was the second child of the merchant Theus. A hedonist, Ariel would spend her time with the local bards, sorcerers, fighters, and thieves where she would eventually earn her nickname Midnight due to her late night activities. Eventually she would develop a fascination with magic and left her home in the pursuit of a higher calling.

Name: Nico Minoru
Summary: Nico Minoru is the sole daughter of Robert and Tina Minoru, who hail from a powerful mystic bloodline. As a 16 year old attending an annual "charity event" under the organization known as Pride, Nico and her friends discovered their parents were actually super-villains, and the yearly event was a pretense for Pride to sacrifice children to the deities of Gibborim. After witnessing the sacrifice, they chose to run away from home while Nico adopted the alias: Sister Grimm. Nico would come to learn of the family treasure known as the Staff of One as their parents pursued them. Following the chaotic betrayal of her then boyfriend Alex Wilder, the parents were forced to die saving their kids, rendering Nico and her friends lonesome allies, who branded themselves as Runaways. She would serve as the leader of the Runaways, a member of the heroine team A-Force, and even an instructor at the Strange Academy.

Name: Nightmare (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Nightmares are horse-like creatures originating from the Lower Planes, such as the Abyss, the Nine Hells, or Gehenna. They are the standard choice of mount for high-ranking fiends and undead alike, most often searching devil and demon lords, vampires, liches, and other evil-aligned creatures such as the shadar-kai. They are truly wicked beings and are best known for their flaming bodies and vicious tempers.

Name: Norman Osborn
Summary: Norman Osborn is the corrupt founder and head of Oscorp, a multi-billion dollar multinational corporation. After he took the experimental "Goblin Formula" to enhance his intelligence, his already unstable mind fractured further, leading to him becoming the original Green Goblin. In this role, he has been Spider-Man's greatest and most persistent archenemy, responsible for the death of Gwen Stacy. While his primary opponent and obsession is Spider-Man, his goals have branched out further in the past, and, at one time, he was the director of H.A.M.M.E.R., a replacement for S.H.I.E.L.D., and the leader of an Avengers populated by "reformed" supervillains, as the "Iron Patriot".

Name: Nuke (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Frank Simpson was an American soldier deployed to Vietnam. He was an exemplary soldier, but at some point he was captured and tortured, which broke his mind, and then his body was nearly destroyed. The United States Government, seeing both Frank's potential and that he could be controlled, put him through another experimental Super Soldier project. They replaced a large amount of his body with cybernetics, and replaced the outside of his skin with hard plastics. They also devised a pill based system to control him. Red pills made him aggressive, White pills made him calm down, and blue pills kept him calm.

Name: Ogremon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C, up to Low 1-C | At least 6-C, up to Low 1-C

Name: Ouryumon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least 5-B, possibly 1-C

Name: Overdrive (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Beverley was once a boy who dreamed to become a superhero like his hero Spider-Man. However, after failing to obtain superpowers in any way and proving himself to be inept at martial arts, he resigned himself to become a motorist like his father. However, after an accident left him seriously injured, he was approached by Mr. Negative, who sought his talents as a driver and promised to enhance his abilities through a swarm of nanobacteria that would allow him to transform any vehicle he came into contact with, as well as heal his injuries.

Name: Paul Rabin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Paul Rabin is the son of the Emissary who encountered Peter Parker and Mary Jane Watson after they entered his reality while fighting their own Emissary. After MJ used a device to send Peter back home, Paul spent nearly four years with her due to time dilation before Peter's return. During that time, Paul and MJ had found and adopted two kids to raise as their own. Apparently married, MJ refused to leave Paul, and they continued their family life in Earth-616.

Name: Poison Ivy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Poison Ivy is an enemy of Batman. She is depicted as one of the world's most prominent eco-terrorists. She is obsessed with plants, botany, and environmentalism. She uses toxins from plants and her own bloodstream for her criminal activities, which are usually aimed at protecting the natural environment. Fellow villain Harley Quinn is her recurring partner-in-crime and possibly her only human friend.

Name: Punisher (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lt. Frank Castle returned home from duty only to see his wife and children murdered in front of him in cold blood by the Mafia. Unable to find justice by any fair means for them, Castle vowed to spend the rest of his life avenging them. Now equipped with state-of-the-art weapons, decades of combat experience, guerrilla and urban warfare techniques, as well as detective-like skills, he wages a one-man war against crime as the Punisher, a murderous vigilante that takes no prisoners, and comes at odds with both heroes and villains for his methods.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Quicksilver (FOX)
Summary: Quicksilver, born Peter Maximoff, is a mutant who has the ability to move at superhuman speed.

Name: Radioactive Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Chen Lu was originally a Chinese nuclear physicist working on a way to defeat Thor, who had stopped his country's military strike on India. His plan was to expose himself to radiation, making him strong enough to defeat the Asgardian, and this granted him immense strength and various abilities. A frequent foe to Thor, Dr. Lu has been a member of the Thunderbolts and the Masters of Evil with an undying loyalty to his nation, as Radioactive Man.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Ras Nsi
Summary: Ras Nsi was once a Chosen of Ubtao, a Primordial planar power residing in Chult. Some time long ago, however, he cast off his oaths and his power, and became an evil warlord, raising the dead to be his armies. When he did so, he lost control of his necromantic hordes, and in his defeat sought out the Yuan-Ti of Omu to take control.

Name: Rath Modar
Summary: Rath Modar is a Red Wizard of Thay and the primary conspirator against the lich Szass Tam in the campaign to retake Thay. During the crisis concerning the Cult of the Dragons, Rath offered his wizards' might to assist the cult in their goal of summoning Tiamat from the Nine Hells. It was his silent hope that Tiamat would, when she saw how useful he had been, offer to him an army of dragons to wipe out Szass Tam once and for all.

Name: Ravemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Red Goblin (Normie Osborn)
Summary: Grandson of Norman Osborn, Norman Harold Osborn, more commonly referred to as Normie, is also Red Goblin. Attaining his current symbiote Rascal through Venom giving him it, Normie is bonded to it. Together they escaped Norman, deciding to join the Avengers Academy instead, being ashamed of his heritage.

Name: Remorhaz
Summary: Native to frozen lands, the Remorhaz spends all its days hunting prey. They are a millipede like creature that emits incredible heat from its body, using it burrow through ice without any issue.

Name: Retriever
Summary: Retrievers are the "gopher" units of any demonic fiefdom. Whenever a powerful lord or commander desires to search out lost artifacts, runaway slaves, or unruly underlings, the Retriever is sent out to find them and return them through any means possible. Most scholars can agree that the Retriever is built to mimic the structural design of the Bebilith, though the reason is unknown. Since they are constructs that are easily accessible to most demonic leaders, the Retrievers are also regularly entrusted with tasks that cannot be given to the demon's kin, for their ugly kind are not reliable.

Name: Rezmir the Black
Summary: Rezmir is a black half-dragon warrior placed in charge of a regional sect of the Cult of the Dragon, an organization dedicated to furthering Tiamat's goals across the plains. Around the time of Rezmir's leadership, the cult grew greatly in power and began to enact a plan to bring living dragons to great power, and eventually summon the Dragon Queen herself.

Name: Rhino (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Aleksei Sytsevich was an ordinary member of the Russian mob up, until the day he accepted to undergo experimental treatments that would augment his physical capabilities. He was then equipped with an armored suit which warranted him the codename Rhino. Aleksei became a superpowered thug for hire, and clashed with many superheroes, notably Spider-Man and the Hulk.

Name: Roc
Summary: A massive bird, the Roc is the supreme ruler of the skies in the mountains. They only go against large targets such as elephants, with the Roc being able to lift them with one leg. Sometimes Cloud and Storm Giants tame Rocs and use them as a deadly asset.

Name: Roper
Summary: The larva form, also known as a Piercer is an ambush predator in underground places that uses it camouflage in order to let itself drop upon prey whenever it senses someone below it. The adult form, also known as a Roper meanwhile is a far more active hunter, which while still using stealth, also employs tentacles it tosses at enemies in order to pull them to its maw.

Name: Russian (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Russian, real name Ivan Vassilovitch Dragovsky is a supervillain in Marvel Comics. He is an opponent of the antihero known as The Punisher - originally a fairly traditional Punisher foe (having little in the way of superhuman powers) he evolved into a more powerful comic book super villain following his resurrection by a paramilitary group.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Sandman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in a modest family, young William Baker was abandoned by his father and left in poverty with his alcoholic mother. He soon learned that this world rewards the strong, so he turned to violence first and to crime then, going by the alias of "Flint Marko".

Name: Sangonomiya Kokomi
Summary: Sangonomiya Kokomi (珊さん瑚ご宮のみや心ここ海み, Sangonomiya Kokomi?), is a playable Hydro character in Genshin Impact. The young Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island and a descendant of the Sangonomiya Clan, Kokomi is in charge of most of Watatsumi's affairs, shouldering heavy responsibilities alone in hopes of giving Watatsumi Island's people the hopes and happiness that they desire.

Name: Scarlet Spider
Summary: Benjamin "Ben" Reilly, also known as Scarlet Spider, is a clone of the original Spider-Man created by the Jackal.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wanda Maximoff is a Romani Transian sorceress and twin sister of the speedster Quicksilver. Once believed to have been mutant children of Magneto, the twins are in truth orphans enhanced by the High Evolutionary at Mount Wundagore. Wanda became a conduit of chaos magic, allowing her to shift probabilities and warp reality itself in the form of "hexes". After being saved from an angry mob by Magneto, the Scarlet Witch and her brother joined the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants to fight for Magneto's mutant supremacy cause. Disagreeing with Magneto's ruthless approach, the twins left him and joined the super-heroic Avengers instead, as the Scarlet Witch.

Name: Scientist Supreme (Andrew Forson)
Summary: Andrew Forson is an A.I.M. scientist who has served as its Scientist Supreme in the past. A manipulative yet driven personality, he led A.I.M. initially as it went public, and was able to use his charisma and leadership to form the new High Council of A.I.M. He was eventually ousted from his position by Sunspot, and has remained a prominent leader within the now-fractured organization.

Name: Scorpion (Marvel Comics)
Summary: MacDonald Gargan is a former detective hired by J. Jonah Jameson to investigate Peter Parker who was subjected to a painful experiment that gave him superhuman abilities and drove him insane, leading to him becoming Scorpion, one of Spider-Man's many persistent foes.

Name: ShineGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode | 1-C

Name: Shocker
Summary: Herman Schultz was a bold criminal who attempted to make a living off of stealing. When he ended up getting caught he began building a suit and vibro-shock units in prison, afterward using them to become the Shocker.

Name: ShogunGekomon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Shruikan
Summary: Shruikan was a black male Dragon, forcibly bonded to Galbatorix. He was the only dragon other than Glaedr to survive the Fall of the Dragon Riders to modern times. Galbatorix used Magic to artificially speed up Shruikan's growth, making him gigantic in size.

Name: Silk
Summary: nan

Name: Silver Sable (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of a famed Nazi hunter Ernst Sablinova, Silvija asked to train under her father to avenge her mother's death, soon exceeding her father's expectations to be one of the best assassins across the globe, and succeeded him as the Head of Sable International, leader of the Wild Pack and monarch of Symkaria.

Name: Sleipmon (Species)
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Solarmon
Summary: Solarmon is a Machine Digimon that appears to be a rare species of Machine-species Digimon. Among researchers, it is said to be a mutation of Hagurumon, but the truth is a mystery. Due to its "Computer Kernel" generating heat, its body has become hot enough to cause burns.

Name: Sora Takenouchi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Sora Takenouchi and Piyomon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Sora bears the crest of love, Piyomon is her partner Digimon. She is a "Chick" type Digimon who specializes in fire based attacks.

Name: Spider-Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Peter Benjamin Parker, more well-known as Spider-Man, was once just a nerdy teenager in High School. But after he was bitten by a radioactive spider at a science exhibition, he gained the proportionate strength, speed, and agility of a spider alongside a special precognitive ability known as the "Spider Sense" to warn him of incoming danger. However, after using his powers to in a wrestling match to earn money yet not prevent a burglary going on backstage that he had witnessed first-hand, he later returned home to find out that his Uncle Ben was murdered by someone who broke into their house.

Name: Spider-Man 2099
Summary: In the year 2099, Miguel O'Hara, the head of the genetics department for the Alchemax Corporation, becomes the legendary hero known as Spider-Man.

Name: Spider-Woman
Summary: Jessica Drew lived with her parents in the nation of Transia. At the age of 7, she suffered from uranium poisoning because of her father's work. Her father Jonathan with Dr. Herbert Wyndham, managed to save her life using a spider-derived serum. Jessica spent decades in stasis until she was finally awakened, realized she was cured. Wanting a new life, she left her house but ended up being caught by Hydra. They brainwashed her and trained her to become their operative. On one of her missions, she was tasked with killing Nick Fury but was caught by him and told the truth about the organization she was working with. The truth made her quit and start again, trying to find her path in life. She started going by the superhero name Spider-Woman and saving people, sometimes working for S.H.I.E.L.D.

Name: Spidercide
Summary: Much like Scarlet Spider and Kaine Parker, Spidercide is a clone of Peter Parker created by the Jackal. Unlike his “brothers”, he had been given additional abilities so he could defeat them.

Name: Stature (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of Scott Lang, Cassie Lang developed growth powers as a result of repeated exposure to Pym Particles, which were interlinked to her emotional state. After the demise of her father, Cassie carried his legacy by becoming a member of the Young Avengers under the alias of Stature.

Name: Stegron (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Vincent Stegron was working as an assistant to Dr. Curtis Connors on a project for S.H.I.E.L.D. that used dinosaur tissue supplied by Ka-Zar from the Savage Land. Becoming obsessed with the Lizard experiments and growing tired of the ills of human civilization, he decided to steal the dinosaur extract. He fled to the Savage Land and ingested the Connors Formula with the Stegosaurus DNA, turning himself into a Dinosaur Man.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Stone Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Stone Golem is the strongest of the common golems, often also being the prettiest looking due to being often assigned to guard museums.

Name: Susztam Mar-Shinn
Summary: Susztam is the Head Student of the Inverted Tower, a Drow outpost of arcane learning located in Szith Mercane. As the Head Student, he maintains the greatest control over his magic, and one day hopes to usurp his master in becoming the position of his master- until then, he spends his days in the Inverted Tower, training and learning constantly. He is particularly known to be a master of illusory spells and makes use of them frequently[1]. The position of head student is one envied by his peers, and thus Susztam spends his days preparing for their inevitable betrayal[2]. During the takeover of Szith Mercane, Susztam has entered the service of Dorina T'sarran, occasionally acting as a strike-team killer on her behalf[3].

Name: Taichi Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from the 2020 Reboot of Digimon Adventure. After being forcefully sucked into a Digital Space, Taichi meets Agumon alongside Yamato and Gabumon and defeats Algomon. Afterwards, Taichi and Co end up being sent to the Digital World where they go on an adventure to save the Holy Digimon while learning the secrets behind the Holy War between the forces of Light and Darkness.

Name: Takeru Takaishi (Adventure 2020)
Key: '''Takeru Takaishi''' | '''Patamon''' | '''Pegasusmon''' | '''Angemon''' | '''HolyAngemon''' / '''Holyangemon Priest Mode''' | '''Goddramon''' | '''Seraphimon and BlackSeraphimon''' | '''DanDevimon Shadow'''
Summary: Takeru and Patamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Takeru is the crest bearer of Hope and the younger brother of Yamato Ishida.

Name: Takuto and Shiki
Key: '''Start of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game and Post Game''' | '''During Voltobautamon rematch'''
Summary: Takuto and Shiki are the male and female protagonists of Digimon World: Next Order. They are a high school-senior ramping down the extracurricular activities and preparing for college exams. Addicted to Digimon games as a kid, even earning a second-place finish in the national championships as a fifth-grader. In present, they once again take the Digivice, which suddenly shines with light and transports them into the Digital World. Landing in a sealed dimension, they meet their partners, WarGreymon and MetalGarurumon, only to be suddenly attacked by a Machinedramon.

Name: Taskmaster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tony Masters is a man who can mimic and copy physical actions. He considered a career as a crime fighter but decided to become a professional criminal. After using his skills to complete a series of jobs, he used the capital to start an academy to train aspiring professional criminals around the world. Eventually, his operations were discovered and shut down by the Avengers. Since then Taskmaster has worked as a spy, a mercenary and still acts as a teacher to certain individuals, all for the sake of profit.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: The Fly (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Fly (formerly the Human Fly) once used to be Richard "Rick" Deacon, born in Newark, New Jersey, a small-time criminal who was shot by the police and left for dead after an unsuccessful kidnapping attempt, which was foiled by Spider-Man. Stumbling into the laboratory of Dr. Harlan Stillwell (whose brother Farley Stillwell created the Scorpion for J. Jonah Jameson), Deacon coerces the scientist into saving his life.

Name: The Inspector
Summary: From the 1965 cartoon series, stars the inspector. The Inspector is a police detective from France who is always trying to bring justice, thus getting into situations where he must find out a way to solve the problem.

Name: The Lizard (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Curtis Connors was a military surgeon turned herpetologist who lost his right arm during the war and sought to restore it by performing genetic research on the regenerative capabilities of reptiles. The serum that should have been the cure has instead turned him into the Lizard, a crazed but cunning monster who plans to return the planet to reptiles, which he believes being their righftul owners. Spider-Man always managed to foil his plans and reverse him back to a human, but every attempt at erasing the Lizard forever proved uneffective, and it remained a looming threat which could manifest anytime.

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Tigra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 8-C, at most High 8-C

Name: Titanium Man
Summary: Boris Bullski was a high ranking official in the Soviet government and a popular member in the Communist Party. In order to prove the USSR's superiority over the U.S, he created the Titanium Man armor to rival Tony Stark's Iron Man armor.

Name: Tombstone (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lonnie Lincoln was born an albino and thus, subject to both racism and mockery for his albinism. He responded by bullying and extorting his classmates, including his only friend, Joe Robertson. Lonnie eventually went further into bad behavior and became a thug for mob bosses or a mob boss himself, depending on what was more convenient for him at the time. This was when he earned the moniker Tombstone.

Name: Tornado
Summary: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air, in contact with the ground, either pendant from a cumuliform cloud or underneath a cumuliform cloud, and often (but not always) visible as a funnel cloud. Tornadoes come in many shapes and sizes, but they are typically in the form of a visible condensation funnel originating from the base of a huge storm cloud, whose narrow end touches the earth and is often encircled by a basal cloud of debris and dust. Most tornadoes have wind speeds less than 110 miles per hour (180 km/h), are about 250 feet (80 m) across, and travel a few miles (several kilometers) before dissipating. The most extreme tornadoes can attain wind speeds of more than 300 miles per hour (480 km/h), are more than two miles (3 km) in diameter, and stay on the ground for dozens of miles (more than 100 km).

Name: Toxie Doxie (Marvel Comics)
Summary: You get to understand there are haves and have-nots in this world, you know? And that the have-nots don't really have the same right to life as the people who worked hard to be selected for greatness. And when the have-nots accidentally enter a position of power, where they can prevent Darwinian victors from exercising their talents... That's just wrong.

Name: Trienath Salazar
Summary: Trienath Salazar is a veteran Hellbreaker, a group of thieves adept at intruding into the depths of Baator and taking the diabolical treasure from within. Trienath is fleeing from the Pit Fiend Zaebos, a member of the Dark Eight of Avernus, and offers to help player characters if she finds them to be righteous.

Name: Tsukaimon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | High 8-C | High 8-C | High 8-C

Name: Umber Hulk
Key: '''Umber Hulk''' | '''Truly Horrid Umber Hulk''' | '''Vodyanoi''' | '''Shadow Hulk''' | '''Umber Ravager''' | '''Abyssal Hulk''' | '''Astral Hulk'''
Summary: Umber Hulks are ancient mutant creatures born countless eons ago, possibly before the onset of the Dawn War[1]. Hulking bug-eyed monstrosities, the Umber Hulks lurk in the Underdark, tunneling from cavern to cavern in search of food (and little else), often causing wars and conflicts over territory as they move. They are feared on a nearly mythological level to some due to their peculiar ability to incapacitate hostiles with a glance- and leave survivors with nary a memory of what occurred.

Name: V-mon (Daisuke Motomiya)
Summary: Daisuke "Davis" Motomiya and his partner Veemon are two of the protagonists of Digimon Adventure 02. The de facto leader of the DigiDestined, their hot-blooded and reckless natures mean they have a lot of room for improvement, but they nevertheless step up to the plate and take the reins of their adventures with enthusiasm.

Name: Velasta and Velina T'sarran
Summary: Velasta and Velina T'sarran are a pair of Drow identical twins, nieces of Irae T'sarran who server under her daughter, Dorina, in Szith Mercane. Their duties there vary from humdrum to violent, but primarily include raiding on the surface and serving in the elite Hunter-Killer team alongside Susztam Mar-Shinn and Zedarr T'sarran[1]. While they are considered somewhat important to Irae's plans, if slain they are not outright given the time or resources for resurrection- instead they rise as revenants created by Irae.

Name: Venom (Edward Brock)
Summary: Eddie Brock was a journalist who tried to expose the identity of a serial killer only for the real killer to be caught by Spider-Man, thus he ended up accusing the wrong man. Disgraced, he came into contact with an alien Symbiote, rejected by Spider-Man. The Symbiote bonded with him and they became Venom.

Name: Venom Ooze
Summary: Theorised to be off shoots of ochre jellies this ooze is atypical in that it doesn't remain mostly in one spot and instead seeks out prey actively, which it's able to capture with its great strength and potent poison. This ooze is most commonly found in the Underdark alone but have been known to be used by evil individuals or simply migrated to another environment due to their incredible resistance to the elements.

Name: Venom Symbiote (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The symbiote that would be later known as the Venom Symbiote was the 998th of its lineage and was spawned at some point during the reign of the dark elder god Knull. Beyond this, much of the symbiote's history prior to its arrival on Battleworld is unclear -- in part due to the symbiote's memories having been erased, modified, or otherwise altered numerous times.

Name: Verdant Prince
Summary: Verdant Princes are powerful fey that roam the Prime Material, offering pacts with adventurers or even entire families.
