While often the pacts seem benign in nature (generally, the Prince won't even profit from the pact for many generations), each is in fact a malign curse on the pact-bearer, where when the Prince's plans come to fruition, that individual's descendants may well pay the full price of their ancestor's impudence.

Name: Vermin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Edward Whelan was once a young scientist working under Baron Zemo. Upon questioning his plan to create mutated soldiers, Edward was taken and subjected the same experiments, which were meant to bring out the darkest parts of a one's inner self and change their appearance accordingly. Edward's childhood trauma of being abused by his father resurfaced, and the sense of guilt and shame he felt at the time gave birth to an entirely new personality, bearing the name of the most ugly and vile creature Edward thought to be like: Vermin.

Name: Vitreous Drinker
Summary: Vitreous Drinkers are undead servants of Vecna, known to wander the lands stealing their victims' eyesight. To do this, they collect certain arcane items to surprise and ambush targets, and uses its skills to, after the attack, see through their victims' eyes. As worshippers of the God of Secrets, they often target great sages, spies, and magi to gain their information.

Name: Volcanicdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | Low 1-C | 1-C

Name: Vulture (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Vulture is a supervillain and one of Spider-Man's most die-hard enemies. Before becoming a criminal, Adrian Toomes was a capable engineer who had made a breakthrough when he invented a new kind of magnetic harness. It was an overwhelming joy after a life of hardships. But everything crumbled when he learned his business partner had been stealing a large sum of his profits before finally ousting him from the company they founded. Adrian was sad and angry, so he used what he knew to make a flying suit and become the Vulture.

Name: W54 warhead
Summary: Tier: High 8-C to 8-B | High 8-C to 8-A | 8-A | 8-A

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Water Weird
Summary: Made from water, the Water Weird is one of the possible Elemental Weirds. In their younger form they appear like a water serpent, shooting cold water at enemies and using their physiology to drown people who come close to them. Their adult self meanwhile is a powerful caster, being able to use various healing and water spells alongside regular Sorcerer spells.

Name: Web-Weaver (Marvel Comics)
Summary: As a high school student, Cooper Coen had a crush on classmate Peter Parker. While on a field trip, Cooper saved Peter from being bitten by a radioactive spider, resulting in Cooper being bitten instead and gaining super-human abilities. Cooper's already rocky relationship with his homophobic parents was strained further by his need to hide his secret identity, ultimately resulting in them kicking him out of his home. Cooper came to live with his aunts, Laurie and Mel Coen. The two encouraged Cooper to follow his passions and put him in New York's best fashion school, which later led to him receiving a job at the premier fashion house, Van Dyne. He then became a superhero under the alias of Web-Weaver.

Name: Wheep
Summary: An eyeless pathetic creature, the Wheep is a servant of other more powerful creatures which is often used as a bodyguard. It constantly emits a black vile from its eyes which makes tracking it down rather easy, although if they choose to, a Wheep is more than capable of using stealth to gain the edge in combat.

Name: Whiplash (Anton Vanko)
Summary: Anton Vanko lost his father, his town and his hand, after a devastating attack on Vostok by someone wearing a stolen battlesuit of Iron Man Armor. Presuming Tony Stark himself was responsible for the attack, he sought vengeance by modifying one of his armors, and has been a persistent threat to him ever since, as the all-new Whiplash.

Name: Whiplash (Marco Scarlotti)
Summary: Marco Scarlotti was a Maggia enforcer who cared deeply about supporting his family financially, and has been a persistent foe for Iron Man as the first Whiplash.

Name: White Rabbit (Marvel Comics)
Summary: White Rabbit: We don't need them! We're the Terrible Two! We're evil personified! The vilest villains on the face of the-- Walrus: They hung up on you, didn't they? White Rabbit: Uh-huh. After they were done laughing.

Name: Whizzer (Post-Golden Age)
Summary: Robert Frank was born to Dr. Emil Frank, a health practitioner. In the year 1941, Robert, an adult, was an assistant for his father's practice. One day, Emil was performing surgery on mobster Gabe Granno, when Granno's rival Neal Jennings burst in and forced Emil's scalpel down, fatally wounding Granno. Jennings then threatened to accuse Emil of murdering Granno if he did not flee the country. Fearing persecution, Emil and Robert left America and partook in a medical expedition in Cameroon. There, Robert contracted a rare tropical virus and was near death. Trying to save his son via blood transfusion from his own body, Emil became delirious and irrational. Determined to save the life of his son, Emil witnessed a mongoose fighting off a killing a cobra, only to be fatally wounded itself. Believing local folklore about the recuperative properties of the mongoose, Emil used the animal in a transfusion, reviving his son. Emil soon died from a combination of the blood transfusions and shock. Robert meanwhile found that he was endowed with super-human speed. Although initially believed that the mongoose blood was the source of his super-human powers, later reports suggest that the mongoose blood was actually a catalyst that triggered latent mutant abilities within Robert.

Name: Wisemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Wormmon (Ken Ichijouji)
Summary: Ken Ichijouji and Wormmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Ken as the Digimon Kaiser was the first major enemy of the Chosen Children. Being cruel, cold and sadistic person who enjoyed nothing more than causing pain to others and seeing them suffer. This persona was fueled by a corrupting Dark Seed that was planted in the back of his neck from defeating of Millenniummon.

Name: Yagnoloth
Summary: Yagnoloths are the minor lords of the yugoloth armies, controlling small swathes of the Lower Middle planes as command posts in the Blood War. They serve as basic negotiators for the yugoloth mercenary forces, and tend to bring in contracts for arcanaloths. They are most known for two distinctive traits- firstly, the physical trait of a single massively swelled arm, and secondly, the manipulative trait of always including a loophole in their contracts that voids the entire contract should the situation call for it.

Name: Yamato Ishida (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Yamato Ishida and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure 2020. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship and the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Zephiel (Fire Emblem)
Summary: Zephiel (ゼフィール Zefīru, Zefhyr in the Japanese versions) is the main antagonist of Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade and a minor non-playable character in its prequel, Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Adam Taurus
Summary: Adam Taurus was an antagonist in RWBY. Previously the leader of the White Fang's Vale branch, he became the High Leader after deposing the former leader Sienna Khan in a coup, but was ousted after the White Fang's defeat in the Battle of Haven. Following this, he began relentlessly chasing Blake Belladonna, only to be overpowered and killed by her and Yang Xiao Long.

Name: Akane Yashiro (Kiryu Saga)
Key: '''Akane Yashiro''' | '''Piloting Maser Cannon''' | '''Piloting AC-3 White Heron''' | '''Piloting Kiryu'''
Summary: Akane Yashiro (家城茜) is the human protagonist of the 2002 Toho Godzilla film Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla, also appearing in a minor role in its 2003 sequel Godzilla: Tokyo SOS. First Lieutenant Akane Yashiro A Type 90 Maser Cannon operator for the JSDF's Anti-Megalosaurus Force, Akane unintentionally caused the death of her comrades in a battle against Godzilla in 1999. Subsequently reassigned to a desk job, Akane was recruited to become a pilot for the Kiryu Squad in 2003, receiving the rank of Second Lieutenant. A member of the Kiryu team and the pilot of Kiryu Type-3. She is an excellent operator, but as the only member without relatives, she can be a bit awkward due to not being good at reading the feelings of others. Despite the odds against her, Akane earned the respect of her squad and played a key role in the battle between Kiryu and Godzilla in Tokyo. By 2004, she had been promoted to First Lieutenant and sought further training in the United States.

Name: Alan Keane
Summary: Alan Keane is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is an extraordinarily friendly teal balloon who is a student at Elmore Junior High. Alan is a very optimistic and diligent person, always working hard to try to make the world a better place and aspires to make the world such a good place that no one will have a reason to be sad. He has a high-pitched voice, and is currently dating Carmen.

Name: Alucard (Rosario + Vampire)
Summary: nan

Name: Alvida
Summary: "Iron Mace" Alvida is the former captain of the Alvida Pirates and the first obstacle Luffy faces after setting sail for the first time. She is currently one of the two captains of the Buggy and Alvida Alliance.

Name: Anais Watterson
Summary: Anais Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is the youngest and most intelligent member of the Watterson family despite being only four years old. She attends Elmore Junior High with her older brothers, Gumball and Darwin, and is in a higher grade than them.

Name: Anne Boonchuy
Key: '''Season 1-2''' | '''Season 3''' | '''Incomplete Calamity Form''' | '''Complete Calamity Form''' | '''With Secret Spell'''
Summary: Anne Boonchuy was pressured by her friends into stealing a strange music box on her 13th birthday which mystically activated and sent them to Amphibia, a realm populated by talking amphibians, where Anne lands in the town of Wartwood. There she is taken in by the Plantar family, who help Anne on her journey to find a way back home.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Arlong
Summary: Arlong the Saw is a Sawshark Fishman, older half-brother of Madam Shyarly and the captain of the Arlong Pirates, who is very prejudiced towards humans. He was a former member of the Sun Pirates, but after their captain Jinbe ​​became one of the Seven Warlords of the Sea, he broke off, taking his former crew with him, and searched for easy targets in the relatively tame East Blue. There, he and his crew enslaved Nami's home island and forced her to work for them as a cartographer, after killing her surrogate mother Bellemere. With her cartography skills and his connections with the Marines allowing him to operate under the radar, Arlong's plan was to turn the East Blue into his own personal empire. He was the main antagonist of the Arlong Park arc.

Name: Arslan Altan
Summary: Arslan Altan is the leader of Team ABRN. Arslan and her team faced Team RWBY during the Vytal Festival and later helped defend Beacon against the invading forces of Grimm.

Name: Arthur Watts
Summary: Arthur Watts is a major antagonist in RWBY. Originally a scientist working for the advancement of technology in Atlas, Watts became infuriated and vengeful when James Ironwood chose to fund the Penny Project proposed by Pietro Polendina as opposed to Arthur's own proposal. Thought to have perished in an incident involving the testing of Atlesian Paladins, Watts secretly allied himself with Salem and became the brains of her operation. Having designed and programmed the Mantle security grid himself, Arthur becomes instrumental in the Atlas portion of Salem's plan.

Name: Atsuya Kusakabe
Summary: Listen up you curse users!! I don't know what the hell happened, but those two there fighting are special grade! Think of them as elephants tap dancing on ants. To be clear, we're the ants...

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: Babe (Mr. 4)
Summary: Babe, also known by his epithet "Catcher-Killing" and alias Mr. 4, is a former officer agent of the Baroque Works and the slow and dimwitted partner of Miss Merry Christmas. Due to his slow nature, he tends to acts as the muscle of the Mr. 4 pair. He rarely takes any initiative and is his partner the duo's driving force.He's very strong, able to wield a four ton baseball bat and has a bazooka named Lassoo which has (somehow) eaten the Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Dachshund, turning it into a bazooka-dog that sneezes explosives baseballs.

Name: Bedtime Bear (Original)
Summary: Bedtime Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. As his name would suggest, he can most often be found dozing off at just about any place or time. However, when the situation calls for it, he can be dependable and is always willing to help out those who need it. It is his duty to make sure everyone on Earth and in the Care Bear family gets enough sleep and dreams peacefully.

Name: Bellamy
Summary: Bellamy the Hyena is the former captain of the Bellamy Pirates, and a former member of the Donquixote Pirates.

Name: Blake Belladonna
Summary: Blake Belladonna is one of the main characters and the third character introduced in RWBY. A young woman with long black hair, amber-colored eyes and a black ribbon resembling animal ears on her head, she wields the Gambol Shroud, a katana with a sharpened sheath that has a pistol in the hilt attached to a long ribbon which she uses in the style of kusarigama. In battle, her Semblance allows her to create a shadow of herself, an empty copy that distracts or takes hits from enemies for her while she moves in a different direction. Blake has a quiet nature and a love for books. She is a Faunus (a humanoid race with animal-like features) and a former member of the White Fang, a social rights advocacy group turned extremist paramilitary organization. However, she left in disgust of their violence and joined Beacon Academy to become a Huntress. Blake keeps her Faunus identity a secret by concealing her cat ears because she feels that she is not ready for the attention it would give her if the secret got out and doesn't want to face the discrimination other Faunus receive from humanity.

Name: Bling-Bling Boy
Summary: Eugene "Bling-Bling Boy" Hamilton is a recurring anti-hero in the series who has a one-sided crush on Susan Test.

Name: Bobert
Summary: Bobert is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. It is a robot that is a student at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Buchi
Summary: Buchi, along with his brother Sham, is a protector of the Black Cat Pirates' ship, the Bezan Black. The brothers are also known as the Nyaban Brothers and are some of the strongest men under Captain Kuro.

Name: Buggy the Clown
Summary: Buggy the Clown was initially one of the first real pirates that Luffy encountered early on in his travels. Buggy is a rather gaudy individual who used to be on the legendary Roger Pirates crew, along with Luffy's idol Shanks, who Buggy eventually bore a grudge against for unwittingly foiling a scheme to find a legendary treasure. After Gol D. Roger's death, the two went their separate ways, and while Shanks went on to become one of the Four Emperors, Buggy hung around the relatively tame East Blue.

Name: Captain Grime
Summary: Captain Grime was the ruthless commander of the Toad Army and superior of lieutenant Sasha Waybright, until his attempt to execute Hopadiah Plantar for treason lead to the first Toad Tower's destruction. After this, he became a fugitive along with his close circle, plotting a coup against the Newtopian throne. While initially very stern with his subordinates, Sasha's influence helped him to show them genuine respect, leading to improvement in their morale and performance.

Name: Carmine Esclados
Summary: Carmine Esclados is a character from RWBY: After the Fall. She is a veteran Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who was active in Vacuo, but was revealed to be a member of The Crown. She serves as the main antagonist of RWBY: After the Fall along with her partner Bertilak Celadon.

Name: Carrie Krueger
Summary: Carrie Krueger is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a ghost who is in Miss Simian's class at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Charles Bernard
Summary: Manga creators travel to a fictitious space in their minds because they aren't satisfied with reality. But my reality has been taken over by jujutsu. I've lost my motivation as a reader and as a creator. Do you know what that feeling is called? Despair

Name: Cheer Bear (2019)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She's the positive, enthusiastic pilot of the Cloudseeker and the leader of the expedition. Her upbeat personality is contagious and appreciated by just about everyone who meets her. Although she's always up for a challenge, she often feels a lack of confidence in her abilities.

Name: Cheer Bear (Original)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first debuted as a character on American Greetings cards in 1982. True to her name, Cheer specializes in lifting people's spirits whenever they're feeling down. Just about the only time one will find her feeling down is when there's someone who seems like they are nigh-impossible to encourage. However, this only ever leads Cheer to try harder. She constantly surprises those who doubt her capabilities with how multi-talented she truly is.

Name: Chizome Akaguro (Stain)
Summary: Chizome Akaguro (赤黒血染 Akaguro Chizome), known as the Hero Killer: Stain (ヒーロー殺し ステイン Hīrō Goroshi Sutein), is a villain that is notorious for having killed many Pro Heroes. In the Vigilante series, he was known as Stendhal (スタンダール Sutandāru) in which he killed criminals as his means of justice.

Name: Choso
Key: '''Shibuya Incident Arc/Itadori's Extermination Arc''' | '''The Culling Game Arc'''
Summary: Choso (脹ちょう相そう, Chōsō?) is the "older brother" of Itadori and his 9 other brothers siblings who were once just Cursed Womb. Choso is a "person" who is mainly concerned about his brothers, worrying about being a good example and making sure that his brothers do not make the mistakes that he made.

Name: Cinder Fall
Summary: Cinder Fall is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. She is a member of Salem's Inner Circle as well as the leader of her own faction, which includes Roman Torchwick, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black. Cinder is imperious and cunning, with a touch of cruelty. Usually, she maintains a calm and collected demeanor and is willing to take over a fight if necessary. She is also ambitious and demanding, doesn't seem to tolerate failure, and dislikes when she is disobeyed, reprimanding Emerald and Mercury when they failed to obey her orders to keep their hands clean. She is shown to be an excellent strategist as well, often planning ahead to keep her goals in reach while keeping her accomplices on a strict "need to know" basis. Following the Battle of Beacon, Cinder is the current Fall Maiden.

Name: Clayton (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: Clayton is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a shapeshifting ball of clay, and a student at Elmore Junior High. Clayton is a pathological liar; he impulsively makes up sequences of events and he can't help but lie about lots of things. This is most likely due to Clayton's wild imagination.

Name: Clover Ebi
Summary: Clover Ebi is a supporting character in RWBY. He is the leader of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. He has been described as a total bro character who always makes luck puns. He constantly feels like he's in an action movie because things always go right for him, so he doesn't need to look when he's about to jump. This ultimately leads him to be a person that relies too much on his Semblance and causing him to ride the lines between confidence vs arrogance. He appears to be cordial and calm, as well as good-humored and easy to get along with. However, Clover is quick to turn back to a task at hand when needed. He is fiercely loyal, and tends to bring out the best in people, and does whatever it takes to protect his Kingdom.

Name: Coco Adel
Summary: Coco Adel is the leader of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. She is first seen in "Field Trip", after returning from fighting the Grimm. Coco appears to be very confident; her self-assurance is expressed in the very way she struts down the battlefield. Her experience with Grimm has been consistent enough that their appearance no longer fazes her. She is confident enough in her team that she holds Velvet Scarlatina back from combat when she tries to unleash her weapon. Given her attire and her reaction to the Grimm's destruction of her "favorite clothing store", fashion seems to be strongly integrated into her personality. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Combustion Man
Summary: Combustion Man was a mysterious, silent assassin sent by Zuko to eliminate Aang.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Cozy Heart Penguin
Summary: Cozy Heart Penguin is a Care Bear Cousin who originated in the first feature length Care Bears Movie. She can frequently be found swimming in the arctic waters of the Forest of Feelings, and she considers it her task to spread warmth and joy to all she comes across. Cozy Heart also happens to be the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't a mammal.

Name: Curious Cat
Summary: The Curious Cat is a creature residing in the Ever After. They are connected to the Great Tree, and help facilitate the ascension process by determining who requires it. At first, they acted as a guide for Team RWBY, trying to help them reach the Great Tree. However they later revealed that they were only trying to wear down Ruby emotionally so they could possess her body and travel to Remnant, in order to find out why their makers abandoned them.

Name: Danjuro Tobita (Gentle Criminal)
Summary: Danjuro Tobita (飛田 弾柔郎 Tobita Danjūrō), better known as Gentle Criminal (ジェントル・クリミナル Jentoru Kuriminaru), is a small-time villain who has his assistant La Brava film his numerous petty crimes in order to raise awareness of the flaws in hero society. Once an aspiring hero-in-training with failing grades, his life turned upside down when he used his Quirk to try and save someone in the middle of a hero operation, inadvertently causing the person serious injury and his expulsion from school as well as being disowned by his parents.

Name: Dark Heart
Summary: Dark Heart is the primary antagonist of the second Care Bears feature film. He is a demonic entity who intends to capture each member of the Care Bear Family and spread his influence to everyone on Earth. Unlike most other adversaries of Care-a-Lot, however, Dark Heart's malicious ways come not from his hatred of caring but from his initial inability to understand it. After the near-death of his friend, Christy, helps him realize his capacity to care about others, he abandons his evil ways and his powers in the process.

Name: Darwin Watterson
Summary: Darwin Raglan Caspian Ahab Poseidon Nicodemius Watterson Ⅲ is the deuteragonist of The Amazing World of Gumball, and is Gumball and Anais' adoptive sibling.

Name: Denki Kaminari (Chargebolt)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Denki Kaminari (上鳴電気 Kaminari Denki), also known as Chargebolt (チャージズマ Chājizuma), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. Chargebolt is a friendly, social, and energetic boy who likes to hang out with people. He is rather casual when interacting with others, including the generally unfriendly Dynamight. He may come off as blunt and reckless at times, but is always well-meaning.

Name: Don Krieg
Summary: Don Krieg is the captain of the Krieg Pirates and an infamous pirate of East Blue. Because of his underhanded methods and domination over a fleet of 50 pirate ships, he is infamously known as "Foul-Play" Krieg and "Pirate Fleet Admiral" and is supremely confident in the weapons of his large arsenal.

Name: Dracula Duck
Summary: Count Dracula Duck (Or in some cases, referred as Drake Von Vladstone) is a Disney character and provides the role as the Final Boss in the game, Ducktales for NES, later to be the Final Boss once more for its Remastered version for the Wii U, Ducktales Remastered.

Name: Drophy (Miss Merry Christmas)
Summary: Drophy, also known by her epithet “Town-Collapser” and alias Miss Merry Christmas, is a former officer agent of Baroque Works and the talkative partner of Mr. 4. Due to her love of talking, she tends to acts as the brains of the Mr. 4 pair. Unlike her partner, who is very slow, Drophy talks very quickly, often only pronouncing the first syllable of the word in a high-pitched, child-like voice. She has eaten the Mogu Mogu no Mi which grants her the ability to turn into a human-mole and dig large tunnels.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Ectoplasm (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Ectoplasm is a Pro Hero who teaches mathematics as a member of the U.A. High School faculty.

Name: Eijiro Kirishima (Red Riot)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Shie Hassaikai Arc''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Eijiro Kirishima (切島鋭児郎 Kirishima Eijirō), also known as Red Riot (烈怒頼雄斗 Reddo Raiotto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero. Like Deku, he's kind, friendly, and has real dreams of being an altruistic hero, having been inspired by his idol, Crimson Riot. He has a bit of a fixation with doing "manly" things, rating actions as "manly" or "unmanly" depending on how much he approves of them.

Name: Elm Ederne
Summary: Elm Ederne is a supporting character in RWBY. She is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Elm is described as being a "big buff lady with a heart of gold", illustrating she has a very kind and good nature. She also shows to be a tough and loud person who is not afraid to let someone know what is on her mind. She appears to be somewhat overzealous and is stated to not have a filter.

Name: Emerald Sustrai
Summary: Emerald Sustrai is a former associate of Cinder Fall and former partner of Mercury Black. While she worked with Cinder, she initially appeared to be affable and disarmingly friendly, however, this belies a darker side of her character. On the whole, she seemed to be genuinely outgoing and quick-witted, if a little short-fused. She had a tendency to maintain a pretense of friendliness amongst people in order to gain their trust, and showed a strong sense of loyalty, specifically to Cinder, whom she appeared incredibly eager to please. However, Emerald eventually had a change of heart and joined Ruby and her friends after learning from Ozpin about Salem's true goals.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Flynt Coal
Summary: Flynt Coal is a student at Atlas Academy and the leader of Team FNKI.

Name: Fox Alistair
Summary: Fox Alistair is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Fox is sarcastic and laid back in personality. Though he is reserved in new social situations, he is lively in familiar ones to the point where he considers himself the comedic relief of Team CFVY. He is comfortable enough on the subject of his own blindness to make jokes about it himself. Fox thinks of himself as a prankster; he has a tendency to make practical jokes and poke fun of his friends. He holds himself in high esteem and directs himself with confidence, having no qualms being blunt about people if need be. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: Funshine Bear (2019)
Summary: Funshine Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. He's the blindly optimistic co-pilot of the Cloudseeker who's always looking to have as much fun as possible. He rarely takes things seriously, which has both helped with the team's morale but also hindered their progress, depending on the situation. As a thrill seeker, Funshine's hobbies include hang-gliding and skating; he also is seen working on a superhero comic book from time to time.

Name: Galdino (Mr. 3)
Summary: Galdino, also known by his epithet “Loan Shark Galdino” and his alias Mr. 3, is a former officer agent, alongside his former partner Miss Goldenweek. He is regarded as the smartest of the officers and only got the position of "Mr. 3" because of that. He has eaten the Doru Doru no Mi which allows him to create and control candle wax at will.

Name: Gem (Mr. 5)
Summary: Gem is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works. His codename was Mr. 5 and his partner was Miss Valentine.

Name: General Tesler
Summary: General Tesler is the main antagonist of TRON: Uprising. He is one of CLU's generals and is both extremely ambitious and a coldly calculating sadist. Tesler rules over Argon City from his command ship.

Name: General Yunnan
Summary: General Yunnan is a general of the Newtopian army sent to hunt down Captain Grime for military desertion, but fails after being defeated. However, she later assists in stopping him and Sasha during the toad invasion of Newtopia. Following the reveal of King Andrias' true goals, she tries to defect but is placed under a mind control collar, until Anne and Sasha free her, at which point she helps fight against her former king's invasion of Earth.

Name: Giant Crow
Summary: Giant Crow is a Demon level threat that appeared in City M during the Monster Raid. It was first seen ramming directly into King's apartment.

Name: Gin (One Piece)
Summary: Gin the "Man-Demon" is a pirate and a member of the Krieg Pirates. Due to his actions, he can be considered the secondary antagonist of the Baratie Arc.

Name: Glynda Goodwitch
Summary: Glynda Goodwitch is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, she was introduced in Volume 1, in which she saved Ruby Rose from an attack by Cinder Fall. She is the first known Huntress in the series. Her weapon of choice is The Disciplinarian.

Name: Goliath (RWBY)
Summary: Goliaths are giant elephant-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "Search and Destroy". It is the cousin Grimm of the Megoliath in the continent of Solitas.

Name: Good Luck Bear (2019)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. Due to his lucky streak and natural intuition, he's assigned the role of the Cloudseeker's navigator. His Belly Badge power ensures luck is always on his side, which has frequently helped the crew on their mission. He's often the one to reassure his companions when things are tense. On the other hand, he can also be overconfident and over-reliant on this power. On multiple occasions, he's dived headfirst into situations without thinking things through.

Name: Good Luck Bear (Original)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. Good Luck is a fortuitous bear that never seems to run out of good luck. However, this has just as much to do with his exceptionally bright, positive outlook on life as it does with his ability to create his own four-leaf clovers. Truly believing that there is no such thing as "bad luck", the fortunate fellow tries to help others by improving the power of their own self-confidence and removing all doubt from their heart.

Name: Goto Imasuji (Muscular)
Summary: Goto Imasuji (今筋強斗 Imasuji Gōto), also known as Muscular (マスキュラー Masukyurā), was a member of the League of Villain's Vanguard Action Squad. He lost his left eye to the efforts of Water Hose, a pair of Pro Heroes who defended a town he was attacking. Because of this, he appears at U.A.'s secret summer training camp to attack Water Hose's only son, Kota Izumi, forcing Deku to intervene and save the boy from the villain's wrath.

Name: Gray Fox
Summary: Gray Fox, real name Frank Jaeger, was a mercenary and former agent of U.S. Special Forces Unit FOXHOUND. Originally a child soldier, Jaeger was the only operative in FOXHOUND to achieve the codename "Fox," the unit's highest commendation and was decorated five times.

Name: Grumpy Bear (2019)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with protecting the Silver Lining. He is the creator of the Cloudseeker, the vehicle the bears use to navigate the uncharted territory. He's frequently having to upgrade or fix it, thanks to the unpredictability of the area they explore. As the crew's resident worrywart, he often either brings up an important detail the rest of the Bears hadn't considered, or he reaches a point where his pessimism needs to be dialed back.

Name: Grumpy Bear (Original)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. He is quite recognizable, possibly more so than his friends, due to being the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't always smiling and cheerful. Despite his default mood, he is just as caring and dedicated to helping others as anyone else in Care-a-lot.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Hammerhead (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Hammerhead (ハンマーヘッド Hamaheddo) is a B-Class criminal and the leader of the Paradise Group, a terrorist group insisting that people shouldn't have to work if they don't want to.

Name: Harriet Bree
Summary: Harriet Bree is a supporting character in RWBY. She is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Harriet is competitive and quick-witted in nature, causing her to only be loyal to those who earn her respect. However, she is still cordial and well-mannered. Harriet also displays great confidence in her skills, bordering on arrogance, and she is quick to rush into action.

Name: Hatchan
Summary: Hatchan, often called “Hachi” by most characters, is an octopus fish-man, a former officer of the Arlong Pirates and a member of the Sun Pirates before that. After the crew split up, he joined Arlong's crew and became the handler of the sea cow Momoo. When the Straw Hats came to take down Arlong, he was defeated by Zoro, and was imprisoned by the Marines. However, he managed to escape, and met the mermaid Camie and the starfish Pappag after saving them from Sea Kings and Fishman slavers. He opened up a floating takoyaki stand, fulfilling a childhood dream of his, with the mermaid and starfish occasionally helping on support.

Name: Hazel Rainart
Summary: Hazel Rainart was one of the antagonists of RWBY. Introduced in Volume 4 as a member of Salem's Inner Circle, he was a very calm and reasonable person who would only use violence when it had a clear purpose. However, this all disappeared when in the presence of Ozpin who Hazel held responsible for the death of his sister. While in Ozpin's presence he would go into a murderous rage and was willing to kill anyone who stood in his way.

Name: Higari Maijima (Power Loader)
Summary: Higari Maijima (埋島干狩 Maijima Higari), also known as Power Loader (パワーローダー Pawārōdā), is a Pro Hero and faculty member at U.A. High School who manages the Support Course Development Studio.

Name: Himiko Toga
Summary: Himiko Toga (渡我被身子 Toga Himiko) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was a member of the group's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, L.O.V. and the Meta Liberation Army merged to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and Himiko became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Hiryu Rin (Dragon Shroud)
Summary: Hiryu Rin (鱗飛 竜 Rin Hiryū), also known as Dragon Shroud (龍帷子 Ron Wei Dzū), is a student of Class 1-B at U.A. High School, aspiring to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Hitoshi Shinso (Nighthide)
Summary: Hitoshi Shinso (心操人使 Shinsō Hitoshi), also known as the Hypnosis Hero: Nighthide (ヒプノシスヒーロー ナイトハイド Hipunoshisu Hīrō Naitohaido) was a student at U.A. High School, attending Class 1-C of the Department of General Education before being transferred into Class 2-A of the school's Hero Course.

Name: Hizashi Yamada (Present Mic)
Summary: Hizashi Yamada (山田ひざし Yamada Hizashi), also known as Present Mic (プレゼント・マイク Purezento Maiku), is a Pro Hero who teaches English at U.A. High School.

Name: Hood (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Hood (フード Fūdo), also known simply as High-End (ハイエンド Hai Endo), was one of Dr. Garaki's intelligent High-End Nomu and the primary antagonist of the Pro Hero Arc.

Name: Hoyo Makihara (Mummy)
Summary: Hoyo Makihara (巻まき原はら包ほう傭よう Makihara Hōyō), also known as Mummy (マミー Mamī) is a villain working alongside Nine.

Name: Inasa Yoarashi (Gale Force)
Summary: Inasa Yoarashi (夜嵐イナサ Yoarashi Inasa), also known as Gale Force (レップウ Reppū), is a first-year student at Shiketsu High School, U.A.'s rival. He was the top-recommended student for U.A. High before withdrawing his application. Gale Force is an energetic and enthusiastic young man who expresses himself with vigor. His signature trait is his undying love for passion above all else. He believes all heroes should have a fiery passion that motivates them to help others. He has a habit of approaching strangers to try and make friends with them. He also appears to enjoy passionate battles and desires to be a part of them. He disapproves of heroes who do not have hot spirits and believes people filled with hatred are unfit to be heroes and he refuses to recognize them as such. This is why he hates Endeavor and his son Shoto. Both of them had cold angry eyes when he met them and both of them blew him off despite his warm greetings.

Name: Itsuka Kendo (Battle Fist)
Summary: Itsuka Kendo (拳藤一佳 Kendō Itsuka), also known as Battle Fist (バトルフィスト Batoru Fisuto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero, and the Class President of Class 1-B. Thoughtful, tomboyish, and reliable, she is often the one taking charge of her class when no one else is around, particularly when keeping Phantom Thief in line.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Final Act)
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as the One For All Hero: Deku (ワン・フォー・オール ヒーロー デク Wan Fō Ōru Hīrō: Deku), is one of the 20% of people on Earth who were born without a Quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in modern society, causing him endless torment at school. However, thanks to his innate heroism, he was able to earn the Quirk "One For All", bestowed upon him by his idol All Might, and use it to grow into one of the world's greatest heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: James Ironwood
Summary: General James Ironwood is the headmaster of Atlas Academy, a general in the Atlesian Military, and a holder of two seats on the Atlesian Council. For unknown reasons, the entire right section of his body was replaced with a robotic prosthesis. Originally, he was an ally to Ruby's Group. However, after learning that they lied to him and Salem was on her way, he turned against them and intended on raising Atlas out of her reach. He serves as a main antagonist in Volume 8. At the end of the Volume, he is killed when Atlas crashes into Mantle, destroying them both.

Name: Jaune Arc
Summary: Jaune Arc is the leader of Team JNPR who wields a sword and shield named Crocea Mors, an heirloom formerly belonging to his great-great-grandfather. He comes from a long line of esteemed Hunters and feels pressured to live up to their reputations. Because of his family line, Jaune is obsessed with being a hero. However, he was never formally trained like the rest of his family, which causes him to lack self-esteem and assign a lot of importance to his image as a fighter. He also does not seem to be very proud of having a weapon given to him, rather than earning or crafting it on his own, referring to his weapon as a simple "hand-me-down" instead of a "family heirloom." However, Jaune has demonstrated capable leadership skills and good tactical judgment. He also possesses a strong Aura which allows him to heal himself, although he cannot yet control this ability.

Name: Jin Bubaigawara (Twice)
Summary: Jin Bubaigawara (分倍河原仁 Bubaigawara Jin), also known as Twice (トゥワイス Tuwaisu), was a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, his organization and the Meta Liberation Army merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants. Even Hawks, the number 2 Pro Hero, believed Twice to be the most dangerous of Shigaraki's lieutenants.

Name: Joe Sparrow
Summary: Joe Sparrow is a character from Amphibia.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome. He's the only son of Hugh and Lila and brother of Susan and Mary (who had brown hair in the 2004 pilot). Because he has Susan and Mary by his side, he can live any kid's dream, only to find that some dreams aren't worth living. He is usually seen with his partner-in-crime and best friend Dukey, his genetically altered dog. He also gives Johnny Coupons to his sisters for helping him with his daily problems. When redeemed, he does their tests for free. Johnny and his sisters are often the cause of some problems in Porkbelly.

Name: Jurota Shishida (Gevaudan)
Summary: Jurota Shishida (宍しし田だ獣じゅう郎ろう太た Shishida Jūrōta), also known as Gevaudan (ジェボーダン Jebōdan), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School.

Name: Kai Chisaki (Overhaul)
Summary: Kai Chisaki (治崎廻 Chisaki Kai), better known as Overhaul (オーバーホール Ōbāhōru), is the leader of the Shie Hassaikai ("Eight Precepts of Death") yakuza group in the world of My Hero Academia.

Name: Katsuki Bakugo (Dynamight) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''With One For All'''
Summary: Katsuki Bakugo (爆豪勝己 Bakugō Katsuki) is a student in Class 1-A at U.A High School training to become a Pro Hero. He is the complete opposite of Deku, being stubborn, hot-headed, arrogant, and gifted.

Name: Kendo Rappa
Summary: Kendo Rappa (乱波肩動 Rappa Kendō), also known as The Rapper (ザ ラッパー Za Rappā), is a member of Overhaul's Shie Hassaikai. Rappa is a hot-blooded man who thrives on violence and bloodshed. He has a warrior-like mentality and only cares about seeking out a battle that can satisfy him. Originally an MMA fighter who fought in many underground rings for years. He was usually unsatisfied, most of his opponents were defeated in one punch and those that could take his punch would beg for their lives. His routine would end after he met Overhaul who offered him to join his group.

Name: Kenji Hikiishi (Magne)
Summary: Kenji Hikiishi (引ひき石いし健けん磁じ Hikiishi Kenji), also known by her villain name Magne (マグネ Magune), was a member of the League of Villains and part of its Vanguard Action Squad. She and the rest of her team serve as the main antagonists of the Forest Training Camp Arc.

Name: King Andrias
Summary: King Andrias is the king of Amphibia and leader of Newtopia. He is initially introduced as a benevolent king who only wants to help Anne and her friends, but as events unfold he is revealed to actually be a major antagonist in the series, serves as a major opposing force against the main cast while also being a pawn in his master's plan.

Name: King Thorax
Summary: King Thorax is a character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Kinji Hakari
Summary: It all has to do with the fever. Both the deceiver and the deceived are in a fever to change their lives. People get high on the fever and make mistakes. And me? I love the fever! However, without it, people can't even fall in love. Do you know a more direct way of dealing with the fever? Life itself is a gamble. Lots of girls have dumped me 'cause they hate gambling, but they don't understand. Society tramples on guys who can't bet big and guys who don't know when to quit. Everyone gambles. What they hate is losing and going to ruin.

Name: Kiruka Hasaki (Slice)
Summary: Kiruka Hasaki (羽は咲さき斬きる香か Hasaki Kiruka), also known as Slice (スライス Suraisu), is a villain working alongside Nine.

Name: Koji Koda (Anima)
Summary: Koji Koda (口田甲司 Kōda Kōji), also known as Anima (アニマ Anima), is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero. He is a very shy and timid person despite his large and imposing appearance, and rarely speaks, even to his classmates and prefers to use sign language to communicate.

Name: Kuro (One Piece)
Summary: nan

Name: Kuroobi
Summary: Kuroobi is a ray fishman, first mate of the Arlong Pirates as well as a former member of the Sun Pirates. He is a 40th rank practitioner of Fishman Island Karate. Though similar to his captain in their disdain of humans in general, he has some respect for those whose strength impressed him but still will act cruel overall. He is a very cautious person, as he's the only one to not trust Nami, and was proven to be right.

Name: Kyoka Jiro (Earphone Jack)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Kyoka Jiro (耳郎響香 Jirō Kyōka) is a student at U.A. High, training to become a Pro Hero. She is known as Earphone Jack (イヤホンジャック Iyahon Jakku).

Name: Laboon
Summary: Laboon is an Island Whale native to the West Blue, and a close friend and companion to Brook and the Rumbar Pirates when he was a baby. Due to the dangers of the Grand Line, Laboon was told to stay near Reverse Mountain and promised him that they would come back after two or three years once they've finished their adventure. The Rumbar Piraters were killed during their journey, and Laboon waited for fifty years without knowledge of what their fate was.

Name: Lena Sabrewing (2017)
Summary: Lena is a major character in the reboot of Ducktales. Serving as a spy for Magica De Spell after she was trapped in Scrooge McDuck's Number One Dime, she befriended Webby Vanderquack in order to steal the dime, only to be morally swayed by her friendship with Webby in order to fight back against Magica. After being trapped in the Shadow World by Magica, she was eventually freed with the help of Webby and her new friend, Violet Sabrewing.

Name: Leonardo Lionheart
Summary: Leonardo Lionheart is a supporting antagonist in RWBY and the Headmaster of Haven Academy. Formerly a trusted member of Ozpin's inner circle, he has turned to Salem's side as a spy, out of fear of the latter, who he feels cannot be defeated, a decision he is implied to regret. On the surface, Leonardo Lionheart demonstrated a rather polite and jovial persona and genuinely came off as a well-meaning and compassionate man. He was also shown to be easily startled and seemed to be somewhat timid. Despite this, he was willing to argue with people like Qrow Branwen and seemed unafraid to speak his mind to his fellow Huntsman. Lionheart also showed to be less impulsive than Qrow, and was also quite perceptive.

Name: Lie Ren
Summary: Lie Ren, more commonly referred to as Ren, is a student at Beacon Academy and a member of Team JNPR. His weapon of choice is a pair of green automatic pistols which have blades attached to them, named StormFlower. He and Nora are long-time friends, though he is the exact opposite of her, as he is mostly quiet, mellow and mature.

Name: Lord Tirek
Summary: Lord Tirek is the sixth main villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, acting as the main antagonist for the season four finale Twilight's Kingdom.

Name: Mahito
Summary: Mahito (真ま人ひと?) is the secondary antagonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is a Cursed Spirit allied with Suguru Geto, Jogo, Hanami, and several others. Their ultimate goal is eradicating humanity and ultimately replacing the population with Cursed Spirits.

Name: Maki Zenin
Summary: nan

Name: Manga Fukidashi (Comicman)
Summary: Manga Fukidashi (吹ふき出だし漫まん我が Fukidashi Manga), also known as Comicman (コミックマン Komikkuman), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Marcy Wu
Summary: Marcy Wu: The day we left, your birthday, they told me my dad got a new job out of state. They're making me move away, they were gonna tear us apart! Anne Boonchuy: Marcy... Marcy Wu: I... I found the box. I had no idea it would actually work, but it did. It sent us to a place where we'd never have to grow apart, where the three of us could friends forever together! Anne Boonchuy: How could you?! I've been missing my parents, my life! Marcy Wu: But look at how much fun we've had. Look at how much you've both grown. Look at Sprig. I gave you this, I gave you everything! I just didn't want to be alone.

Name: Maria Calavera
Summary: Maria Calavera, known in her youth as The Grimm Reaper is a supporting character who appears in Volume 6 of RWBY. While she seems to just be a frail old woman who tagged along on Ruby's crew's journey to Atlas due to a train crash, she is actually one of the most renowned huntresses in her time, someone who inspired the likes of Qrow to choose that path in life.

Name: Marrow Amin
Summary: Marrow Amin is a supporting character in RWBY. He is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Marrow is described as mischievous in personality, having been kicked out of an undisclosed place at least three times in the past. As the novice member of the Ace-Ops, he is also the most naive and childish of the group, having to be 'babysat' by Harriet Bree. A large aspect of Marrow's motivation to have become a Huntsman in the past was that many said he couldn't. However, beating those odds, Marrow was able to rise to the top of the ranks, becoming an Ace-Op.

Name: Masami Yoshida
Summary: Masami Yoshida (吉田正美 Yoshida Masami) is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a cloud student at Elmore Junior High. Masami comes from a very rich family; her dad is the owner of the Rainbow Factory and her mom has affiliation there. Along with her elemental abilities, this makes Masami one of the most feared and popular students at school.

Name: Mashirao Ojiro (Tailman)
Summary: Mashirao Ojiro (尾白猿夫 Ojiro Mashirao), also known as Tailman (テイルマン Teiruman), is a student at U.A. High School from Class 1-A training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Megatron (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Megatron is the leader of the decepticons. He left cybertron to chase after the Allspark, only to end up frozen on Earth. Depending on the version of the game, he would either face an Allspark amped Stascream, or he himself would be amped by the power of the Allspark.

Name: Mei Hatsume
Summary: Mei Hatsume (発目明 Hatsume Mei) is a student attending U.A. High School's Department of Support from Class 1-H.

Name: Mercury Black
Summary: Mercury Black is an antagonist in RWBY.

Name: Metal Gear RAY
Summary: A Metal Gear unit designed by the United States Navy for the purpose of destroying REX imitators before being stolen and redesigned by the Patriots, along with a whole bunch of other people who somehow got their hands on models. Raiden in his post-MSG4 years later fought a modified version of RAY.

Name: Mezo Shoji (Tentacole)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Mezo Shoji (障子目蔵 Shōji Mezō), also known as Tentacole (テンタコル Tentakoru), is a student attending U.A. in order to become a Pro Hero. Despite his intimidating appearance, he is quite a friendly and gentle person who will work well with anyone. He is not the type to hold grudges and displays no ill will towards those who unwillingly harm him.

Name: Mii Fighter
Summary: The Mii Fighters are warriors based on the customizable Mii avatars.

Name: Mikita (Miss Valentine)
Summary: Mikata is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works. Her codename was Miss Valentine and her partner was Mr. 5.

Name: Mina Ashido (Pinky)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Mina Ashido (芦戸三奈 Ashido Mina), also known as Pinky (ピンキー Pinkī), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. She is cheerful and can be seen with a smile on her face most of the time. She is easily excited, but also very emotional and easily brought to tears in various situations, out of relief, out of sadness, and out of frustration. However, she is still very easygoing and sociable.

Name: Mirio Togata (Lemillion)
Summary: Mirio Togata (通形ミリオ Tōgata Mirio), also known as Lemillion (ルミリオン Rumirion), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School.

Name: Moka Akashiya
Summary: Moka Akashiya (Akashiya Moka, 赤夜 萌香) is a vampiress in Yōkai Academy and the main female protagonist of the series. She serves as the primary love interest to Tsukune Aono, who is the sole human enrolled in an academy of monsters. She has an enchanted rosary that gives her a split personality; her outer persona is gentle, compassionate, and seemingly weaker than average monsters. In contrast, the inner persona is a bold and domineering vampire lady; she is also a remarkably strong fighter, even among vampires.

Name: Momo Yaoyorozu (Creati)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Momo Yaoyorozu (八百万百 Yaoyorozu Momo) is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training under the name, "The Everything Hero: Creati" (万物ヒーロー クリエイティ Banbutsu Hīrō Kurieiti). She is a very intelligent and dedicated person who acts as a natural leader. She is generally very level-headed and calm even in dangerous situations.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Moonfish
Summary: Moonfish (ムーンフィッシュ Mūnfisshu) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and also part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He and the rest of his team serve as the main antagonists of the Forest Training Camp Arc.

Name: Mr. Compress
Summary: Atsuhiro Sako (迫圧紘 Sako Atsuhiro), also known as Mr. Compress (Mr.コンプレス Misutā Konpuresu), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. He is known for being one of the smartest villains in the world and acts as the brains of the League of Villains. His organization later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Naoya Zenin
Summary: Naoya Zenin (禪院ぜんいん 直なお哉や, Zen'in Naoya?) is an antagonist in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was the youngest son of Naobito Zenin and believed himself to be the true heir of the Zenin Family. Naoya was also the head of the clan's elite unit of jujutsu sorcerers, the Hei.

Name: Neito Monoma (Phantom Thief)
Summary: Neito Monoma (物間寧人 Monoma Neito), also known as Phantom Thief (ファントムシーフ Fantomu Shīfu), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School. Flamboyant with an inferiority-superiority complex towards the more famous Class 1-A, Monoma is determined to one-up Class 1-A at every turn, never hesitating to rub any sort of mistake or mishap in their face while ignoring his own many flaws.

Name: Nejire Hado (Nejire Chan)
Summary: Nejire Hado (波動ねじれ Hadō Nejire), also known as Nejire Chan (ネジレちゃん Nejirechan), is a recently graduated hero from the U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Nemuri Kayama (Midnight)
Summary: Nemuri Kayama (香山睡 Kayama Nemuri, also known as Midnight (ミッドナイト Middonaito), is a Pro Hero and faculty member at U.A. High School. She teaches Modern Hero Art History and was the Chief Referee of the U.A. Sports Festival for first year students as well.

Name: Neon Katt
Summary: Neon Katt is a member of Team FNKI, of Atlas Academy. She participated in the Vytal Festival tournament, fighting against Yang Xiao Long and Weiss Schnee during the doubles round in the episode "Never Miss a Beat".

Name: Neopolitan
Summary: Neopolitan, better known as Neo, is a major antagonist in RWBY and the former partner of Roman Torchwick.

Name: Neptune Vasilias
Summary: Neptune Vasilias is a character in RWBY and a member of Team SSSN.

Name: Nine (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Nine (ナイン Nain) was a villain and the primary antagonist of My Hero Academia: Heroes Rising. Having contracted an illness, Nine proved himself to be compatible with All For One's Quirk Factor, allowing him to obtain a weaker version of All For One. With it, he went to Nabu Island and tried to steal a Quirk that would have cured his illness, but he failed in his task.

Name: Nirengeki Shoda
Summary: Nirengeki Shoda (庄田二連撃 Shōda Nirengek), also known as Mines (マインズ Mainzu), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: No Heart
Summary: No Heart is the primary antagonist of Nelvana's Care Bears cartoon series. He is a wicked sorcerer whose goal is to rid the world of any and all love and caring. Though his creations are dastardly and his plans thorough, he is thwarted time and again by the Care Bears' intervention and the incompetence of his own henchmen. Although he is an expert in his craft, he is constantly irritable and will often snap at the slightest hindrance to himself and his objective.

Name: Nora Valkyrie
Summary: Nora Valkyrie is a Huntress-in-Training at Beacon Academy. Her weapon is Magnhild, a grenade launcher that can be converted into a war hammer. Nora is a happy-go-lucky, bubbly, and cheerful young girl who displays boundless enthusiasm and never fails to let it show. Her excitable nature makes her rather hyperactive and hasty. Even in combat, Nora retains her joyful personality, but she is seen to stay focused when actually fighting. Despite her generally cute personality, Nora does seem to have a love of battle, much like Ruby. She may be a little extreme when it comes to dealing with issues, as her suggested solution to help Jaune Arc with Cardin Winchester's bullying was breaking Cardin's legs. As all Non-Grimm, living creatures do, she has an Aura that can help her in many situations and her Semblance can turn the tide of battle to her favor.

Name: Ochako Uraraka (Uravity)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Ochako Uraraka (麗日お茶子 Uraraka Ochako), also known as Uravity (ウラビティ Urabiti), is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training assisting to the U.A. High School.

Name: Oscar Pine
Summary: Oscar Pine was an ordinary farmboy who lived with his aunt in Mistral for most of his life. On one fateful day, he discovered that his soul has been irrevocably merged with that of Professor Ozpin, the Headmaster of Beacon Academy, who urged Oscar to leave home and head to Haven Academy.

Name: Ozai
Summary: Ozai was the Fire Lord and absolute ruler of the Fire Nation during the final years of the Hundred Year War. He was the second son of Azulon and Ilah, the younger brother of Iroh, uncle of Lu Ten, husband to Ursa, the father of Prince Zuko and Princess Azula, and grandfather to Izumi. Ozai was a firebending master and, prior to the ending of the War, was believed to have been one of the most powerful firebenders in the world.

Name: Pearl (One Piece)
Summary: Pearl the Iron Wall is the commander of the Krieg Pirates' second unit.

Name: Penny Fitzgerald
Summary: Penny Fitzgerald is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a shape-shifting fairy, formerly a peanut, who is in Miss Simian's class in Elmore Junior High.

Name: Penny Polendina
Summary: Penny Polendina is a character introduced in the episode "The Stray," when she was found lying on the ground after Weiss Schnee crashed into her whilst chasing after Sun Wukong. Penny speaks robotically, behaves erratically, and is overly active in general. All her actions and emotional states were rather extreme and overacted. When Ruby Rose unintentionally made an unconditional offer of friendship, Penny seemed both immensely pleased and somewhat surprised.

Name: Pharynx
Summary: Pharynx a minion in the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic series.

Name: Pony Tsunotori (Rocketti)
Summary: Pony Tsunotori (角取ポニー Tsunotori Ponī), also known as Rocketti (ロケッティ Roketti), is a student in Class 1-B of U.A. High School, and is training to become a Pro Hero. She comes from the United States, because of this she has some difficulty speaking Japanese.

Name: Primid
Summary: The Primids are the most basic infantry force of the Subspace Army. While they are one of the weakest, they are also the most common by far, often coming in huge groups.

Name: Qrow Branwen
Summary: Qrow Branwen is the younger twin brother of Raven Branwen, biological uncle of Yang Xiao Long and honorary uncle of Ruby Rose. He is a former member of the Branwen Tribe as well as a former teacher at Signal Academy.

Name: Raiden (Metal Gear)
Key: '''Metal Gear Solid 2''' | '''Metal Gear Solid 4''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Updated Patriots Cyborg Body)''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Custom Cyborg Body)'''
Summary: Vamp: You, too... Immortal? Raiden: No. I just don't fear death.

Name: Raika
Summary: Tier: 8-A

Name: Raven Branwen
Summary: Raven Branwen is the mysterious mother of Yang Xiao Long and Qrow Branwen's twin sister. She was originally a member of Team STRQ, though unlike most Hunters, she has little issue killing and is described by her brother as a dangerous person. Raven has a high "survival of the fittest" mentality in which she is rather indifferent towards innocents dying if they were too weak to defend themselves. On one occasion she saved the life of her daughter, who she had abandoned shortly after her birth, though not without warning that she won't be looking out for her a second time. Raven is currently concerned about Salem and the power that she possesses.

Name: Reiko Yanagi (Emily)
Summary: Reiko Yanagi (柳やなぎレイ子こ Yanagi Reiko), also known as Emily (エミリー Emirī), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Richard Watterson
Summary: Richard Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. He serves the role of the father in the Watterson family. Unlike the traditional father, however, Richard is not wise, nor is he a good role model for his children in any way. Despite his misguided advice and uncouth mannerisms, Richard has good intentions and loves his family all the same.

Name: Rikido Sato (Sugarman)
Summary: Rikido Sato (砂藤力道 Satō Rikidō), also known as Sugarman (シュガーマン Shugā Man), is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Rikiya Katsukame
Summary: Rikiya Katsukame (活瓶力也 Katsukame Rikiya) is one of the Eight Bullets of the Shie Hassaikai. He was the first of the bullets to be fought by the heroes and managed to take down half of them before being defeated.

Name: RJ
Summary: Robert James, usually referred to as RJ, is the laid-back and carefree master and instructor of the Jungle Fury Power Rangers, as well as, the boss and owner of a pizza restaurant that serves as their headquaters. During his childhood, his father, Master Finn, constantly tried to force RJ to learn the Shark Technique in order become a Shark Master. RJ, being against this, left home and found his own master, who instructed him in the ways of the Wolf. Upon mastering his Wolf Spirit, RJ became the new Wolf Master and eventually the Jungle Fury Wolf Ranger after his students help him revert from his werewolf form, a curse inflicted by Da' Shi.

Name: Rob (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: Rob (AKA Dr. Wrecker) is the main antagonist of The Amazing World of Gumball. He was formerly a minor background student at Elmore Junior High before he was cast into the Void, a dimension which harbors "all the mistakes the world has ever made." Following his escape and recollection, he becomes Gumball's arch-nemesis for revenge over his abandonment and to have a part to play in the world.

Name: Robyn Hill
Summary: Robyn Hill, Mantle's hometown hero and leader of the Happy Huntresses. First appearing in Volume 7, she was running for a spot on the Atlas Council in hopes of improving conditions in her home of Mantle. Her Happy Huntresses are known for fighting for the poor against the wealthy, and is more than willing to commit acts that are less than legal in order to protect her home.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Ruby Rose
Summary: Ruby Rose is the 15-year old leader of Team RWBY attending Beacon Academy two years early, due to her abilities impressing Professor Ozpin. Trained by her Uncle Qrow, Ruby wields a unique weapon named Crescent Rose, a cross between a scythe and a high-caliber sniper rifle that is able to fold up into itself. Her Semblance is speed, enabling her to run at rates that are too fast for the eye to catch. As she is the youngest of the group, she can be a bit childish, naïve, and weapon-obsessed, but displays leadership qualities and an understanding of people that ultimately led her to be chosen as Team RWBY's leader. She was inspired to become a Huntress by the fairy tales her half-sister Yang read her, wanting to become just like the heroes in the stories. She is determined to make the world a better place for others and try to stop the forces that conspire against it.

Name: Ruby Tojo
Summary: As a young child, her parents were killed in a car crash. As a result of this, she became a human-hating witch serving under Lady Oyakata. She later betrayed her after meeting the human Tsukune. She later becomes the Headmaster's assistant and helps defend Japan against Fairy Tale.

Name: Rumi Usagiyama (Mirko)
Summary: Rumi Usagiyama (兎山 ルミ Usagiyama Rumi), also known as Rabbit Hero: Mirko (ラビットヒーロー ミルコ Rabitto Hīrō Miruko), is currently the No. 5 Pro Hero in Japan.

Name: Ryuko Tatsuma (Ryukyu)
Summary: Ryuko Tatsuma (竜間龍子 Tatsuma Ryūko), also known as the Dragoon Hero: Ryukyu (ドラグーンヒーロー リューキュウ Doragūn Hīrō Ryūkyū), is the current No. 10 Hero in Japan. She worked with Nejire Chan, Uravity, and Froppy during the Shie Hassaikai Arc.

Name: Salem
Summary: An incredibly enigmatic figure from Remnant's forgotten past, Salem is the true main antagonist of RWBY.

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sarah G. Lato
Summary: Sarah G. Lato is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is an introverted yet jaunty student at Elmore Junior High, who admires Gumball and Darwin, and wants to be included in their escapades. Sarah loves fan fiction and manga, and considers herself an otaku.

Name: Sasha Waybright
Summary: Sasha Waybright was sent to the realm of Amphibia along with her friends after being exposed to the Calamity Box, where she was imprisoned by Captain Grime in the Toad Tower until using her manipulation skills to prove she would be a valuable asset. Thus, she is instated as first lieutenant of Grime's toad army, putting her at odds with Anne and the frogs of Wartwood.

Name: Satoru Gojo
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Scarlet David
Summary: Scarlet David is a member of Team SSSN, who made his first appearance in "Extracurricular". Scarlet has red hair that comes down over his right eye, with a complete undercut. There are a number of red markings around his left eye. He wears a green, mulberry, navy color feather earring on his left ear, and has a red military pelisse-like jacket draped over the left side. He also wears a gray bandanna around his neck. On his right hand, he wears a fingerless glove, and on his right biceps, he has a gray band. He wears a white sleeveless shirt and light gray pants. He also wears a pair of long, brown, laced boots. Around his waist, he wears a slightly slanted gray belt.

Name: Sekijiro Kan (Vlad King)
Summary: Sekijiro Kan (管かん赤せき慈じ郎ろう Kan Sekijirō), also known as Vlad King (ブラドキング Buradokingu), is a Pro Hero and the homeroom teacher of U.A. High School's Class 1-B.

Name: Sen Kaibara (Spiral)
Summary: Sen Kaibara (回原かいばら旋せん Kaibara Sen), also known as Spiral (スパイラル Supairaru), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, where he got in through official recommendations, and is currently training there to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Setsuna Tokage (Lizardy)
Summary: Setsuna Tokage (取蔭切奈 Tokage Setsuna), also known as Lizardy (リザーディ Rizādi), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero, and one of the four first year students who entered through recommendations.

Name: Share Bear (2019)
Summary: Share Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She is the team's communicator, receiving and relaying information from the Caring Tower. Additionally, she acts as the point of contact for any new species and civilizations the crew encounters. While Share is more than happy to help others however she can, this often leads her to putting a lot of pressure on herself and getting discouraged whenever she makes mistakes.

Name: Shihai Kuroiro (Vantablack)
Summary: Shihai Kuroiro (黒くろ色いろ支し配はい Kuroiro Shihai), also known as Vantablack (ベンタブラック Bentaburakku), is one of the students in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Shinji Nishiya (Kamui Woods)
Summary: Shinji Nishiya (西屋森児 Nishiya Shinji), also known by his hero name, Kamui Woods (シンリンカムイ Shinrin Kamui), is the No. 7 Pro Hero and member of The Lurkers.

Name: Shino Sosaki (Mandalay)
Summary: Shino Sosaki (送崎信乃 Sōsaki Shino), better known by her hero name, Mandalay (マンダレイ Mandarei) , is Pro Hero and member of the Wild Wild Pussycats alongside Tiger, Ragdoll, and Pixie-Bob. She is a calm and collected woman who doesn't hesitate to help someone in danger. Her Quirk, Telepath, allows her to advise and instruct anyone with her mind through mental transmissions.

Name: Shota Aizawa (Eraser Head)
Summary: Shota Aizawa (相澤消太 Aizawa Shōta), also known as Eraser Head (イレイザー・ヘッド Ireizā Heddo), is a Pro Hero and Class 1-A's Homeroom Teacher. Apathetic and stern at a glance, he nevertheless holds his class to incredibly high standards, going so far as to expel entire classes for failing to meet them.

Name: Shoto Todoroki (Shoto)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Shoto Todoroki (轟焦凍 Todoroki Shōto), also known as Shoto (ショート Shōto), is one of main protagonists of the My Hero Academia manga and anime series.

Name: Shuichi Iguchi (Spinner)
Summary: Shuichi Iguchi (伊口秀一 Iguchi Shūichi), also known as Spinner (スピナー Supinā), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He is obsessed with the ideals of the Hero Killer: Stain, and is determined to revive Stain's vision of society through himself. His group later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Sienna Khan
Summary: Sienna Khan was a character in RWBY. The High Leader of the White Fang after Ghira Belladonna stepped down, she was a charismatic new leader, and with her rise came the use of violence and militarization as the fringe elements of the White Fang became the core, with members such as Adam Taurus embracing the philosophy of his new leader. However, after condemning Adam for his participation in the Fall of Beacon, she was killed by him, who usurped her role after covering up her murder.

Name: Sludge Villain
Summary: The Sludge Villain is a villain that appeared in the first chapter of My Hero Academia. It attempted to possess Deku, and later Dynamight's body. He was defeated by All Might on both occasions.

Name: Snipe (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Snipe (スナイプ Sunaipu) is the current No. 25 Pro Hero and a member of the teaching staff at U.A. High School. He is in charge of the third year students.

Name: Solid Snake
Summary: We can tell about other people about--having faith. What we had faith in. What we found important enough to fight for. It's not whether you were right or wrong, but how much faith you were willing to have, that decides the future.

Name: Sphinx (RWBY)
Summary: Sphinxes are large, flying feline Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in the episode "Argus Limited."

Name: Spike the Dragon
Key: '''Baby Dragon Form''' | '''Equestria Girls Dog Form''' | '''Adult Dragon Form ''' | '''Post Puberty'''
Summary: Spike the Dragon is a protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Starscream (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: After the disappearance of Megatron nearly a million years ago, Starscream took over the Decepticons as their high commander. Arriving on Earth, he instructed Create-A-Bot to follow Barricade until he arrived. However, none of the other Decepticons would trust him, and he confided in Create-A-Bot a great number of secrets, including the location of the AllSpark and the identity of the lost Decepticon they were retrieving: Megatron. Starscream reasoned that he hid these things because revealing them would lead to a power struggle, but no one bought it except the naive rookie.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Stygian
Summary: Tier: Unknown, likely 8-A | 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Subspace Bomb
Summary: The Subspace Bomb is a powerful weapon used in the Super Smash Bros. story mode. A large portion of the game is set to keep them from being set.

Name: Suguru Geto
Summary: An endless cycle of exorcism and consumption. Exorcise. Consume. It's a taste that nobody knows. The taste of a curse. Like ingesting a rag used to wipe up vomit. Exorcise. Consume.
