For whom? Ever since that day... It's been running through my head. What I saw was nothing out of the ordinary. A hideous evil known to everyone. Knowing that full well... I chose to protect them as a Jujutsu Sorcerer. Don't lose your way. Follow through with your duty as a Jujutsu Sorcerer... Monkeys...

Name: Sun Wukong (RWBY)
Summary: Sun Wukong is a Faunus from the kingdom of Vacuo, who later moved to Mistral and made his first appearance in "The Stray". His weapon is a collapsible staff that separates into two pairs of nunchucks made of guns called Ruyi Bang and Jingu Bang. In his first appearance, Sun is shown to be fun-loving and mischievous, with little regard for the law - stowing away on a ship, thanking the crew for the ride during his escape, throwing a banana peel in a detective's face, and stealing apples. He has a lot of self-confidence, referring to himself as a "great stowaway". He is also a bit of a flirt towards Blake. In conversation, Sun is very laid-back and casual. He is also kind and patient, willing to listen to Blake's story and waiting for her to do so for nearly two days, bearing with her "small talk and weird looks". He is not afraid to give his opinion and has a dislike for those who regard themselves as "holier than thou", or who "use force to get whatever they want", such as the White Fang. Sun also seems to be willing to help others, regardless of whether he is asked or not, even if he barely knows them. This quality is further demonstrated when he readily volunteers to help Team RWBY with their investigation, despite both Blake and Ruby stating their opposition to his involvement.

Name: Sweetie Belle
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A

Name: Swift Heart Rabbit
Summary: Swift Heart Rabbit is one of the Care Bear Cousins who has been a frequently recurring character since the first feature-length movie. True to her name, she is easily the fastest member of the Family, and she's not one to let people forget that. Her hubris and insistence to get things done as quickly as possible frequently lead to much needed lessons in humility. Despite her flaws, she's quick to get back up, and will always be there to lend her speed and a helping hand where she can.

Name: Tamaki Amajiki (Suneater)
Summary: Tamaki Amajiki (天喰 環 Amajiki Tamaki), also known as Suneater (サンイーター San'ītā), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Tashigi
Summary: Tashigi was first introduced when the Straw Hat Pirates docked in Loguetown, where she was stationed. Smoker, her superior officer, seems to regard her as a protege; the two work very well together.

Name: Team RWBY
Summary: Team RWBY (pronounced "Ruby") is a Huntress team of former Beacon Academy students, which is comprised of RWBY's main characters: team leader Ruby Rose, Weiss Schnee, Blake Belladonna, and Yang Xiao Long. Originally unable to even hold a proper conversation together, the team eventually develops a familial bond and grows into a tightly-knit group, willing to risk their futures and even their lives for each other. They have no qualms breaking the rules to do what they believe is right.

Name: Tenderheart Bear (Original)
Summary: Tenderheart Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared as an illustration on American Greetings greeting cards in August 1982. Exemplifying the very best qualities of the Care Bears, Tenderheart is usually considered the de facto leader of the gang. He frequently organizes their efforts to help spread love and care around the world, and keep their own home of Care-a-Lot in working shape. He is responsible for initiating new members into the Care Bear Family by bestowing their very own belly symbols, and has been directly involved in nearly every major event in their history.

Name: Tensei Iida (Ingenium)
Summary: Tensei Iida (飯いい田だ天てん晴せい Īda Tensei), also known as the Turbo Hero: Ingenium (ターボヒーロー・インゲニウム Tābo Hīrō Ingeniumu), is the older brother of Tenya Iida and a Pro Hero.

Name: Tenya Iida (Ingenium)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tenya Iida (飯田天哉 Īda Ten'ya), also known as Ingenium is the Class President of Class 1-A and a major character in My Hero Academia. Being born into a wealthy family of prestigious and esteemed heroes, he works tirelessly to uphold his family values and embody what it truly means to be a hero.

Name: Teru Momijiyama (Shy)
Key: '''Beginning of Series to Yuri Orphanage Arc''' | '''Tokyo Recapture arc'''
Summary: Teru Momijiyama (紅葉山テル, Momijiyama Teru), better known as Shy (シャイ Shai), is the main protagonist of the manga series SHY. Living in a world where every country has a hero to protect it. She is a middle school student and the successor to her older sister Mei Momijiyama, the previous Hero of Japan. After her passing, her Heart Shift Bracelets were given to her at her funeral. After which she chose to use the Bracelets to become Japan's new hero, and to live up to her sister's legacy. Even though she struggles with talking to crowds, or even just doing her job as a hero.

Name: Tetsutetsu Tetsutetsu (Real Steel)
Summary: Tetsutetsu Tetsutetsu (鉄哲徹鐵), also known as Real Steel (リアルスティール Riaru Sutīru), is a student at U.A. training to become a Pro Hero. His similar hardening Quirk and attitude make him akin to a carbon copy of Red Riot.

Name: The Core (Amphibia)
Summary: The Core is the collective consciousness of the greatest minds of Amphibia and serves as the main antagonist throughout the later half of Amphibia. Being a collection of consciousness in a robotic shell it needs a host to properly interact with the outside world. As such The Core takes the body of Marcy and uses it for much of season 3.

Name: The Hound (RWBY)
Summary: The Hound is a highly intelligent Creature of Grimm created by Salem that can adapt itself to its surroundings. It makes its first appearance in "Divide", when she commands it to hunt down the one who can show her how to use the Relic of Knowledge.

Name: The Spirit (Care Bears)
Summary: The Spirit is the primary antagonist of the first Care Bears feature film. While Nicholas Cherrywood was cleaning out the old trunk which belonged to the magician, Mr. Fettuccine, he stumbled upon an ancient book of spells. The book spoke to him from within its pages and beckoned him to open it, offering the fame and notoriety he had been seeking all his life. Upon doing so, he met The Spirit. This would initiate their venture to render everyone in the world just as cold and uncaring as The Spirit herself.

Name: Tobias Wilson
Summary: Tobias Wilson is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a student at Elmore Junior High. He claims to be popular with the ladies, but he is actually pretentious and is just good at projecting the persona of someone who is successful. Tobias frequently fails to impress his female classmates, yet continues to believe that he is the coolest person. He is overconfident in his social and physical capabilities, and enjoys boasting about his supposed status and accomplishments, much to the annoyance of others. Despite his shortcomings, Tobias does have plenty of friends anyway, and does actually come from a well-off family.

Name: Tock
Summary: Tock is a crocodile Faunus with a shaved head, dark-green mohawk and yellow eyes. She was part of a team of assassins sent to eliminate Maria Calavera, known as The Grimm Reaper. After a prolonged battle between the two, Tock manages to slash the Grimm Reaper's eyes, rendering her permanently blind and robbing her of the Silver Eyes technique. Before being dealt the killing blow, however, Maria manages to catch Tock off guard and decapitate her.

Name: Togaru Kamakiri (Jack Mantis)
Summary: Togaru Kamakiri (鎌かま切きり尖とがる Kamakiri Togaru), also known as Jack Mantis (ジャックマンティス Jakku Mantisu), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Toji Fushiguro
Summary: nan

Name: Tomura Shigaraki (Pre-Surgery)
Summary: Tomura Shigaraki (死柄木 弔 Shigaraki Tomura), original name Tenko Shimura (志村転弧 Shimura Tenko), was the protégé of All For One and the leader of the League of Villains. A dangerously unstable individual who looks up to his "Sensei" with the utmost awe and respect, Shigaraki plans on tearing down the society of heroes built up by All Might by any means necessary. His organization and the Meta Liberation Army later merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and he became its Grand Commander.

Name: Toru Hagakure (Invisible Girl)
Summary: Toru Hagakure (葉隠透 Hagakure Tōru), also known as the Stealth Hero: Invisible Girl, is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero. She is a bubbly, cheery, and easygoing girl that does most things with an upbeat, positive attitude, even if she's been manipulated by her less reputable classmates.

Name: Tsunagu Hakamada (Best Jeanist)
Summary: Tsunagu Hakamata (袴田はかまだ維つなぐ Hakamata Tsunagu), also known as Fiber Hero: Best Jeanist (ファイバーヒーロー ベストジー二スト Faibā Hīrō Besuto Jīnisuto), is the formerly No. 4, now No. 3 Pro Hero and recipient of the "Best Jeanist" award for eight consecutive years.

Name: Tsuyu Asui (Froppy)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tsuyu Asui (蛙吹梅雨 Asui Tsuyu), also known as Froppy (フロッピー Furoppī), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. She's known for her stoic and unflappable attitude, being able to work well under pressure, contrasting heavily against her far more emotional classmates.

Name: Tyrian Callows
Summary: Tyrian Callows is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. A known serial killer, he is an associate of Salem and part of her inner circle. He first serves as a main antagonist in Volume 4, hunting down Ruby Rose on the order of Salem. He again serves as one in Volume 7 alongside Arthur Watts. Tyrian is described as being psychotic incarnate and someone who wants to see the world burn. He is a highly unstable, disturbed, maladjusted, manipulative, and outright sadistic individual. He frequently bursts into fits of uncontrollable, maniacal laughter and relishes in gruesome thoughts, such as the idea of removing one of Ruby's eyes in payment for her taking one of Cinder Fall's. His depravity is described in The World of RWBY: The Official Companion as someone who is irredeemable.

Name: Tzveta Kooriskaya
Summary: Tzveta Kooriskaya (ツィベタ＝コオリスカヤ), formerly Letana Andreanova is a member of the villain group Amarariruku. She is the mother of the current hero of Russia, Spirits (Pepesha Andreanova). Born without her parents to take care of her she grew up in the Yuri Orphanage before leaving and having her own child. However, due to an economic recession which struck Russia at the time, she was struggling to provide for her daughter as a single mother. Often struggling to keep up with rent, having to choose between eating or keeping the apartment warm. This lead to her starting to believe her daughter would be happier if she wasn't the one raising her. Eventually she would fall to her death after a thief pushed her off a bridge. Afterwards she was resurrected by the leader of Amarariruku, Stigma but without her old memories. Now reborn with a new hatred for the world.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Vamp
Summary: One of the members of the anti-terrorist squad Dead Cell's founding lineup, Vamp was orphaned in his youth when his church was bombed, forcing him to resort to feeding on the blood of his family to survive, giving him a taste for it. His codename was not gained from these vampiric traits, however, but from his bisexuality.

Name: Velvet Scarlatina
Summary: Velvet Scarlatina is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Velvet is a very shy, quiet girl who tends to keep to herself, either by choice or because she is isolated by others for being a Faunus. Even when being picked on by others, she tends to act very reserved and refuses to fight back. One can say that she is very timid. However, despite her shy personality, she seems to get along with others, as seen with Team RWBY, and being an older student, she wishes them safety on their mission. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Vernal
Summary: Vernal is a character in RWBY and a member of the Branwen tribe, a group of bandits that operate in Mistral. In order to keep the identity of the Spring Maiden a secret, she took on the name "Vernal", posing as a decoy to fool others. As such, her true name is unknown. Her weapons of choice were crescent shaped blades combined into a gun.

Name: Villain Bots
Summary: We exist... to serve humans' desires.

Name: Vine Zeki
Summary: Vine Zeki is a supporting character in RWBY. He is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. He is described as calm and tranquil in both speech and temperament and is shown to be in control of himself, especially when compared to the rest of Ace-Ops. He is also shown to be easily exasperated by their comparatively more gung-ho approach. Vine believed self-improvement is the highest pursuit. At the end of Volume 8, he gave his life to protect Mantle from being blown up by a bomb, using his Semblance to contain the explosion.

Name: Weiss Schnee
Summary: Weiss Schnee is the second member of Team RWBY. Her weapon is a Dust revolver/rapier named Myrtenaster, and her Semblance allows her to create glyphs in battle. At 17 years of age, she is the heiress to the Schnee Dust Company, a corporation famous for its sometimes shady business dealings, dangerous practices, and mistreatment of its Faunus laborers. Both the Schnee Dust Company and the Schnee family have been targets of the White Fang terrorist organization for years, leading to Weiss' inherent distrust of the Faunus. Weiss chose to become a Huntress over taking a job at SDC to restore her family's honor, as her father caused the company to decline. At the start of the show, she was shown as self-centered, standoffish, and an obnoxious know-it-all, but has matured somewhat throughout the show. She has a noticeable scar over her left eye, which she is assumed to have acquired in a fight against a living suit of armor in the 'White Trailer'. As of Volume 4, she is the former heiress of the Schnee Dust Company.

Name: Winter Schnee
Summary: Winter Schnee is a character in RWBY and the elder sister of Weiss Schnee. Despite being the eldest child, Winter's right to inherit the Schnee Dust Company was abdicated upon her decision to join the Atlas Military. At first glance, Winter appears to be cold, dignified, and distant, preferring to keep her emotions subdued and speaking in a very high-class, eloquent, almost robotic fashion. However, when interacting with Weiss, she smiles and shows that she cares about her younger sister's life and well-being. Although she strives to keep her emotions in check, she can be rather hot-headed at times. Once she becomes angry, she drops her dignified ladylike demeanor and loses all restraint. Winter consistently wrestles with her emotions, never letting them overpower her, yet still allowing them to guide her on what she believes to be a righteous path.

Name: Wish Bear (Original)
Summary: Wish Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. As one can infer from her name, she is tasked with making sure the wishes of everyone on Earth, and often even those of the Care Bear Family, come true. Sometimes this can be accomplished by her own supernatural wish granting abilities; other times she prefers to work towards seeing the wishes of others and even herself come to light.

Name: Wolfram (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Wolfram is a greedy and manipulative villain who will crush anything or anyone to get what he wants. He lusts for money and works as the leader of a company of thieves. They even posed as fake villains for hire to gain David Shield's trust just so they could steal his invention.

Name: Yang Xiao Long
Summary: Yang Xiao Long is one of the main characters and the fifth character introduced in RWBY. A yellow-haired girl and Ruby Rose's older half-sister, she wields twin shotgun gauntlets called Ember Celica. Easily the most hotheaded member of the group, when she gets very angry or if her hair is damaged during battle, she completely loses her temper.

Name: Yatsuhashi Daichi
Summary: Yatsuhashi Daichi is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. He is first seen in the Volume 2 Opening, walking with his teammates and is later seen falling from the sky with other teams; he subsequently makes his first, albeit brief appearance in "Field Trip", before making a full-fledged appearance in "Breach". He is also one of the members of his team chosen to advance to the doubles round of the Vytal Festival Tournament, along with Coco Adel. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Yawara Chatora (Tiger)
Summary: Yawara Chatora (茶ちゃ虎とら柔やわら Chatora Yawara), also known as Tiger (虎とら Tora), is a Pro Hero and member of the Wild, Wild Pussycats.

Name: Yo Shindo (Grand)
Key: '''Provisional Hero License Exam Arc''' | '''Dark Hero Arc'''
Summary: Yo Shindo (真堂しんどう揺よう Shindō Yō), also known as Grand (グランド Gurando), is a student at Ketsubutsu Academy High School.

Name: Yu Takeyama (Mount Lady)
Summary: Yu Takeyama (岳山優 Takeyama Yū), better known by her hero alias Mount Lady (Mt. レディ Maunto Redī), is a relatively new Pro Hero. She's in the business for fame and fortune, quickly becoming popular for her flirtatious nature and the raw power her Gigantification Quirk provides, but is nevertheless a kind person at heart. She is the No. 23 Pro Hero.

Name: Yuga Aoyama (Can't Stop Twinkling)
Summary: Yuga Aoyama (青山優雅 Aoyama Yūga), also known as Can't Stop Twinkling (キャント・ストップ・トゥインクリング Kyanto Sutoppu Tuinkuringu), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. He is flamboyant and loves the spotlight, but is prone to cracking under pressure and is somewhat cowardly. Nevertheless, he does pitch in when push comes to shove.

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die. I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Alex (Street Fighter)
Summary: Alex is a playable character in the Street Fighter series, and the protagonist of the Street Fighter III games. He is a professional wrestler who lives day-by-day out of his trailer house in New York, which he never left and has no interest in doing so. His day is spent between construction jobs, wrestling events and training. Tom, Alex's mentor and a friend of his father, is worried about him, as he always keeps his emotions in check, isn't very talkative and lacks sensitivity, which makes it seem he lacks a true purpose in his life, although things apparently started to change after his meeting with Dhalsim.

Name: AllSpark Drones (Transformers 2007 DS Games)
Summary: These non-sentient robots were created by the AllSpark to protect itself from being stolen before Megatron got his hands on it and began commanding these drones for his own purposes in the Autobots game. In the Decepticons game they're instead created by Starscream in multiple attempts to destroy Create-A-Bot after his betrayal.

Name: Amber (RWBY)
Summary: Amber was the previous Fall Maiden. As a young girl, she received the powers of the Fall Maiden, granting her tremendous power and becoming the next in a line that persisted for thousands of years. However, due to the actions of Cinder Fall, half of her powers were stolen, causing her to fall into a coma. As she was unlikely to ever wake up, and in order to ensure that the rest of the powers would not go to her assailant, Ozpin and his group planned on transferring her portion to someone else. However, she would eventually be killed by Cinder during the Battle of Beacon, causing the rest of the powers to go to her.

Name: Anne Boonchuy
Key: '''Season 1-2''' | '''Season 3''' | '''Incomplete Calamity Form''' | '''Complete Calamity Form''' | '''With Secret Spell'''
Summary: Anne Boonchuy was pressured by her friends into stealing a strange music box on her 13th birthday which mystically activated and sent them to Amphibia, a realm populated by talking amphibians, where Anne lands in the town of Wartwood. There she is taken in by the Plantar family, who help Anne on her journey to find a way back home.

Name: Aoi Todo
Summary: Aoi Todo (東とう堂どう葵あおい, Tōdō Aoi?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is a third-year student at Kyoto Jujutsu High School and a grade 1 jujutsu sorcerer. He was mentored by Yuki Tsukumo in his youth and considers Yuji Itadori his best friend.

Name: Argento Pocoron
Summary: Argento Pocoron is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. He is a former Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, serving as an enforcer for The Crown.

Name: Arslan Altan
Summary: Arslan Altan is the leader of Team ABRN. Arslan and her team faced Team RWBY during the Vytal Festival and later helped defend Beacon against the invading forces of Grimm.

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Atsuya Kusakabe
Summary: Listen up you curse users!! I don't know what the hell happened, but those two there fighting are special grade! Think of them as elephants tap dancing on ants. To be clear, we're the ants...

Name: Aunn Komano
Summary: Aunn Komano is a Komainu living near the Hakurei Shrine. Without its owner's knowledge, she guards the Shrine against intruders.

Name: Barricade (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Barricade was one of Megatron's most loyal soldiers and acted as Create-A-Bot's mentor in the Decepticon campaign of the game.

Name: Barricade (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Dark of the Moon''' | '''The Last Knight'''
Summary: Barricade is apparently a complicated robot. He's considered "fractious" even by Decepticon standards, yet is willing to give Starscream the benefit of the doubt and follow where he leads, at least for the time being. Though not totally dedicated to the service of the Decepticons' current leader, he is much more cautious and reserved about expressing mutinous dissent than say most. He believes that Starscream is vital in their search for Megatron and the AllSpark. In many ways this makes him Starscream's closest ally in the naturally combative Decepticon ranks. Then again, it's been said that he likes to trick people into trusting him, just so he can see their reactions when they find out just how much of a bad idea it was. As such, he has disguised himself as an Earth police car in an attempt to fool the humans around him.

Name: Bartholomew Oobleck
Summary: Doctor Bartholomew Oobleck is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, he is first seen in "Jaunedice, Pt.2" teaching history to the students, specifically teaching about the war between the humans and the Faunus which took place a few generations before the start of the series. He is also shown to be more of an intellectual than a fighter through his actions on the battlefield in "Search and Destroy", but he still wields a weapon, which takes the form of his thermos, shown in the episode "Mountain Glenn"

Name: Beringel
Summary: Beringels are Creatures of Grimm first seen in the "Volume 4 Character Short" that resemble large gorillas.

Name: Bertilak Celadon
Summary: Bertilak Celadon is a character from RWBY: After the Fall. He is a veteran Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy that was active in Vacuo. He serves as one of the main antagonists of RWBY: After the Fall alongside his partner Carmine Esclados.

Name: Big Boss
Summary: Ahab: Who are you...? Ishmael: Who am I? You're talking to yourself.

Name: Blackout (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Blackout is a Cybertronian appearing in the 2007 Transformers DS Games, being an antagonist in Autobots and a playable character in Decepticons. Throughout the story Blackout appears in multiple levels serving the Decepticon forces.

Name: Blake Belladonna
Summary: Blake Belladonna is one of the main characters and the third character introduced in RWBY. A young woman with long black hair, amber-colored eyes and a black ribbon resembling animal ears on her head, she wields the Gambol Shroud, a katana with a sharpened sheath that has a pistol in the hilt attached to a long ribbon which she uses in the style of kusarigama. In battle, her Semblance allows her to create a shadow of herself, an empty copy that distracts or takes hits from enemies for her while she moves in a different direction. Blake has a quiet nature and a love for books. She is a Faunus (a humanoid race with animal-like features) and a former member of the White Fang, a social rights advocacy group turned extremist paramilitary organization. However, she left in disgust of their violence and joined Beacon Academy to become a Huntress. Blake keeps her Faunus identity a secret by concealing her cat ears because she feels that she is not ready for the attention it would give her if the secret got out and doesn't want to face the discrimination other Faunus receive from humanity.

Name: Brawl (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Brawl is a formidable member of the Decepticons, being a relatively high ranking member of the group, Brawl is a warrior at heart, living to destroy Autobot forces. However Brawl has not been shown as a tactician by any means, often making rash decisions, and taking on others without thinking.

Name: Bugs Bunny
Summary: Bugs Bunny is an animated cartoon character, the iconic mascot of Warner Brothers and the primary protagonist throughout much of the Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies series of animated short films.

Name: Bumblebee (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Bumblebee arrived in Tranquility to meet up with Create-A-Bot, and after a short discussion created from radio sound clips, instructed Create-a-Bot to scan a number of vehicles, the last of which was a Decepticon. After a short battle, Bumblebee then used Create-a-Bot's mad h4x0r skills to break into the internet and find the location of Archibald Witwicky's glasses, which turned out to be conveniently in Tranquility.

Name: Bumblebee (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Revenge of the Fallen''' | '''Dark of the Moon''' | '''Age of Extinction to The Last Knight'''
Summary: Bumblebee is an Autobot Scout and one of Optimus Prime's most trusted lieutenants. Although he is not the strongest or most powerful of the Autobots, Bumblebee more than makes up for this with a bottomless well of luck, determination, and bravery. He would gladly give his life to protect others and stop the Decepticons.

Name: Buzz Lightyear (Cartoon)
Summary: Buzz Lightyear is the deuteragonist of the Disney/Pixar Toy Story movies and the titular protagonist of his own television series. He also appears in both the Toy Story Toons and Toy Story Treats shorts. His often repeated catchphrase is: "To infinity and beyond!" He also returns as a supporting character in Toy Story of Terror! and Toy Story That Time Forgot.

Name: Cammy White
Summary: Cammy White, also known by the codename Killer Bee, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Super Street Fighter II. She was once a deadly assassin working for Shadaloo before breaking free and becoming an MI6 operative for the British government.

Name: Captain Grime
Summary: Captain Grime was the ruthless commander of the Toad Army and superior of lieutenant Sasha Waybright, until his attempt to execute Hopadiah Plantar for treason lead to the first Toad Tower's destruction. After this, he became a fugitive along with his close circle, plotting a coup against the Newtopian throne. While initially very stern with his subordinates, Sasha's influence helped him to show them genuine respect, leading to improvement in their morale and performance.

Name: Cardin Winchester
Summary: Cardin Winchester is an attendee of Beacon Academy, and the leader of Team CRDL. His weapon of choice is The Executioner, a large, black mace.

Name: Chen
Summary: Chen is a Bakeneko youkai and the shikigami of Ran Yakumo. Unlike Ran, as she doesn't spend much time with her master, she is usually quite weak.

Name: Choso
Key: '''Shibuya Incident Arc/Itadori's Extermination Arc''' | '''The Culling Game Arc'''
Summary: Choso (脹ちょう相そう, Chōsō?) is the "older brother" of Itadori and his 9 other brothers siblings who were once just Cursed Womb. Choso is a "person" who is mainly concerned about his brothers, worrying about being a good example and making sure that his brothers do not make the mistakes that he made.

Name: Cinder Fall
Summary: Cinder Fall is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. She is a member of Salem's Inner Circle as well as the leader of her own faction, which includes Roman Torchwick, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black. Cinder is imperious and cunning, with a touch of cruelty. Usually, she maintains a calm and collected demeanor and is willing to take over a fight if necessary. She is also ambitious and demanding, doesn't seem to tolerate failure, and dislikes when she is disobeyed, reprimanding Emerald and Mercury when they failed to obey her orders to keep their hands clean. She is shown to be an excellent strategist as well, often planning ahead to keep her goals in reach while keeping her accomplices on a strict "need to know" basis. Following the Battle of Beacon, Cinder is the current Fall Maiden.

Name: Cirno
Summary: Cirno (チルノ) is an ice fairy who first appeared on the second stage of Embodiment of Scarlet Devil. As a fairy, she is exceptionally strong for her kind, matching the power of some weak youkai. However, compared to most of Gensokyo's residents, she's quite weak. Her personality is childish and she is sometimes considered stupid.

Name: Coco Adel
Summary: Coco Adel is the leader of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. She is first seen in "Field Trip", after returning from fighting the Grimm. Coco appears to be very confident; her self-assurance is expressed in the very way she struts down the battlefield. Her experience with Grimm has been consistent enough that their appearance no longer fazes her. She is confident enough in her team that she holds Velvet Scarlatina back from combat when she tries to unleash her weapon. Given her attire and her reaction to the Grimm's destruction of her "favorite clothing store", fashion seems to be strongly integrated into her personality. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Creeper (Minecraft)
Summary: The Creeper is one of the primary and most iconic Minecraft monsters. Unlike others of their kind, Creepers cannot attack directly, instead having to blow themselves up to damage enemies.

Name: Dagon (Jujutsu Kaisen)
Summary: Dagon (陀だ艮ごん, Dagon?) is an antagonist in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was an unregistered special grade cursed spirit aligned with Mahito, Jogo, and Hanami. Dagon was born from the fear of water-based natural disasters and existed as a cursed womb until he evolved during the Shibuya Incident.

Name: Daiyousei
Summary: Daiyousei is a fairy who loiters around the Misty Lake, located near the Scarlet Devil Mansion. Aside from her appearing as the second stage midboss in Embodiment of Scarlet Devil, and being similar in behavior to other fairies, not much is not known about her.

Name: Danjuro Tobita (Gentle Criminal)
Summary: Danjuro Tobita (飛田 弾柔郎 Tobita Danjūrō), better known as Gentle Criminal (ジェントル・クリミナル Jentoru Kuriminaru), is a small-time villain who has his assistant La Brava film his numerous petty crimes in order to raise awareness of the flaws in hero society. Once an aspiring hero-in-training with failing grades, his life turned upside down when he used his Quirk to try and save someone in the middle of a hero operation, inadvertently causing the person serious injury and his expulsion from school as well as being disowned by his parents.

Name: Death Stalker
Summary: Death Stalkers are large scorpion-like Creatures of Grimm first encountered in "The Emerald Forest, Pt.2".

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Dogora (Showa)
Summary: Dogora (ドゴラ) is a mutant space cell kaiju that first appeared in the 1964 Toho film, Dogora.

Name: Dr. Merlot
Summary: Dr. Merlot is the main antagonist of RWBY: Grimm Eclipse.

Name: Drones (2007 DS Game)
Summary: While on Earth, Create-A-Bot and his comrades would face off many drones or fodder enemies from the opposing faction. Some even work alongside Sector 7

Name: Eika Ebisu
Summary: Eika Ebisu is the spirit of a stillborn child, and a god of fortune, inhabiting the riverbank of the Sanzu River. Here, she acts as the leader of other stillborn children, where she often organize stone stacking contests.

Name: Emerald Sustrai
Summary: Emerald Sustrai is a former associate of Cinder Fall and former partner of Mercury Black. While she worked with Cinder, she initially appeared to be affable and disarmingly friendly, however, this belies a darker side of her character. On the whole, she seemed to be genuinely outgoing and quick-witted, if a little short-fused. She had a tendency to maintain a pretense of friendliness amongst people in order to gain their trust, and showed a strong sense of loyalty, specifically to Cinder, whom she appeared incredibly eager to please. However, Emerald eventually had a change of heart and joined Ruby and her friends after learning from Ozpin about Salem's true goals.

Name: End City
Summary: The End Cities are the only inhabited places in the End, an alternate dimension to the Overworld. They are occupied by the Endermen, a mysterious alien kind who travels to the other dimensions at night and comes back when day breaks. They appear to worship a being of immense power; the Ender Dragon.

Name: Eso
Summary: Eso (壊え相そう, Esō?) is a Cursed Womb: Death Painting and the middle brother of Choso and Kechizu. He and Kechizu serve as the primary antagonists of the Death Painting Arc.

Name: Evil Dragon (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Evil Dragon was a dragon that was sealed long ago into the local Inari Shrine. It recently tricked Marisa into unsealing it.

Name: Evoker
Summary: The Evoker is a kind of Illager that lives in Woodland Mansions. They attack intruders using a variety of magic spells.

Name: Finger Bearer
Summary: Finger Bearers (指ゆびの寄き主しゅ, Yubi no Kishu?) are a type of Cursed Spirit that have become a special grade after devouring one of Sukuna's fingers. Finger Bearers begin as Cursed Wombs where they gestate until birth. During this period they can be seen by non-sorcerers. Once born they create an Incomplete Domain from purely Cursed Energy, a precursor to a Domain Expansion, that warps the dimensions of its birthplace.

Name: Flynt Coal
Summary: Flynt Coal is a student at Atlas Academy and the leader of Team FNKI.

Name: Fortune (Metal Gear)
Summary: Fortune is a previous member of Dead Cell and antagonist/protagonist of Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty.

Name: Fox (Minecraft)
Summary: Foxes are nocturnal neutral mobs that spawn commonly in taiga and snowy taiga biomes.

Name: Fox Alistair
Summary: Fox Alistair is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Fox is sarcastic and laid back in personality. Though he is reserved in new social situations, he is lively in familiar ones to the point where he considers himself the comedic relief of Team CFVY. He is comfortable enough on the subject of his own blindness to make jokes about it himself. Fox thinks of himself as a prankster; he has a tendency to make practical jokes and poke fun of his friends. He holds himself in high esteem and directs himself with confidence, having no qualms being blunt about people if need be. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Fumihiko Takaba
Summary: Fumihiko Takaba (髙たか羽ば 史彦ふみひこ, Takaba Fumihiko?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a comedian before awakening his cursed technique during the culling games and becoming one of the strongest competitors and his role was vital in defeating the Special Grade past sorcerer Kenjaku.

Name: G (Street Fighter)
Summary: G is a playable character introduced in Street Fighter V. G's identity is unknown for the most part, as very little details are provided, and even the few available are mostly obscure and unclear. He just appeared one day in the middle of the street, challenging the best fighters of the world while streaming himself on Footube, which slowly granted him popularity. He claims to be the president or the world (and even of the universe, at times), and to be one with the Earth itself and with every citizen of the planet, reason why he always treats every person as if they had a strong and familiar connection. Although it can't be proven, his words might be somewhat true, as his powers and physical traits show a strong relation with the planet, and his energy was stated by Oro to be "one with nature".

Name: Gedomaru
Summary: Gedomaru is a Shikigami of the Ketsuno Clan. She was given to Gintoki Sakata of the Yorozuya as a precaution, during the Exorcist Chapter, by Ketsuno Ana, who had requested the Yorozuya's assistance.

Name: General Yunnan
Summary: General Yunnan is a general of the Newtopian army sent to hunt down Captain Grime for military desertion, but fails after being defeated. However, she later assists in stopping him and Sasha during the toad invasion of Newtopia. Following the reveal of King Andrias' true goals, she tries to defect but is placed under a mind control collar, until Anne and Sasha free her, at which point she helps fight against her former king's invasion of Earth.

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Gideon Graves
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, 8-B with sword, Varies with subspace manipulation and The Glow

Name: Gill
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheMarkOfMyDignityShallScarThyDNA.ogg

Name: Gillian Asturias
Summary: Gillian Asturias is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a former Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, ruling as a queen and leader of The Crown.

Name: Gintoki Sakata
Key: '''Beginning of the series''' | '''Yoshiwara in Flames Arc and onwards''' | '''Diviner Arc to End of the Series'''
Summary: Sakata Gintoki (坂田 銀時, Sakata Gintoki) is the founder and president of the Yorozuya Gin-Chan, as well as a highly skilled samurai, having fought in the Joui War in the past. During the war, he became known as the White Demon (白悪魔, Shiroyasha) due to his powerful swordplay and demonic white appearance. Now, he is in an era where the samurai are no longer needed. To add to his troubles, oppressive aliens have moved in to invade. Gintoki lives with Kagura and Shinpachi, taking on odd jobs to make the world a better place... and to pay their rent.

Name: Godzilla (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ) is a daikaiju created by Toho that appears in Godzilla the Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle.
ID: Godzilla (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8-B

Name: Gray Fox
Summary: Gray Fox, real name Frank Jaeger, was a mercenary and former agent of U.S. Special Forces Unit FOXHOUND. Originally a child soldier, Jaeger was the only operative in FOXHOUND to achieve the codename "Fox," the unit's highest commendation and was decorated five times.

Name: Great Philosopher
Summary: Great Philosopher (大哲人, Dai Tetsujin) is an A-Class Rank 13 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Green (RWBY)
Summary: Green is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. He is a Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy and serves as an unwilling enforcer for the Crown.

Name: Griffon (RWBY)
Summary: Griffons are a species of Grimm with both feline and avian traits. They appeared en masse just prior to the Fall of Beacon, having responded to the distress created by the machinations of Cinder Fall.

Name: Gyro Gearloose
Summary: Gyro Gearloose is a Disney character featured in the 1987-1990 Disney cartoon, Ducktales, and in many other types of media. He is Duckburg's most famous inventor, although some of his inventions don't always work out like he intends them to. He's associated with Scrooge McDuck, Donald Duck, and many others.

Name: Hanami
Summary: Hanami (花はな御み, Hanami?) is an unregistered special grade Cursed Spirit and an antagonist in Jujutsu Kaisen. They wish to kill humans to create a cleaner world controlled by Cursed Spirits. They are one of the Disaster Curses, who symbolizes humanity's collective fear of natural disasters.

Name: Hei Xiong
Summary: Hei Xiong, more commonly known by his nickname Junior, is the owner, or at least manager, of a club in Vale and is in charge of several henchmen, including Melanie and Miltiades Malachite. He was introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer, as its main antagonist. He makes his first proper appearance in the series in "Painting the Town...", giving what information he knows about Roman Torchwick to Yang Xiao Long and Neptune Vasilias.

Name: Hiromi Higuruma
Summary: Hiromi Higuruma (日ひ車ぐるま 寛ひろ見み, Higuruma Hiromi?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a defense attorney who often took on impossibly difficult cases in order to protect the wrongfully accused. Having since given up on the justice system completely, Hiromi participated in the Culling Game as one of the top players. He initially serves as an antagonist of the Culling Game Arc before battling Yuji Itadori and choosing to cooperate after he reminded him of his roots. He used his one hundred to add a rule to the Culling Game allowing the transfer of points between players as per Yuji's request and departed, planning to turn himself in for the murder of the judge and prosecutor at his last trial once the Culling Game's barriers were lifted.

Name: Ice King (Fortnite)
Summary: The Ice King is a character from the game Fortnite. The ruler of Polar Peak and the wielder of the legendary Infinity Blade, he wreaked havoc during Fortnite's seventh season by freezing the entire island over in minutes and summoning a legion of Ice Fiends across the map. The Ice King was formerly unlockable during Season 7 by getting to Tier 100 on the Battle Pass but has since been unavailable.

Name: Ilia Amitola
Summary: Ilia Amitola is a supporting character appearing primarily in Volumes 4-5 of RWBY. She is a young chameleon Faunus with tan skin, light gray eyes, and brown hair tied up in a ponytail which curls up at the end— similarly to a chameleon's tail. Ilia grew up in Mantle, though her parents, who worked in the mines, wanted something better for their daughter. Thus, they enrolled her in an Atlas program and told her to disguise her Faunus heritage so she would fit in with the higher society. Managing to actually make some friends and blend in quite well, everything was going well until reports came in that the mines had suffered a cave-in which resulted in the deaths of her parents. Her friends simply laughed at the news, causing Ilia to uncontrollably change color and reveal her secret. Suddenly her so-called friends were afraid of her, and she assaulted them in retaliation.

Name: Ironhide (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Ironhide arrived sometime after Bumblebee to assist in finding the Allspark. Advising Create-A-Bot, Ironhide acted as something of an older mentor figure to him as he learned the ropes.

Name: Isamu (Child Emperor)
Summary: Child Emperor (童帝, Dōtei) is the S-Class Rank 5 hero for the Hero Association. So far, he is the youngest hero in the Hero Association. He has his own laboratory in Y-City.

Name: Jaune Arc
Summary: Jaune Arc is the leader of Team JNPR who wields a sword and shield named Crocea Mors, an heirloom formerly belonging to his great-great-grandfather. He comes from a long line of esteemed Hunters and feels pressured to live up to their reputations. Because of his family line, Jaune is obsessed with being a hero. However, he was never formally trained like the rest of his family, which causes him to lack self-esteem and assign a lot of importance to his image as a fighter. He also does not seem to be very proud of having a weapon given to him, rather than earning or crafting it on his own, referring to his weapon as a simple "hand-me-down" instead of a "family heirloom." However, Jaune has demonstrated capable leadership skills and good tactical judgment. He also possesses a strong Aura which allows him to heal himself, although he cannot yet control this ability.

Name: Jax Asturias
Summary: Jax Asturias is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn and is the main antagonist of the novel. He is a former Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy who was deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, ruling as a king and leader of The Crown.

Name: Jazz (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Much like his Movie counterpart, First Lieutenant Jazz is a good natured Autobot who is always capable of taking things in his stride. In the games, Jazz helps hack into Sector Sevens systems to locate the Allspark. He also contended with Blackout, eventually overpowering him. Jazz is seen many times in the game series, but is eventually killed by Megatron.

Name: Jinichi Zenin
Summary: Jinichi Zenin (禪院ぜんいん 甚壱じんいち, Zen'in Jin'ichi?) is a minor antagonist in Jujutsu Kaisen, belonging to the powerful Zenin Clan and a member of its elite unit of jujutsu sorcerers, the Hei. He's focused on safeguarding the clan's riches and authority, even if it requires disregarding certain traditions. When Megumi is selected to lead, he swiftly teams up with others to oppose it, driven by his desire to retain control and influence.

Name: Jiro Awasaka
Summary: Jiro Awasaka is a Curse User who used to torture and kill people to understand the human body better. After Gojo came into the world he went into hiding. He was recruited by Pseudo-Geto and Uraume to participate in the Shibuya incident to defend a set of commissioned curtains and ended up losing to Yuji and Megumi.

Name: Joe Sparrow
Summary: Joe Sparrow is a character from Amphibia.

Name: Jogo
Summary: Jogo (漏じょう瑚ご, Jōgo?) is a character in Jujutsu Kaisen. He is a Cursed Spirit and one of the main antagonists of the series. Jogo has immense pride as a Cursed Spirit and a passionate hatred for humans. He believes that Curses are the actual humans as they represent pure truths of life, such as hatred, while normal humans fake many positive emotions and should be exterminated.

Name: Jumping Spider (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Jumping Spider (ハエトリノ, Haetorino) was a human who didn't remove a spider that went into his ear. This act, or lack of, caused him to turn into a monster.

Name: Junpei Yoshino
Summary: Junpei Yoshino (吉よし野の順じゅん平ぺい, Yoshino Junpei?) is a supporting character in the Vs. Mahito Arc of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a high school student in Satozakura High School who befriended Yuji Itadori, but turned into a curse user after meeting Mahito.

Name: Juri Han
Summary: Juri Han (ハン・ジュリ Han Juri, Hangul: 한주리, Hanja: 韓蛛俐) is a character in the Street Fighter series. She makes her debut in Super Street Fighter IV, where she is a main character in the storyline. She is 25 years old (as of Super Street Fighter IV) and is described as a brutal and sadistic member of S.I.N. who relishes fighting and inflicting pain upon her foes.

Name: Kagerou Imaizumi
Summary: Kagerou Imaizumi is a werewolf from the Bamboo Forest of the Lost. Usually quite docile, the recent events made her much more aggressive.

Name: Kagura (Gintama)
Summary: Kagura (神楽) is a member of the Yorozuya and the main female protagonist of Gintama. She is a member of the Yato Tribe and the daughter of Umibouzu. Kamui, one of the main antagonists of the series, is also her older brother.

Name: Kamotarou Itou
Summary: Kamotarou Itou (伊東 鴨太郎, Itou Kamotarou) was an advisor to the Shinsengumi who appeared during the Shinsengumi Mutiny arc as the main antagonist until his betrayal by Bansai Kawakami. He made an agreement with Shinsuke Takasugi and aimed to become the head of Shinsengumi.

Name: Ken Masters
Summary: Ken (ケン or 拳 "Fist"), also known by his full name, Ken Masters (ケン・マスターズ Ken Masutāzu), is a video game character created by Capcom. He is one of the main protagonists of the Street Fighter series. Ken is also stated to be the second most popular character in the series, coming second to his best friend Ryu. Like Ryu, Ken's goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strive to become stronger but holds more restraint due to not wanting to jeopardize his family life.

Name: Kento Nanami
Summary: I won't praise or insult you. I am here to identify the truth and uphold the law.

Name: King Ghidorah (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: King Ghidorah (キングギドラ, Kingu Gidora?), is a giant three-headed dragon daikaiju created by Toho in 2021 for Godzilla the Ride: Large Monster Summit Battle.
ID: King Ghidorah (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8-B

Name: King Taijitu
Summary: King Taijitu are large serpentine Creatures of Grimm. The first one to appear in the series is encountered by Lie Ren in the episode "The Emerald Forest".

Name: Kisume
Summary: Kisume is a minor character in Subterranean Animism. She appears as a minor enemy who attacks the protagonist.

Name: Koakuma
Summary: Koakuma is a small devil that serves Patchouli Knowledge. Almost nothing is known about her.

Name: Kuma
Summary: Kuma (クマ; literally meaning "Bear") is the name of two characters within the Tekken series, both of which were bears and bodyguards to Heihachi Mishima. Kuma II is the son of the original Kuma, who died of old age sometime after the second King of Iron Fist Tournament.

Name: Kurumu Kurono
Summary: Kurumu is a Succubus and a third-year student at Yōkai Academy. Kurumu initially planned to enslave all the boys at the academy, until she met Tsukune and Moka and the following incident, she became convinced that Tsukune was her "fateful mate", and planned to win his heart without the use of her powers. Kurumu later becomes one of the most prominent supporting characters and proactively involved in the adventures.

Name: Kuyo
Summary: Tier 9-A | 8-C | At least 8-B

Name: Kyouko Kasodani
Summary: Kyouko Kasodani is one of the last Yamabiko of Gensokyo. Due to her species' reliance on people's belief about mountain echoes, they have come near extinction even in Gensokyo due to the growing scientific knowledge of the true reasons behind the echoes created by mountains.

Name: Lancer (RWBY)
Summary: Lancers are large hornet-like Creatures of Grimm. There are two types: a smaller, more common version called a Warrior Drone and a larger variation known as a Queen Lancer.

Name: Layla Prismriver
Summary: Layla is the fourth and youngest daughter of the Prismriver family. Orphaned after a mishap with her father, each of the 4 daughters went on their path. Only Layla stayed, not willing to leave the mansion that had held much of her memories. Using her powers, she created three poltergeists that resembled her three older sisters, and afterwards, disappeared, alongside the mansion and her three creations.

Name: Letty Whiterock
Summary: Letty Whiterock (レティ・ホワイトロック) is a seasonal youkai who's only seen during winter. She seems fittingly cold towards most of the humans she meets and is feared by humans as she is known to freeze them.

Name: Lie Ren
Summary: Lie Ren, more commonly referred to as Ren, is a student at Beacon Academy and a member of Team JNPR. His weapon of choice is a pair of green automatic pistols which have blades attached to them, named StormFlower. He and Nora are long-time friends, though he is the exact opposite of her, as he is mostly quiet, mellow and mature.

Name: Lily White
Summary: Lily White is a fairy representing spring. Her favorite hobby seems to be celebrating and announcing Spring.

Name: Luna Child
Summary: Luna Child (ルナチャイルド) is a fairy and one of the members of the Three Fairies of Light, composed of her, Sunny Milk, and Star Sapphire.

Name: Lunar Capital
Key: '''Basic Infantry | Higher Technology and High Ranking Members | Gods'''
Summary: The Lunar Capital (月の都, Tsuki no Miyako) is an extremely powerful and advanced civilization on the Moon of the Touhou Project universe. They used to be humans living on Earth. However, their leader, Lord Tsukuyomi, wanted him and his kind to escape the impurity of Earth. They did so by colonizing the moon, an otherwise untouched and pure land, where they could live a completely pure life.

Name: Lunasa Prismriver
Summary: Lunasa Prismriver (ルナサ・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lyrica and Merlin, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the violin. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Lunasa.

Name: Lyrica Prismriver
Summary: Lyrica Prismriver (リリカ・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lunasa and Merlin, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the keyboard. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Lyrica.

Name: M. Bison
Key: '''Base''' | '''Empowered by the Psycho Drive''' | '''Empowered by the Black Moons''' | '''Street Fighter VI'''
Summary: For unknown reasons, the child who grew up to be M. Bison (Vega in Japan) murdered his parents in cold blood before he was adopted by a tribe of Romani who taught him the art of Soul Power, an ancient art that allows the user to manipulate one's soul. Bison quickly mastered Soul Power and used it to expel all of the good and humanity out of him, turning him into an egotistical psychopath. He then evolved Soul Power into Psycho Power, took on the title M. Bison, and organized a group of mercenaries to help him succeed in global conquest.

Name: Magma Cube
Summary: The Magma Cube is a monster found in the Nether. It is a sentient cube of Magma, capable of duplicating.

Name: Mahito
Summary: Mahito (真ま人ひと?) is the secondary antagonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is a Cursed Spirit allied with Suguru Geto, Jogo, Hanami, and several others. Their ultimate goal is eradicating humanity and ultimately replacing the population with Cursed Spirits.

Name: Maki Zenin
Summary: nan

Name: Marcy Wu
Summary: Marcy Wu: The day we left, your birthday, they told me my dad got a new job out of state. They're making me move away, they were gonna tear us apart! Anne Boonchuy: Marcy... Marcy Wu: I... I found the box. I had no idea it would actually work, but it did. It sent us to a place where we'd never have to grow apart, where the three of us could friends forever together! Anne Boonchuy: How could you?! I've been missing my parents, my life! Marcy Wu: But look at how much fun we've had. Look at how much you've both grown. Look at Sprig. I gave you this, I gave you everything! I just didn't want to be alone.

Name: Mechamaru
Summary: The fact that a doll like you and not a human like me gets to live so carefree in the sun really pisses me off!

Name: Medicine Melancholy
Summary: Medicine Melancholy (メディスン・メランコリー) is a young doll youkai that lives on Nameless Hill surrounded by poisonous lily-of-the-valley flowers.

Name: Megatron (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Megatron is the leader of the decepticons. He left cybertron to chase after the Allspark, only to end up frozen on Earth. Depending on the version of the game, he would either face an Allspark amped Stascream, or he himself would be amped by the power of the Allspark.

Name: Megumi Fushiguro
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: Megumi Fushiguro (伏ふし黒ぐろ 恵めぐみ, Fushiguro Megumi?) is the deuteragonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Born into the Zenin clan, a prestigious family of jujutsu sorcerers, Megumi inherits the unique Ten Shadows Technique, which allows him to summon and control various shikigami using his cursed energy.

Name: Mei Mei
Summary: Mei Mei (冥冥めいめい?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. She is a Grade 1 Jujutsu sorcerer who works independently and only in exchange for money. She is also the older sister of Ui Ui and was a senpai of Satoru Gojo and Suguru Geto during their time at Jujutsu High.

Name: Melanie Malachite
Summary: Melanie Malachite is a character introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer. She and her twin sister Miltiades Malachite are seen working for Hei Xiong when they fight Yang Xiao Long. Melanie's weapons of choice are her heels.

Name: Mercury Black
Summary: Mercury Black is an antagonist in RWBY.

Name: Merlin Prismriver
Summary: Merlin Prismriver (メルラン・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lunasa and Lyrica, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the trumpet. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Merlin.

Name: Metal Gear RAY
Summary: A Metal Gear unit designed by the United States Navy for the purpose of destroying REX imitators before being stolen and redesigned by the Patriots, along with a whole bunch of other people who somehow got their hands on models. Raiden in his post-MSG4 years later fought a modified version of RAY.

Name: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus
Summary: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus is a Metal Gear featured in Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain. Created by Huey Emmerich and funded by the Soviet Union, Sahelanthropus was in actuality a project overseen by XOF, the covert strike force and at-the-time usurper of the shadow government known as The Patriots. Encountered by Venom Snake several times in Afghanistan, he managed to best the machine multiple times, eventually capturing it after the death of Skull Face, the leader of XOF. Snake kept it at Mother Base for some time, until it was stolen by Eli with the help of the Third Child, who took it to Central Africa, where he, the remnants of XOF and Venom Snake with his Diamond Dogs private military company, fought to reclaim the weapon. Snake eventually won the day, but Sahelanthropus was destroyed in battle.

Name: Midas (Fortnite)
Summary: Midas is a Legendary skin and main antagonist of Fortnite Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the leader of Ghost and a double agent for Shadow. He is based on the Greek mythology, King Midas. At the end of Chapter 2 Season 2, he becomes Cyclo, the Defiant to the Storm. At the start of Chapter 2 Season 3, he gets attacked by a shark and survived. Around Chapter 2 Season 4, he becomes Shadow Midas.

Name: Miltiades Malachite
Summary: Miltiades "Miltia" Malachite is a character introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer. She and her twin sister, Melanie Malachite, are seen working for Hei Xiong at his club, where they fight Yang Xiao Long. Miltia's weapons of choice are her claws.

Name: Ministry of Right and Wrong
Summary: The Ministry of Right and Wrong is the organization that manages the entire system regarding Souls and the afterlife in the Touhou Project series. Created in response to humanity's growing numbers, it is mainly composed of the many judges who deal with the deceased and of the leaders of Heaven, the Netherworld and the many hells.

Name: Minoriko Aki
Summary: Minoriko Aki is one of the two goddesses of autumn. Her job is to make harvest fruitful by helping farmers with their plantations.

Name: Mizore Shirayuki
Summary: Mizore was introduced as an antagonist to Tsukune and Moka. However, she eventually became a friend and an ally. She later fell in love with Tsukune, and even wanted to marry him. She was rescued from a forced marriage by him. She participated in the final battle against Fairy Tale.

Name: Mystia Lorelei
Summary: Mystia Lorelei (ミスティア・ローレライ) is an egocentric and outgoing night sparrow who roams the Youkai Trail in search of humans to frighten. She also manages a grilled lamprey stand, and is part of a punk rock band with Kyouko Kasodani named Choujuu Gigaku.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Naobito Zenin
Summary: Naobito Zenin (禪ぜん院いん 直なお毘び人と, Zen'in Naobito?) is the 26th head of the Zen'in clan, renowned for being the fastest Jujutsu Sorcerer, besides Gojo, thanks to his Cursed Technique.

Name: Naoya Zenin
Summary: Naoya Zenin (禪院ぜんいん 直なお哉や, Zen'in Naoya?) is an antagonist in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was the youngest son of Naobito Zenin and believed himself to be the true heir of the Zenin Family. Naoya was also the head of the clan's elite unit of jujutsu sorcerers, the Hei.

Name: Narumi Yatadera
Summary: Narumi Yatadera is a former Jizo statue who became a magician from the Forest of Magic's influence. As she was a statue that gained life on it's own, she's a bit like a golem. She serves as the Stage 4 boss of Hidden Star in Four Seasons.

Name: Nazrin
Summary: Nazrin (ナズーリン) is a mouse youkai who's a skilled dowser and the leader of a great number of mice. As the leader of many mice, she often employs them to search for things for her; though if she were to ask them to find food, it would most likely be gone by the time they returned.

Name: Nemuno Sakata
Summary: Nemuno Sakata is a Yamanba living in the Youkai mountain. She dwells mostly alone there, ocasionally kidnapping children and raising them as a Yamanba.

Name: Neon Katt
Summary: Neon Katt is a member of Team FNKI, of Atlas Academy. She participated in the Vytal Festival tournament, fighting against Yang Xiao Long and Weiss Schnee during the doubles round in the episode "Never Miss a Beat".

Name: Neopolitan
Summary: Neopolitan, better known as Neo, is a major antagonist in RWBY and the former partner of Roman Torchwick.

Name: Neptune Vasilias
Summary: Neptune Vasilias is a character in RWBY and a member of Team SSSN.

Name: Nevermore (RWBY)
Summary: Nevermores are large avian Creatures of Grimm first encountered during the Beacon Academy Initiation in RWBY Volume 1.

Name: Nick Ramos (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Nizo Okada
Summary: Nizo Okada (岡田 似蔵, Okada Nizou), also known as Nizo the Butcher, or Manslayer Nizo (Hito Kiri Nizou) was a blind assassin and a master of Iai jutsu, which are techniques for drawing a sword. He was a member of the Kiheitai, an extremist Joui faction bent on causing world destruction, and would become fused with the Benizakura bio-mechanical sword, which would ultimately take over his body completely and lead to his defeat. He is the main antagonist of the Infant Strife Arc and Benizakura Arc.

Name: Nobara Kugisaki
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: I love the me that dresses up and looks beautiful! I love the me that's strong! I'm Nobara Kugisaki!

Name: Nora Valkyrie
Summary: Nora Valkyrie is a Huntress-in-Training at Beacon Academy. Her weapon is Magnhild, a grenade launcher that can be converted into a war hammer. Nora is a happy-go-lucky, bubbly, and cheerful young girl who displays boundless enthusiasm and never fails to let it show. Her excitable nature makes her rather hyperactive and hasty. Even in combat, Nora retains her joyful personality, but she is seen to stay focused when actually fighting. Despite her generally cute personality, Nora does seem to have a love of battle, much like Ruby. She may be a little extreme when it comes to dealing with issues, as her suggested solution to help Jaune Arc with Cardin Winchester's bullying was breaking Cardin's legs. As all Non-Grimm, living creatures do, she has an Aura that can help her in many situations and her Semblance can turn the tide of battle to her favor.

Name: Noritoshi Kamo
Summary: If I am no longer needed, then let me set my life ablaze, so that at the very least, my companions' lives will burn brightly on my ashes.

Name: Nuckelavee (RWBY)
Summary: The Nuckelavee was a large, horse-like Creature of Grimm that first appeared in "Kuroyuri". It served as the main antagonist of RWBY Volume 4.

Name: Ogi Zenin
Summary: Ogi Zenin (禪ぜん院いん扇おうぎ, Zen'in Ōgi?) is the father of Maki and Mai as well as the brother of Naobito. He is mostly unknown for the majority of the series and considered inferior to Naobito in regards to the quality of his children as jujutsu sorcerers.

Name: Optimus Prime (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Optimus helped to advise his warriors in some of their mission to try locate the Allspark. Arriving on Earth, Optimus met up with the other Autobots to give further commands to his troops. During the final battle against Megatron, Megatron set Allspark drones on Prime, but Create-A-Bot, who tailed Prime to the fight sacrificed himself to weaken Megatron. Galvanized by the rookie's sacrifice, Optimus fought Megatron in a final duel. After besting Megatron, Optimus decided the Allspark was worth sacrificing to stop Megatron. Megatron defeated, Optimus commended the dying young Autobot and swore he would always be remembered as a war hero, and sent out an interstellar message to any Autobots living among the stars to join them.

Name: Patchouli Knowledge
Summary: Patchouli Knowledge is a very smart, anemic and asthmatic magician from the Scarlet Devil Mansion. As opposed to the rest of the inhabitants, she is neither an employee or relative of Remilia Scarlet, instead being a close friend whose role is to cause and solve problems. She spends most of her time in the mansion's library reading and writing magic books. It seems that she's capable of very powerful magic of all kinds, using many elements in a single spell, but due to her anemia, asthma and general poor health she's often unable to recite her spells.

Name: Peace Walker
Summary: Peace Walker, also known as Basilisk, was a walking nuclear-armed AI weapon developed by Huey Emmerich and Strangelove. In 1973, CIA Station Chief Hot Coldman commissioned the creation of Peace Walker in order to fulfill his vision of the "perfect nuclear deterrent".

Name: Peely
Summary: Peely is one of many characters in Fortnite. Peely became a robot in Fortnite's Season X called P-1000. In Season 2, Chapter 2, he becomes an agent named, Agent Peely.

Name: Penny Polendina
Summary: Penny Polendina is a character introduced in the episode "The Stray," when she was found lying on the ground after Weiss Schnee crashed into her whilst chasing after Sun Wukong. Penny speaks robotically, behaves erratically, and is overly active in general. All her actions and emotional states were rather extreme and overacted. When Ruby Rose unintentionally made an unconditional offer of friendship, Penny seemed both immensely pleased and somewhat surprised.

Name: Peter Port
Summary: Peter Port is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, he is first seen in "The Badge and The Burden" teaching the Grimm Studies class, with Team RWBY and Jaune Arc from Team JNPR being present in his class. His weapon of choice is Blowhard, a blunderbuss outfitted with the blades of a battle axe.

Name: Phantoms (Touhou Project)
Summary: Phantoms are a kind of spirit in the Touhou Project series. They are the embodiment of the spirits of things, be it plants, humans or otherwise. They are not to be confused with ghosts.

Name: Pyrrha Nikos
Summary: Pyrrha Nikos is a character in RWBY. A famous, level-headed, and highly skilled student at Beacon Academy and a member of Team JNPR, she wields a rifle/javelin/sword combination weapon called Miló and a shield called Akoúo̱. Prior to her tenure at Beacon, she graduated from Sanctum Academy with highest honors and had a record number of wins at the Mistral Regional Tournament. More so, she is seen as a warrior who's seemingly untouchable to the point where she is believed to be "fated for victory".

Name: Quiet
Summary: Quiet was a female assassin during the 1980s. Originally an assassin for XOF, Quiet later defected to Diamond Dogs after being defeated by Venom Snake. Quiet can only breathe and drink through her skin. As a result, she can only wear a minimal amount of clothing due to the parasite-treatment she received as a result of being severely burned while trying to kill Big Boss during a hospital raid. After being defeated by Venom Snake in Afghanistan following a tense sniper duel, Quiet became a prisoner at Mother Base until she was allowed to accompany Venom Snake on missions.

Name: Raiden (Metal Gear)
Key: '''Metal Gear Solid 2''' | '''Metal Gear Solid 4''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Updated Patriots Cyborg Body)''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Custom Cyborg Body)'''
Summary: Vamp: You, too... Immortal? Raiden: No. I just don't fear death.

Name: Ramona Flowers
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, weapons are higher against certain types of people, 8-B with the Power of Love, Varies with Subspace manipulation

Name: Rampage (Michael Bay)
Summary: Rampage is a Decepticon and member of the Constructicons. He aided in Megatron's resurrection and later went to Egypt to aid the Fallen and the rest of the Decepticons. He took Sam's captured parents and used them to try and get the Matrix of Leadership though he was killed by Bumblebee in the process.

Name: Ravage (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ravage is a Decepticon scout and partner of Soundwave. He was sent down to Earth with a group of microcons to steal a shard of the Allspark. Following the completion of the mission, he journeyed to Egypt to aid in the Fallen's plan to harvest Earth's Sun but he was killed by Bumblebee in the process.

Name: Rei'sen
Summary: Rei'sen is a lunar rabbit. Originally she had fled the moon to Earth, but upon being taken back, she was sentenced to becoming the Watatsukis' pet, replacing the original Reisen.

Name: Rikido Sato (Sugarman)
Summary: Rikido Sato (砂藤力道 Satō Rikidō), also known as Sugarman (シュガーマン Shugā Man), is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Ringo
Summary: Ringo (鈴瑚 Ringo) is a moon rabbit, and the stage 2 boss of Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Rinnosuke Morichika
Summary: Rinnosuke Morichika (森近 霖之助, Morichika Rinnosuke), nicknamed Kourin (香霖), is a half-human half-youkai hybrid and using his ability to know the name and purpose of an object, he runs Kourindou, an antique shop specializing in items from the Outside World. He's one of the few male characters depicted in the Touhou Project and is the protagonist of Curiosities of Lotus Asia.

Name: Rodan (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: Rodan (ラドン, Radon?) is a giant pteranodon daikaiju created by Toho that appeared in Godzilla the Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle.
ID: Rodan (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8-B

Name: Roman Torchwick
Summary: Roman Torchwick is a character in the world of RWBY. A master criminal, he orchestrated the robbery of Dust supplies from many stores throughout Vale. He emits charm and speaks calmly even in the middle of an armed robbery. Though he also emits hostility towards people he either hates or dislikes, as seen with Ruby Rose, when he tried to kill her, even ordering the White Fang to shoot her.

Name: Rosa Schwein
Summary: Rosa Schwein is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a former Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, serving as an enforcer for The Crown.

Name: Rose (Street Fighter)
Summary: Rose is a Street Fighter character who makes her first appearance in Street Fighter Alpha. She is a fortune teller from Italy who attacks with Soul Power. She shares a soul with M. Bison and has bested him in battle in the past.

Name: Roy Stallion
Summary: Roy Stallion was a member of Team BRNZ. Along with his team, Roy was a student of Shade Academy from the kingdom of Vacuo. He and his team journeyed to participate in the 40th Vytal Festival combat tournament, hosted by the kingdom of Vale. His team was defeated by Team JNPR of Vale's Beacon Academy in the team round of the tournament.

Name: Ruby Rose
Summary: Ruby Rose is the 15-year old leader of Team RWBY attending Beacon Academy two years early, due to her abilities impressing Professor Ozpin. Trained by her Uncle Qrow, Ruby wields a unique weapon named Crescent Rose, a cross between a scythe and a high-caliber sniper rifle that is able to fold up into itself. Her Semblance is speed, enabling her to run at rates that are too fast for the eye to catch.
