As she is the youngest of the group, she can be a bit childish, naïve, and weapon-obsessed, but displays leadership qualities and an understanding of people that ultimately led her to be chosen as Team RWBY's leader. She was inspired to become a Huntress by the fairy tales her half-sister Yang read her, wanting to become just like the heroes in the stories. She is determined to make the world a better place for others and try to stop the forces that conspire against it.

Name: Rumia
Summary: Rumia (ルーミア) is a youkai with the ability of manipulating the darkness. She is one of the few youkai that doesn't seem to belong to any particular species.

Name: Russel Thrush
Summary: Russel Thrush is a student of Beacon Academy, and a member of Team CRDL. His weapons are a pair of daggers. Although he has not had a substantial speaking role, Russel can be seen as a "school bully", just like his leader Cardin, where he calls Velvet Scarlatina a freak because of her rabbit ears.

Name: Ryomen Sukuna
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Sasha Waybright
Summary: Sasha Waybright was sent to the realm of Amphibia along with her friends after being exposed to the Calamity Box, where she was imprisoned by Captain Grime in the Toad Tower until using her manipulation skills to prove she would be a valuable asset. Thus, she is instated as first lieutenant of Grime's toad army, putting her at odds with Anne and the frogs of Wartwood.

Name: Scarlet David
Summary: Scarlet David is a member of Team SSSN, who made his first appearance in "Extracurricular". Scarlet has red hair that comes down over his right eye, with a complete undercut. There are a number of red markings around his left eye. He wears a green, mulberry, navy color feather earring on his left ear, and has a red military pelisse-like jacket draped over the left side. He also wears a gray bandanna around his neck. On his right hand, he wears a fingerless glove, and on his right biceps, he has a gray band. He wears a white sleeveless shirt and light gray pants. He also wears a pair of long, brown, laced boots. Around his waist, he wears a slightly slanted gray belt.

Name: Scott Pilgrim
Summary: Scott William Pilgrim is the titular protagonist of the Scott Pilgrim media franchise.

Name: Screaming Mantis
Summary: Screaming Mantis was the leader and psychological warfare specialist of the Beauty and the Beast unit. Born in a war torn village in South America, she was separated from her family as a child when her village was burned down, and hid in the basement of a building that she discovered was actually a makeshift torture room. Haunted by the corpses surrounding her and the screams of the tortured villagers, she was left horribly traumatized, and trapped there for weeks, she had no choice but to consume the remains of the victims around her, but only the men, emulating a mantis.

Name: Sea Feilong
Summary: The Sea Feilong is an abnormally large and powerful Grimm that inhabited the waters near Menagerie. It was felled by the combined efforts of Blake Belladonna, Sun Wukong, and the crew of the ship they Huntsmen-in-Training were sailing with.

Name: Seiran
Summary: Seiran (清蘭 Seiran) is a moon rabbit, and the stage 1 boss of Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Sekibanki
Summary: Sekibanki is a rokurokubi who lives in the Human Village, disguised as a human.

Name: Seth (Street Fighter)
Summary: Seth (セス Sesu) is the main antagonist of the Street Fighter IV series and serves as the usual final boss for all characters in the games. He is the CEO of Shadaloo's weapon division, S.I.N., and is one of many genetically engineered replacement bodies for M. Bison.

Name: Shizuha Aki
Summary: Shizuha Aki is one of the two Aki goddesses of Autumn. Her job is to turn leaves red and make them fall from trees, although she does this by physically painting them red.

Name: Solid Snake
Summary: We can tell about other people about--having faith. What we had faith in. What we found important enough to fight for. It's not whether you were right or wrong, but how much faith you were willing to have, that decides the future.

Name: Solidus Snake
Summary: All I want is to be remembered. By other people, by history. The Patriots are trying to protect their power, their own interests, by controlling the digital flow of information. I want my memory, my existence to remain. Unlike an intron of history, I will be remembered as an exon. That will be my legacy, my mark on history. But the Patriots would deny us even that. I will triumph over the Patriots, and liberate us all. And we will become the Sons of Liberty!

Name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''Post-Muscle Tower''' | '''Post-Korin Training''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Post-Chōshinsui''' | '''23rd Budōkai'''
Summary: Son Goku (孫そん悟ご空くう, Son Gokū?) is the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball metaseries.

Name: Soundwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Soundwave, the Decepticon communications officer and one of Megatron's staunchest supporters, doesn't just master the frequencies that carry information across our planet, he revels in them. Stationed high in the upper atmosphere and capable of processing millions of data streams at once, he is fully capable of taking over communications on a planetary scale. Whether he uses this to direct civilization or destroy it remains to be seen.

Name: Star Sapphire (Touhou Project)
Summary: Star Sapphire (スターサファイア) is a fairy and one of the members of the Three Fairies of Light, along with Sunny Milk and Luna Child.

Name: Starscream (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: After the disappearance of Megatron nearly a million years ago, Starscream took over the Decepticons as their high commander. Arriving on Earth, he instructed Create-A-Bot to follow Barricade until he arrived. However, none of the other Decepticons would trust him, and he confided in Create-A-Bot a great number of secrets, including the location of the AllSpark and the identity of the lost Decepticon they were retrieving: Megatron. Starscream reasoned that he hid these things because revealing them would lead to a power struggle, but no one bought it except the naive rookie.

Name: Stinger
Summary: Stinger (スティンガー, Sutingā) is the A-Class Rank 10 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Sun Wukong (RWBY)
Summary: Sun Wukong is a Faunus from the kingdom of Vacuo, who later moved to Mistral and made his first appearance in "The Stray". His weapon is a collapsible staff that separates into two pairs of nunchucks made of guns called Ruyi Bang and Jingu Bang. In his first appearance, Sun is shown to be fun-loving and mischievous, with little regard for the law - stowing away on a ship, thanking the crew for the ride during his escape, throwing a banana peel in a detective's face, and stealing apples. He has a lot of self-confidence, referring to himself as a "great stowaway". He is also a bit of a flirt towards Blake. In conversation, Sun is very laid-back and casual. He is also kind and patient, willing to listen to Blake's story and waiting for her to do so for nearly two days, bearing with her "small talk and weird looks". He is not afraid to give his opinion and has a dislike for those who regard themselves as "holier than thou", or who "use force to get whatever they want", such as the White Fang. Sun also seems to be willing to help others, regardless of whether he is asked or not, even if he barely knows them. This quality is further demonstrated when he readily volunteers to help Team RWBY with their investigation, despite both Blake and Ruby stating their opposition to his involvement.

Name: Sunny Milk
Summary: Sunny Milk is the leader of the Three Fairies of Light, first appearing as one of the protagonists of Eastern and Little Nature Deity and later as one of the antagonists of Fairy Wars.

Name: Takuma Ino
Summary: Takuma Ino (猪い野の 琢たく真ま, Ino Takuma?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Ino is a grade 2 jujutsu sorcerer and a close associate of Kento Nanami who operates out of Tokyo Jujutsu High.

Name: Tasmanian Devil (Looney Tunes)
Summary: Page one: Aardvarks, Ants, Bears, Boars, Cats, Bats, Dogs, Hogs, Elephants, Antelopes, Pheasants, Ferrets, Giraffes, Gazelles, Stoats, Goats, Shoats, Ostriches, Lions, Jackals, Muskrats, Minks, Dingoes, Zebras, Foxes, Boxes, Octopus, Penguins, People, Warthogs, Yaks, Gnus, Newts, Walrus---Wildebeests.

Name: Team RWBY
Summary: Team RWBY (pronounced "Ruby") is a Huntress team of former Beacon Academy students, which is comprised of RWBY's main characters: team leader Ruby Rose, Weiss Schnee, Blake Belladonna, and Yang Xiao Long. Originally unable to even hold a proper conversation together, the team eventually develops a familial bond and grows into a tightly-knit group, willing to risk their futures and even their lives for each other. They have no qualms breaking the rules to do what they believe is right.

Name: Tewi Inaba
Summary: Tewi Inaba is the leader of Gensokyo's rabbit youkai and one of the inhabitants of the hidden mansion of Eientei. She is implied to possibly be the White Hare of Inaba.

Name: The Boss (Metal Gear)
Summary: The Boss, also known as The Joy, The Mother of Special Forces, Mercury Lady and Voyevoda (Russian: Воевода, "Warlord"), was a renowned American female soldier, founder and leader of the Cobra Unit, the biological mother of Ocelot, and mentor and mother figure to Naked Snake. In June 1944, during World War II, she led the Cobra Unit to victory at the Battle of Normandy. Together with Naked Snake, she developed the technique of CQC.

Name: The Cube (Fortnite)
Summary: The Cube (Or Kevin) is a recurring object from Fortnite: Battle Royale. First appearing in Season 5 of Chapter 1, the Cube was a singular antagonistic device that traveled the map and created runes around it. It was later destroyed in the Butterfly Event, where it self destructed.

Name: The End (Metal Gear)
Summary: The End is a supporting antagonist of the 2004 video game; Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater, along with it's 2025 remake, Metal Gear Solid Δ: SNAKE EATER. He is a member of The Boss's Cobra Unit. He has an extensive lifespan and the ability to absorb solar energy after being infected by a parasite. He is also considered the greatest sniper in history. Like all members of the Cobra Unit, he bears the codename of an emotion he brings into battle: True Oblivion.

Name: The Fear
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheFearIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Fury (Metal Gear)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheFuryIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Pain
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:ThePainIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Sorrow
Summary: The Sorrow was the "Spirit Medium Soldier" of the Cobra Unit. Gifted with the powers of a medium, he was able to summon the dead and assume their abilities by bringing their spirits into himself, along with being able to accurately predict the outcome of any fight by talking to the dead. Like the other Cobras, his codename reflected the emotion he brought to the battlefield, unending sadness.

Name: Toge Inumaki
Summary: Run Away

Name: Tokiko
Summary: Tokiko is a minor youkai that appears in Curiosities of Lotus Asia, also known as the "book reading youkai".

Name: Tsukune Aono
Summary: Tsukune Aono (nicknamed Tsuki by his cousin Kyouko) is a former human and the main protagonist of the Rosario + Vampire series. He is mistakenly enrolled in Yokai Academy, a high school dedicated to teaching monsters to peacefully live alongside humans in disguise, where he meets and falls in love with Moka Akashiya, a vampire who takes a mutual interest in him and the sweet flavor of his blood. Tsukune becomes a member of the school’s Newspaper Club and eventually befriends several monster girls, including Kurumu Kurono, Yukari Sendo, Ruby Tojo, and Mizore Shirayuki—all of whom become obsessed with him—as well as Kokoa Shuzen, Moka’s younger half-sister. He also makes friends with several male monsters such as Ginei Morioka, Hokuto Kaneshiro, Fang-Fang Huang, and Haiji Miyamoto. They support Tsukune’s belief that monsters and humans can coexist and be more than just enemies, their friendship with him being a prime example of that sentiment.

Name: Umber Gorgoneion
Summary: Umber Gorgoneion is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a student hailing from Shade Academy who was assigned to Team FNDU after Theodore shuffled teams, and a secret agent of the Crown.

Name: Urien
Summary: Urien is the younger brother of Gill, who bears an intense grudge against him, stemming from an inferiority complex. His inferiority stems mainly from his emotional instability. Being the second strongest member of the Illuminati, Urien originally holds the position of the Vice President of the organization during the tournament of Street Fighter III 2nd Impact, outranked only by Gill who serves as the President.

Name: Vamp
Summary: One of the members of the anti-terrorist squad Dead Cell's founding lineup, Vamp was orphaned in his youth when his church was bombed, forcing him to resort to feeding on the blood of his family to survive, giving him a taste for it. His codename was not gained from these vampiric traits, however, but from his bisexuality.

Name: Velvet Scarlatina
Summary: Velvet Scarlatina is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Velvet is a very shy, quiet girl who tends to keep to herself, either by choice or because she is isolated by others for being a Faunus. Even when being picked on by others, she tends to act very reserved and refuses to fight back. One can say that she is very timid. However, despite her shy personality, she seems to get along with others, as seen with Team RWBY, and being an older student, she wishes them safety on their mission. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Venom Snake
Summary: Punished "Venom" Snake, also known as Big Boss, and formerly known as Ahab, V, Big Boss' phantom, or simply Snake, was a mercenary commander, formerly a combat medic for Militaires Sans Frontières (MSF). Big Boss made him lead the Diamond Dogs and Outer Heaven as his body double. Venom Snake served as a decoy to place all focus on him so that the real Big Boss could work under the radar. The phantom was killed by Solid Snake during the Outer Heaven Uprising, an operation directed by the real Big Boss.

Name: Villagers (Minecraft)
Summary: The Villagers are the main civilization found in Minecraft. They are mainly found in isolated villages in biomes with flat terrains. The relationship between villages is unknown, but they are likely in somewhat friendly terms due to neighboring villages capable of easily fusing into one.Their lifestyle is passive, as they spend most of their times on local farms and shops. However, their access to Nether-exclusive goods and their possession of maps leading to faraway places such as the Water Temples seems to hint that some of them may be more adventurous than usual.

Name: Volgin
Summary: Yevgeny Borisovich Volgin was a Stalinist colonel who attempted to seize control of the Soviet Union by ousting Khrushchev and installing Brezhnev in his place. He was the son of Boris Volgin, a treasurer for the Philosophers. After his death, Volgin acquired their vast fortune, which his father had stolen, granting him access to what were practically limitless funds. With this money, Volgin constructed the Groznyj Grad fort and began building the Shagohod, a nuclear-armed tank designed by Nikolai Stepanovich Sokolov.

Name: Wakasagihime
Summary: Wakasagihime is a mermaid Youkai living in the Misty Lake. She is usually gentle and shy, although the release of magical energy from the Miracle Mallet made her aggressive in the events of Double Dealing Characters.

Name: Wapol
Summary: Wapol is the former monarch of the Drum Kingdom, originally named for the "Drum Peak" mountains which support Wapol's castle. He became a pirate after fleeing from his country when Blackbeard and his crew attacked Drum Island.

Name: Weiss Schnee
Summary: Weiss Schnee is the second member of Team RWBY. Her weapon is a Dust revolver/rapier named Myrtenaster, and her Semblance allows her to create glyphs in battle. At 17 years of age, she is the heiress to the Schnee Dust Company, a corporation famous for its sometimes shady business dealings, dangerous practices, and mistreatment of its Faunus laborers. Both the Schnee Dust Company and the Schnee family have been targets of the White Fang terrorist organization for years, leading to Weiss' inherent distrust of the Faunus. Weiss chose to become a Huntress over taking a job at SDC to restore her family's honor, as her father caused the company to decline. At the start of the show, she was shown as self-centered, standoffish, and an obnoxious know-it-all, but has matured somewhat throughout the show. She has a noticeable scar over her left eye, which she is assumed to have acquired in a fight against a living suit of armor in the 'White Trailer'. As of Volume 4, she is the former heiress of the Schnee Dust Company.

Name: White Fang Lieutenant
Summary: The White Fang Lieutenant is an officer in the White Fang and made his first appearance in the episode "Painting the Town..." at the White Fang Faction Meeting. As Adam Taurus' right hand Faunus, this hulking masked figure is a capable fighter with strength, speed, and toughness beyond even his most bestial peers. He has been seen leading many of the biggest White Fang Attacks in Remnant with his massive chainsaw. Yet none, know what kind of Faunus he is.

Name: Wile E. Coyote (Looney Tunes)
Summary: Wile E. Coyote is the persistent predator that chases the Roadrunner but often fails due to his own shortsightedness and hubris.

Name: Withered Sprout
Summary: Withered Sprout (やせ細りモヤツ, ) was a previously assumed Wolf-level threat that was later assumed to be a Dragon-level threat before finally being agreed upon to be a Tiger-level threat by the Hero Association, using his meek appearance he deceives people into letting their guard down before instantly freezing with the use of his powers. He acts as the main antagonist of the special chapter 'Disaster level'.

Name: Wriggle Nightbug
Summary: Wriggle Nightbug is a firefly with the ability to control other insects. She likes using her ability to direct concerted performances for her own amusement, as well as to attack humans who underestimate her significance or the importance of insects in general.

Name: Yang Xiao Long
Summary: Yang Xiao Long is one of the main characters and the fifth character introduced in RWBY. A yellow-haired girl and Ruby Rose's older half-sister, she wields twin shotgun gauntlets called Ember Celica. Easily the most hotheaded member of the group, when she gets very angry or if her hair is damaged during battle, she completely loses her temper.

Name: Yatsuhashi Daichi
Summary: Yatsuhashi Daichi is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. He is first seen in the Volume 2 Opening, walking with his teammates and is later seen falling from the sky with other teams; he subsequently makes his first, albeit brief appearance in "Field Trip", before making a full-fledged appearance in "Breach". He is also one of the members of his team chosen to advance to the doubles round of the Vytal Festival Tournament, along with Coco Adel. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Yo Shindo (Grand)
Key: '''Provisional Hero License Exam Arc''' | '''Dark Hero Arc'''
Summary: Yo Shindo (真堂しんどう揺よう Shindō Yō), also known as Grand (グランド Gurando), is a student at Ketsubutsu Academy High School.

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die. I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Zurg (Buzz Lightyear of Star Command)
Summary: Zurg is Buzz Lightyear's arch-nemesis, and the biggest threat to Star Command and the Galactic Alliance. His main goal is to conquer them and rule over the galaxy. However, Team Lightyear continually thwarts his plans.

Name: Abe Simpson
Summary: Abraham Jay "Abe" Simpson II, commonly known as Grampa Simpson or simply Grampa, is a major recurring character in The Simpsons and a supporting character in The Simpsons Movie. He is the elderly patriarch of the Simpson family, Abe was a World War II veteran who was later sent to the Springfield Retirement Castle by Homer. He is known for his long, rambling, and often inaccurate stories.

Name: Ada Wong
Summary: Ada Wong is a secret agent appearing in the Resident Evil franchise. She was first introduced in Resident Evil 2 as a supporting character and reappeared in Resident Evil 4 and Resident Evil 6 as one of the main characters.

Name: Alex Louis Armstrong
Summary: Major Alex Louis Armstrong (アレックス・ルイ・アームストロング, Arekkusu Rui Āmusutorongu), also known as the Strong Arm Alchemist (豪腕の錬金術師, Gōwan no Renkinjutsushi), is a State Alchemist and officer in the Amestrian State Military. The scion of the illustrious Armstrong family, Alex is a remarkably caring commander and friend despite his intimidating appearance, as well as an invaluable skilled ally to Colonel Roy Mustang and Edward Elric.

Name: Alphonse Elric
Summary: Alphonse Elric (アルフォンス・エルリック, Arufonsu Erurikku) is the younger brother of Edward Elric, the Fullmetal Alchemist, Al is also a victim of the failed Human Transmutation experiment in which Ed lost his right arm and left leg. Having had his entire physical being taken away from him in the aftermath of the tragedy, Alphonse exists solely as a soul alchemically bound to a large suit of steel armor. Now, Al travels with his brother in search of the legendary Philosopher's Stone, an item with the power to restore their bodies to normal.

Name: Aphrodite (Fortnite)
Summary: Aphrodite is a Character introduced during Chapter 5: Season 2. She can be found in Lovely Lodge. Medical Specialist. Aphrodite has spent countless eons saving mortals from wrathful gods, and the gods from each other. However, Zeus' current vendetta has proven to be an exhausting challenge.

Name: Apu Nahasapeemapetilon
Summary: In the 1960s, Apu lived in India and spent some time as a student of the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi. He became a friend of Paul and Linda McCartney. He graduated from Calcutta Technical University and then got a scholarship in the United States at the Springfield Heights Institute of Technology. He achieved a doctorate in Computer Science by designing the world's first tic-tac-toe program that only the top human players could beat. After this, he took a job at the Kwik-E-Mart and continues to work there to this day. Due to his past, he is put in an arranged marriage with a woman named Manjula. After having 8 children (octuplets at that), he continues to raise his family and work his business in Springfield.

Name: Artemis (Fortnite)
Summary: Artemis is a Character introduced during Chapter 5: Season 2. She can be found in Lavish Lair. Scout Specialist and a master of stealth and strategy, Artemis believes life is like an honorable hunt, and those who break the rules of the hunt can no longer be trusted. No matter how powerful they think they are.

Name: Bandages the Mummy
Summary: Bandages the Mummy (ミイラくん) is a living dead who works as one of Fortuneteller Baba's fighters. He appears in the Dragon Ball manga and the animes Dragon Ball and Dragon Ball Z.

Name: Barry the Chopper
Summary: Barry the Chopper (also known as "Number 66"-バリー・ザ・チョッパー, Barī za Choppā) is one of the two armor guards ordered by the Homunculi to kill any intruders to the Fifth Central Alchemical Laboratory. A former serial killer, he became a human test subject in the military's alchemical experiments and, in lieu of execution, had his disembodied soul bound to a suit of armor, similarly to Alphonse Elric.

Name: Bart Simpson
Summary: Bartholomew JoJo "Bart" Simpson (born April 1, 1980) is a main character and the tritagonist of The Simpsons.

Name: Blaze (Minecraft)
Summary: The Blaze is a hostile mob that spawns inside Nether Fortresses. Their Blaze Rods are an important ingredient for alchemy, and are needed to craft Eyes of Ender for opening the portal to the End.

Name: Bluto
Summary: Bluto/Brutus is the main antagonist in the Popeye the Sailor Man franchise. He is a nasty sailor who loves to pester Popeye and try to win the heart of his crush, Olive Oyl.

Name: Boo Guy
Summary: Boo Guys are the spectral Boos which take the form of Shy Guys. Greapers and Glum Reapers are special variants that take a form similar to the Grim Reaper.

Name: Buccaneer
Summary: Captain Buccaneer (バッカニア) was an Amestrian State Military Officer stationed at Fort Briggs and a close subordinate of Major General Olivier Mira Armstrong.

Name: Bullfango
Summary: Bullfango are Fanged Beasts (formerly Herbivores), introduced in the first Monster Hunter.

Name: Buyon
Summary: Buyon (ブヨン) is a giant, round-bellied pink monster that lives inside the Muscle Tower. The creature is General White's secret weapon and possible pet.

Name: Byte & Barq
Summary: Byte & Barq are fighters in ARMS. They are a robotic duo that fight alongside each other. Byte is a tall police robot, while Barq is a cubic robot dog with a wheel for movement.

Name: Captain Goomba
Summary: Captain Goomba is the main protagonist of the Minion Quest: The Search for Bowser story mode from Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga + Bowser's Minions, and the Mario Bros' first enemy in the original version of the game.

Name: Captain Punch
Summary: Captain Punch is a heavy robot that has an extremely large health pool, combined with regeneration and innate ranged damage resistance from the Fists of Steel makes this behemoth the toughest robot in the entire game. Since melee resistance upgrade doesn't exist, there's no way to reduce its punching damage through upgrade stations. With the punching power of 325 HP per hit, it's capable of killing any non-overhealed class in a single, deadly blow. It's the final boss of the mission "Bone Shaker".

Name: Cat (Minecraft)
Summary: The Cat is a passive mob in Minecraft. Which can be tamed with raw fish and used for scaring off hostile mobs and getting the occasional random item which they will gift to you in the mornings.

Name: Chargin' Chuck
Summary: Chargin' Chucks are from the Mario Franchise. Unlike most Koopas, these Koopas have infant-like faces, but are antagonists of Mario nevertheless. These Koopas are stronger and not edible by Yoshi. They take three jumps from Mario, five fireballs from Fire Mario, or a swing from Cape Mario to defeat.

Name: Chi-Chi (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Chi-Chi is the former princess of Fire Mountain and the daughter of the Ox-King who later marries Goku and becomes the loving mother of Gohan and Goten. She was first introduced as a shy and fearful girl, but later, as she gets older, develops a very tomboyish, tough and fierce personality, which sometimes causes her to have anger outbursts seen several times throughout the series. Despite this, she has shown her love for Goku and their sons many times throughout the series.

Name: Choco Yuzuki
Summary: Choco Yuzuki is a demon who works as the school nurse of the Underworld Academy. Despite being a common demon, she's sometimes mistaken for a succubus due to having the beauty of one. Thanks to that, she's incredibly popular among the students, the boys in particular coming to get checked up all the time. Choco is polite, respectful and acts a lot more mature than other Hololive talents, with the wisdom and intelligence to back that up. Though she sometimes partakes in shenanigans with her coworkers, she sometimes also shows a no-nonsence attitude when things become too ridiculous. She likes to dote on and spoil Luna Himemori.

Name: Chramine
Summary: Chramine is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Online. Chramine is a Bird Wyvern that is highly similar to Gypceros but also has differences. Some of these differences are crimson red hair standing on its head instead of the crest of Gypceros, a different coloration, and a hard shell much like Yian Kut-Ku.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield. Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Colonel Silver
Summary: Colonel Silver (シルバー大佐) is a high-ranking Red Ribbon Army officer. Silver is first seen in the anime storming homes and looking for Dragon Balls, and eventually, his search brings him and his men to an Antique Shop Owner who tried to con him with a fake Dragon Ball. Silver easily sees through the lie due to the fake Dragon Ball being breakable (as opposed to real Dragon Balls, which are supposedly indestructible). After killing the shopkeeper without mercy, he steals a Dragon Ball from the Pilaf Gang.

Name: Conkdor
Summary: Conkdors are ostrich-like members of Bowser's army, first premiering in Super Mario 3D World.

Name: Cow (Minecraft)
Summary: Cows are a common passive mob found within Minecraft's Overworld. They drop beef and leather upon death and can be milked by the Player with a bucket. Cows can be mounted by Baby Zombies in the Pocket Edition Alpha.

Name: Creaking
Summary: The Creaking is a hostile mob in Minecraft. The Creaking is a mob that spawns at night or during thunderstorms as long as its creaking heart is active. The Creaking naturally appears in the Pale Garden biome, although Creakings can appear if a creaking heart is placed between two pale oak logs.[1]

Name: Darius (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Darius is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Death (Purgatony)
Summary: In the web series Purgatony the character known as Death is a central figure representing the personification of death itself. Death is depicted as a tall, skeletal figure wearing a dark cloak and wearing a sombrero. Throughout the series, Death is portrayed as a mysterious and somewhat enigmatic character. Death's role is to maintain the balance and order of the afterlife, and he often interacts with Tony Pergatelli, the main character. Despite his grim appearance, Death is portrayed with a dry sense of humor and a somewhat detached demeanor. He often delivers deadpan lines and presents an air of stoicism. Death's interactions with Tony often involve providing guidance, offering cryptic advice, or administering punishments when necessary.

Name: Demoman (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: A fierce temper, a fascination with all things explosive, and a terrible plan to kill the Loch Ness Monster cost the six year old Demoman his original set of adoptive parents. Later, at the Crypt Grammar School for Orphans near Ullapool in the Scottish Highlands, the boy's bomb-making skills improved dramatically. His disposition and total number of intact eyeballs, however, did not.

Name: Dr. Coyle
Summary: Dr. Coyle is a playable fighter in ARMS.

Name: Edward Elric
Summary: Rosé: What do I do? What am I supposed to believe in now!? Are you going to tell me? Well, are you?? Edward: ... You need to figure that out on your own. Stand up and walk. Keep going forward. At least you have strong legs to take you there.

Name: Eminem (Fortnite)
Summary: Eminem is a former Boss/Event Character in Fortnite. He appears Spaghetti Grotto as a Boss, which sports Grenades and RG's Minigun and is a tough foe.[1] He also appears as a character in a Live Event as a large version of Marshall Never More that sings his song Godzilla.

Name: Engineer
Summary: This amiable, soft-spoken good ol' boy from tiny Bee Cave, Texas loves barbecues, guns, and higher education. Natural curiosity, ten years as a roughneck in the west Texas oilfields, and eleven hard science PhDs have trained him to design, build and repair a variety of deadly contraptions.

Name: Envy
Summary: Envy (エンヴィー Enbī) is the embodiment of some of Father's envy. Envy is genderless, and their resentment of humanity is more heartful and personal than any other homunculus; having caused the Ishvalan war by shooting a child in the head while in the guise of an Amestrian officer. While Envy typically appears as an androgynous humanoid, their "real form" is a giant, animalistic beast, and their original form before being turned into a Homunculus was a tiny, leech-like bug.

Name: Ethan Winters
Summary: Ethan Winters is a major character in the Resident Evil series. An American systems engineer who was happily married to his wife Mia Winters, Ethan's normal life changed when Mia suddenly disappeared without a trace while working away from home.

Name: Farunokku
Summary: Farunokku is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G.

Name: Forever
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Forever (フォーエバー Fōebā) is a minor antagonist appearing in Stardust Crusaders. He is a malicious orangutan in DIO's service who confronts the group in the South China Sea aboard a freighter. Said ship happens to be possessed by Forever's Stand Strength.

Name: Forokururu
Summary: Forokururu is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G Genuine. Forokururu has evolved on its own in order to live in the Flower Field's unique environment. Its variable body color can be used to appeal to the opposite sex, to warn others or outsiders, and even as part of courtship behavior. By sucking the nectar of various flowers, Forokururu can change its appearance and the attributes of its attacks.

Name: Fu (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Fu (フー) (also spelled Foo in the Viz Manga) was a supporting character of the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He was a retainer of the Xing Empire's Yao clan, a personal bodyguard of Prince Ling Yao and the grandfather of Ling's other bodyguard, Lan Fan. Particularly wise and exceptionally skilled, Fu serves as a valuable asset to Prince Ling by utilizing his advanced combat abilities, strategic and observational expertise, and fierce loyalty to the Yao in a great variety of situations.

Name: Ganimes
Summary: Ganimes (ガニメ) is a giant rubble crab kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba. Ganimes began life on Sergio Island as a rubble crab of the species Daldorfia horrida, otherwise known as the horrid elbow crab. In both the Titan Productions and Hong Kong-recorded English dubs of Space Amoeba, Dr. Kyoichi Miya instead identifies Ganimes as a "pumice stone crab."

Name: Gendrome
Summary: Gendrome are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Gezora
Summary: Gezora (ゲゾラ) is a mutated cuttlefish kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba.

Name: Ghast
Summary: The Ghast are a strange kind of monster found in the Nether. They look like floating Jellyfish, producing cat-like noises.

Name: Gluttony
Summary: Gluttony (グラト二ー, Guratonī) was the second Homunculus to appear in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, typically being in the company of Lust.

Name: Godzilla (Original)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was designed by Teizo Toshimitsu and Akira Watanabe under Eiji Tsuburaya's supervision. Early on, Tanaka contemplated on having the monster be gorilla-like or whale-like in design due to the name "Gojira" (a combination of the Japanese words for gorilla which is gorira, and whale which is kujira) but eventually settled on a dinosaur-like design.

Name: Godzilla Jr.
Key: '''Baby Godzilla''' | '''Little Godzilla''' | '''Godzilla Jr.''' | '''Rebirth Godzilla''' | '''Post-Rebirth''' | '''Powered Up State'''
Summary: Godzilla Jr (ゴジラジュニア, Gojira Junia?), also known as Baby Godzilla (ベビーゴジラ, Bebī Gojira?) and Little Godzilla (リトルゴジラ, Ritoru Gojira?), is a young Godzillasaurus kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II.

Name: Great Apiposu
Summary: Great Apiposu are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Explore.

Name: Great Baggi
Summary: Great Baggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Great Girros
Summary: Great Girros (痺賊竜) is a Fanged Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Great Jaggi
Summary: Tier: 9-B | 8-C

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Great Maccao
Summary: Great Maccao are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Great Wroggi
Summary: Great Wroggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Greed (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Greed (グリード, Gurīdo) is a Homunculus, called the "Ultimate Shield" because he can rearrange the carbon in his body to make his skin as hard as diamond, thus making him impenetrable by most weapons. As his name implies, he is a very avaricious character, who likes living in luxury, surrounded by powerful minions and beautiful women. He also has a habit of flipping people off in the manga. Despite his generally greedy nature, he is shown to care for his subordinates.

Name: Groundskeeper Willie
Summary: William MacMoran is the groundskeeper for Springfield Elementary. He often is referred to as Groundskeeper Willie, and is a very proud Scotsman, though his past is very shady and clouded with mystery. He consistently lies and changes his past including his father being killed, him being incapable of firing a gun, and the part of Scotland he comes from. He has even made up stories where he himself didn't come out alive. It's likely that Willie is crazy, as him being connected with a famous killer known as The Aberdeen Strangler is something he didn't even try to deny. As well, he has accidentally killed at least two other students. He is dysfunctional and has drinking issues along with his hot headed temper.

Name: Guardian (Minecraft)
Summary: Guardians are a kind of monster that dwells in the oceans. They gather around Ocean Monuments and guard it against any intruder, hence their names. The Elder Guardians are a larger, stronger and likely older version of the regular Guardian.

Name: Gypceros
Summary: Gypceros is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Heavy
Summary: Like a hibernating bear, the Heavy appears to be a gentle giant. Also like a bear, confusing his deliberate, sleepy demeanor with gentleness will get you ripped limb from limb. Though he speaks simply and moves with an economy of energy that's often confused with napping, the Heavy isn't dumb; He's not your big friend and he generally wishes that you would just shut up before he has to make you shut up.

Name: Hedlok
Summary: Hedlok is a boss character in ARMS that the player encounters at the end of the tournament. Hedlok was created by Dr. Coyle at ARMS Laboratories to create powerful sparring partners for those with ARMS, however its programming had went wrong and allowed it to become self-aware.

Name: Heinkel (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Heinkel is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Helix (ARMS)
Summary: Helix (or DNA Man) is a playable character in ARMS. He is a mysterious, stretchy being created by scientists at the ARMS Laboratory, in order to find out more secrets and the trigger on the mysterious ARMS.

Name: Hieda no Akyuu
Summary: Hieda no Akyuu is the latest Child of Mare, a series of reincarnations whom have the goal to write a complete encyclopedia based on Gensokyo's history across all ages.

Name: Hol Horse
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Hol Horse is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is an assassin who was hired by DIO to kill the Joestars and allies. He works with his partner, J. Geil, to maximize both his and his partner's Stand abilities.

Name: Homer Simpson
Summary: Homer Jay Simpson is the main protagonist of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons, and one of the most recognizable cartoon characters of all time. He lives in the town of Springfield with his wife and three children and usually works as a nuclear power plant safety inspector, although over the years he has taken on many other jobs, such as being a food critic and a bodyguard. Generally, Homer takes a lazy and sometimes ignorant view on the world around him but has also shown genuine care and love for his family and friends. Homer Simpson was created by Matt Groening all the way back in 1987, with the character still going strong today.

Name: Hypnocatrice
Summary: Hypnocatrices are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 1.0.

Name: Iodrome
Summary: Iodrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Ivor (Minecraft)
Summary: Ivor is an antagonist turned one of the deuteragonists in Minecraft: Story Mode. He is a former member of the Order of the Stone, and the only one who disagreed to keep up with their lie. He thus created the Wither Storm as an attempt to prove that the Order weren't true heroes.

Name: Izumi Curtis
Summary: Izumi Curtis (イズミ・カーティス, Izumi Kātisu), is a master alchemist and skilled martial artist living in the southern Amestrian town of Dublith where she runs a butcher shop with her husband Sig. Though she doesn't usually take on students, Izumi accepted Edward and Alphonse Elric's plea to take them on as her apprentices and instructed them in alchemical theory and martial arts for six months. In that time, she grew to love them as deeply as she would her own children, becoming a long-term source of guidance and support for the Elrics' future endeavors.

Name: Jack Krauser
Summary: Jack Krauser, was a former member of USSOCOM, serving alongside Leon S. Kennedy, then a STRATCOM agent, in an anti-viral weapons mission to South America. Faking his death soon after, Krauser ended up working for Albert Wesker. His SOCOM codename was "Silverdax".

Name: Jake Muller
Summary: Jake Muller is a young mercenary from Eastern Europe who was embroiled in a plot to use the C-Virus in a series of devastating terrorist attacks.

Name: Jasper Beardly
Summary: He is a senior citizen in Springfield and Abe Simpson's best friend. Like Hans Moleman, he suffers many accidents and injuries.

Name: Jerso
Summary: Jerso is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Jesse (Minecraft)
Summary: Jesse is the main protagonist of the spin-off game "Minecraft: Story Mode". They start out as a simple town resident, but they soon get themselves in the middle of a quest to save the world from the Wither Storm.

Name: Jill Valentine
Summary: Jill Valentine is one of the main protagonists in the Resident Evil series. She appears in the first game, Resident Evil 3, the "End of Umbrella" scenario, Revelations, and the RE5 DLCs "Desperate Escape" and "Lost in Nightmares." She appears as a member of S.T.A.R.S. and then later fights zombies and bioterrorism. A senior member of S.T.A.R.S. belonging on the same team as Chris. Jill has also resigned from S.T.A.R.S. in Resident Evil 3 Nemesis and attempts to escape from the T-virus infested town, Raccoon City. She runs into Nemesis, a B.O.W. from Umbrella Corp. Nemesis relentlessly pursued Jill throughout the city. At some point, Nemesis managed to infect Jill with T-NE-virus. She also meets a member of the U.B.C.S. Carlos Olivera. In the end, Jill managed to kill Nemesis, and together with Carlos and Barry, escaped the city successfully.

Name: Kamoebas
Summary: Kamoebas (カメーバ) is a giant mutated turtle kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba.

Name: Karl Heisenberg
Summary: Lord Karl Heisenberg was a human mutant who lived in an Eastern European mountain area. He is the patriarch of the Heisenberg family and an engineering prodigy, and he is one of Miranda's Lords of the Four Houses. He is in charge of the inherited Heisenberg Factory, which is just outside the hamlet and serves Mother Miranda as well as the other three major houses in the mountain range. Heisenberg is enraged by Miranda's use of the village and her view of her "family" as nothing more than an experiment, and he intends to revolt against her by forming a cyborg zombies army and taking Rose's power away from her.

Name: Kasumi Miwa
Summary: If I Remember Correctly, When I Was Captain Of The Youth Basketball Team, Mother Would Often Dye My Hair Black. In Junior High, I Met The Person Who Would Become My Mentor And Chose To Become A Jujutsu Sorcerer Even Though I Had Never Held A Wooden Or Bamboo Sword, Much Less A Katana. I Held On To That Katana Tightly Because I Didn't Want To Be A Burden On My Mother And Because I Didn't Want To Die. I'm Putting Everything-my Present And Future-into This! Even If It Means Never Swing A Katana Again!!

Name: Kid Cobra
Summary: Kid Cobra is a playable character in ARMS. He is a professional snakeboarder and live streamer, as well as one of the rare inheritors of ARMS, the ability to stretch his limbs to greater ranges. His ARMS are also scaly and serpentine like, as well as having heterochromia. Kid Cobra is one of the few people who had his extendable ARMS since birth, which is very rare and occurs to 1 in 100,000 people.

Name: King Bill
Summary: Tier: 8-C

Name: King Bradley
Summary: King Bradley (キング・ブラッドレイ, Kingu Buraddorei) is one of the primary antagonists in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, being that he is one of the seven Homunculi. Bradley was also the original Führer (大総統, Daisōtō) of Amestris. In the manga series and the 2009 anime reboot, he was known as Wrath, the final homunculus created by Father. Bradley is the leader of Amestris and is seen to have almost inhuman swordsmanship. As Führer, Bradley is the respected Commander-in-Chief of the State Military, even though his political standpoints are often questioned in certain instances such as the Ishval Civil War, which was only one of many insurrections focused on creating a massive Philosopher's Stone for Father.

Name: Knack (Character)
Summary: Knack is the titular character in the game of the same name. He is a being made up of ancient relics that was brought to life by Doctor Vargas as a way to combat the Goblin threat.

Name: Koopa Troopa
Summary: The Koopa are a group of turtle-like creatures that inhabit the Mushroom Kingdom.

Name: Kosuzu Motoori
Summary: Kosuzu Motoori (本居 小鈴, Motoori Kosuzu) is the main character of the print work Forbidden Scrollery. She lives in the Human Village and serves as a worker of the Suzunaan book renter.

Name: Koyori Hakui (Holo no Graffiti)
Summary: Koyori Hakui is a scientist and a coyotegirl. She's the self-proclaimed "brains of the operation" of Secret Society holoX and is in charge of R&D. She possesses infinite curiosity and an insatiable thirst for knowledge, which pushes her to sometimes deliberately mess with people just to see how they react, including her fellow members. She's prideful about her creations, but her skill as a researcher is truly genuine.

Name: Krillin (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''23rd Budōkai''' | '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Potential Unlocked by Guru''' | '''Cell Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Krusty the Clown (Fortnite)
Summary: Krusty the Clown, or just Krusty, is a Boss character that can be found during second storm at one of his branded locations. He sports his signature weapon of Krusty's Mr. Blasty to take Loopers down.[1]

Name: Kulu-Ya-Ku
Summary: Kulu-Ya-Ku are Bird Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Kuyo
Summary: Tier 9-A | 8-C | At least 8-B

Name: Lan Fan
Summary: Lan Fan (ランファン, Ranfan) is a retainer of the Xing Empire's Yao Clan, a personal bodyguard of Prince Ling Yao and the grandchild of Ling's senior bodyguard, Fu. Fiercely loyal to her prince, Lan Fan's devotion to Ling borders on romantic infatuation, as insults to his name cause her to fly into a rage (overwhelming her better judgment and dulling her usually sharp combat abilities) and she becomes flustered when unmasked in his presence.

Name: Leon S. Kennedy
Summary: Leon Scott Kennedy is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil horror media franchise by Capcom. He debuted as one of the two playable protagonists of the video game Resident Evil 2. Leon later returned as the main character of Resident Evil 4 and as one of the protagonists in Resident Evil Darkside Chronicles and Resident Evil 6.

Name: Ling Yao
Summary: Lin: If you're going to stand around and mope, then you should give me back this body. I'll take us back to Xing and become Emperor- then you'll be rid of that feeling of emptiness! Greed: Lord of a country, huh? Lin: Pretty grand, right? Greed: Hah! Screw that! You're still thinking small! If we're going to do that... why not shoot for lord of the entire world instead?

Name: Lisa Simpson
Summary: Lisa Marie Simpson is a main character in The Simpsons. She is a highly intelligent 8-year-old girl who serves as the voice of reason in her family. Lisa is the eldest daughter and middle child of the Simpson family.

Name: Llama (Minecraft)
Summary: Llamas are neutral mobs that spawn in herds and are found in Savanna Plateaus and Extreme Hills biomes.

Name: Lola Pop
Summary: Lola Pop is a playable character in ARMS. She is one of the rare inheritors of ARMS in the world, where she is able to extend her arms out. Lola is a street performer in Via Dolce, Italy, of which she hopes to win the ARMS Grand Prix so that she can start up her own circus.

Name: Ludroth
Summary: Ludroth are Leviathans introduced Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Lumpy
Summary: Lumpy is the school snake of Springfield Elementary. Lumpy was a frequent predator of Springfield's children, to the point where the school handbook had a clause exempting the school from liability if Milhouse was eaten.

Name: Lust
Summary: Lust (ラスト, Rasuto) was the first Homunculus to appear in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, playing a significant part in the early chapters before she is killed by Roy Mustang. She is usually partnered with Gluttony to whom she appears to have a particular, almost motherly, closeness. Her Ouroboros mark is located on her sternum, just above her breasts.

Name: Maggie Simpson
Summary: Maggie Simpson is one of the main protagonists of The Simpsons. She is the daughter of Marge Simpson and Homer Simpson. She is 1-year old and their youngest child. Most of the time, Maggie is seen chewing on her pacifier or attempting to walk. She mostly seems like an innocent and sweet baby who just wants her family to stay happy, to learn, and to suck on her iconic pacifier. However, she also on some occasions shows far more self-awareness than she lets on. Several times having wielded different guns, intentionally tried to shoot Mr. Burns a second time, saving her family from The Mob, and several other threats.

Name: Maguma
Summary: Maguma (マグマ) is a giant walrus-like kaiju that appeared in the 1962 Toho film, Gorath.

Name: Maiko Plasma
Summary: Maiko Plasma (舞妓プラズマ, Maiko Purazuma) is a supportive monster, specializing in electricity and lightning-based attacks, and a Tiger level threat that first appeared alongside her partner Electric Catfish Man during the Monster Raid, assigned by Gyoro-Gyoro to attack D-City

Name: Major Bomber
Summary: Major Bomber is an extremely large Demoman giant, although this robot fires grenades that are always critical hits.

Name: Major League Scout
Summary: The Major League Scout is a bigger, badder version of the Minor League Scout, with the same loadout, though the Major League Scout can shoot its baseballs often, hitting a ball every two seconds or so. The Major League Scout moves at the same speed as its smaller counterparts, but not quite as fast as the Super Scout. Nonetheless, the Major League Scout can often be the cause of a round failure, considering its speed and ability to stun players.

Name: Major Metallitron
Summary: Major Metallitron (メタリック軍曹) is an antagonist who appears in the Dragon Ball. He is an android created by the Red Ribbon Army, and Goku's second challenge in the Muscle Tower.

Name: Maki Zenin
Summary: nan

Name: Malfestio
Summary: Malfestios are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Mannequins
Summary: Created to be the perfect army, Mannequins are zombie-like beings created by Alchemy to protect Father and the top dogs of the Amestrian military. However, when they are finally awakened they run wild among its Central City, being a threat against almost all parties involved in a coup d'etat.

Name: Marge Simpson
Summary: Marge Simpson is one of the main protagonists of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons. She is a loving mother to her son Bart, and her daughters Lisa and Maggie. As well, married to her husband Homer Simpson. She is a stay-at-home mom often acts as the voice of reason and logic when her husband or the town, in general, is getting into strange or stupid situations. She is generally very loving towards her kids and husband and is willing to almost anything to protect and help them. She is an extremely dedicated and hard worker. Whether she is working at home, taking a job as a police officer, or helping her children. She always puts her best effort into anything she does.

Name: Master Mummy
Summary: Master Mummy is a playable character in ARMS. Like the other ARMS fighters, Master Mummy was born with extendable ARMS, a rare trait, which allows him to enter the Grand Prix. He had apparently risen from the dead in the Mausoleum, and is looking for answers towards his past and finding his family. He hopes entering the Grand Prix and winning will send them towards him.

Name: Master Roshi
Key: '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Tournament of Power'''
Summary: nan

Name: Max Brass
Summary: Max Brass is a playable character in ARMS. He is an ARMS veteran and the greatest champion ever to compete in the Grand Prix. Max Brass is also the head of the ARMS League (hence his nickname, "The Commish") and the organizer for the Grand Prix.

Name: May Chang
Summary: A very young Alchemist from the eastern country of Xing, May Chang is expert in Xing's own brand of alchemy, allowing her to heal people and use her abilities from afar. Just like Ling Yao, she one of the many princes and princesses born of the Xingese Emperor, and representing one of the weaker dynasties she comes to Amestris searching for the Philosopher's Stone, in hopes of obtaining the Emperor's favors.

Name: Medic (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: What he lacks in compassion for the sick, respect for human dignity, and any sort of verifiable formal training in medicine, the Medic more than makes up for with a bottomless supply of giant needles and a trembling enthusiasm for plunging them into exposed flesh. Raised in Rottenburg, Germany during an era when the Hippocratic oath had been downgraded to an optional Hippocratic suggestion, the Medic considers healing a generally unintended side effect of satisfying his own morbid curiosity.

Name: Megasparkle Goomba
Summary: Megasparkle Goomba is a Goomba who gained the power of a Royal Sticker after Bowser shattered the Sticker Comet. When Paper Mario and Kersti reach his fortress, he attacks them along with fifteen other Goombas. During the battle, they merge into a giant Goomba, though they start flipping after being damaged enough. After the giant Megasparkle Goomba is defeated, the fifteen regular Goombas desert their leader, who is easily defeated by Mario.

Name: Megumi Fushiguro
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: Megumi Fushiguro (伏ふし黒ぐろ 恵めぐみ, Fushiguro Megumi?) is the deuteragonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Born into the Zenin clan, a prestigious family of jujutsu sorcerers, Megumi inherits the unique Ten Shadows Technique, which allows him to summon and control various shikigami using his cursed energy.

Name: Midas (Fortnite)
Summary: Midas is a Legendary skin and main antagonist of Fortnite Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the leader of Ghost and a double agent for Shadow. He is based on the Greek mythology, King Midas. At the end of Chapter 2 Season 2, he becomes Cyclo, the Defiant to the Storm. At the start of Chapter 2 Season 3, he gets attacked by a shark and survived. Around Chapter 2 Season 4, he becomes Shadow Midas.

Name: Millennian
Summary: Millennian Io (ミレニアン) is an alien kaiju that appeared in the 1999 Godzilla film, Godzilla 2000: Millennium.

Name: Min Min
Summary: Min Min is a playable fighter in ARMS. Like the other ARMS fighters, she has inherited the mutation of ARMS, of which have turned her ARMS into extendable strands of noodles.

Name: Miss Pauling
Summary: Miss Pauling is a loyal assistant to the Administrator. She performs a number of tasks, including unusual background reports, ordering and delivering goods, opening communication channels and murders. Miss Pauling generally conforms to the opinion of her employer for fear of incurring her anger, even if he does not necessarily agree with it. Despite the stern behavior of her boss, Miss Pauling insists that the Administrator "is not so bad when you get to know her." When pressed by the Administrator as to what exactly her friends are doing, she replies "Um. Go skateboarding ... look at weapons catalogs ... sometimes we just talk ..."

Name: Moe Szyslak
Summary: Moe Szyslak is the bartender in Springfield. He spends most of his time in his bar selling drinks to his usual customers and friends Homer, Lenny, Carol, and Barney. He as well is shown to run illegal practices like holding and selling animals like Pandas and Orcas in the back of his bar. He is a often sneaky and lazy bar keeper. Refusing to clean his bar, and pulling quick ones on his customers. However, he can and still does feel guilt and compassion towards his closer friends like Homer, and will go out of his way to help them.

Name: Mother of Thorns
Summary: Mother Of Thorns, also known as Doja Cat, is a boss appearing in Fortnite during the Fortnitemares event.

Name: Mr. Burns
Summary: Charles Montgomery Plantagenet Schicklgruber "Monty" Burns,[1] usually referred to as Mr. Burns, is a recurring character and antagonist in the animated television series The Simpsons, voiced initially by Christopher Collins, and currently by Harry Shearer. He is the evil, devious, greedy, and wealthy owner of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant and, by extension, Homer Simpson's boss. He is assisted at almost all times by Smithers, his loyal and sycophantic aide, adviser, confidant, and secret admirer. He is Springfield's richest, oldest, and most powerful citizen. His net worth has been stated to be in the billions and in one instance was pegged at exactly $1,800,037,022.[2]

Name: Nam
Summary: Nam (ナム, Namu) is a warrior from a desert village that competes in World Martial Arts Tournaments. He fights in order to make life better for the people of his village. He makes appearances in the Dragon Ball manga and the anime Dragon Ball, as well as short cameo appearances in Dragon Ball Z and Dragon Ball GT.

Name: Ned Flanders
Summary: Ned Flanders is a supporting character in the animated series, The Simpsons. He is the extremely religious next-door neighbor of the Simpson family. He is the well-mannered widower of Maude and father of Rod and Todd. He immensely worships God and is a strict follower of the Bible.

Name: Nick Ramos (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Ninja Murasaki
Summary: Ninja Murasaki (ムラサキ曹長) is a secondary antagonist who appears in Dragon Ball. He is the second-in-command of Muscle Tower under General White.

Name: Ninjara
Summary: Ninjara is a playable character in ARMS. He, like the other ARMS characters has been gifted with the powers of ARMS, making him able to stretch his own arms to abnormal degrees.

Name: Nizo Okada
Summary: Nizo Okada (岡田 似蔵, Okada Nizou), also known as Nizo the Butcher, or Manslayer Nizo (Hito Kiri Nizou) was a blind assassin and a master of Iai jutsu, which are techniques for drawing a sword. He was a member of the Kiheitai, an extremist Joui faction bent on causing world destruction, and would become fused with the Benizakura bio-mechanical sword, which would ultimately take over his body completely and lead to his defeat. He is the main antagonist of the Infant Strife Arc and Benizakura Arc.

Name: Olivier Mira Armstrong
Summary: Major General Olivier Mira Armstrong (オリヴィエ・ミラ・アームストロング, Orivie Mira Āmusutorongu) is the primary heir to the illustrious Armstrong family, the older sister of Alex Louis Armstrong as well as the commanding officer charged with the protection of Amestris' northern border at Fort Briggs.

Name: Peely
Summary: Peely is one of many characters in Fortnite. Peely became a robot in Fortnite's Season X called P-1000. In Season 2, Chapter 2, he becomes an agent named, Agent Peely.

Name: Piers Niavans
Summary: Piers Nivans was a combat operative for the North American Branch of the BSAA, assigned to the SOU (Special Operations Unit). Nivans served under Captain Chris Redfield during the investigation into the incident at the Marhawa School; the 2012 Edonian Civil War and the 2013 campaign in China.

Name: Pillager
Summary: The Pillager is a type of Illager in Minecraft. It wields a crossbow and attacks players and villagers at long range. It spawns in outposts, patrols, and raids.

Name: Pirako Chin
Summary: Pirako Chin (椿 平子, Chin Pirako) was first introduced as a hitokiri (aka manslayer) trying to join the Yorozuya and Otose's "faction", but soon she was revealed to be the daughter of Jirocho Doromizu, and she had the intention of making him the lone ruler of Kabuki-chou. She played a central role in the 4 Devas arc. She is the secondary antagonist of Kabukicho Four Devas Arc.

Name: Pokio
Summary: Pokios are pheasant-like enemies who first premiered in Super Mario Odyssey. They mostly reside in Bowser's Kingdom, though there are a select few that make their home in both Seaside Kingdom and the Darker Side of the Moon. They act as one of the many captures Mario can control with the help of Cappy and was an essential tool to defeat the Broodals' RoboBrood.

Name: Polar Bear (Minecraft)
Summary: The Polar Bear is a wild animal from the Tundra and Taiga biomes.

Name: Popeye
Summary: First introduced Dice Island, a story arc in the comic strip Thimble Theater in 1928, Popeye the Sailor Man would later become the main focus of the strip, as well becoming as one of the most iconic comic and cartoon characters of all time. "Borned to the sea" near the bay of Santa Monica, Popeyes' childhood was hard. The ship he was born on was rocked by a massive typhoon just moments after his birth, though his family was ultimately unharmed by the event. Growing up, both his father, "Poopdeck Pappy" and his unnamed mother left his life at a young age. Eventually, Popeye decided to join the military. Despite his rough and gruff appearance, Popeye was a good guy who hated bullies and defended the weak.

Name: Principal Skinner
Summary: Seymour Skinner, also known as Principal Skinner, is the principal of Springfield Elementary School. He has a passion for education which is consistently challenged by a lack of school funds, incompetent teachers and unenthusiastic students, the most notable being Bart Simpson. He is generally strict on discipline, likely stemming from his time serving in the army, but is otherwise quite nervous and fidgety.

Name: Puar
Summary: Puar is a character introduced in Dragon Ball. He is Yamcha’s loyal companion and fellow desert thief, as well as Oolong’s old classmate from the Southern Transformation Kindergarten. He is an ally of the Z Fighters.

Name: Pukei-Pukei
Summary: Pukei-Pukei is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World. They can be found in the Ancient Forest and Wildspire Waste.

Name: Pyro
Summary: The Pyro is a mumbling pyromaniac of indeterminate origin who has a burning passion for all things fire related. The Pyro appears to be insane and delusional, living in a utopian fantasy world known as Pyroland.

Name: Qurupeco
Summary: Qurupecos are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Rebecca Chambers
Summary: Dr. Rebecca Chambers is a former member of S.T.A.R.S., a special forces unit of the Raccoon Police Department. Despite her sweet and seemingly fragile appearance, she is a medical expert and a capable fighter. She is currently a professor at a university in Chicago, USA.

Name: Ribbon Girl
Summary: Ribbon Girl is a playable fighter in ARMS. She is a Japanese pop singer and appears similarly to a cheerleader. Like the other ARMS fighters, she was gifted the ability of ARMS, where her arms are able to stretch out

Name: Rikiya Katsukame
Summary: Rikiya Katsukame (活瓶力也 Katsukame Rikiya) is one of the Eight Bullets of the Shie Hassaikai. He was the first of the bullets to be fought by the heroes and managed to take down half of them before being defeated.

Name: Roy Mustang
Summary: Roy Mustang (ロイ・マスタング, Roi Masutangu), also known as the Flame Alchemist (炎の錬金術師, Honō no Renkinjutsushi), is the tritagonist of the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a State Alchemist and officer in the Amestrian State Military. A hero of the Ishval Civil War and Edward Elric's superior officer, Colonel Mustang is a remarkably capable commander who plans to become the next Führer of Amestris.

Name: Runuganga
Summary: Runuganga is a special Hollow which guards the outside of Las Noches from unwanted intruders, be described as the "Guardian of the White Sands", he was eventually killed by Rukia Kuchiki.

Name: Santa’s Little Helper
Summary: Santa’s Little Helper is the family dog in The Simpsons.

Name: Scar (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: The Scarred Man (傷の男, Kizu no Otoko), known more casually as "Scar" (スカー, Suka), is a nameless lone serial killer and revolutionary who targets State Alchemists for his own brand of lethal justice in accordance with the fundamental tenets of his religion and for the revenge of his slaughtered people and his older brother. An Ishvalan survivor of the Ishval Civil War, Scar's moniker comes from the large X-shaped scar on his forehead and sports a conspicuous and intricate alchemical tattoo on his right arm, which originally belonged to his brother, and which he uses as his murder weapon of choice.

Name: Scout
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Meet_The_Scout_%22Grass_grows%22.wav

Name: Sherry Birkin
Summary: Sherry Birkin is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil series. She was born around 1986 to the Umbrella virologist, William Birkin, and his research colleague and new wife, Annette, when the two were both working at the Arklay Laboratory. She is one of the survivors of the Raccoon City incident, thanks to Claire Redfield and Leon S. Kennedy, who came to her aid. They eventually escaped the fallen city together.

Name: Sheva Alomar
Summary: Sheva Alomar (シェバ・アローマ Sheba Arōma) is a fictional character in the Resident Evil horror video series by Capcom. She first appeared in Resident Evil 5 as one of the main characters. She was introduced in the E3 trailer and later on in E3 demo videos where she was a playable character that assists Chris Redfield throughout the game. She was introduced in 2009's Resident Evil 5 as a native African operative of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA) and a new partner of the series' veteran Chris Redfield. The character was met with mostly positive reception, but has yet not returned for any further installment of the series. Operating as part of its West African branch. She was assigned to the current mission to assist Chris Redfield, who was unfamiliar with the area. A versatile fighter with extensive experience, her ability to use firearms is on par with Chris. She is much smaller and more flexible than Chris, enabling her to perform certain maneuvers that Chris cannot. In turn, this allows Chris to throw her up to high ledges, or over large gaps in order to reach areas or objectives that a lone operative couldn't reach.

Name: Shroob
Summary: The Shroobs are a race of purple Toad-like aliens from the Shroob Planet, which was ruled by Princess Shroob and her older sister.

Name: Shulker
Summary: The Shulker is a kind of monster found in the End, particularly in the End Cities. They camouflage themselves as blocks until a target comes nearby.

Name: Skeleton (Minecraft)
Summary: The Skeleton is a hostile mob in Minecraft. It carries a bow and attacks players at long range.

Name: Slicer Brothers
Summary: The Slicer Brothers are a pair of serial killers who become one of the guardians of Laboratory 5 under the joint alias of Number 48 after being supposedly sentenced to execution, but instead being bound to a suit of armor, with one of them being the helmet and the other the rest of the armor.

Name: Slime (Minecraft)
Summary: A Slime is a hostile mob that spawns in caves underground or in swamps. It is squishy and can vary in sizes. The smallest of the slimes are harmless and deal no damage. However, the bigger the slime is, the more capable it is to harm a player.

Name: Sloth
Summary: Sloth (スロウス, Surōsu) is a Homunculus in the manga and the 2009 anime. Slow and dim-witted, he is used as a servant for menial and tiring tasks by Father, proving to be an infaticable worker despite his laziness.

Name: Snake Jailbird
Summary: Chester Turley, better known as Snake Jailbird, is a recurring antagonist in the animated TV series The Simpsons and a minor antagonist in the 2007 theatrical film The Simpsons Movie. He is a recidivist criminal, always getting arrested, but rarely being kept locked up for long. He speaks with a "Valley Boy" accent and has a tattoo of a snake on his arm, which is presumably the source of his nickname.

Name: Sneed
Summary: Sneed is a farmer that appears in the episode E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt). He is the owner of the convenience store Sneed's Feed and Seed (Formerly Chuck's).

Name: Sniper
Summary: The Sniper is one of the support classes in Team Fortress 2. His job is to defend the base while also attacking enemy targets from afar. Half rugged outdoorsman, half alien observer, this taciturn strip of beef jerky has spent the better part of his life alone in the bush, slow baking under the Australian sun.

Name: Snowball 2
Summary: Snowball 2 is the black cat that The Simpsons family took in after their original cat, Snowball 1, was killed. Snowball 2 is often portrayed as fairly intelligent for an animal, understanding human english, and pulling off human activities such as dancing. Aside from her decent intelligence shown every now and then, she is your typical stereotypical cat. She lived as the Simpsons family cat for many years until being ran over and killed by Dr. Herbert in season 15.

Name: Snowball V
Summary: nan

Name: Soldier
Summary: I have personally killed 6,578 men in cold blood while looking them in the eye; jumped on 1,336 live grenades; and stuffed fourteen feet of my own intestine back into my stomach. If that doesn't scare you out of your frilly pink leotards, guess what: You are an idiot and you hate America.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''Post-Muscle Tower''' | '''Post-Korin Training''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Post-Chōshinsui''' | '''23rd Budōkai'''
Summary: Son Goku (孫そん悟ご空くう, Son Gokū?) is the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball metaseries.

Name: Spike (Mario)
Summary: The Spike are a group of turtle-like creatures that inhabit the Mushroom Kingdom and a subspecies of Koopa.

Name: Spike the Devil Man
Summary: Spike the Devil Man, or just Devilman (アックマン, Akkuman?) is a devil from Hell and one of Fortuneteller Baba's fighters; he was once the strongest of all her fighters, and has won the World Martial Arts Tournament in the past, but he was bumped down one rank by Grandpa Gohan.

Name: Spring Man (ARMS)
