Summary: Spring Man is a playable fighter in ARMS. In the game, he is a young, enthusiastic fighter, and the newest contestant to join the Grand Prix. As his name implies, his visual appearance revolves around springs.

Name: Springtron
Summary: Springtron is a playable character in ARMS. He is a robotic ARMS Fighter, who resembles that of Spring Man, created by ARMS Labs, who interrupts the Grand Prix and acts as a boss battle. He is constantly learning and adapting in order to be the strongest, as well as provide more information on ARMS.

Name: Spy
Summary: This Spy has already breached our defenses... You've seen what he's done to our colleagues! And worst of all: He could be any one of us.

Name: T-A.L.O.S.
Summary: T-A.L.O.S. was created to be a superior and controllable version of the Tyrant, and Umbrella North America's response to Umbrella Europe's Nemesis project.

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Looper (Lego)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the sub-game Lego Fortnite. The focus of the game is on long-term survival, crafting and online cooperation with friends.

Name: The Visitor (Fortnite)
Summary: The Visitor is a mysterious entity who had arrived to the planet via a meteorite in Season 3 of Fortnite: Battle Royale, responsible for having launched the rocket during Season 4 as well. Though nothing is known about their original intentions, it was through the launching of this rocket that a multitude of spatial and temporal rifts were opened up within the atmosphere, leading to the events in Seasons 4 - 6.

Name: Three-Eyed Ghost
Summary: Three-Eyed Ghost was a Tiger Level Monster that appeared in the office district. The negative emotions of the social workers gathered and it became the size of a building. The act of destroying the office building was due to a grudge against the company.

Name: Todd Ingram
Summary: Todd Ingram is Ramona Flowers's third ex-boyfriend. He is in a relationship with Envy Adams (cheating on Envy with Lynette Guycott) and the bass player for The Clash at Demonhead. He is also a Vegan, though known to cheat on both his vegan diet as well as his girlfriend, believing he can get away with mostly anything because he's a rock star.

Name: Toridcless
Summary: Toridcless are mild mannered Bird Wyverns with control over electricity. They can be found living in the Gorge and Highland, and appear in the Bamboo Forest and Fortress Ruins.

Name: Truckasaurus
Summary: Truckasaurus is a giant mechanical truck/dinosaur first appearing in "Bart the Daredevil". It was inspired by the real life robotic dinosaur, Robosaurus.

Name: Tsukune Aono
Summary: Tsukune Aono (nicknamed Tsuki by his cousin Kyouko) is a former human and the main protagonist of the Rosario + Vampire series. He is mistakenly enrolled in Yokai Academy, a high school dedicated to teaching monsters to peacefully live alongside humans in disguise, where he meets and falls in love with Moka Akashiya, a vampire who takes a mutual interest in him and the sweet flavor of his blood. Tsukune becomes a member of the school’s Newspaper Club and eventually befriends several monster girls, including Kurumu Kurono, Yukari Sendo, Ruby Tojo, and Mizore Shirayuki—all of whom become obsessed with him—as well as Kokoa Shuzen, Moka’s younger half-sister. He also makes friends with several male monsters such as Ginei Morioka, Hokuto Kaneshiro, Fang-Fang Huang, and Haiji Miyamoto. They support Tsukune’s belief that monsters and humans can coexist and be more than just enemies, their friendship with him being a prime example of that sentiment.

Name: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku
Summary: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku are Bird Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Van Hohenheim
Summary: Van Hohenheim (ヴァン・ホーエンハイム, Ban Hōenhaimu) is the estranged father of Edward and Alphonse Elric. Previously, he had been known only as Slave No. 23. However, the Homunculus, grateful for the blood that brought him into the world and the unwavering friendship, bestowed upon the slave the gifts of a proper name, education, freedom, and ultimately, a body that never decays. Nevertheless, the freed slave, now known as Hohenheim, strongly condemned the gift of immortality that cost countless lives. Since then, Hohenheim has turned bitterly against Homunculus, sworn to end his agonizing immortality, and set free all the souls trapped within their bodies. Likewise, to prevent a similar tragedy from ever happening again.

Name: Varan
Summary: Varan (バラン) is a tri-phibian kaiju that first appeared in the 1958 Toho film, Varan, and later debuted in the Godzilla series in the 1968 film Destroy All Monsters.

Name: Velocidrome
Summary: Velocidromes are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Viruses (Mario)
Summary: The Viruses are a group of germ-based enemies which became a duplicated problem during an experiment gone wrong in the Mushroom Kingdom Hospital's virus research lab. There are several types of viruses, but the classic three (Chill, Fever, and Weird) appears the most.

Name: Wither Skeleton
Summary: The Wither Skeleton is a tall, black and withering skeleton found in the Nether. They roam the place aimlessly and viciously attack any intruders.

Name: Wolf (Minecraft)
Summary: The Wolf is a neutral mob in Minecraft that can be allied by the player.

Name: Yamcha
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''23rd Budōkai''' | '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Cell Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Yian Kut-ku
Summary: Yian Kut-Kus are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Yog
Summary: The Space Amoeba (宇宙生物) is an alien lifeform that serves as the antagonist of the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba. The entity's name is not spoken in American International Pictures' version of the film, although its title suggests it may be called Yog (ヨグ). According to producer Fumio Tanaka, this name may have been chosen as an homage to the works of H. P. Lovecraft.

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die. I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Zampano
Summary: Zampano is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Zeus (Fortnite)
Summary: nan

Name: Zombie (Minecraft)
Summary: The Zombie is a hostile mob and the most common and basic enemy of the sandbox video game, Minecraft. They come out only at night, and attack local villages, killing Villagers and often turning them into Zombie Villagers.

Name: Zombified Piglin
Summary: The Zombie Pigman, or Zombified Piglin is a kind of monster found in the Nether. They don't indiscriminately attack living beings, unlike Zombies, although they will be merciless against those who dare to attack their brethren.

Name: Zwei (RWBY)
Summary: Zwei is the pet dog of Ruby Rose and Yang Xiao Long. He first appeared in the episode "Field Trip", when he was mailed to Beacon Academy from Patch by Taiyang Xiao Long along with a pile of canned dog food and a can opener. Taiyang sent Zwei to his daughters to take care of him temporarily due to him leaving Patch for undisclosed reasons.

Name: ZZ
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: ZZ (ズィー・ズィー Zī Zī) is a minor antagonist featured in Stardust Crusaders. ZZ is another of DIO's assassins who confronts the Joestar Group. He is a Stand User who drives his stand Wheel of Fortune.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Abe Simpson
Summary: Abraham Jay "Abe" Simpson II, commonly known as Grampa Simpson or simply Grampa, is a major recurring character in The Simpsons and a supporting character in The Simpsons Movie. He is the elderly patriarch of the Simpson family, Abe was a World War II veteran who was later sent to the Springfield Retirement Castle by Homer. He is known for his long, rambling, and often inaccurate stories.

Name: Abiorugu
Summary: Abiorugu are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.3.

Name: Ada Wong
Summary: Ada Wong is a secret agent appearing in the Resident Evil franchise. She was first introduced in Resident Evil 2 as a supporting character and reappeared in Resident Evil 4 and Resident Evil 6 as one of the main characters.

Name: Adam Taurus
Summary: Adam Taurus was an antagonist in RWBY. Previously the leader of the White Fang's Vale branch, he became the High Leader after deposing the former leader Sienna Khan in a coup, but was ousted after the White Fang's defeat in the Battle of Haven. Following this, he began relentlessly chasing Blake Belladonna, only to be overpowered and killed by her and Yang Xiao Long.

Name: Agnaktor
Summary: Agnaktor is a large Leviathan which was first introduced in Monster Hunter 3 or Monster Hunter Tri.

Name: Akane Yashiro (Kiryu Saga)
Key: '''Akane Yashiro''' | '''Piloting Maser Cannon''' | '''Piloting AC-3 White Heron''' | '''Piloting Kiryu'''
Summary: Akane Yashiro (家城茜) is the human protagonist of the 2002 Toho Godzilla film Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla, also appearing in a minor role in its 2003 sequel Godzilla: Tokyo SOS. First Lieutenant Akane Yashiro A Type 90 Maser Cannon operator for the JSDF's Anti-Megalosaurus Force, Akane unintentionally caused the death of her comrades in a battle against Godzilla in 1999. Subsequently reassigned to a desk job, Akane was recruited to become a pilot for the Kiryu Squad in 2003, receiving the rank of Second Lieutenant. A member of the Kiryu team and the pilot of Kiryu Type-3. She is an excellent operator, but as the only member without relatives, she can be a bit awkward due to not being good at reading the feelings of others. Despite the odds against her, Akane earned the respect of her squad and played a key role in the battle between Kiryu and Godzilla in Tokyo. By 2004, she had been promoted to First Lieutenant and sought further training in the United States.

Name: Alan Keane
Summary: Alan Keane is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is an extraordinarily friendly teal balloon who is a student at Elmore Junior High. Alan is a very optimistic and diligent person, always working hard to try to make the world a better place and aspires to make the world such a good place that no one will have a reason to be sad. He has a high-pitched voice, and is currently dating Carmen.

Name: Albert Wesker
Summary: Albert Wesker is the main antagonist in the Resident Evil series. He was the leader of S.T.A.R.S. while secretly working for Umbrella Corporation as a Researcher. Later working for The 3rd Organization, H.C.F. (Hive/Host Capture Force), TriCell, he shifts allegiances at will to further his own goals of world domination. Wesker has been directly or indirectly responsible for the events of every game, and always seems to come out on top. Eventually, he would go on to pursue his megalomaniacal desires for world domination with the Uroboros virus, but was stopped by his arch-nemesis Chris Redfield and the BSAA.

Name: Alex (Street Fighter)
Summary: Alex is a playable character in the Street Fighter series, and the protagonist of the Street Fighter III games. He is a professional wrestler who lives day-by-day out of his trailer house in New York, which he never left and has no interest in doing so. His day is spent between construction jobs, wrestling events and training. Tom, Alex's mentor and a friend of his father, is worried about him, as he always keeps his emotions in check, isn't very talkative and lacks sensitivity, which makes it seem he lacks a true purpose in his life, although things apparently started to change after his meeting with Dhalsim.

Name: Alex Louis Armstrong
Summary: Major Alex Louis Armstrong (アレックス・ルイ・アームストロング, Arekkusu Rui Āmusutorongu), also known as the Strong Arm Alchemist (豪腕の錬金術師, Gōwan no Renkinjutsushi), is a State Alchemist and officer in the Amestrian State Military. The scion of the illustrious Armstrong family, Alex is a remarkably caring commander and friend despite his intimidating appearance, as well as an invaluable skilled ally to Colonel Roy Mustang and Edward Elric.

Name: AllSpark Drones (Transformers 2007 DS Games)
Summary: These non-sentient robots were created by the AllSpark to protect itself from being stolen before Megatron got his hands on it and began commanding these drones for his own purposes in the Autobots game. In the Decepticons game they're instead created by Starscream in multiple attempts to destroy Create-A-Bot after his betrayal.

Name: Alphonse Elric
Summary: Alphonse Elric (アルフォンス・エルリック, Arufonsu Erurikku) is the younger brother of Edward Elric, the Fullmetal Alchemist, Al is also a victim of the failed Human Transmutation experiment in which Ed lost his right arm and left leg. Having had his entire physical being taken away from him in the aftermath of the tragedy, Alphonse exists solely as a soul alchemically bound to a large suit of steel armor. Now, Al travels with his brother in search of the legendary Philosopher's Stone, an item with the power to restore their bodies to normal.

Name: Alucard (Rosario + Vampire)
Summary: nan

Name: Alvida
Summary: "Iron Mace" Alvida is the former captain of the Alvida Pirates and the first obstacle Luffy faces after setting sail for the first time. She is currently one of the two captains of the Buggy and Alvida Alliance.

Name: Amber (RWBY)
Summary: Amber was the previous Fall Maiden. As a young girl, she received the powers of the Fall Maiden, granting her tremendous power and becoming the next in a line that persisted for thousands of years. However, due to the actions of Cinder Fall, half of her powers were stolen, causing her to fall into a coma. As she was unlikely to ever wake up, and in order to ensure that the rest of the powers would not go to her assailant, Ozpin and his group planned on transferring her portion to someone else. However, she would eventually be killed by Cinder during the Battle of Beacon, causing the rest of the powers to go to her.

Name: Anais Watterson
Summary: Anais Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is the youngest and most intelligent member of the Watterson family despite being only four years old. She attends Elmore Junior High with her older brothers, Gumball and Darwin, and is in a higher grade than them.

Name: Ancient Leshen (Monster Hunter)
Summary: An old Leshen that arrived through a portal to assume control over the Ancient Forest. Sometimes revered as an indigenous deity. Dwelling deep inside the forest, this creature uses their innate magic to control all flora and fauna within their territory. Resulted from a crossover between Monster Hunter World and The Witcher 3.

Name: Angry Dad
Summary: Angry Dad is a fictional character made by Bart Simpson from The Simpsons. It is about a father who has extremely bad anger issues, throwing fits over the smallest problems he runs into. This show being based on his father, Homer Simpson, and his anger problems.

Name: Anjanath
Summary: Anjanath is a brute wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Anne Boonchuy
Key: '''Season 1-2''' | '''Season 3''' | '''Incomplete Calamity Form''' | '''Complete Calamity Form''' | '''With Secret Spell'''
Summary: Anne Boonchuy was pressured by her friends into stealing a strange music box on her 13th birthday which mystically activated and sent them to Amphibia, a realm populated by talking amphibians, where Anne lands in the town of Wartwood. There she is taken in by the Plantar family, who help Anne on her journey to find a way back home.

Name: Anorupatisu
Summary: Anorupatisu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Aoi Todo
Summary: Aoi Todo (東とう堂どう葵あおい, Tōdō Aoi?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is a third-year student at Kyoto Jujutsu High School and a grade 1 jujutsu sorcerer. He was mentored by Yuki Tsukumo in his youth and considers Yuji Itadori his best friend.

Name: Aphrodite (Fortnite)
Summary: Aphrodite is a Character introduced during Chapter 5: Season 2. She can be found in Lovely Lodge. Medical Specialist. Aphrodite has spent countless eons saving mortals from wrathful gods, and the gods from each other. However, Zeus' current vendetta has proven to be an exhausting challenge.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Apu Nahasapeemapetilon
Summary: In the 1960s, Apu lived in India and spent some time as a student of the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi. He became a friend of Paul and Linda McCartney. He graduated from Calcutta Technical University and then got a scholarship in the United States at the Springfield Heights Institute of Technology. He achieved a doctorate in Computer Science by designing the world's first tic-tac-toe program that only the top human players could beat. After this, he took a job at the Kwik-E-Mart and continues to work there to this day. Due to his past, he is put in an arranged marriage with a woman named Manjula. After having 8 children (octuplets at that), he continues to raise his family and work his business in Springfield.

Name: Argento Pocoron
Summary: Argento Pocoron is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. He is a former Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, serving as an enforcer for The Crown.

Name: Arlong
Summary: Arlong the Saw is a Sawshark Fishman, older half-brother of Madam Shyarly and the captain of the Arlong Pirates, who is very prejudiced towards humans. He was a former member of the Sun Pirates, but after their captain Jinbe ​​became one of the Seven Warlords of the Sea, he broke off, taking his former crew with him, and searched for easy targets in the relatively tame East Blue. There, he and his crew enslaved Nami's home island and forced her to work for them as a cartographer, after killing her surrogate mother Bellemere. With her cartography skills and his connections with the Marines allowing him to operate under the radar, Arlong's plan was to turn the East Blue into his own personal empire. He was the main antagonist of the Arlong Park arc.

Name: Arslan Altan
Summary: Arslan Altan is the leader of Team ABRN. Arslan and her team faced Team RWBY during the Vytal Festival and later helped defend Beacon against the invading forces of Grimm.

Name: Artemis (Fortnite)
Summary: Artemis is a Character introduced during Chapter 5: Season 2. She can be found in Lavish Lair. Scout Specialist and a master of stealth and strategy, Artemis believes life is like an honorable hunt, and those who break the rules of the hunt can no longer be trusted. No matter how powerful they think they are.

Name: Arthur Watts
Summary: Arthur Watts is a major antagonist in RWBY. Originally a scientist working for the advancement of technology in Atlas, Watts became infuriated and vengeful when James Ironwood chose to fund the Penny Project proposed by Pietro Polendina as opposed to Arthur's own proposal. Thought to have perished in an incident involving the testing of Atlesian Paladins, Watts secretly allied himself with Salem and became the brains of her operation. Having designed and programmed the Mantle security grid himself, Arthur becomes instrumental in the Atlas portion of Salem's plan.

Name: Astalos
Summary: Astalos is one of four flagships of Monster Hunter Generations/Monster Hunter X.

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Atsuya Kusakabe
Summary: Listen up you curse users!! I don't know what the hell happened, but those two there fighting are special grade! Think of them as elephants tap dancing on ants. To be clear, we're the ants...

Name: Aunn Komano
Summary: Aunn Komano is a Komainu living near the Hakurei Shrine. Without its owner's knowledge, she guards the Shrine against intruders.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: Babe (Mr. 4)
Summary: Babe, also known by his epithet "Catcher-Killing" and alias Mr. 4, is a former officer agent of the Baroque Works and the slow and dimwitted partner of Miss Merry Christmas. Due to his slow nature, he tends to acts as the muscle of the Mr. 4 pair. He rarely takes any initiative and is his partner the duo's driving force.He's very strong, able to wield a four ton baseball bat and has a bazooka named Lassoo which has (somehow) eaten the Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Dachshund, turning it into a bazooka-dog that sneezes explosives baseballs.

Name: Banbaro
Summary: Banbaro is a Brute Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter World: Iceborne.

Name: Bandages the Mummy
Summary: Bandages the Mummy (ミイラくん) is a living dead who works as one of Fortuneteller Baba's fighters. He appears in the Dragon Ball manga and the animes Dragon Ball and Dragon Ball Z.

Name: Barioth
Summary: Barioth is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Barricade (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Barricade was one of Megatron's most loyal soldiers and acted as Create-A-Bot's mentor in the Decepticon campaign of the game.

Name: Barricade (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Dark of the Moon''' | '''The Last Knight'''
Summary: Barricade is apparently a complicated robot. He's considered "fractious" even by Decepticon standards, yet is willing to give Starscream the benefit of the doubt and follow where he leads, at least for the time being. Though not totally dedicated to the service of the Decepticons' current leader, he is much more cautious and reserved about expressing mutinous dissent than say most. He believes that Starscream is vital in their search for Megatron and the AllSpark. In many ways this makes him Starscream's closest ally in the naturally combative Decepticon ranks. Then again, it's been said that he likes to trick people into trusting him, just so he can see their reactions when they find out just how much of a bad idea it was. As such, he has disguised himself as an Earth police car in an attempt to fool the humans around him.

Name: Barroth
Summary: Barroth are Brute Wyverns uniquely adapted to living in arid desert environments. While normally docile, they will become territorial if disturbed and are capable of using their heavy head to smash through the environment. Unlike most Brute Wyverns, Barroth are insectivores and are known to attack Altaroth nests in order to devour their occupants.

Name: Barry the Chopper
Summary: Barry the Chopper (also known as "Number 66"-バリー・ザ・チョッパー, Barī za Choppā) is one of the two armor guards ordered by the Homunculi to kill any intruders to the Fifth Central Alchemical Laboratory. A former serial killer, he became a human test subject in the military's alchemical experiments and, in lieu of execution, had his disembodied soul bound to a suit of armor, similarly to Alphonse Elric.

Name: Bart Simpson
Summary: Bartholomew JoJo "Bart" Simpson (born April 1, 1980) is a main character and the tritagonist of The Simpsons.

Name: Bartholomew Oobleck
Summary: Doctor Bartholomew Oobleck is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, he is first seen in "Jaunedice, Pt.2" teaching history to the students, specifically teaching about the war between the humans and the Faunus which took place a few generations before the start of the series. He is also shown to be more of an intellectual than a fighter through his actions on the battlefield in "Search and Destroy", but he still wields a weapon, which takes the form of his thermos, shown in the episode "Mountain Glenn"

Name: Baruragaru
Summary: Baruragaru are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G3.

Name: Basarios
Summary: Basarios are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter. Basarios is a small, rocky wyvern. It is the juvenile form of Gravios. Its hard, stone-like shell can be used for protection against other large wyverns, doubling up as effective camouflage when Basarios partially buries itself in the ground.

Name: Beck (TRON)
Summary: Beck is a young program who adopts the persona of Tron to free his home and friends from the reign of the villainous CLU and his henchman General Tesler. With training from Tron, the greatest warrior the Grid has ever come to know, he not only teaches Beck the fighting and lightcycle skills he needs to challenge this brutal military occupation, but becomes a guide and mentor to him as he grows beyond his youthful, impulsive nature into a courageous, powerful, strong leader.

Name: Bedtime Bear (Original)
Summary: Bedtime Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. As his name would suggest, he can most often be found dozing off at just about any place or time. However, when the situation calls for it, he can be dependable and is always willing to help out those who need it. It is his duty to make sure everyone on Earth and in the Care Bear family gets enough sleep and dreams peacefully.

Name: Bellamy
Summary: Bellamy the Hyena is the former captain of the Bellamy Pirates, and a former member of the Donquixote Pirates.

Name: Beowolf
Summary: Beowolves are large werewolf-like Creatures of Grimm. They are the most basic and abundant type of Grimm on Remnant and are the first Grimm seen in the series.

Name: Beringel
Summary: Beringels are Creatures of Grimm first seen in the "Volume 4 Character Short" that resemble large gorillas.

Name: Bertilak Celadon
Summary: Bertilak Celadon is a character from RWBY: After the Fall. He is a veteran Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy that was active in Vacuo. He serves as one of the main antagonists of RWBY: After the Fall alongside his partner Carmine Esclados.

Name: Big Boss
Summary: Ahab: Who are you...? Ishmael: Who am I? You're talking to yourself.

Name: Blackout (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Blackout is a Cybertronian appearing in the 2007 Transformers DS Games, being an antagonist in Autobots and a playable character in Decepticons. Throughout the story Blackout appears in multiple levels serving the Decepticon forces.

Name: Blake Belladonna
Summary: Blake Belladonna is one of the main characters and the third character introduced in RWBY. A young woman with long black hair, amber-colored eyes and a black ribbon resembling animal ears on her head, she wields the Gambol Shroud, a katana with a sharpened sheath that has a pistol in the hilt attached to a long ribbon which she uses in the style of kusarigama. In battle, her Semblance allows her to create a shadow of herself, an empty copy that distracts or takes hits from enemies for her while she moves in a different direction. Blake has a quiet nature and a love for books. She is a Faunus (a humanoid race with animal-like features) and a former member of the White Fang, a social rights advocacy group turned extremist paramilitary organization. However, she left in disgust of their violence and joined Beacon Academy to become a Huntress. Blake keeps her Faunus identity a secret by concealing her cat ears because she feels that she is not ready for the attention it would give her if the secret got out and doesn't want to face the discrimination other Faunus receive from humanity.

Name: Blangonga
Summary: Blangonga is a Fanged Beast introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Blaze (Minecraft)
Summary: The Blaze is a hostile mob that spawns inside Nether Fortresses. Their Blaze Rods are an important ingredient for alchemy, and are needed to craft Eyes of Ender for opening the portal to the End.

Name: Blind Worm
Summary: Blind Worms are large worm-like Creatures of Grimm that appeared in RWBY: After the Fall. They are enormous worm-like Grimm capable of burrowing underground and through the sands of Vacuo. They have a singular red eye and a giant fanged mouth. These Worms can range from 6 feet to bigger than Flatback Sliders, which tower at over 100 feet in height, and are built to be far faster when traveling in sands. Like the King Taijitu, they have a head on each end of their body. Their defenses include bone plates, hooks and acidic blood. They attack with spiked teeth and are capable of spitting acid. According to Fox, when the Blind Worm is cut in half, the two halves will eventually regrow to each become individual Blind Worms.

Name: Bling-Bling Boy
Summary: Eugene "Bling-Bling Boy" Hamilton is a recurring anti-hero in the series who has a one-sided crush on Susan Test.

Name: Bluto
Summary: Bluto/Brutus is the main antagonist in the Popeye the Sailor Man franchise. He is a nasty sailor who loves to pester Popeye and try to win the heart of his crush, Olive Oyl.

Name: Bobert
Summary: Bobert is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. It is a robot that is a student at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Bogabadorumu
Summary: Bogabadorumu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z Zenith.

Name: Boo Guy
Summary: Boo Guys are the spectral Boos which take the form of Shy Guys. Greapers and Glum Reapers are special variants that take a form similar to the Grim Reaper.

Name: Brachydios
Summary: Brachydios is the Flagship Monster of Monster Hunter 3 Ultimate.

Name: Brawl (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Brawl is a formidable member of the Decepticons, being a relatively high ranking member of the group, Brawl is a warrior at heart, living to destroy Autobot forces. However Brawl has not been shown as a tactician by any means, often making rash decisions, and taking on others without thinking.

Name: Buccaneer
Summary: Captain Buccaneer (バッカニア) was an Amestrian State Military Officer stationed at Fort Briggs and a close subordinate of Major General Olivier Mira Armstrong.

Name: Buchi
Summary: Buchi, along with his brother Sham, is a protector of the Black Cat Pirates' ship, the Bezan Black. The brothers are also known as the Nyaban Brothers and are some of the strongest men under Captain Kuro.

Name: Buggy the Clown
Summary: Buggy the Clown was initially one of the first real pirates that Luffy encountered early on in his travels. Buggy is a rather gaudy individual who used to be on the legendary Roger Pirates crew, along with Luffy's idol Shanks, who Buggy eventually bore a grudge against for unwittingly foiling a scheme to find a legendary treasure. After Gol D. Roger's death, the two went their separate ways, and while Shanks went on to become one of the Four Emperors, Buggy hung around the relatively tame East Blue.

Name: Bugs Bunny
Summary: Bugs Bunny is an animated cartoon character, the iconic mascot of Warner Brothers and the primary protagonist throughout much of the Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies series of animated short films.

Name: Bullfango
Summary: Bullfango are Fanged Beasts (formerly Herbivores), introduced in the first Monster Hunter.

Name: Bumblebee (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Bumblebee arrived in Tranquility to meet up with Create-A-Bot, and after a short discussion created from radio sound clips, instructed Create-a-Bot to scan a number of vehicles, the last of which was a Decepticon. After a short battle, Bumblebee then used Create-a-Bot's mad h4x0r skills to break into the internet and find the location of Archibald Witwicky's glasses, which turned out to be conveniently in Tranquility.

Name: Bumblebee (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Revenge of the Fallen''' | '''Dark of the Moon''' | '''Age of Extinction to The Last Knight'''
Summary: Bumblebee is an Autobot Scout and one of Optimus Prime's most trusted lieutenants. Although he is not the strongest or most powerful of the Autobots, Bumblebee more than makes up for this with a bottomless well of luck, determination, and bravery. He would gladly give his life to protect others and stop the Decepticons.

Name: Buyon
Summary: Buyon (ブヨン) is a giant, round-bellied pink monster that lives inside the Muscle Tower. The creature is General White's secret weapon and possible pet.

Name: Buzz Lightyear (Cartoon)
Summary: Buzz Lightyear is the deuteragonist of the Disney/Pixar Toy Story movies and the titular protagonist of his own television series. He also appears in both the Toy Story Toons and Toy Story Treats shorts. His often repeated catchphrase is: "To infinity and beyond!" He also returns as a supporting character in Toy Story of Terror! and Toy Story That Time Forgot.

Name: Byte & Barq
Summary: Byte & Barq are fighters in ARMS. They are a robotic duo that fight alongside each other. Byte is a tall police robot, while Barq is a cubic robot dog with a wheel for movement.

Name: Cammy White
Summary: Cammy White, also known by the codename Killer Bee, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Super Street Fighter II. She was once a deadly assassin working for Shadaloo before breaking free and becoming an MI6 operative for the British government.

Name: Captain America's Shield (Fortnite)
Summary: Captain America’s Shield refers to the main weapon of Captain America in Fortnite: Battle Royale. Curiously, the shield that belongs to him during the events of Fortnite: Endgame is far superior to the shield he carried when he travelled to the Fortnite island in Chapter 2, Season 3, so it's likely he has multiple shields.

Name: Captain Goomba
Summary: Captain Goomba is the main protagonist of the Minion Quest: The Search for Bowser story mode from Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga + Bowser's Minions, and the Mario Bros' first enemy in the original version of the game.

Name: Captain Grime
Summary: Captain Grime was the ruthless commander of the Toad Army and superior of lieutenant Sasha Waybright, until his attempt to execute Hopadiah Plantar for treason lead to the first Toad Tower's destruction. After this, he became a fugitive along with his close circle, plotting a coup against the Newtopian throne. While initially very stern with his subordinates, Sasha's influence helped him to show them genuine respect, leading to improvement in their morale and performance.

Name: Captain Punch
Summary: Captain Punch is a heavy robot that has an extremely large health pool, combined with regeneration and innate ranged damage resistance from the Fists of Steel makes this behemoth the toughest robot in the entire game. Since melee resistance upgrade doesn't exist, there's no way to reduce its punching damage through upgrade stations. With the punching power of 325 HP per hit, it's capable of killing any non-overhealed class in a single, deadly blow. It's the final boss of the mission "Bone Shaker".

Name: Cardin Winchester
Summary: Cardin Winchester is an attendee of Beacon Academy, and the leader of Team CRDL. His weapon of choice is The Executioner, a large, black mace.

Name: Carmine Esclados
Summary: Carmine Esclados is a character from RWBY: After the Fall. She is a veteran Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who was active in Vacuo, but was revealed to be a member of The Crown. She serves as the main antagonist of RWBY: After the Fall along with her partner Bertilak Celadon.

Name: Carrie Krueger
Summary: Carrie Krueger is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a ghost who is in Miss Simian's class at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Cat (Minecraft)
Summary: The Cat is a passive mob in Minecraft. Which can be tamed with raw fish and used for scaring off hostile mobs and getting the occasional random item which they will gift to you in the mornings.

Name: Chargin' Chuck
Summary: Chargin' Chucks are from the Mario Franchise. Unlike most Koopas, these Koopas have infant-like faces, but are antagonists of Mario nevertheless. These Koopas are stronger and not edible by Yoshi. They take three jumps from Mario, five fireballs from Fire Mario, or a swing from Cape Mario to defeat.

Name: Charles Bernard
Summary: Manga creators travel to a fictitious space in their minds because they aren't satisfied with reality. But my reality has been taken over by jujutsu. I've lost my motivation as a reader and as a creator. Do you know what that feeling is called? Despair

Name: Cheer Bear (2019)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She's the positive, enthusiastic pilot of the Cloudseeker and the leader of the expedition. Her upbeat personality is contagious and appreciated by just about everyone who meets her. Although she's always up for a challenge, she often feels a lack of confidence in her abilities.

Name: Cheer Bear (Original)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first debuted as a character on American Greetings cards in 1982. True to her name, Cheer specializes in lifting people's spirits whenever they're feeling down. Just about the only time one will find her feeling down is when there's someone who seems like they are nigh-impossible to encourage. However, this only ever leads Cheer to try harder. She constantly surprises those who doubt her capabilities with how multi-talented she truly is.

Name: Chen
Summary: Chen is a Bakeneko youkai and the shikigami of Ran Yakumo. Unlike Ran, as she doesn't spend much time with her master, she is usually quite weak.

Name: Chi-Chi (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Chi-Chi is the former princess of Fire Mountain and the daughter of the Ox-King who later marries Goku and becomes the loving mother of Gohan and Goten. She was first introduced as a shy and fearful girl, but later, as she gets older, develops a very tomboyish, tough and fierce personality, which sometimes causes her to have anger outbursts seen several times throughout the series. Despite this, she has shown her love for Goku and their sons many times throughout the series.

Name: Chizome Akaguro (Stain)
Summary: Chizome Akaguro (赤黒血染 Akaguro Chizome), known as the Hero Killer: Stain (ヒーロー殺し ステイン Hīrō Goroshi Sutein), is a villain that is notorious for having killed many Pro Heroes. In the Vigilante series, he was known as Stendhal (スタンダール Sutandāru) in which he killed criminals as his means of justice.

Name: Choco Yuzuki
Summary: Choco Yuzuki is a demon who works as the school nurse of the Underworld Academy. Despite being a common demon, she's sometimes mistaken for a succubus due to having the beauty of one. Thanks to that, she's incredibly popular among the students, the boys in particular coming to get checked up all the time. Choco is polite, respectful and acts a lot more mature than other Hololive talents, with the wisdom and intelligence to back that up. Though she sometimes partakes in shenanigans with her coworkers, she sometimes also shows a no-nonsence attitude when things become too ridiculous. She likes to dote on and spoil Luna Himemori.

Name: Choso
Key: '''Shibuya Incident Arc/Itadori's Extermination Arc''' | '''The Culling Game Arc'''
Summary: Choso (脹ちょう相そう, Chōsō?) is the "older brother" of Itadori and his 9 other brothers siblings who were once just Cursed Womb. Choso is a "person" who is mainly concerned about his brothers, worrying about being a good example and making sure that his brothers do not make the mistakes that he made.

Name: Chramine
Summary: Chramine is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Online. Chramine is a Bird Wyvern that is highly similar to Gypceros but also has differences. Some of these differences are crimson red hair standing on its head instead of the crest of Gypceros, a different coloration, and a hard shell much like Yian Kut-Ku.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Cinder Fall
Summary: Cinder Fall is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. She is a member of Salem's Inner Circle as well as the leader of her own faction, which includes Roman Torchwick, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black. Cinder is imperious and cunning, with a touch of cruelty. Usually, she maintains a calm and collected demeanor and is willing to take over a fight if necessary. She is also ambitious and demanding, doesn't seem to tolerate failure, and dislikes when she is disobeyed, reprimanding Emerald and Mercury when they failed to obey her orders to keep their hands clean. She is shown to be an excellent strategist as well, often planning ahead to keep her goals in reach while keeping her accomplices on a strict "need to know" basis. Following the Battle of Beacon, Cinder is the current Fall Maiden.

Name: Cirno
Summary: Cirno (チルノ) is an ice fairy who first appeared on the second stage of Embodiment of Scarlet Devil. As a fairy, she is exceptionally strong for her kind, matching the power of some weak youkai. However, compared to most of Gensokyo's residents, she's quite weak. Her personality is childish and she is sometimes considered stupid.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield. Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Clayton (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: Clayton is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a shapeshifting ball of clay, and a student at Elmore Junior High. Clayton is a pathological liar; he impulsively makes up sequences of events and he can't help but lie about lots of things. This is most likely due to Clayton's wild imagination.

Name: Clover Ebi
Summary: Clover Ebi is a supporting character in RWBY. He is the leader of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. He has been described as a total bro character who always makes luck puns. He constantly feels like he's in an action movie because things always go right for him, so he doesn't need to look when he's about to jump. This ultimately leads him to be a person that relies too much on his Semblance and causing him to ride the lines between confidence vs arrogance. He appears to be cordial and calm, as well as good-humored and easy to get along with. However, Clover is quick to turn back to a task at hand when needed. He is fiercely loyal, and tends to bring out the best in people, and does whatever it takes to protect his Kingdom.

Name: Coco Adel
Summary: Coco Adel is the leader of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. She is first seen in "Field Trip", after returning from fighting the Grimm. Coco appears to be very confident; her self-assurance is expressed in the very way she struts down the battlefield. Her experience with Grimm has been consistent enough that their appearance no longer fazes her. She is confident enough in her team that she holds Velvet Scarlatina back from combat when she tries to unleash her weapon. Given her attire and her reaction to the Grimm's destruction of her "favorite clothing store", fashion seems to be strongly integrated into her personality. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Colonel Silver
Summary: Colonel Silver (シルバー大佐) is a high-ranking Red Ribbon Army officer. Silver is first seen in the anime storming homes and looking for Dragon Balls, and eventually, his search brings him and his men to an Antique Shop Owner who tried to con him with a fake Dragon Ball. Silver easily sees through the lie due to the fake Dragon Ball being breakable (as opposed to real Dragon Balls, which are supposedly indestructible). After killing the shopkeeper without mercy, he steals a Dragon Ball from the Pilaf Gang.

Name: Combustion Man
Summary: Combustion Man was a mysterious, silent assassin sent by Zuko to eliminate Aang.

Name: Conkdor
Summary: Conkdors are ostrich-like members of Bowser's army, first premiering in Super Mario 3D World.

Name: Cow (Minecraft)
Summary: Cows are a common passive mob found within Minecraft's Overworld. They drop beef and leather upon death and can be milked by the Player with a bucket. Cows can be mounted by Baby Zombies in the Pocket Edition Alpha.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Cozy Heart Penguin
Summary: Cozy Heart Penguin is a Care Bear Cousin who originated in the first feature length Care Bears Movie. She can frequently be found swimming in the arctic waters of the Forest of Feelings, and she considers it her task to spread warmth and joy to all she comes across. Cozy Heart also happens to be the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't a mammal.

Name: Creaking
Summary: The Creaking is a hostile mob in Minecraft. The Creaking is a mob that spawns at night or during thunderstorms as long as its creaking heart is active. The Creaking naturally appears in the Pale Garden biome, although Creakings can appear if a creaking heart is placed between two pale oak logs.[1]

Name: Creep (RWBY)
Summary: Creeps are subterranean Creatures of Grimm that resemble both lizards and birds. They were first encountered in "No Brakes".

Name: Creeper (Minecraft)
Summary: The Creeper is one of the primary and most iconic Minecraft monsters. Unlike others of their kind, Creepers cannot attack directly, instead having to blow themselves up to damage enemies.

Name: Curious Cat
Summary: The Curious Cat is a creature residing in the Ever After. They are connected to the Great Tree, and help facilitate the ascension process by determining who requires it. At first, they acted as a guide for Team RWBY, trying to help them reach the Great Tree. However they later revealed that they were only trying to wear down Ruby emotionally so they could possess her body and travel to Remnant, in order to find out why their makers abandoned them.

Name: Dagon (Jujutsu Kaisen)
Summary: Dagon (陀だ艮ごん, Dagon?) is an antagonist in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was an unregistered special grade cursed spirit aligned with Mahito, Jogo, and Hanami. Dagon was born from the fear of water-based natural disasters and existed as a cursed womb until he evolved during the Shibuya Incident.

Name: Daiyousei
Summary: Daiyousei is a fairy who loiters around the Misty Lake, located near the Scarlet Devil Mansion. Aside from her appearing as the second stage midboss in Embodiment of Scarlet Devil, and being similar in behavior to other fairies, not much is not known about her.

Name: Danjuro Tobita (Gentle Criminal)
Summary: Danjuro Tobita (飛田 弾柔郎 Tobita Danjūrō), better known as Gentle Criminal (ジェントル・クリミナル Jentoru Kuriminaru), is a small-time villain who has his assistant La Brava film his numerous petty crimes in order to raise awareness of the flaws in hero society. Once an aspiring hero-in-training with failing grades, his life turned upside down when he used his Quirk to try and save someone in the middle of a hero operation, inadvertently causing the person serious injury and his expulsion from school as well as being disowned by his parents.

Name: Darius (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Darius is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Dark Heart
Summary: Dark Heart is the primary antagonist of the second Care Bears feature film. He is a demonic entity who intends to capture each member of the Care Bear Family and spread his influence to everyone on Earth. Unlike most other adversaries of Care-a-Lot, however, Dark Heart's malicious ways come not from his hatred of caring but from his initial inability to understand it. After the near-death of his friend, Christy, helps him realize his capacity to care about others, he abandons his evil ways and his powers in the process.

Name: Darwin Watterson
Summary: Darwin Raglan Caspian Ahab Poseidon Nicodemius Watterson Ⅲ is the deuteragonist of The Amazing World of Gumball, and is Gumball and Anais' adoptive sibling.

Name: Death (Purgatony)
Summary: In the web series Purgatony the character known as Death is a central figure representing the personification of death itself. Death is depicted as a tall, skeletal figure wearing a dark cloak and wearing a sombrero. Throughout the series, Death is portrayed as a mysterious and somewhat enigmatic character. Death's role is to maintain the balance and order of the afterlife, and he often interacts with Tony Pergatelli, the main character. Despite his grim appearance, Death is portrayed with a dry sense of humor and a somewhat detached demeanor. He often delivers deadpan lines and presents an air of stoicism. Death's interactions with Tony often involve providing guidance, offering cryptic advice, or administering punishments when necessary.

Name: Death Stalker
Summary: Death Stalkers are large scorpion-like Creatures of Grimm first encountered in "The Emerald Forest, Pt.2".

Name: Demoman (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: A fierce temper, a fascination with all things explosive, and a terrible plan to kill the Loch Ness Monster cost the six year old Demoman his original set of adoptive parents. Later, at the Crypt Grammar School for Orphans near Ullapool in the Scottish Highlands, the boy's bomb-making skills improved dramatically. His disposition and total number of intact eyeballs, however, did not.

Name: Denki Kaminari (Chargebolt)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Denki Kaminari (上鳴電気 Kaminari Denki), also known as Chargebolt (チャージズマ Chājizuma), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. Chargebolt is a friendly, social, and energetic boy who likes to hang out with people. He is rather casual when interacting with others, including the generally unfriendly Dynamight. He may come off as blunt and reckless at times, but is always well-meaning.

Name: Devo the Cursed
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Devo the Cursed is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is given a Stand and hired by Dio Brando to kill the Joestars and allies. He appears in Singapore in an attempt to ambush Polnareff in a hotel room.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Disaster Wyvern
Summary: Disaster Wyvern is a Brute Wyvern, first introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Dogora (Showa)
Summary: Dogora (ドゴラ) is a mutant space cell kaiju that first appeared in the 1964 Toho film, Dogora.

Name: Don Krieg
Summary: Don Krieg is the captain of the Krieg Pirates and an infamous pirate of East Blue. Because of his underhanded methods and domination over a fleet of 50 pirate ships, he is infamously known as "Foul-Play" Krieg and "Pirate Fleet Admiral" and is supremely confident in the weapons of his large arsenal.

Name: Dr. Coyle
Summary: Dr. Coyle is a playable fighter in ARMS.

Name: Dr. Merlot
Summary: Dr. Merlot is the main antagonist of RWBY: Grimm Eclipse.

Name: Dracula Duck
Summary: Count Dracula Duck (Or in some cases, referred as Drake Von Vladstone) is a Disney character and provides the role as the Final Boss in the game, Ducktales for NES, later to be the Final Boss once more for its Remastered version for the Wii U, Ducktales Remastered.

Name: Dromedon
Summary: Dromedons are camel-like Grimm introduced in RWBY: After the Fall. They are native to Vacuo that can spit acidic venom. and are shown to have armored humps.

Name: Drones (2007 DS Game)
Summary: While on Earth, Create-A-Bot and his comrades would face off many drones or fodder enemies from the opposing faction. Some even work alongside Sector 7

Name: Drophy (Miss Merry Christmas)
Summary: Drophy, also known by her epithet “Town-Collapser” and alias Miss Merry Christmas, is a former officer agent of Baroque Works and the talkative partner of Mr. 4. Due to her love of talking, she tends to acts as the brains of the Mr. 4 pair. Unlike her partner, who is very slow, Drophy talks very quickly, often only pronouncing the first syllable of the word in a high-pitched, child-like voice. She has eaten the Mogu Mogu no Mi which grants her the ability to turn into a human-mole and dig large tunnels.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Duramboros
Summary: Duramboros are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Ebirah (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: Ebirah returned 35 years later for the final entry in the Millennium series, Godzilla Final Wars, in which he was a mind-controlled pawn of the Xiliens. Ebirah was initially defeated by the Earth Defense Force's mutant soldiers at Tokai, and was deployed again to assist Hedorah against Godzilla in Tokyo Bay.

Name: Ectoplasm (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Ectoplasm is a Pro Hero who teaches mathematics as a member of the U.A. High School faculty.

Name: Edward Elric
Summary: Rosé: What do I do? What am I supposed to believe in now!? Are you going to tell me? Well, are you?? Edward: ... You need to figure that out on your own. Stand up and walk. Keep going forward. At least you have strong legs to take you there.

Name: Eijiro Kirishima (Red Riot)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Shie Hassaikai Arc''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Eijiro Kirishima (切島鋭児郎 Kirishima Eijirō), also known as Red Riot (烈怒頼雄斗 Reddo Raiotto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero. Like Deku, he's kind, friendly, and has real dreams of being an altruistic hero, having been inspired by his idol, Crimson Riot. He has a bit of a fixation with doing "manly" things, rating actions as "manly" or "unmanly" depending on how much he approves of them.

Name: Eika Ebisu
Summary: Eika Ebisu is the spirit of a stillborn child, and a god of fortune, inhabiting the riverbank of the Sanzu River. Here, she acts as the leader of other stillborn children, where she often organize stone stacking contests.

Name: Elm Ederne
Summary: Elm Ederne is a supporting character in RWBY. She is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Elm is described as being a "big buff lady with a heart of gold", illustrating she has a very kind and good nature. She also shows to be a tough and loud person who is not afraid to let someone know what is on her mind. She appears to be somewhat overzealous and is stated to not have a filter.

Name: Emerald Sustrai
Summary: Emerald Sustrai is a former associate of Cinder Fall and former partner of Mercury Black. While she worked with Cinder, she initially appeared to be affable and disarmingly friendly, however, this belies a darker side of her character. On the whole, she seemed to be genuinely outgoing and quick-witted, if a little short-fused. She had a tendency to maintain a pretense of friendliness amongst people in order to gain their trust, and showed a strong sense of loyalty, specifically to Cinder, whom she appeared incredibly eager to please. However, Emerald eventually had a change of heart and joined Ruby and her friends after learning from Ozpin about Salem's true goals.

Name: Eminem (Fortnite)
Summary: Eminem is a former Boss/Event Character in Fortnite. He appears Spaghetti Grotto as a Boss, which sports Grenades and RG's Minigun and is a tough foe.[1] He also appears as a character in a Live Event as a large version of Marshall Never More that sings his song Godzilla.

Name: End City
Summary: The End Cities are the only inhabited places in the End, an alternate dimension to the Overworld. They are occupied by the Endermen, a mysterious alien kind who travels to the other dimensions at night and comes back when day breaks. They appear to worship a being of immense power; the Ender Dragon.

Name: Enderman
Summary: The Enderman is a mob in Minecraft. It stands at 2.9 meters/blocks tall, one taller than The Player.

Name: Engineer
Summary: This amiable, soft-spoken good ol' boy from tiny Bee Cave, Texas loves barbecues, guns, and higher education. Natural curiosity, ten years as a roughneck in the west Texas oilfields, and eleven hard science PhDs have trained him to design, build and repair a variety of deadly contraptions.

Name: Envy
Summary: Envy (エンヴィー Enbī) is the embodiment of some of Father's envy. Envy is genderless, and their resentment of humanity is more heartful and personal than any other homunculus; having caused the Ishvalan war by shooting a child in the head while in the guise of an Amestrian officer. While Envy typically appears as an androgynous humanoid, their "real form" is a giant, animalistic beast, and their original form before being turned into a Homunculus was a tiny, leech-like bug.

Name: Eso
Summary: Eso (壊え相そう, Esō?) is a Cursed Womb: Death Painting and the middle brother of Choso and Kechizu. He and Kechizu serve as the primary antagonists of the Death Painting Arc.

Name: Estrellian
Summary: Estrellian is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Ethan Winters
Summary: Ethan Winters is a major character in the Resident Evil series. An American systems engineer who was happily married to his wife Mia Winters, Ethan's normal life changed when Mia suddenly disappeared without a trace while working away from home.

Name: Evil Dragon (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Evil Dragon was a dragon that was sealed long ago into the local Inari Shrine. It recently tricked Marisa into unsealing it.

Name: Evoker
Summary: The Evoker is a kind of Illager that lives in Woodland Mansions. They attack intruders using a variety of magic spells.

Name: Excella Gionne
Summary: Excella Gionne was the regional director of TRICELL's African division and a business partner of Albert Wesker.

Name: Farunokku
Summary: Farunokku is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G.

Name: Fenton Crackshell
Summary: Fenton Crackshell is a Disney character and a protagonist that appears in the 1987 Disney cartoon Ducktales, later to be featured in Darkwing Duck as his superhero alter ego, Gizmoduck. In Ducktales, Fenton has the role of Scrooge McDuck's accountant due to his fast counting. Once portrayed as Gizmoduck, he then plays the role of Scrooge's personal security system. In Darkwing Duck, Gizmoduck and Darkwing seem to look at each other eye to eye in a rivalry.

Name: Finger Bearer
Summary: Finger Bearers (指ゆびの寄き主しゅ, Yubi no Kishu?) are a type of Cursed Spirit that have become a special grade after devouring one of Sukuna's fingers. Finger Bearers begin as Cursed Wombs where they gestate until birth. During this period they can be seen by non-sorcerers. Once born they create an Incomplete Domain from purely Cursed Energy, a precursor to a Domain Expansion, that warps the dimensions of its birthplace.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Flynt Coal
Summary: Flynt Coal is a student at Atlas Academy and the leader of Team FNKI.

Name: Forever
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Forever (フォーエバー Fōebā) is a minor antagonist appearing in Stardust Crusaders. He is a malicious orangutan in DIO's service who confronts the group in the South China Sea aboard a freighter. Said ship happens to be possessed by Forever's Stand Strength.

Name: Forokururu
Summary: Forokururu is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G Genuine. Forokururu has evolved on its own in order to live in the Flower Field's unique environment. Its variable body color can be used to appeal to the opposite sex, to warn others or outsiders, and even as part of courtship behavior. By sucking the nectar of various flowers, Forokururu can change its appearance and the attributes of its attacks.

Name: Fortune (Metal Gear)
Summary: Fortune is a previous member of Dead Cell and antagonist/protagonist of Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty.

Name: Fox (Minecraft)
Summary: Foxes are nocturnal neutral mobs that spawn commonly in taiga and snowy taiga biomes.

Name: Fox Alistair
Summary: Fox Alistair is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Fox is sarcastic and laid back in personality. Though he is reserved in new social situations, he is lively in familiar ones to the point where he considers himself the comedic relief of Team CFVY. He is comfortable enough on the subject of his own blindness to make jokes about it himself. Fox thinks of himself as a prankster; he has a tendency to make practical jokes and poke fun of his friends. He holds himself in high esteem and directs himself with confidence, having no qualms being blunt about people if need be. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Fu (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Fu (フー) (also spelled Foo in the Viz Manga) was a supporting character of the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He was a retainer of the Xing Empire's Yao clan, a personal bodyguard of Prince Ling Yao and the grandfather of Ling's other bodyguard, Lan Fan. Particularly wise and exceptionally skilled, Fu serves as a valuable asset to Prince Ling by utilizing his advanced combat abilities, strategic and observational expertise, and fierce loyalty to the Yao in a great variety of situations.

Name: Fumihiko Takaba
Summary: Fumihiko Takaba (髙たか羽ば 史彦ふみひこ, Takaba Fumihiko?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a comedian before awakening his cursed technique during the culling games and becoming one of the strongest competitors and his role was vital in defeating the Special Grade past sorcerer Kenjaku.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: Funshine Bear (2019)
Summary: Funshine Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. He's the blindly optimistic co-pilot of the Cloudseeker who's always looking to have as much fun as possible. He rarely takes things seriously, which has both helped with the team's morale but also hindered their progress, depending on the situation. As a thrill seeker, Funshine's hobbies include hang-gliding and skating; he also is seen working on a superhero comic book from time to time.

Name: G (Street Fighter)
Summary: G is a playable character introduced in Street Fighter V. G's identity is unknown for the most part, as very little details are provided, and even the few available are mostly obscure and unclear. He just appeared one day in the middle of the street, challenging the best fighters of the world while streaming himself on Footube, which slowly granted him popularity. He claims to be the president or the world (and even of the universe, at times), and to be one with the Earth itself and with every citizen of the planet, reason why he always treats every person as if they had a strong and familiar connection. Although it can't be proven, his words might be somewhat true, as his powers and physical traits show a strong relation with the planet, and his energy was stated by Oro to be "one with nature".

Name: Galdino (Mr. 3)
Summary: Galdino, also known by his epithet “Loan Shark Galdino” and his alias Mr. 3, is a former officer agent, alongside his former partner Miss Goldenweek. He is regarded as the smartest of the officers and only got the position of "Mr. 3" because of that. He has eaten the Doru Doru no Mi which allows him to create and control candle wax at will.

Name: Ganimes
Summary: Ganimes (ガニメ) is a giant rubble crab kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba. Ganimes began life on Sergio Island as a rubble crab of the species Daldorfia horrida, otherwise known as the horrid elbow crab. In both the Titan Productions and Hong Kong-recorded English dubs of Space Amoeba, Dr. Kyoichi Miya instead identifies Ganimes as a "pumice stone crab."

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Gasurabazura
Summary: Gasurabazuras are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G8.

Name: Gedomaru
Summary: Gedomaru is a Shikigami of the Ketsuno Clan. She was given to Gintoki Sakata of the Yorozuya as a precaution, during the Exorcist Chapter, by Ketsuno Ana, who had requested the Yorozuya's assistance.

Name: Geist
Summary: Geists are Creatures of Grimm that resemble ghosts and are capable of "possessing" and controlling any inert object.

Name: Gem (Mr. 5)
Summary: Gem is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works. His codename was Mr. 5 and his partner was Miss Valentine.

Name: Gendrome
Summary: Gendrome are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: General Blue
Summary: General Blue (ブルー将軍) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga and the anime Dragon Ball, and also makes an appearance in Dragon Ball GT. He is a powerful high-ranking officer in the Red Ribbon Army and is the leader of the Blue Corps. He also has powerful psychic abilities and is considered to be the strongest Red Ribbon soldier.

Name: General Tesler
Summary: General Tesler is the main antagonist of TRON: Uprising. He is one of CLU's generals and is both extremely ambitious and a coldly calculating sadist. Tesler rules over Argon City from his command ship.

Name: General Yunnan
Summary: General Yunnan is a general of the Newtopian army sent to hunt down Captain Grime for military desertion, but fails after being defeated. However, she later assists in stopping him and Sasha during the toad invasion of Newtopia. Following the reveal of King Andrias' true goals, she tries to defect but is placed under a mind control collar, until Anne and Sasha free her, at which point she helps fight against her former king's invasion of Earth.

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Gezora
Summary: Gezora (ゲゾラ) is a mutated cuttlefish kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba.

Name: Ghast
Summary: The Ghast are a strange kind of monster found in the Nether. They look like floating Jellyfish, producing cat-like noises.

Name: Giadrome
Summary: Giadrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2. It is physically very similar to the Velocidrome, the only key difference being the pale blue colouration and the presence of a frost sac.

Name: Giant Crow
Summary: Giant Crow is a Demon level threat that appeared in City M during the Monster Raid. It was first seen ramming directly into King's apartment.

Name: Giaorugu
Summary: Giaorugus are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Gideon Graves
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, 8-B with sword, Varies with subspace manipulation and The Glow

Name: Gigginox
Summary: Gigginox is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Gill
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheMarkOfMyDignityShallScarThyDNA.ogg

Name: Gillian Asturias
Summary: Gillian Asturias is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a former Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, ruling as a queen and leader of The Crown.

Name: Gin (One Piece)
Summary: Gin the "Man-Demon" is a pirate and a member of the Krieg Pirates. Due to his actions, he can be considered the secondary antagonist of the Baratie Arc.

Name: Gintoki Sakata
Key: '''Beginning of the series''' | '''Yoshiwara in Flames Arc and onwards''' | '''Diviner Arc to End of the Series'''
Summary: Sakata Gintoki (坂田 銀時, Sakata Gintoki) is the founder and president of the Yorozuya Gin-Chan, as well as a highly skilled samurai, having fought in the Joui War in the past. During the war, he became known as the White Demon (白悪魔, Shiroyasha) due to his powerful swordplay and demonic white appearance. Now, he is in an era where the samurai are no longer needed. To add to his troubles, oppressive aliens have moved in to invade. Gintoki lives with Kagura and Shinpachi, taking on odd jobs to make the world a better place... and to pay their rent.

Name: Glavenus
Summary: Glavenus are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Gluttony
Summary: Gluttony (グラト二ー, Guratonī) was the second Homunculus to appear in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, typically being in the company of Lust.

Name: Glynda Goodwitch
Summary: Glynda Goodwitch is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, she was introduced in Volume 1, in which she saved Ruby Rose from an attack by Cinder Fall. She is the first known Huntress in the series. Her weapon of choice is The Disciplinarian.

Name: Gobul
Summary: Gobuls are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Godzilla (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ) is a daikaiju created by Toho that appears in Godzilla the Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle.
ID: Godzilla (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8

Name: Godzilla (Original)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was designed by Teizo Toshimitsu and Akira Watanabe under Eiji Tsuburaya's supervision. Early on, Tanaka contemplated on having the monster be gorilla-like or whale-like in design due to the name "Gojira" (a combination of the Japanese words for gorilla which is gorira, and whale which is kujira) but eventually settled on a dinosaur-like design.

Name: Godzilla Jr.
Key: '''Baby Godzilla''' | '''Little Godzilla''' | '''Godzilla Jr.''' | '''Rebirth Godzilla''' | '''Post-Rebirth''' | '''Powered Up State'''
Summary: Godzilla Jr (ゴジラジュニア, Gojira Junia?), also known as Baby Godzilla (ベビーゴジラ, Bebī Gojira?) and Little Godzilla (リトルゴジラ, Ritoru Gojira?), is a young Godzillasaurus kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II.

Name: Goliath (RWBY)
Summary: Goliaths are giant elephant-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "Search and Destroy". It is the cousin Grimm of the Megoliath in the continent of Solitas.

Name: Good Luck Bear (2019)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. Due to his lucky streak and natural intuition, he's assigned the role of the Cloudseeker's navigator. His Belly Badge power ensures luck is always on his side, which has frequently helped the crew on their mission. He's often the one to reassure his companions when things are tense. On the other hand, he can also be overconfident and over-reliant on this power. On multiple occasions, he's dived headfirst into situations without thinking things through.

Name: Good Luck Bear (Original)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. Good Luck is a fortuitous bear that never seems to run out of good luck. However, this has just as much to do with his exceptionally bright, positive outlook on life as it does with his ability to create his own four-leaf clovers. Truly believing that there is no such thing as "bad luck", the fortunate fellow tries to help others by improving the power of their own self-confidence and removing all doubt from their heart.

Name: Gore Magala
Key: '''Gore Magala''' | '''Chaotic Gore Magala''' | '''Shagaru Magala''' | '''Risen Shagaru Magala'''
