Summary: Gore Magala debuted as the flagship monster of "Monster Hunter 4", being the main antagonist of the games low rank story.

Name: Goto Imasuji (Muscular)
Summary: Goto Imasuji (今筋強斗 Imasuji Gōto), also known as Muscular (マスキュラー Masukyurā), was a member of the League of Villain's Vanguard Action Squad. He lost his left eye to the efforts of Water Hose, a pair of Pro Heroes who defended a town he was attacking. Because of this, he appears at U.A.'s secret summer training camp to attack Water Hose's only son, Kota Izumi, forcing Deku to intervene and save the boy from the villain's wrath.

Name: Grandpa Gohan
Summary: Grandpa Gohan is the elderly gentleman who found and raised the Saiyan Son Goku when he landed on Earth. A former disciple of Master Roshi, he taught Goku everything he knew. He died when Goku accidentally turned into an Oozaru and crushed him underneath his foot. He was brought back for a short time to spar against Goku in Fortuneteller Baba's tournament. Goku's son, Gohan, was named in honor of him.

Name: Gravios
Summary: nan

Name: Gray Fox
Summary: Gray Fox, real name Frank Jaeger, was a mercenary and former agent of U.S. Special Forces Unit FOXHOUND. Originally a child soldier, Jaeger was the only operative in FOXHOUND to achieve the codename "Fox," the unit's highest commendation and was decorated five times.

Name: Great Apiposu
Summary: Great Apiposu are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Explore.

Name: Great Baggi
Summary: Great Baggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Great Girros
Summary: Great Girros (痺賊竜) is a Fanged Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Great Jaggi
Summary: Tier: 9-B | 8-C

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Great Maccao
Summary: Great Maccao are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Great Philosopher
Summary: Great Philosopher (大哲人, Dai Tetsujin) is an A-Class Rank 13 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Great Wroggi
Summary: Great Wroggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Greed (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Greed (グリード, Gurīdo) is a Homunculus, called the "Ultimate Shield" because he can rearrange the carbon in his body to make his skin as hard as diamond, thus making him impenetrable by most weapons. As his name implies, he is a very avaricious character, who likes living in luxury, surrounded by powerful minions and beautiful women. He also has a habit of flipping people off in the manga. Despite his generally greedy nature, he is shown to care for his subordinates.

Name: Green (RWBY)
Summary: Green is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. He is a Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy and serves as an unwilling enforcer for the Crown.

Name: Griffon (RWBY)
Summary: Griffons are a species of Grimm with both feline and avian traits. They appeared en masse just prior to the Fall of Beacon, having responded to the distress created by the machinations of Cinder Fall.

Name: Groundskeeper Willie
Summary: William MacMoran is the groundskeeper for Springfield Elementary. He often is referred to as Groundskeeper Willie, and is a very proud Scotsman, though his past is very shady and clouded with mystery. He consistently lies and changes his past including his father being killed, him being incapable of firing a gun, and the part of Scotland he comes from. He has even made up stories where he himself didn't come out alive. It's likely that Willie is crazy, as him being connected with a famous killer known as The Aberdeen Strangler is something he didn't even try to deny. As well, he has accidentally killed at least two other students. He is dysfunctional and has drinking issues along with his hot headed temper.

Name: Grumpy Bear (2019)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with protecting the Silver Lining. He is the creator of the Cloudseeker, the vehicle the bears use to navigate the uncharted territory. He's frequently having to upgrade or fix it, thanks to the unpredictability of the area they explore. As the crew's resident worrywart, he often either brings up an important detail the rest of the Bears hadn't considered, or he reaches a point where his pessimism needs to be dialed back.

Name: Grumpy Bear (Original)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. He is quite recognizable, possibly more so than his friends, due to being the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't always smiling and cheerful. Despite his default mood, he is just as caring and dedicated to helping others as anyone else in Care-a-lot.

Name: Guardian (Minecraft)
Summary: Guardians are a kind of monster that dwells in the oceans. They gather around Ocean Monuments and guard it against any intruder, hence their names. The Elder Guardians are a larger, stronger and likely older version of the regular Guardian.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Gurenzeburu
Summary: Gurenzeburu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 9.0.

Name: Gypceros
Summary: Gypceros is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Gyro Gearloose
Summary: Gyro Gearloose is a Disney character featured in the 1987-1990 Disney cartoon, Ducktales, and in many other types of media. He is Duckburg's most famous inventor, although some of his inventions don't always work out like he intends them to. He's associated with Scrooge McDuck, Donald Duck, and many others.

Name: Halk
Summary: Halk, first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.2, is a Flying Wyvern-type creature that is able to help the Hunter in battle.

Name: Hammerhead (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Hammerhead (ハンマーヘッド Hamaheddo) is a B-Class criminal and the leader of the Paradise Group, a terrorist group insisting that people shouldn't have to work if they don't want to.

Name: Hanami
Summary: Hanami (花はな御み, Hanami?) is an unregistered special grade Cursed Spirit and an antagonist in Jujutsu Kaisen. They wish to kill humans to create a cleaner world controlled by Cursed Spirits. They are one of the Disaster Curses, who symbolizes humanity's collective fear of natural disasters.

Name: Harriet Bree
Summary: Harriet Bree is a supporting character in RWBY. She is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Harriet is competitive and quick-witted in nature, causing her to only be loyal to those who earn her respect. However, she is still cordial and well-mannered. Harriet also displays great confidence in her skills, bordering on arrogance, and she is quick to rush into action.

Name: Hatchan
Summary: Hatchan, often called “Hachi” by most characters, is an octopus fish-man, a former officer of the Arlong Pirates and a member of the Sun Pirates before that. After the crew split up, he joined Arlong's crew and became the handler of the sea cow Momoo. When the Straw Hats came to take down Arlong, he was defeated by Zoro, and was imprisoned by the Marines. However, he managed to escape, and met the mermaid Camie and the starfish Pappag after saving them from Sea Kings and Fishman slavers. He opened up a floating takoyaki stand, fulfilling a childhood dream of his, with the mermaid and starfish occasionally helping on support.

Name: Hazel Rainart
Summary: Hazel Rainart was one of the antagonists of RWBY. Introduced in Volume 4 as a member of Salem's Inner Circle, he was a very calm and reasonable person who would only use violence when it had a clear purpose. However, this all disappeared when in the presence of Ozpin who Hazel held responsible for the death of his sister. While in Ozpin's presence he would go into a murderous rage and was willing to kill anyone who stood in his way.

Name: Heavy
Summary: Like a hibernating bear, the Heavy appears to be a gentle giant. Also like a bear, confusing his deliberate, sleepy demeanor with gentleness will get you ripped limb from limb. Though he speaks simply and moves with an economy of energy that's often confused with napping, the Heavy isn't dumb; He's not your big friend and he generally wishes that you would just shut up before he has to make you shut up.

Name: Hedlok
Summary: Hedlok is a boss character in ARMS that the player encounters at the end of the tournament. Hedlok was created by Dr. Coyle at ARMS Laboratories to create powerful sparring partners for those with ARMS, however its programming had went wrong and allowed it to become self-aware.

Name: Hei Xiong
Summary: Hei Xiong, more commonly known by his nickname Junior, is the owner, or at least manager, of a club in Vale and is in charge of several henchmen, including Melanie and Miltiades Malachite. He was introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer, as its main antagonist. He makes his first proper appearance in the series in "Painting the Town...", giving what information he knows about Roman Torchwick to Yang Xiao Long and Neptune Vasilias.

Name: Heinkel (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Heinkel is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Helix (ARMS)
Summary: Helix (or DNA Man) is a playable character in ARMS. He is a mysterious, stretchy being created by scientists at the ARMS Laboratory, in order to find out more secrets and the trigger on the mysterious ARMS.

Name: Hieda no Akyuu
Summary: Hieda no Akyuu is the latest Child of Mare, a series of reincarnations whom have the goal to write a complete encyclopedia based on Gensokyo's history across all ages.

Name: Higari Maijima (Power Loader)
Summary: Higari Maijima (埋島干狩 Maijima Higari), also known as Power Loader (パワーローダー Pawārōdā), is a Pro Hero and faculty member at U.A. High School who manages the Support Course Development Studio.

Name: Himiko Toga
Summary: Himiko Toga (渡我被身子 Toga Himiko) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was a member of the group's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, L.O.V. and the Meta Liberation Army merged to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and Himiko became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Hiromi Higuruma
Summary: Hiromi Higuruma (日ひ車ぐるま 寛ひろ見み, Higuruma Hiromi?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a defense attorney who often took on impossibly difficult cases in order to protect the wrongfully accused. Having since given up on the justice system completely, Hiromi participated in the Culling Game as one of the top players. He initially serves as an antagonist of the Culling Game Arc before battling Yuji Itadori and choosing to cooperate after he reminded him of his roots. He used his one hundred to add a rule to the Culling Game allowing the transfer of points between players as per Yuji's request and departed, planning to turn himself in for the murder of the judge and prosecutor at his last trial once the Culling Game's barriers were lifted.

Name: Hiroshi Shibata
Summary: Hiroshi Shibata is a powerful esper and a former member of the terrorist organization Claw as a part of the Ultimate 5.

Name: Hiryu Rin (Dragon Shroud)
Summary: Hiryu Rin (鱗飛 竜 Rin Hiryū), also known as Dragon Shroud (龍帷子 Ron Wei Dzū), is a student of Class 1-B at U.A. High School, aspiring to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Hitoshi Shinso (Nighthide)
Summary: Hitoshi Shinso (心操人使 Shinsō Hitoshi), also known as the Hypnosis Hero: Nighthide (ヒプノシスヒーロー ナイトハイド Hipunoshisu Hīrō Naitohaido) was a student at U.A. High School, attending Class 1-C of the Department of General Education before being transferred into Class 2-A of the school's Hero Course.

Name: Hizashi Yamada (Present Mic)
Summary: Hizashi Yamada (山田ひざし Yamada Hizashi), also known as Present Mic (プレゼント・マイク Purezento Maiku), is a Pro Hero who teaches English at U.A. High School.

Name: Hoglin
Summary: The Hoglin is a large, boar-like hostile mob that spawn within Crimson Forests in herds.

Name: Hol Horse
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Hol Horse is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is an assassin who was hired by DIO to kill the Joestars and allies. He works with his partner, J. Geil, to maximize both his and his partner's Stand abilities.

Name: Homer Simpson
Summary: Homer Jay Simpson is the main protagonist of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons, and one of the most recognizable cartoon characters of all time. He lives in the town of Springfield with his wife and three children and usually works as a nuclear power plant safety inspector, although over the years he has taken on many other jobs, such as being a food critic and a bodyguard. Generally, Homer takes a lazy and sometimes ignorant view on the world around him but has also shown genuine care and love for his family and friends. Homer Simpson was created by Matt Groening all the way back in 1987, with the character still going strong today.

Name: Hood (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Hood (フード Fūdo), also known simply as High-End (ハイエンド Hai Endo), was one of Dr. Garaki's intelligent High-End Nomu and the primary antagonist of the Pro Hero Arc.

Name: Hoyo Makihara (Mummy)
Summary: Hoyo Makihara (巻まき原はら包ほう傭よう Makihara Hōyō), also known as Mummy (マミー Mamī) is a villain working alongside Nine.

Name: Hypnocatrice
Summary: Hypnocatrices are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 1.0.

Name: Hyujikiki
Summary: Hyujikiki is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G.

Name: Ice King (Fortnite)
Summary: The Ice King is a character from the game Fortnite. The ruler of Polar Peak and the wielder of the legendary Infinity Blade, he wreaked havoc during Fortnite's seventh season by freezing the entire island over in minutes and summoning a legion of Ice Fiends across the map. The Ice King was formerly unlockable during Season 7 by getting to Tier 100 on the Battle Pass but has since been unavailable.

Name: Ilia Amitola
Summary: Ilia Amitola is a supporting character appearing primarily in Volumes 4-5 of RWBY. She is a young chameleon Faunus with tan skin, light gray eyes, and brown hair tied up in a ponytail which curls up at the end— similarly to a chameleon's tail. Ilia grew up in Mantle, though her parents, who worked in the mines, wanted something better for their daughter. Thus, they enrolled her in an Atlas program and told her to disguise her Faunus heritage so she would fit in with the higher society. Managing to actually make some friends and blend in quite well, everything was going well until reports came in that the mines had suffered a cave-in which resulted in the deaths of her parents. Her friends simply laughed at the news, causing Ilia to uncontrollably change color and reveal her secret. Suddenly her so-called friends were afraid of her, and she assaulted them in retaliation.

Name: Inasa Yoarashi (Gale Force)
Summary: Inasa Yoarashi (夜嵐イナサ Yoarashi Inasa), also known as Gale Force (レップウ Reppū), is a first-year student at Shiketsu High School, U.A.'s rival. He was the top-recommended student for U.A. High before withdrawing his application. Gale Force is an energetic and enthusiastic young man who expresses himself with vigor. His signature trait is his undying love for passion above all else. He believes all heroes should have a fiery passion that motivates them to help others. He has a habit of approaching strangers to try and make friends with them. He also appears to enjoy passionate battles and desires to be a part of them. He disapproves of heroes who do not have hot spirits and believes people filled with hatred are unfit to be heroes and he refuses to recognize them as such. This is why he hates Endeavor and his son Shoto. Both of them had cold angry eyes when he met them and both of them blew him off despite his warm greetings.

Name: Iodrome
Summary: Iodrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Ironhide (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Ironhide arrived sometime after Bumblebee to assist in finding the Allspark. Advising Create-A-Bot, Ironhide acted as something of an older mentor figure to him as he learned the ropes.

Name: Isamu (Child Emperor)
Summary: Child Emperor (童帝, Dōtei) is the S-Class Rank 5 hero for the Hero Association. So far, he is the youngest hero in the Hero Association. He has his own laboratory in Y-City.

Name: Ishiguro
Summary: Ishiguro is a minor antagonist appearing within Mob Psycho 100. He is the leader of Claw's Seventh Division and is a member of the organization's elite group of Scars, who have in one way or the other challenged the leader of the organization in combat.

Name: Itsuka Kendo (Battle Fist)
Summary: Itsuka Kendo (拳藤一佳 Kendō Itsuka), also known as Battle Fist (バトルフィスト Batoru Fisuto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero, and the Class President of Class 1-B. Thoughtful, tomboyish, and reliable, she is often the one taking charge of her class when no one else is around, particularly when keeping Phantom Thief in line.

Name: Ivor (Minecraft)
Summary: Ivor is an antagonist turned one of the deuteragonists in Minecraft: Story Mode. He is a former member of the Order of the Stone, and the only one who disagreed to keep up with their lie. He thus created the Wither Storm as an attempt to prove that the Order weren't true heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Final Act)
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as the One For All Hero: Deku (ワン・フォー・オール ヒーロー デク Wan Fō Ōru Hīrō: Deku), is one of the 20% of people on Earth who were born without a Quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in modern society, causing him endless torment at school. However, thanks to his innate heroism, he was able to earn the Quirk "One For All", bestowed upon him by his idol All Might, and use it to grow into one of the world's greatest heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: Izumi Curtis
Summary: Izumi Curtis (イズミ・カーティス, Izumi Kātisu), is a master alchemist and skilled martial artist living in the southern Amestrian town of Dublith where she runs a butcher shop with her husband Sig. Though she doesn't usually take on students, Izumi accepted Edward and Alphonse Elric's plea to take them on as her apprentices and instructed them in alchemical theory and martial arts for six months. In that time, she grew to love them as deeply as she would her own children, becoming a long-term source of guidance and support for the Elrics' future endeavors.

Name: Jack Krauser
Summary: Jack Krauser, was a former member of USSOCOM, serving alongside Leon S. Kennedy, then a STRATCOM agent, in an anti-viral weapons mission to South America. Faking his death soon after, Krauser ended up working for Albert Wesker. His SOCOM codename was "Silverdax".

Name: Jake Muller
Summary: Jake Muller is a young mercenary from Eastern Europe who was embroiled in a plot to use the C-Virus in a series of devastating terrorist attacks.

Name: James Ironwood
Summary: General James Ironwood is the headmaster of Atlas Academy, a general in the Atlesian Military, and a holder of two seats on the Atlesian Council. For unknown reasons, the entire right section of his body was replaced with a robotic prosthesis. Originally, he was an ally to Ruby's Group. However, after learning that they lied to him and Salem was on her way, he turned against them and intended on raising Atlas out of her reach. He serves as a main antagonist in Volume 8. At the end of the Volume, he is killed when Atlas crashes into Mantle, destroying them both.

Name: Jasper Beardly
Summary: He is a senior citizen in Springfield and Abe Simpson's best friend. Like Hans Moleman, he suffers many accidents and injuries.

Name: Jaune Arc
Summary: Jaune Arc is the leader of Team JNPR who wields a sword and shield named Crocea Mors, an heirloom formerly belonging to his great-great-grandfather. He comes from a long line of esteemed Hunters and feels pressured to live up to their reputations. Because of his family line, Jaune is obsessed with being a hero. However, he was never formally trained like the rest of his family, which causes him to lack self-esteem and assign a lot of importance to his image as a fighter. He also does not seem to be very proud of having a weapon given to him, rather than earning or crafting it on his own, referring to his weapon as a simple "hand-me-down" instead of a "family heirloom." However, Jaune has demonstrated capable leadership skills and good tactical judgment. He also possesses a strong Aura which allows him to heal himself, although he cannot yet control this ability.

Name: Jax Asturias
Summary: Jax Asturias is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn and is the main antagonist of the novel. He is a former Huntsman hailing from Shade Academy who was deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, ruling as a king and leader of The Crown.

Name: Jazz (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Much like his Movie counterpart, First Lieutenant Jazz is a good natured Autobot who is always capable of taking things in his stride. In the games, Jazz helps hack into Sector Sevens systems to locate the Allspark. He also contended with Blackout, eventually overpowering him. Jazz is seen many times in the game series, but is eventually killed by Megatron.

Name: Jerso
Summary: Jerso is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Jesse (Minecraft)
Summary: Jesse is the main protagonist of the spin-off game "Minecraft: Story Mode". They start out as a simple town resident, but they soon get themselves in the middle of a quest to save the world from the Wither Storm.

Name: Jill Valentine
Summary: Jill Valentine is one of the main protagonists in the Resident Evil series. She appears in the first game, Resident Evil 3, the "End of Umbrella" scenario, Revelations, and the RE5 DLCs "Desperate Escape" and "Lost in Nightmares." She appears as a member of S.T.A.R.S. and then later fights zombies and bioterrorism. A senior member of S.T.A.R.S. belonging on the same team as Chris. Jill has also resigned from S.T.A.R.S. in Resident Evil 3 Nemesis and attempts to escape from the T-virus infested town, Raccoon City. She runs into Nemesis, a B.O.W. from Umbrella Corp. Nemesis relentlessly pursued Jill throughout the city. At some point, Nemesis managed to infect Jill with T-NE-virus. She also meets a member of the U.B.C.S. Carlos Olivera. In the end, Jill managed to kill Nemesis, and together with Carlos and Barry, escaped the city successfully.

Name: Jin Bubaigawara (Twice)
Summary: Jin Bubaigawara (分倍河原仁 Bubaigawara Jin), also known as Twice (トゥワイス Tuwaisu), was a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, his organization and the Meta Liberation Army merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants. Even Hawks, the number 2 Pro Hero, believed Twice to be the most dangerous of Shigaraki's lieutenants.

Name: Jinichi Zenin
Summary: Jinichi Zenin (禪院ぜんいん 甚壱じんいち, Zen'in Jin'ichi?) is a minor antagonist in Jujutsu Kaisen, belonging to the powerful Zenin Clan and a member of its elite unit of jujutsu sorcerers, the Hei. He's focused on safeguarding the clan's riches and authority, even if it requires disregarding certain traditions. When Megumi is selected to lead, he swiftly teams up with others to oppose it, driven by his desire to retain control and influence.

Name: Jiro Awasaka
Summary: Jiro Awasaka is a Curse User who used to torture and kill people to understand the human body better. After Gojo came into the world he went into hiding. He was recruited by Pseudo-Geto and Uraume to participate in the Shibuya incident to defend a set of commissioned curtains and ended up losing to Yuji and Megumi.

Name: Joe Sparrow
Summary: Joe Sparrow is a character from Amphibia.

Name: Jogo
Summary: Jogo (漏じょう瑚ご, Jōgo?) is a character in Jujutsu Kaisen. He is a Cursed Spirit and one of the main antagonists of the series. Jogo has immense pride as a Cursed Spirit and a passionate hatred for humans. He believes that Curses are the actual humans as they represent pure truths of life, such as hatred, while normal humans fake many positive emotions and should be exterminated.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome. He's the only son of Hugh and Lila and brother of Susan and Mary (who had brown hair in the 2004 pilot). Because he has Susan and Mary by his side, he can live any kid's dream, only to find that some dreams aren't worth living. He is usually seen with his partner-in-crime and best friend Dukey, his genetically altered dog. He also gives Johnny Coupons to his sisters for helping him with his daily problems. When redeemed, he does their tests for free. Johnny and his sisters are often the cause of some problems in Porkbelly.

Name: Jumping Spider (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Jumping Spider (ハエトリノ, Haetorino) was a human who didn't remove a spider that went into his ear. This act, or lack of, caused him to turn into a monster.

Name: Junpei Yoshino
Summary: Junpei Yoshino (吉よし野の順じゅん平ぺい, Yoshino Junpei?) is a supporting character in the Vs. Mahito Arc of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a high school student in Satozakura High School who befriended Yuji Itadori, but turned into a curse user after meeting Mahito.

Name: Juri Han
Summary: Juri Han (ハン・ジュリ Han Juri, Hangul: 한주리, Hanja: 韓蛛俐) is a character in the Street Fighter series. She makes her debut in Super Street Fighter IV, where she is a main character in the storyline. She is 25 years old (as of Super Street Fighter IV) and is described as a brutal and sadistic member of S.I.N. who relishes fighting and inflicting pain upon her foes.

Name: Jurota Shishida (Gevaudan)
Summary: Jurota Shishida (宍しし田だ獣じゅう郎ろう太た Shishida Jūrōta), also known as Gevaudan (ジェボーダン Jebōdan), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School.

Name: Kagerou Imaizumi
Summary: Kagerou Imaizumi is a werewolf from the Bamboo Forest of the Lost. Usually quite docile, the recent events made her much more aggressive.

Name: Kagura (Gintama)
Summary: Kagura (神楽) is a member of the Yorozuya and the main female protagonist of Gintama. She is a member of the Yato Tribe and the daughter of Umibouzu. Kamui, one of the main antagonists of the series, is also her older brother.

Name: Kai Chisaki (Overhaul)
Summary: Kai Chisaki (治崎廻 Chisaki Kai), better known as Overhaul (オーバーホール Ōbāhōru), is the leader of the Shie Hassaikai ("Eight Precepts of Death") yakuza group in the world of My Hero Academia.

Name: Kamoebas
Summary: Kamoebas (カメーバ) is a giant mutated turtle kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba.

Name: Kamotarou Itou
Summary: Kamotarou Itou (伊東 鴨太郎, Itou Kamotarou) was an advisor to the Shinsengumi who appeared during the Shinsengumi Mutiny arc as the main antagonist until his betrayal by Bansai Kawakami. He made an agreement with Shinsuke Takasugi and aimed to become the head of Shinsengumi.

Name: Karl Heisenberg
Summary: Lord Karl Heisenberg was a human mutant who lived in an Eastern European mountain area. He is the patriarch of the Heisenberg family and an engineering prodigy, and he is one of Miranda's Lords of the Four Houses. He is in charge of the inherited Heisenberg Factory, which is just outside the hamlet and serves Mother Miranda as well as the other three major houses in the mountain range. Heisenberg is enraged by Miranda's use of the village and her view of her "family" as nothing more than an experiment, and he intends to revolt against her by forming a cyborg zombies army and taking Rose's power away from her.

Name: Kasumi Miwa
Summary: If I Remember Correctly, When I Was Captain Of The Youth Basketball Team, Mother Would Often Dye My Hair Black. In Junior High, I Met The Person Who Would Become My Mentor And Chose To Become A Jujutsu Sorcerer Even Though I Had Never Held A Wooden Or Bamboo Sword, Much Less A Katana. I Held On To That Katana Tightly Because I Didn't Want To Be A Burden On My Mother And Because I Didn't Want To Die. I'm Putting Everything-my Present And Future-into This! Even If It Means Never Swing A Katana Again!!

Name: Katsuki Bakugo (Dynamight) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''With One For All'''
Summary: Katsuki Bakugo (爆豪勝己 Bakugō Katsuki) is a student in Class 1-A at U.A High School training to become a Pro Hero. He is the complete opposite of Deku, being stubborn, hot-headed, arrogant, and gifted.

Name: Ken Masters
Summary: Ken (ケン or 拳 "Fist"), also known by his full name, Ken Masters (ケン・マスターズ Ken Masutāzu), is a video game character created by Capcom. He is one of the main protagonists of the Street Fighter series. Ken is also stated to be the second most popular character in the series, coming second to his best friend Ryu. Like Ryu, Ken's goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strive to become stronger but holds more restraint due to not wanting to jeopardize his family life.

Name: Kendo Rappa
Summary: Kendo Rappa (乱波肩動 Rappa Kendō), also known as The Rapper (ザ ラッパー Za Rappā), is a member of Overhaul's Shie Hassaikai. Rappa is a hot-blooded man who thrives on violence and bloodshed. He has a warrior-like mentality and only cares about seeking out a battle that can satisfy him. Originally an MMA fighter who fought in many underground rings for years. He was usually unsatisfied, most of his opponents were defeated in one punch and those that could take his punch would beg for their lives. His routine would end after he met Overhaul who offered him to join his group.

Name: Kenji Hikiishi (Magne)
Summary: Kenji Hikiishi (引ひき石いし健けん磁じ Hikiishi Kenji), also known by her villain name Magne (マグネ Magune), was a member of the League of Villains and part of its Vanguard Action Squad. She and the rest of her team serve as the main antagonists of the Forest Training Camp Arc.

Name: Kento Nanami
Summary: I won't praise or insult you. I am here to identify the truth and uphold the law.

Name: Khezu
Summary: Khezu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Kid Cobra
Summary: Kid Cobra is a playable character in ARMS. He is a professional snakeboarder and live streamer, as well as one of the rare inheritors of ARMS, the ability to stretch his limbs to greater ranges. His ARMS are also scaly and serpentine like, as well as having heterochromia. Kid Cobra is one of the few people who had his extendable ARMS since birth, which is very rare and occurs to 1 in 100,000 people.

Name: King Andrias
Summary: King Andrias is the king of Amphibia and leader of Newtopia. He is initially introduced as a benevolent king who only wants to help Anne and her friends, but as events unfold he is revealed to actually be a major antagonist in the series, serves as a major opposing force against the main cast while also being a pawn in his master's plan.

Name: King Bill
Summary: Tier: 8-C

Name: King Bradley
Summary: King Bradley (キング・ブラッドレイ, Kingu Buraddorei) is one of the primary antagonists in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, being that he is one of the seven Homunculi. Bradley was also the original Führer (大総統, Daisōtō) of Amestris. In the manga series and the 2009 anime reboot, he was known as Wrath, the final homunculus created by Father. Bradley is the leader of Amestris and is seen to have almost inhuman swordsmanship. As Führer, Bradley is the respected Commander-in-Chief of the State Military, even though his political standpoints are often questioned in certain instances such as the Ishval Civil War, which was only one of many insurrections focused on creating a massive Philosopher's Stone for Father.

Name: King Ghidorah (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: King Ghidorah (キングギドラ, Kingu Gidora?), is a giant three-headed dragon daikaiju created by Toho in 2021 for Godzilla the Ride: Large Monster Summit Battle.
ID: King Ghidorah (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8

Name: King Taijitu
Summary: King Taijitu are large serpentine Creatures of Grimm. The first one to appear in the series is encountered by Lie Ren in the episode "The Emerald Forest".

Name: King Thorax
Summary: King Thorax is a character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Kinji Hakari
Summary: It all has to do with the fever. Both the deceiver and the deceived are in a fever to change their lives. People get high on the fever and make mistakes. And me? I love the fever! However, without it, people can't even fall in love. Do you know a more direct way of dealing with the fever? Life itself is a gamble. Lots of girls have dumped me 'cause they hate gambling, but they don't understand. Society tramples on guys who can't bet big and guys who don't know when to quit. Everyone gambles. What they hate is losing and going to ruin.

Name: Kiruka Hasaki (Slice)
Summary: Kiruka Hasaki (羽は咲さき斬きる香か Hasaki Kiruka), also known as Slice (スライス Suraisu), is a villain working alongside Nine.

Name: Kisume
Summary: Kisume is a minor character in Subterranean Animism. She appears as a minor enemy who attacks the protagonist.

Name: Knack (Character)
Summary: Knack is the titular character in the game of the same name. He is a being made up of ancient relics that was brought to life by Doctor Vargas as a way to combat the Goblin threat.

Name: Knives Chau
Summary: Knives Chau is a protagonist in Scott Pilgrim graphic novel series. Introduced as a 17-year-old Chinese-Canadian student, she began dating Scott Pilgrim after the two encountered one another on a public transit bus. Originally a calm and kind girl, Knives quickly fell in love with Scott early into their relationship, which would escalate into pure obsession after he cheated on her with Ramona Flowers.

Name: Koakuma
Summary: Koakuma is a small devil that serves Patchouli Knowledge. Almost nothing is known about her.

Name: Koji Koda (Anima)
Summary: Koji Koda (口田甲司 Kōda Kōji), also known as Anima (アニマ Anima), is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero. He is a very shy and timid person despite his large and imposing appearance, and rarely speaks, even to his classmates and prefers to use sign language to communicate.

Name: Koopa Troopa
Summary: The Koopa are a group of turtle-like creatures that inhabit the Mushroom Kingdom.

Name: Korin
Summary: Korin is a wise cat who is over 800 years old that lives atop Korin Tower. He is one of the martial arts teacher of Goku as well as Master Roshi. His teachings include anticipating the opponent's movements and reducing the needless movements of one's own body.

Name: Kosuzu Motoori
Summary: Kosuzu Motoori (本居 小鈴, Motoori Kosuzu) is the main character of the print work Forbidden Scrollery. She lives in the Human Village and serves as a worker of the Suzunaan book renter.

Name: Koyori Hakui (Holo no Graffiti)
Summary: Koyori Hakui is a scientist and a coyotegirl. She's the self-proclaimed "brains of the operation" of Secret Society holoX and is in charge of R&D. She possesses infinite curiosity and an insatiable thirst for knowledge, which pushes her to sometimes deliberately mess with people just to see how they react, including her fellow members. She's prideful about her creations, but her skill as a researcher is truly genuine.

Name: Krillin (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''23rd Budōkai''' | '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Potential Unlocked by Guru''' | '''Cell Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Krusty the Clown (Fortnite)
Summary: Krusty the Clown, or just Krusty, is a Boss character that can be found during second storm at one of his branded locations. He sports his signature weapon of Krusty's Mr. Blasty to take Loopers down.[1]

Name: Kuarusepusu
Summary: Kuarusepusu are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.4.

Name: Kulu-Ya-Ku
Summary: Kulu-Ya-Ku are Bird Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Kuma
Summary: Kuma (クマ; literally meaning "Bear") is the name of two characters within the Tekken series, both of which were bears and bodyguards to Heihachi Mishima. Kuma II is the son of the original Kuma, who died of old age sometime after the second King of Iron Fist Tournament.

Name: Kuro (One Piece)
Summary: nan

Name: Kuroobi
Summary: Kuroobi is a ray fishman, first mate of the Arlong Pirates as well as a former member of the Sun Pirates. He is a 40th rank practitioner of Fishman Island Karate. Though similar to his captain in their disdain of humans in general, he has some respect for those whose strength impressed him but still will act cruel overall. He is a very cautious person, as he's the only one to not trust Nami, and was proven to be right.

Name: Kurumu Kurono
Summary: Kurumu is a Succubus and a third-year student at Yōkai Academy. Kurumu initially planned to enslave all the boys at the academy, until she met Tsukune and Moka and the following incident, she became convinced that Tsukune was her "fateful mate", and planned to win his heart without the use of her powers. Kurumu later becomes one of the most prominent supporting characters and proactively involved in the adventures.

Name: Kuyo
Summary: Tier 9-A | 8-C | At least 8-B

Name: Kyle and Ken Katayanagi
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C | At least High 8-C

Name: Kyoka Jiro (Earphone Jack)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Kyoka Jiro (耳郎響香 Jirō Kyōka) is a student at U.A. High, training to become a Pro Hero. She is known as Earphone Jack (イヤホンジャック Iyahon Jakku).

Name: Kyouko Kasodani
Summary: Kyouko Kasodani is one of the last Yamabiko of Gensokyo. Due to her species' reliance on people's belief about mountain echoes, they have come near extinction even in Gensokyo due to the growing scientific knowledge of the true reasons behind the echoes created by mountains.

Name: Laboon
Summary: Laboon is an Island Whale native to the West Blue, and a close friend and companion to Brook and the Rumbar Pirates when he was a baby. Due to the dangers of the Grand Line, Laboon was told to stay near Reverse Mountain and promised him that they would come back after two or three years once they've finished their adventure. The Rumbar Piraters were killed during their journey, and Laboon waited for fifty years without knowledge of what their fate was.

Name: Lagiacrus
Summary: Lagiacrus are a variety of Leviathan introduced in Monster Hunter 3. They are feared by sailors as the "Lords of the Seas" and are the apex predators of their aquatic environment.

Name: Lan Fan
Summary: Lan Fan (ランファン, Ranfan) is a retainer of the Xing Empire's Yao Clan, a personal bodyguard of Prince Ling Yao and the grandchild of Ling's senior bodyguard, Fu. Fiercely loyal to her prince, Lan Fan's devotion to Ling borders on romantic infatuation, as insults to his name cause her to fly into a rage (overwhelming her better judgment and dulling her usually sharp combat abilities) and she becomes flustered when unmasked in his presence.

Name: Lancer (RWBY)
Summary: Lancers are large hornet-like Creatures of Grimm. There are two types: a smaller, more common version called a Warrior Drone and a larger variation known as a Queen Lancer.

Name: Layla Prismriver
Summary: Layla is the fourth and youngest daughter of the Prismriver family. Orphaned after a mishap with her father, each of the 4 daughters went on their path. Only Layla stayed, not willing to leave the mansion that had held much of her memories. Using her powers, she created three poltergeists that resembled her three older sisters, and afterwards, disappeared, alongside the mansion and her three creations.

Name: Legiana
Summary: Legiana are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Lena Sabrewing (2017)
Summary: Lena is a major character in the reboot of Ducktales. Serving as a spy for Magica De Spell after she was trapped in Scrooge McDuck's Number One Dime, she befriended Webby Vanderquack in order to steal the dime, only to be morally swayed by her friendship with Webby in order to fight back against Magica. After being trapped in the Shadow World by Magica, she was eventually freed with the help of Webby and her new friend, Violet Sabrewing.

Name: Leon S. Kennedy
Summary: Leon Scott Kennedy is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil horror media franchise by Capcom. He debuted as one of the two playable protagonists of the video game Resident Evil 2. Leon later returned as the main character of Resident Evil 4 and as one of the protagonists in Resident Evil Darkside Chronicles and Resident Evil 6.

Name: Leonardo Lionheart
Summary: Leonardo Lionheart is a supporting antagonist in RWBY and the Headmaster of Haven Academy. Formerly a trusted member of Ozpin's inner circle, he has turned to Salem's side as a spy, out of fear of the latter, who he feels cannot be defeated, a decision he is implied to regret. On the surface, Leonardo Lionheart demonstrated a rather polite and jovial persona and genuinely came off as a well-meaning and compassionate man. He was also shown to be easily startled and seemed to be somewhat timid. Despite this, he was willing to argue with people like Qrow Branwen and seemed unafraid to speak his mind to his fellow Huntsman. Lionheart also showed to be less impulsive than Qrow, and was also quite perceptive.

Name: Letty Whiterock
Summary: Letty Whiterock (レティ・ホワイトロック) is a seasonal youkai who's only seen during winter. She seems fittingly cold towards most of the humans she meets and is feared by humans as she is known to freeze them.

Name: Lie Ren
Summary: Lie Ren, more commonly referred to as Ren, is a student at Beacon Academy and a member of Team JNPR. His weapon of choice is a pair of green automatic pistols which have blades attached to them, named StormFlower. He and Nora are long-time friends, though he is the exact opposite of her, as he is mostly quiet, mellow and mature.

Name: Lily White
Summary: Lily White is a fairy representing spring. Her favorite hobby seems to be celebrating and announcing Spring.

Name: Ling Yao
Summary: Lin: If you're going to stand around and mope, then you should give me back this body. I'll take us back to Xing and become Emperor- then you'll be rid of that feeling of emptiness! Greed: Lord of a country, huh? Lin: Pretty grand, right? Greed: Hah! Screw that! You're still thinking small! If we're going to do that... why not shoot for lord of the entire world instead?

Name: Lisa Simpson
Summary: Lisa Marie Simpson is a main character in The Simpsons. She is a highly intelligent 8-year-old girl who serves as the voice of reason in her family. Lisa is the eldest daughter and middle child of the Simpson family.

Name: Llama (Minecraft)
Summary: Llamas are neutral mobs that spawn in herds and are found in Savanna Plateaus and Extreme Hills biomes.

Name: Lola Pop
Summary: Lola Pop is a playable character in ARMS. She is one of the rare inheritors of ARMS in the world, where she is able to extend her arms out. Lola is a street performer in Via Dolce, Italy, of which she hopes to win the ARMS Grand Prix so that she can start up her own circus.

Name: Lord Tirek
Summary: Lord Tirek is the sixth main villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, acting as the main antagonist for the season four finale Twilight's Kingdom.

Name: Ludroth
Summary: Ludroth are Leviathans introduced Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Lumpy
Summary: Lumpy is the school snake of Springfield Elementary. Lumpy was a frequent predator of Springfield's children, to the point where the school handbook had a clause exempting the school from liability if Milhouse was eaten.

Name: Luna Child
Summary: Luna Child (ルナチャイルド) is a fairy and one of the members of the Three Fairies of Light, composed of her, Sunny Milk, and Star Sapphire.

Name: Lunar Capital
Key: '''Basic Infantry | Higher Technology and High Ranking Members | Gods'''
Summary: The Lunar Capital (月の都, Tsuki no Miyako) is an extremely powerful and advanced civilization on the Moon of the Touhou Project universe. They used to be humans living on Earth. However, their leader, Lord Tsukuyomi, wanted him and his kind to escape the impurity of Earth. They did so by colonizing the moon, an otherwise untouched and pure land, where they could live a completely pure life.

Name: Lunasa Prismriver
Summary: Lunasa Prismriver (ルナサ・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lyrica and Merlin, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the violin. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Lunasa.

Name: Lust
Summary: Lust (ラスト, Rasuto) was the first Homunculus to appear in the Fullmetal Alchemist series, playing a significant part in the early chapters before she is killed by Roy Mustang. She is usually partnered with Gluttony to whom she appears to have a particular, almost motherly, closeness. Her Ouroboros mark is located on her sternum, just above her breasts.

Name: Lyrica Prismriver
Summary: Lyrica Prismriver (リリカ・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lunasa and Merlin, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the keyboard. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Lyrica.

Name: M. Bison
Key: '''Base''' | '''Empowered by the Psycho Drive''' | '''Empowered by the Black Moons''' | '''Street Fighter VI'''
Summary: For unknown reasons, the child who grew up to be M. Bison (Vega in Japan) murdered his parents in cold blood before he was adopted by a tribe of Romani who taught him the art of Soul Power, an ancient art that allows the user to manipulate one's soul. Bison quickly mastered Soul Power and used it to expel all of the good and humanity out of him, turning him into an egotistical psychopath. He then evolved Soul Power into Psycho Power, took on the title M. Bison, and organized a group of mercenaries to help him succeed in global conquest.

Name: Maggie Simpson
Summary: Maggie Simpson is one of the main protagonists of The Simpsons. She is the daughter of Marge Simpson and Homer Simpson. She is 1-year old and their youngest child. Most of the time, Maggie is seen chewing on her pacifier or attempting to walk. She mostly seems like an innocent and sweet baby who just wants her family to stay happy, to learn, and to suck on her iconic pacifier. However, she also on some occasions shows far more self-awareness than she lets on. Several times having wielded different guns, intentionally tried to shoot Mr. Burns a second time, saving her family from The Mob, and several other threats.

Name: Magma Cube
Summary: The Magma Cube is a monster found in the Nether. It is a sentient cube of Magma, capable of duplicating.

Name: Maguma
Summary: Maguma (マグマ) is a giant walrus-like kaiju that appeared in the 1962 Toho film, Gorath.

Name: Mahito
Summary: Mahito (真ま人ひと?) is the secondary antagonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is a Cursed Spirit allied with Suguru Geto, Jogo, Hanami, and several others. Their ultimate goal is eradicating humanity and ultimately replacing the population with Cursed Spirits.

Name: Maiko Plasma
Summary: Maiko Plasma (舞妓プラズマ, Maiko Purazuma) is a supportive monster, specializing in electricity and lightning-based attacks, and a Tiger level threat that first appeared alongside her partner Electric Catfish Man during the Monster Raid, assigned by Gyoro-Gyoro to attack D-City

Name: Major Bomber
Summary: Major Bomber is an extremely large Demoman giant, although this robot fires grenades that are always critical hits.

Name: Major League Scout
Summary: The Major League Scout is a bigger, badder version of the Minor League Scout, with the same loadout, though the Major League Scout can shoot its baseballs often, hitting a ball every two seconds or so. The Major League Scout moves at the same speed as its smaller counterparts, but not quite as fast as the Super Scout. Nonetheless, the Major League Scout can often be the cause of a round failure, considering its speed and ability to stun players.

Name: Major Metallitron
Summary: Major Metallitron (メタリック軍曹) is an antagonist who appears in the Dragon Ball. He is an android created by the Red Ribbon Army, and Goku's second challenge in the Muscle Tower.

Name: Maki Zenin
Summary: nan

Name: Malfestio
Summary: Malfestios are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Manga Fukidashi (Comicman)
Summary: Manga Fukidashi (吹ふき出だし漫まん我が Fukidashi Manga), also known as Comicman (コミックマン Komikkuman), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Mannequins
Summary: Created to be the perfect army, Mannequins are zombie-like beings created by Alchemy to protect Father and the top dogs of the Amestrian military. However, when they are finally awakened they run wild among its Central City, being a threat against almost all parties involved in a coup d'etat.

Name: Marcy Wu
Summary: Marcy Wu: The day we left, your birthday, they told me my dad got a new job out of state. They're making me move away, they were gonna tear us apart! Anne Boonchuy: Marcy... Marcy Wu: I... I found the box. I had no idea it would actually work, but it did. It sent us to a place where we'd never have to grow apart, where the three of us could friends forever together! Anne Boonchuy: How could you?! I've been missing my parents, my life! Marcy Wu: But look at how much fun we've had. Look at how much you've both grown. Look at Sprig. I gave you this, I gave you everything! I just didn't want to be alone.

Name: Marge Simpson
Summary: Marge Simpson is one of the main protagonists of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons. She is a loving mother to her son Bart, and her daughters Lisa and Maggie. As well, married to her husband Homer Simpson. She is a stay-at-home mom often acts as the voice of reason and logic when her husband or the town, in general, is getting into strange or stupid situations. She is generally very loving towards her kids and husband and is willing to almost anything to protect and help them. She is an extremely dedicated and hard worker. Whether she is working at home, taking a job as a police officer, or helping her children. She always puts her best effort into anything she does.

Name: Maria Calavera
Summary: Maria Calavera, known in her youth as The Grimm Reaper is a supporting character who appears in Volume 6 of RWBY. While she seems to just be a frail old woman who tagged along on Ruby's crew's journey to Atlas due to a train crash, she is actually one of the most renowned huntresses in her time, someone who inspired the likes of Qrow to choose that path in life.

Name: Marrow Amin
Summary: Marrow Amin is a supporting character in RWBY. He is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. Marrow is described as mischievous in personality, having been kicked out of an undisclosed place at least three times in the past. As the novice member of the Ace-Ops, he is also the most naive and childish of the group, having to be 'babysat' by Harriet Bree. A large aspect of Marrow's motivation to have become a Huntsman in the past was that many said he couldn't. However, beating those odds, Marrow was able to rise to the top of the ranks, becoming an Ace-Op.

Name: Masami Yoshida
Summary: Masami Yoshida (吉田正美 Yoshida Masami) is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a cloud student at Elmore Junior High. Masami comes from a very rich family; her dad is the owner of the Rainbow Factory and her mom has affiliation there. Along with her elemental abilities, this makes Masami one of the most feared and popular students at school.

Name: Mashirao Ojiro (Tailman)
Summary: Mashirao Ojiro (尾白猿夫 Ojiro Mashirao), also known as Tailman (テイルマン Teiruman), is a student at U.A. High School from Class 1-A training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Master Mummy
Summary: Master Mummy is a playable character in ARMS. Like the other ARMS fighters, Master Mummy was born with extendable ARMS, a rare trait, which allows him to enter the Grand Prix. He had apparently risen from the dead in the Mausoleum, and is looking for answers towards his past and finding his family. He hopes entering the Grand Prix and winning will send them towards him.

Name: Master Roshi
Key: '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Tournament of Power'''
Summary: nan

Name: Max Brass
Summary: Max Brass is a playable character in ARMS. He is an ARMS veteran and the greatest champion ever to compete in the Grand Prix. Max Brass is also the head of the ARMS League (hence his nickname, "The Commish") and the organizer for the Grand Prix.

Name: May Chang
Summary: A very young Alchemist from the eastern country of Xing, May Chang is expert in Xing's own brand of alchemy, allowing her to heal people and use her abilities from afar. Just like Ling Yao, she one of the many princes and princesses born of the Xingese Emperor, and representing one of the weaker dynasties she comes to Amestris searching for the Philosopher's Stone, in hopes of obtaining the Emperor's favors.

Name: Mechamaru
Summary: The fact that a doll like you and not a human like me gets to live so carefree in the sun really pisses me off!

Name: Medic (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: What he lacks in compassion for the sick, respect for human dignity, and any sort of verifiable formal training in medicine, the Medic more than makes up for with a bottomless supply of giant needles and a trembling enthusiasm for plunging them into exposed flesh. Raised in Rottenburg, Germany during an era when the Hippocratic oath had been downgraded to an optional Hippocratic suggestion, the Medic considers healing a generally unintended side effect of satisfying his own morbid curiosity.

Name: Medicine Melancholy
Summary: Medicine Melancholy (メディスン・メランコリー) is a young doll youkai that lives on Nameless Hill surrounded by poisonous lily-of-the-valley flowers.

Name: Megasparkle Goomba
Summary: Megasparkle Goomba is a Goomba who gained the power of a Royal Sticker after Bowser shattered the Sticker Comet. When Paper Mario and Kersti reach his fortress, he attacks them along with fifteen other Goombas. During the battle, they merge into a giant Goomba, though they start flipping after being damaged enough. After the giant Megasparkle Goomba is defeated, the fifteen regular Goombas desert their leader, who is easily defeated by Mario.

Name: Megatron (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: Megatron is the leader of the decepticons. He left cybertron to chase after the Allspark, only to end up frozen on Earth. Depending on the version of the game, he would either face an Allspark amped Stascream, or he himself would be amped by the power of the Allspark.

Name: Megumi Fushiguro
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: Megumi Fushiguro (伏ふし黒ぐろ 恵めぐみ, Fushiguro Megumi?) is the deuteragonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Born into the Zenin clan, a prestigious family of jujutsu sorcerers, Megumi inherits the unique Ten Shadows Technique, which allows him to summon and control various shikigami using his cursed energy.

Name: Mei Hatsume
Summary: Mei Hatsume (発目明 Hatsume Mei) is a student attending U.A. High School's Department of Support from Class 1-H.

Name: Mei Mei
Summary: Mei Mei (冥冥めいめい?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. She is a Grade 1 Jujutsu sorcerer who works independently and only in exchange for money. She is also the older sister of Ui Ui and was a senpai of Satoru Gojo and Suguru Geto during their time at Jujutsu High.

Name: Melanie Malachite
Summary: Melanie Malachite is a character introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer. She and her twin sister Miltiades Malachite are seen working for Hei Xiong when they fight Yang Xiao Long. Melanie's weapons of choice are her heels.

Name: Mercury Black
Summary: Mercury Black is an antagonist in RWBY.

Name: Merlin Prismriver
Summary: Merlin Prismriver (メルラン・プリズムリバー) is one of the three Prismriver Sisters alongside her sisters Lunasa and Lyrica, a group of poltergeist musicians who perform magnificent music as the "Prismriver Ensemble". She plays the trumpet. She is not a ghost, instead being a magical construct created by her deceased sister, Layla, in the image of the original Merlin.

Name: Metal Gear RAY
Summary: A Metal Gear unit designed by the United States Navy for the purpose of destroying REX imitators before being stolen and redesigned by the Patriots, along with a whole bunch of other people who somehow got their hands on models. Raiden in his post-MSG4 years later fought a modified version of RAY.

Name: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus
Summary: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus is a Metal Gear featured in Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain. Created by Huey Emmerich and funded by the Soviet Union, Sahelanthropus was in actuality a project overseen by XOF, the covert strike force and at-the-time usurper of the shadow government known as The Patriots. Encountered by Venom Snake several times in Afghanistan, he managed to best the machine multiple times, eventually capturing it after the death of Skull Face, the leader of XOF. Snake kept it at Mother Base for some time, until it was stolen by Eli with the help of the Third Child, who took it to Central Africa, where he, the remnants of XOF and Venom Snake with his Diamond Dogs private military company, fought to reclaim the weapon. Snake eventually won the day, but Sahelanthropus was destroyed in battle.

Name: Mezo Shoji (Tentacole)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Mezo Shoji (障子目蔵 Shōji Mezō), also known as Tentacole (テンタコル Tentakoru), is a student attending U.A. in order to become a Pro Hero. Despite his intimidating appearance, he is quite a friendly and gentle person who will work well with anyone. He is not the type to hold grudges and displays no ill will towards those who unwillingly harm him.

Name: Midas (Fortnite)
Summary: Midas is a Legendary skin and main antagonist of Fortnite Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the leader of Ghost and a double agent for Shadow. He is based on the Greek mythology, King Midas. At the end of Chapter 2 Season 2, he becomes Cyclo, the Defiant to the Storm. At the start of Chapter 2 Season 3, he gets attacked by a shark and survived. Around Chapter 2 Season 4, he becomes Shadow Midas.

Name: Mii Fighter
Summary: The Mii Fighters are warriors based on the customizable Mii avatars.

Name: Mikita (Miss Valentine)
Summary: Mikata is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works. Her codename was Miss Valentine and her partner was Mr. 5.

Name: Millennian
Summary: Millennian Io (ミレニアン) is an alien kaiju that appeared in the 1999 Godzilla film, Godzilla 2000: Millennium.

Name: Miltiades Malachite
Summary: Miltiades "Miltia" Malachite is a character introduced in the "Yellow" Trailer. She and her twin sister, Melanie Malachite, are seen working for Hei Xiong at his club, where they fight Yang Xiao Long. Miltia's weapons of choice are her claws.

Name: Min Min
Summary: Min Min is a playable fighter in ARMS. Like the other ARMS fighters, she has inherited the mutation of ARMS, of which have turned her ARMS into extendable strands of noodles.

Name: Mina Ashido (Pinky)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Mina Ashido (芦戸三奈 Ashido Mina), also known as Pinky (ピンキー Pinkī), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. She is cheerful and can be seen with a smile on her face most of the time. She is easily excited, but also very emotional and easily brought to tears in various situations, out of relief, out of sadness, and out of frustration. However, she is still very easygoing and sociable.

Name: Ministry of Right and Wrong
Summary: The Ministry of Right and Wrong is the organization that manages the entire system regarding Souls and the afterlife in the Touhou Project series. Created in response to humanity's growing numbers, it is mainly composed of the many judges who deal with the deceased and of the leaders of Heaven, the Netherworld and the many hells.

Name: Minoriko Aki
Summary: Minoriko Aki is one of the two goddesses of autumn. Her job is to make harvest fruitful by helping farmers with their plantations.

Name: Mirio Togata (Lemillion)
Summary: Mirio Togata (通形ミリオ Tōgata Mirio), also known as Lemillion (ルミリオン Rumirion), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School.

Name: Miss Pauling
Summary: Miss Pauling is a loyal assistant to the Administrator. She performs a number of tasks, including unusual background reports, ordering and delivering goods, opening communication channels and murders. Miss Pauling generally conforms to the opinion of her employer for fear of incurring her anger, even if he does not necessarily agree with it. Despite the stern behavior of her boss, Miss Pauling insists that the Administrator "is not so bad when you get to know her." When pressed by the Administrator as to what exactly her friends are doing, she replies "Um. Go skateboarding ... look at weapons catalogs ... sometimes we just talk ..."

Name: Mizore Shirayuki
Summary: Mizore was introduced as an antagonist to Tsukune and Moka. However, she eventually became a friend and an ally. She later fell in love with Tsukune, and even wanted to marry him. She was rescued from a forced marriage by him. She participated in the final battle against Fairy Tale.

Name: Mizutsune
Summary: Mizutsune is a Leviathan first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Moe Szyslak
Summary: Moe Szyslak is the bartender in Springfield. He spends most of his time in his bar selling drinks to his usual customers and friends Homer, Lenny, Carol, and Barney. He as well is shown to run illegal practices like holding and selling animals like Pandas and Orcas in the back of his bar. He is a often sneaky and lazy bar keeper. Refusing to clean his bar, and pulling quick ones on his customers. However, he can and still does feel guilt and compassion towards his closer friends like Homer, and will go out of his way to help them.

Name: Moka Akashiya
Summary: Moka Akashiya (Akashiya Moka, 赤夜 萌香) is a vampiress in Yōkai Academy and the main female protagonist of the series. She serves as the primary love interest to Tsukune Aono, who is the sole human enrolled in an academy of monsters. She has an enchanted rosary that gives her a split personality; her outer persona is gentle, compassionate, and seemingly weaker than average monsters. In contrast, the inner persona is a bold and domineering vampire lady; she is also a remarkably strong fighter, even among vampires.

Name: Momo Yaoyorozu (Creati)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Momo Yaoyorozu (八百万百 Yaoyorozu Momo) is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training under the name, "The Everything Hero: Creati" (万物ヒーロー クリエイティ Banbutsu Hīrō Kurieiti). She is a very intelligent and dedicated person who acts as a natural leader. She is generally very level-headed and calm even in dangerous situations.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Monoblos
Summary: Monoblos are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Moonfish
Summary: Moonfish (ムーンフィッシュ Mūnfisshu) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and also part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He and the rest of his team serve as the main antagonists of the Forest Training Camp Arc.

Name: Mother of Thorns
Summary: Mother Of Thorns, also known as Doja Cat, is a boss appearing in Fortnite during the Fortnitemares event.

Name: Mr. Burns
Summary: Charles Montgomery Plantagenet Schicklgruber "Monty" Burns,[1] usually referred to as Mr. Burns, is a recurring character and antagonist in the animated television series The Simpsons, voiced initially by Christopher Collins, and currently by Harry Shearer. He is the evil, devious, greedy, and wealthy owner of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant and, by extension, Homer Simpson's boss. He is assisted at almost all times by Smithers, his loyal and sycophantic aide, adviser, confidant, and secret admirer. He is Springfield's richest, oldest, and most powerful citizen. His net worth has been stated to be in the billions and in one instance was pegged at exactly $1,800,037,022.[2]

Name: Mr. Chau
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C

Name: Mr. Compress
Summary: Atsuhiro Sako (迫圧紘 Sako Atsuhiro), also known as Mr. Compress (Mr.コンプレス Misutā Konpuresu), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. He is known for being one of the smartest villains in the world and acts as the brains of the League of Villains. His organization later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Muhammad Avdol
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Muhammad Avdol is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders.

Name: Musashi Goda
Summary: Musashi Goda (郷田武蕨, Gōda Musashi) is a student of Salt Middle School and the Body Improvement Club's President. He's a close friend of Mob.

Name: Mutants (Godzilla)
Summary: The Mutants are the genetic descendents of both humans and Xiliens. They were trained as a form of highly elite soldiers by the EDF under Commander Kumasaka. In Godzilla: Final Wars, all but Ozaki (and later Kazama) fell under the control of X. The most notable Mutant is Ozaki, who used his Keizer Energy to revive Godzilla.

Name: Mystia Lorelei
Summary: Mystia Lorelei (ミスティア・ローレライ) is an egocentric and outgoing night sparrow who roams the Youkai Trail in search of humans to frighten. She also manages a grilled lamprey stand, and is part of a punk rock band with Kyouko Kasodani named Choujuu Gigaku.

Name: Nam
Summary: Nam (ナム, Namu) is a warrior from a desert village that competes in World Martial Arts Tournaments. He fights in order to make life better for the people of his village. He makes appearances in the Dragon Ball manga and the anime Dragon Ball, as well as short cameo appearances in Dragon Ball Z and Dragon Ball GT.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Naobito Zenin
Summary: Naobito Zenin (禪ぜん院いん 直なお毘び人と, Zen'in Naobito?) is the 26th head of the Zen'in clan, renowned for being the fastest Jujutsu Sorcerer, besides Gojo, thanks to his Cursed Technique.

Name: Naoya Zenin
Summary: Naoya Zenin (禪院ぜんいん 直なお哉や, Zen'in Naoya?) is an antagonist in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was the youngest son of Naobito Zenin and believed himself to be the true heir of the Zenin Family. Naoya was also the head of the clan's elite unit of jujutsu sorcerers, the Hei.

Name: Nargacuga
Summary: Nargacuga are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Name: Narumi Yatadera
Summary: Narumi Yatadera is a former Jizo statue who became a magician from the Forest of Magic's influence. As she was a statue that gained life on it's own, she's a bit like a golem. She serves as the Stage 4 boss of Hidden Star in Four Seasons.

Name: Nazrin
Summary: Nazrin (ナズーリン) is a mouse youkai who's a skilled dowser and the leader of a great number of mice. As the leader of many mice, she often employs them to search for things for her; though if she were to ask them to find food, it would most likely be gone by the time they returned.

Name: Ned Flanders
Summary: Ned Flanders is a supporting character in the animated series, The Simpsons. He is the extremely religious next-door neighbor of the Simpson family. He is the well-mannered widower of Maude and father of Rod and Todd. He immensely worships God and is a strict follower of the Bible.

Name: NegaScott
Summary: NegaScott, also known as Nega Scott, is Scott Pilgrim's alter ego and dark side, and represents his forgotten past mistakes. He has no lines, and has only appeared in a few panels of the comic. NegaScott is the manifestation of all of Scott's callousness, spite, faults, and flaws, and rather than accepting them and himself, he runs from them, thus creating this physical persona. Though NegaScott doesn't appear that often in the series, he can be considered a major character because of what he represents.

Name: Neito Monoma (Phantom Thief)
Summary: Neito Monoma (物間寧人 Monoma Neito), also known as Phantom Thief (ファントムシーフ Fantomu Shīfu), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School. Flamboyant with an inferiority-superiority complex towards the more famous Class 1-A, Monoma is determined to one-up Class 1-A at every turn, never hesitating to rub any sort of mistake or mishap in their face while ignoring his own many flaws.

Name: Nejire Hado (Nejire Chan)
Summary: Nejire Hado (波動ねじれ Hadō Nejire), also known as Nejire Chan (ネジレちゃん Nejirechan), is a recently graduated hero from the U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Nemuno Sakata
Summary: Nemuno Sakata is a Yamanba living in the Youkai mountain. She dwells mostly alone there, ocasionally kidnapping children and raising them as a Yamanba.

Name: Nemuri Kayama (Midnight)
Summary: Nemuri Kayama (香山睡 Kayama Nemuri, also known as Midnight (ミッドナイト Middonaito), is a Pro Hero and faculty member at U.A. High School. She teaches Modern Hero Art History and was the Chief Referee of the U.A. Sports Festival for first year students as well.

Name: Neon Katt
Summary: Neon Katt is a member of Team FNKI, of Atlas Academy. She participated in the Vytal Festival tournament, fighting against Yang Xiao Long and Weiss Schnee during the doubles round in the episode "Never Miss a Beat".

Name: Neopolitan
Summary: Neopolitan, better known as Neo, is a major antagonist in RWBY and the former partner of Roman Torchwick.

Name: Neptune Vasilias
Summary: Neptune Vasilias is a character in RWBY and a member of Team SSSN.

Name: Nevermore (RWBY)
Summary: Nevermores are large avian Creatures of Grimm first encountered during the Beacon Academy Initiation in RWBY Volume 1.

Name: Nibelsnarf
Summary: Nibelsnarf is a Leviathan introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Nick Ramos (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Nine (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Nine (ナイン Nain) was a villain and the primary antagonist of My Hero Academia: Heroes Rising. Having contracted an illness, Nine proved himself to be compatible with All For One's Quirk Factor, allowing him to obtain a weaker version of All For One. With it, he went to Nabu Island and tried to steal a Quirk that would have cured his illness, but he failed in his task.

Name: Ninja Murasaki
Summary: Ninja Murasaki (ムラサキ曹長) is a secondary antagonist who appears in Dragon Ball. He is the second-in-command of Muscle Tower under General White.

Name: Ninjara
Summary: Ninjara is a playable character in ARMS. He, like the other ARMS characters has been gifted with the powers of ARMS, making him able to stretch his own arms to abnormal degrees.

Name: Nirengeki Shoda
Summary: Nirengeki Shoda (庄田二連撃 Shōda Nirengek), also known as Mines (マインズ Mainzu), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Nizo Okada
Summary: Nizo Okada (岡田 似蔵, Okada Nizou), also known as Nizo the Butcher, or Manslayer Nizo (Hito Kiri Nizou) was a blind assassin and a master of Iai jutsu, which are techniques for drawing a sword. He was a member of the Kiheitai, an extremist Joui faction bent on causing world destruction, and would become fused with the Benizakura bio-mechanical sword, which would ultimately take over his body completely and lead to his defeat. He is the main antagonist of the Infant Strife Arc and Benizakura Arc.

Name: No Heart
Summary: No Heart is the primary antagonist of Nelvana's Care Bears cartoon series. He is a wicked sorcerer whose goal is to rid the world of any and all love and caring. Though his creations are dastardly and his plans thorough, he is thwarted time and again by the Care Bears' intervention and the incompetence of his own henchmen. Although he is an expert in his craft, he is constantly irritable and will often snap at the slightest hindrance to himself and his objective.

Name: Nobara Kugisaki
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: I love the me that dresses up and looks beautiful! I love the me that's strong! I'm Nobara Kugisaki!

Name: Nora Valkyrie
Summary: Nora Valkyrie is a Huntress-in-Training at Beacon Academy. Her weapon is Magnhild, a grenade launcher that can be converted into a war hammer. Nora is a happy-go-lucky, bubbly, and cheerful young girl who displays boundless enthusiasm and never fails to let it show. Her excitable nature makes her rather hyperactive and hasty. Even in combat, Nora retains her joyful personality, but she is seen to stay focused when actually fighting. Despite her generally cute personality, Nora does seem to have a love of battle, much like Ruby. She may be a little extreme when it comes to dealing with issues, as her suggested solution to help Jaune Arc with Cardin Winchester's bullying was breaking Cardin's legs. As all Non-Grimm, living creatures do, she has an Aura that can help her in many situations and her Semblance can turn the tide of battle to her favor.

Name: Noritoshi Kamo
Summary: If I am no longer needed, then let me set my life ablaze, so that at the very least, my companions' lives will burn brightly on my ashes.

Name: Nuckelavee (RWBY)
Summary: The Nuckelavee was a large, horse-like Creature of Grimm that first appeared in "Kuroyuri". It served as the main antagonist of RWBY Volume 4.

Name: Ochako Uraraka (Uravity)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Ochako Uraraka (麗日お茶子 Uraraka Ochako), also known as Uravity (ウラビティ Urabiti), is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training assisting to the U.A. High School.

Name: Odogaron
Summary: Odogaron are Fanged Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Ogi Zenin
Summary: Ogi Zenin (禪ぜん院いん扇おうぎ, Zen'in Ōgi?) is the father of Maki and Mai as well as the brother of Naobito. He is mostly unknown for the majority of the series and considered inferior to Naobito in regards to the quality of his children as jujutsu sorcerers.

Name: Olivier Mira Armstrong
Summary: Major General Olivier Mira Armstrong (オリヴィエ・ミラ・アームストロング, Orivie Mira Āmusutorongu) is the primary heir to the illustrious Armstrong family, the older sister of Alex Louis Armstrong as well as the commanding officer charged with the protection of Amestris' northern border at Fort Briggs.

Name: Optimus Prime (2007 DS Game)
Summary: Optimus helped to advise his warriors in some of their mission to try locate the Allspark. Arriving on Earth, Optimus met up with the other Autobots to give further commands to his troops. During the final battle against Megatron, Megatron set Allspark drones on Prime, but Create-A-Bot, who tailed Prime to the fight sacrificed himself to weaken Megatron. Galvanized by the rookie's sacrifice, Optimus fought Megatron in a final duel. After besting Megatron, Optimus decided the Allspark was worth sacrificing to stop Megatron. Megatron defeated, Optimus commended the dying young Autobot and swore he would always be remembered as a war hero, and sent out an interstellar message to any Autobots living among the stars to join them.

Name: Oscar Pine
Summary: Oscar Pine was an ordinary farmboy who lived with his aunt in Mistral for most of his life. On one fateful day, he discovered that his soul has been irrevocably merged with that of Professor Ozpin, the Headmaster of Beacon Academy, who urged Oscar to leave home and head to Haven Academy.

Name: Ozai
Summary: Ozai was the Fire Lord and absolute ruler of the Fire Nation during the final years of the Hundred Year War. He was the second son of Azulon and Ilah, the younger brother of Iroh, uncle of Lu Ten, husband to Ursa, the father of Prince Zuko and Princess Azula, and grandfather to Izumi. Ozai was a firebending master and, prior to the ending of the War, was believed to have been one of the most powerful firebenders in the world.

Name: Paolumu
Summary: Paolumu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Pariapuria
Summary: Pariapuria are Flying Wyverns that was introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 5.0.

Name: Patchouli Knowledge
Summary: Patchouli Knowledge is a very smart, anemic and asthmatic magician from the Scarlet Devil Mansion.
