As opposed to the rest of the inhabitants, she is neither an employee or relative of Remilia Scarlet, instead being a close friend whose role is to cause and solve problems. She spends most of her time in the mansion's library reading and writing magic books. It seems that she's capable of very powerful magic of all kinds, using many elements in a single spell, but due to her anemia, asthma and general poor health she's often unable to recite her spells.

Name: Peace Walker
Summary: Peace Walker, also known as Basilisk, was a walking nuclear-armed AI weapon developed by Huey Emmerich and Strangelove. In 1973, CIA Station Chief Hot Coldman commissioned the creation of Peace Walker in order to fulfill his vision of the "perfect nuclear deterrent".

Name: Pearl (One Piece)
Summary: Pearl the Iron Wall is the commander of the Krieg Pirates' second unit.

Name: Peely
Summary: Peely is one of many characters in Fortnite. Peely became a robot in Fortnite's Season X called P-1000. In Season 2, Chapter 2, he becomes an agent named, Agent Peely.

Name: Penny Fitzgerald
Summary: Penny Fitzgerald is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a shape-shifting fairy, formerly a peanut, who is in Miss Simian's class in Elmore Junior High.

Name: Penny Polendina
Summary: Penny Polendina is a character introduced in the episode "The Stray," when she was found lying on the ground after Weiss Schnee crashed into her whilst chasing after Sun Wukong. Penny speaks robotically, behaves erratically, and is overly active in general. All her actions and emotional states were rather extreme and overacted. When Ruby Rose unintentionally made an unconditional offer of friendship, Penny seemed both immensely pleased and somewhat surprised.

Name: Pet Shop
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Pet Shop is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is a trusted pet of Dio Brando and the guardian of his mansion.

Name: Peter Port
Summary: Peter Port is a character in RWBY. A professor at Beacon Academy, he is first seen in "The Badge and The Burden" teaching the Grimm Studies class, with Team RWBY and Jaune Arc from Team JNPR being present in his class. His weapon of choice is Blowhard, a blunderbuss outfitted with the blades of a battle axe.

Name: Phantoms (Touhou Project)
Summary: Phantoms are a kind of spirit in the Touhou Project series. They are the embodiment of the spirits of things, be it plants, humans or otherwise. They are not to be confused with ghosts.

Name: Pharynx
Summary: Pharynx a minion in the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic series.

Name: Piers Niavans
Summary: Piers Nivans was a combat operative for the North American Branch of the BSAA, assigned to the SOU (Special Operations Unit). Nivans served under Captain Chris Redfield during the investigation into the incident at the Marhawa School; the 2012 Edonian Civil War and the 2013 campaign in China.

Name: Piglin Brute
Summary: The Piglin Brute is a potent foe wandering and guarding the Bastion Remnant, although appearing rarely. They allow to spot the subtle differences of The Player with gold equipment, thus allowing them to eliminate The Player unlike the Piglin fellows.

Name: Pillager
Summary: The Pillager is a type of Illager in Minecraft. It wields a crossbow and attacks players and villagers at long range. It spawns in outposts, patrols, and raids.

Name: Pirako Chin
Summary: Pirako Chin (椿 平子, Chin Pirako) was first introduced as a hitokiri (aka manslayer) trying to join the Yorozuya and Otose's "faction", but soon she was revealed to be the daughter of Jirocho Doromizu, and she had the intention of making him the lone ruler of Kabuki-chou. She played a central role in the 4 Devas arc. She is the secondary antagonist of Kabukicho Four Devas Arc.

Name: Pirate Robot
Summary: The Pirate Robot (海賊ロボ) is a powerful combat robot from Dragon Ball created by pirates to protect the lair where they keep their treasure.

Name: Pokaradon
Summary: Pokaradon are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G1.

Name: Pokio
Summary: Pokios are pheasant-like enemies who first premiered in Super Mario Odyssey. They mostly reside in Bowser's Kingdom, though there are a select few that make their home in both Seaside Kingdom and the Darker Side of the Moon. They act as one of the many captures Mario can control with the help of Cappy and was an essential tool to defeat the Broodals' RoboBrood.

Name: Polar Bear (Minecraft)
Summary: The Polar Bear is a wild animal from the Tundra and Taiga biomes.

Name: Pony Tsunotori (Rocketti)
Summary: Pony Tsunotori (角取ポニー Tsunotori Ponī), also known as Rocketti (ロケッティ Roketti), is a student in Class 1-B of U.A. High School, and is training to become a Pro Hero. She comes from the United States, because of this she has some difficulty speaking Japanese.

Name: Popeye
Summary: First introduced Dice Island, a story arc in the comic strip Thimble Theater in 1928, Popeye the Sailor Man would later become the main focus of the strip, as well becoming as one of the most iconic comic and cartoon characters of all time. "Borned to the sea" near the bay of Santa Monica, Popeyes' childhood was hard. The ship he was born on was rocked by a massive typhoon just moments after his birth, though his family was ultimately unharmed by the event. Growing up, both his father, "Poopdeck Pappy" and his unnamed mother left his life at a young age. Eventually, Popeye decided to join the military. Despite his rough and gruff appearance, Popeye was a good guy who hated bullies and defended the weak.

Name: Pride
Summary: Pride (プライド, Puraido) was the first Homunculus that Father created, and resembles his original form. He masquerades as Selim Bradley (セリム・ブラッドレイ, Serimu Buraddorei), the adoptive son of King Bradley, and is the final one of the seven Homunculi to be revealed.

Name: Primid
Summary: The Primids are the most basic infantry force of the Subspace Army. While they are one of the weakest, they are also the most common by far, often coming in huge groups.

Name: Principal Skinner
Summary: Seymour Skinner, also known as Principal Skinner, is the principal of Springfield Elementary School. He has a passion for education which is consistently challenged by a lack of school funds, incompetent teachers and unenthusiastic students, the most notable being Bart Simpson. He is generally strict on discipline, likely stemming from his time serving in the army, but is otherwise quite nervous and fidgety.

Name: Puar
Summary: Puar is a character introduced in Dragon Ball. He is Yamcha’s loyal companion and fellow desert thief, as well as Oolong’s old classmate from the Southern Transformation Kindergarten. He is an ally of the Z Fighters.

Name: Pukei-Pukei
Summary: Pukei-Pukei is a Bird Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World. They can be found in the Ancient Forest and Wildspire Waste.

Name: Pyro
Summary: The Pyro is a mumbling pyromaniac of indeterminate origin who has a burning passion for all things fire related. The Pyro appears to be insane and delusional, living in a utopian fantasy world known as Pyroland.

Name: Pyrrha Nikos
Summary: Pyrrha Nikos is a character in RWBY. A famous, level-headed, and highly skilled student at Beacon Academy and a member of Team JNPR, she wields a rifle/javelin/sword combination weapon called Miló and a shield called Akoúo̱. Prior to her tenure at Beacon, she graduated from Sanctum Academy with highest honors and had a record number of wins at the Mistral Regional Tournament. More so, she is seen as a warrior who's seemingly untouchable to the point where she is believed to be "fated for victory".

Name: Qrow Branwen
Summary: Qrow Branwen is the younger twin brother of Raven Branwen, biological uncle of Yang Xiao Long and honorary uncle of Ruby Rose. He is a former member of the Branwen Tribe as well as a former teacher at Signal Academy.

Name: Quiet
Summary: Quiet was a female assassin during the 1980s. Originally an assassin for XOF, Quiet later defected to Diamond Dogs after being defeated by Venom Snake. Quiet can only breathe and drink through her skin. As a result, she can only wear a minimal amount of clothing due to the parasite-treatment she received as a result of being severely burned while trying to kill Big Boss during a hospital raid. After being defeated by Venom Snake in Afghanistan following a tense sniper duel, Quiet became a prisoner at Mother Base until she was allowed to accompany Venom Snake on missions.

Name: Qurupeco
Summary: Qurupecos are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Radobaan
Summary: Radobaans are Brute Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Raiden (Metal Gear)
Key: '''Metal Gear Solid 2''' | '''Metal Gear Solid 4''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Updated Patriots Cyborg Body)''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Custom Cyborg Body)'''
Summary: Vamp: You, too... Immortal? Raiden: No. I just don't fear death.

Name: Raika
Summary: Tier: 8-A

Name: Ramona Flowers
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, weapons are higher against certain types of people, 8-B with the Power of Love, Varies with Subspace manipulation

Name: Rampage (Michael Bay)
Summary: Rampage is a Decepticon and member of the Constructicons. He aided in Megatron's resurrection and later went to Egypt to aid the Fallen and the rest of the Decepticons. He took Sam's captured parents and used them to try and get the Matrix of Leadership though he was killed by Bumblebee in the process.

Name: Rathalos
Key: '''Base/HC/Azure/HC Azure/Destruction Wyvern Rathalos''' | '''Flame Rathalos''' | '''Silver/HC Silver Rathalos''' | '''Dreadking Rathalos''' | '''Zenith Rathalos''' | '''Zerureusu'''
Summary: The flagship monster of the entire Monster Hunter series and one of only two monsters to have appeared in every game in the series. Rathalos is a type of monster known as a Flying Wyvern, and it uses the fire element as its primary weapon.

Name: Rathian
Key: '''Base/HC/Conflagration/Scorching Heat/Pink Rathian''' | '''HC Pink Rathian''' | '''Gold/HC Gold Rathian'''
Summary: Rathian is the female counterpart to Rathalos, and one of only two monsters, together with Rathalos, to appear in every game in the Monster Hunter franchise.

Name: Ravage (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ravage is a Decepticon scout and partner of Soundwave. He was sent down to Earth with a group of microcons to steal a shard of the Allspark. Following the completion of the mission, he journeyed to Egypt to aid in the Fallen's plan to harvest Earth's Sun but he was killed by Bumblebee in the process.

Name: Ravager (RWBY)
Summary: Ravagers are bat-like Creatures of Grimm that first appear in RWBY: After the Fall, where they are encountered by Team CFVY. They later appear in the main series at the end of "Worthy" attacking the refugees from Atlas and Mantle outside the main city of Vacuo.

Name: Raven Branwen
Summary: Raven Branwen is the mysterious mother of Yang Xiao Long and Qrow Branwen's twin sister. She was originally a member of Team STRQ, though unlike most Hunters, she has little issue killing and is described by her brother as a dangerous person. Raven has a high "survival of the fittest" mentality in which she is rather indifferent towards innocents dying if they were too weak to defend themselves. On one occasion she saved the life of her daughter, who she had abandoned shortly after her birth, though not without warning that she won't be looking out for her a second time. Raven is currently concerned about Salem and the power that she possesses.

Name: Rebecca Chambers
Summary: Dr. Rebecca Chambers is a former member of S.T.A.R.S., a special forces unit of the Raccoon Police Department. Despite her sweet and seemingly fragile appearance, she is a medical expert and a capable fighter. She is currently a professor at a university in Chicago, USA.

Name: Rei'sen
Summary: Rei'sen is a lunar rabbit. Originally she had fled the moon to Earth, but upon being taken back, she was sentenced to becoming the Watatsukis' pet, replacing the original Reisen.

Name: Reiko Yanagi (Emily)
Summary: Reiko Yanagi (柳やなぎレイ子こ Yanagi Reiko), also known as Emily (エミリー Emirī), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Ribbon Girl
Summary: Ribbon Girl is a playable fighter in ARMS. She is a Japanese pop singer and appears similarly to a cheerleader. Like the other ARMS fighters, she was gifted the ability of ARMS, where her arms are able to stretch out

Name: Richard Watterson
Summary: Richard Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. He serves the role of the father in the Watterson family. Unlike the traditional father, however, Richard is not wise, nor is he a good role model for his children in any way. Despite his misguided advice and uncouth mannerisms, Richard has good intentions and loves his family all the same.

Name: Rikido Sato (Sugarman)
Summary: Rikido Sato (砂藤力道 Satō Rikidō), also known as Sugarman (シュガーマン Shugā Man), is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Rikiya Katsukame
Summary: Rikiya Katsukame (活瓶力也 Katsukame Rikiya) is one of the Eight Bullets of the Shie Hassaikai. He was the first of the bullets to be fought by the heroes and managed to take down half of them before being defeated.

Name: Ringo
Summary: Ringo (鈴瑚 Ringo) is a moon rabbit, and the stage 2 boss of Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Rinnosuke Morichika
Summary: Rinnosuke Morichika (森近 霖之助, Morichika Rinnosuke), nicknamed Kourin (香霖), is a half-human half-youkai hybrid and using his ability to know the name and purpose of an object, he runs Kourindou, an antique shop specializing in items from the Outside World. He's one of the few male characters depicted in the Touhou Project and is the protagonist of Curiosities of Lotus Asia.

Name: Ritsu Kageyama
Summary: Ritsu Kageyama is the younger brother of Mob and a major supporting character in the anime/manga series Mob Psycho 100. While his brother is socially inept and lacking in motivation and accomplishment, Ritsu is a star student, with perfect grades and a place on the Student Council of Salt Middle School, and is generally amiable to his older brother. However, his drive to be a good brother towards Mob was discovered to be a front to his genuine fear and jealousy of his brother's power only striving to be a good sibling to avoid confronting the form that he observed his brother take when knocked out.

Name: RJ
Summary: Robert James, usually referred to as RJ, is the laid-back and carefree master and instructor of the Jungle Fury Power Rangers, as well as, the boss and owner of a pizza restaurant that serves as their headquaters. During his childhood, his father, Master Finn, constantly tried to force RJ to learn the Shark Technique in order become a Shark Master. RJ, being against this, left home and found his own master, who instructed him in the ways of the Wolf. Upon mastering his Wolf Spirit, RJ became the new Wolf Master and eventually the Jungle Fury Wolf Ranger after his students help him revert from his werewolf form, a curse inflicted by Da' Shi.

Name: Rob (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: Rob (AKA Dr. Wrecker) is the main antagonist of The Amazing World of Gumball. He was formerly a minor background student at Elmore Junior High before he was cast into the Void, a dimension which harbors "all the mistakes the world has ever made." Following his escape and recollection, he becomes Gumball's arch-nemesis for revenge over his abandonment and to have a part to play in the world.

Name: Robyn Hill
Summary: Robyn Hill, Mantle's hometown hero and leader of the Happy Huntresses. First appearing in Volume 7, she was running for a spot on the Atlas Council in hopes of improving conditions in her home of Mantle. Her Happy Huntresses are known for fighting for the poor against the wealthy, and is more than willing to commit acts that are less than legal in order to protect her home.

Name: Rodan (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)
Summary: Rodan (ラドン, Radon?) is a giant pteranodon daikaiju created by Toho that appeared in Godzilla the Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle.
ID: Rodan (Godzilla The Ride: Giant Monsters Ultimate Battle)-Godzilla-8

Name: Roman Torchwick
Summary: Roman Torchwick is a character in the world of RWBY. A master criminal, he orchestrated the robbery of Dust supplies from many stores throughout Vale. He emits charm and speaks calmly even in the middle of an armed robbery. Though he also emits hostility towards people he either hates or dislikes, as seen with Ruby Rose, when he tried to kill her, even ordering the White Fang to shoot her.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Rosa Schwein
Summary: Rosa Schwein is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a former Huntress hailing from Shade Academy who deserted in order to restore the Vacuan monarchy, serving as an enforcer for The Crown.

Name: Rose (Street Fighter)
Summary: Rose is a Street Fighter character who makes her first appearance in Street Fighter Alpha. She is a fortune teller from Italy who attacks with Soul Power. She shares a soul with M. Bison and has bested him in battle in the past.

Name: Roxie Richter
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, at least High 8-C with Winifred Hailey Ninja Clones

Name: Roy Mustang
Summary: Roy Mustang (ロイ・マスタング, Roi Masutangu), also known as the Flame Alchemist (炎の錬金術師, Honō no Renkinjutsushi), is the tritagonist of the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a State Alchemist and officer in the Amestrian State Military. A hero of the Ishval Civil War and Edward Elric's superior officer, Colonel Mustang is a remarkably capable commander who plans to become the next Führer of Amestris.

Name: Roy Stallion
Summary: Roy Stallion was a member of Team BRNZ. Along with his team, Roy was a student of Shade Academy from the kingdom of Vacuo. He and his team journeyed to participate in the 40th Vytal Festival combat tournament, hosted by the kingdom of Vale. His team was defeated by Team JNPR of Vale's Beacon Academy in the team round of the tournament.

Name: Ruby Rose
Summary: Ruby Rose is the 15-year old leader of Team RWBY attending Beacon Academy two years early, due to her abilities impressing Professor Ozpin. Trained by her Uncle Qrow, Ruby wields a unique weapon named Crescent Rose, a cross between a scythe and a high-caliber sniper rifle that is able to fold up into itself. Her Semblance is speed, enabling her to run at rates that are too fast for the eye to catch. As she is the youngest of the group, she can be a bit childish, naïve, and weapon-obsessed, but displays leadership qualities and an understanding of people that ultimately led her to be chosen as Team RWBY's leader. She was inspired to become a Huntress by the fairy tales her half-sister Yang read her, wanting to become just like the heroes in the stories. She is determined to make the world a better place for others and try to stop the forces that conspire against it.

Name: Ruby Tojo
Summary: As a young child, her parents were killed in a car crash. As a result of this, she became a human-hating witch serving under Lady Oyakata. She later betrayed her after meeting the human Tsukune. She later becomes the Headmaster's assistant and helps defend Japan against Fairy Tale.

Name: Rumi Usagiyama (Mirko)
Summary: Rumi Usagiyama (兎山 ルミ Usagiyama Rumi), also known as Rabbit Hero: Mirko (ラビットヒーロー ミルコ Rabitto Hīrō Miruko), is currently the No. 5 Pro Hero in Japan.

Name: Rumia
Summary: Rumia (ルーミア) is a youkai with the ability of manipulating the darkness. She is one of the few youkai that doesn't seem to belong to any particular species.

Name: Runuganga
Summary: Runuganga is a special Hollow which guards the outside of Las Noches from unwanted intruders, be described as the "Guardian of the White Sands", he was eventually killed by Rukia Kuchiki.

Name: Russel Thrush
Summary: Russel Thrush is a student of Beacon Academy, and a member of Team CRDL. His weapons are a pair of daggers. Although he has not had a substantial speaking role, Russel can be seen as a "school bully", just like his leader Cardin, where he calls Velvet Scarlatina a freak because of her rabbit ears.

Name: Ryo Shimazaki
Summary: Ryo Shimazaki is a minor antagonist in the World Domination Arc of Mob Psycho 100. He is an elite member of Scar, a terrorist organization bent on world domination and causing general destruction and chaos in order to leave a mark on the world. As one of its "Ultimate Five", he is easily one of the strongest members of the organization, who took the combined efforts of Claw's former Seventh Division, Teruki, Ritsu, and others before he was defeated.

Name: Ryomen Sukuna
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Ryuko Tatsuma (Ryukyu)
Summary: Ryuko Tatsuma (竜間龍子 Tatsuma Ryūko), also known as the Dragoon Hero: Ryukyu (ドラグーンヒーロー リューキュウ Doragūn Hīrō Ryūkyū), is the current No. 10 Hero in Japan. She worked with Nejire Chan, Uravity, and Froppy during the Shie Hassaikai Arc.

Name: Salem
Summary: An incredibly enigmatic figure from Remnant's forgotten past, Salem is the true main antagonist of RWBY.

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Santa’s Little Helper
Summary: Santa’s Little Helper is the family dog in The Simpsons.

Name: Sarah G. Lato
Summary: Sarah G. Lato is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is an introverted yet jaunty student at Elmore Junior High, who admires Gumball and Darwin, and wants to be included in their escapades. Sarah loves fan fiction and manga, and considers herself an otaku.

Name: Sasha Waybright
Summary: Sasha Waybright was sent to the realm of Amphibia along with her friends after being exposed to the Calamity Box, where she was imprisoned by Captain Grime in the Toad Tower until using her manipulation skills to prove she would be a valuable asset. Thus, she is instated as first lieutenant of Grime's toad army, putting her at odds with Anne and the frogs of Wartwood.

Name: Satoru Gojo
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Scar (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: The Scarred Man (傷の男, Kizu no Otoko), known more casually as "Scar" (スカー, Suka), is a nameless lone serial killer and revolutionary who targets State Alchemists for his own brand of lethal justice in accordance with the fundamental tenets of his religion and for the revenge of his slaughtered people and his older brother. An Ishvalan survivor of the Ishval Civil War, Scar's moniker comes from the large X-shaped scar on his forehead and sports a conspicuous and intricate alchemical tattoo on his right arm, which originally belonged to his brother, and which he uses as his murder weapon of choice.

Name: Scarlet David
Summary: Scarlet David is a member of Team SSSN, who made his first appearance in "Extracurricular". Scarlet has red hair that comes down over his right eye, with a complete undercut. There are a number of red markings around his left eye. He wears a green, mulberry, navy color feather earring on his left ear, and has a red military pelisse-like jacket draped over the left side. He also wears a gray bandanna around his neck. On his right hand, he wears a fingerless glove, and on his right biceps, he has a gray band. He wears a white sleeveless shirt and light gray pants. He also wears a pair of long, brown, laced boots. Around his waist, he wears a slightly slanted gray belt.

Name: Scott Pilgrim
Summary: Scott William Pilgrim is the titular protagonist of the Scott Pilgrim media franchise.

Name: Scout
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Meet_The_Scout_%22Grass_grows%22.wav

Name: Screaming Mantis
Summary: Screaming Mantis was the leader and psychological warfare specialist of the Beauty and the Beast unit. Born in a war torn village in South America, she was separated from her family as a child when her village was burned down, and hid in the basement of a building that she discovered was actually a makeshift torture room. Haunted by the corpses surrounding her and the screams of the tortured villagers, she was left horribly traumatized, and trapped there for weeks, she had no choice but to consume the remains of the victims around her, but only the men, emulating a mantis.

Name: Sea Feilong
Summary: The Sea Feilong is an abnormally large and powerful Grimm that inhabited the waters near Menagerie. It was felled by the combined efforts of Blake Belladonna, Sun Wukong, and the crew of the ship they Huntsmen-in-Training were sailing with.

Name: Seiran
Summary: Seiran (清蘭 Seiran) is a moon rabbit, and the stage 1 boss of Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Sekibanki
Summary: Sekibanki is a rokurokubi who lives in the Human Village, disguised as a human.

Name: Sekijiro Kan (Vlad King)
Summary: Sekijiro Kan (管かん赤せき慈じ郎ろう Kan Sekijirō), also known as Vlad King (ブラドキング Buradokingu), is a Pro Hero and the homeroom teacher of U.A. High School's Class 1-B.

Name: Sen Kaibara (Spiral)
Summary: Sen Kaibara (回原かいばら旋せん Kaibara Sen), also known as Spiral (スパイラル Supairaru), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, where he got in through official recommendations, and is currently training there to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Seregios
Summary: Seregios are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate.

Name: Seth (Street Fighter)
Summary: Seth (セス Sesu) is the main antagonist of the Street Fighter IV series and serves as the usual final boss for all characters in the games. He is the CEO of Shadaloo's weapon division, S.I.N., and is one of many genetically engineered replacement bodies for M. Bison.

Name: Setsuna Tokage (Lizardy)
Summary: Setsuna Tokage (取蔭切奈 Tokage Setsuna), also known as Lizardy (リザーディ Rizādi), is a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero, and one of the four first year students who entered through recommendations.

Name: Share Bear (2019)
Summary: Share Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She is the team's communicator, receiving and relaying information from the Caring Tower. Additionally, she acts as the point of contact for any new species and civilizations the crew encounters. While Share is more than happy to help others however she can, this often leads her to putting a lot of pressure on herself and getting discouraged whenever she makes mistakes.

Name: Sherry Birkin
Summary: Sherry Birkin is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil series. She was born around 1986 to the Umbrella virologist, William Birkin, and his research colleague and new wife, Annette, when the two were both working at the Arklay Laboratory. She is one of the survivors of the Raccoon City incident, thanks to Claire Redfield and Leon S. Kennedy, who came to her aid. They eventually escaped the fallen city together.

Name: Sheva Alomar
Summary: Sheva Alomar (シェバ・アローマ Sheba Arōma) is a fictional character in the Resident Evil horror video series by Capcom. She first appeared in Resident Evil 5 as one of the main characters. She was introduced in the E3 trailer and later on in E3 demo videos where she was a playable character that assists Chris Redfield throughout the game. She was introduced in 2009's Resident Evil 5 as a native African operative of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA) and a new partner of the series' veteran Chris Redfield. The character was met with mostly positive reception, but has yet not returned for any further installment of the series. Operating as part of its West African branch. She was assigned to the current mission to assist Chris Redfield, who was unfamiliar with the area. A versatile fighter with extensive experience, her ability to use firearms is on par with Chris. She is much smaller and more flexible than Chris, enabling her to perform certain maneuvers that Chris cannot. In turn, this allows Chris to throw her up to high ledges, or over large gaps in order to reach areas or objectives that a lone operative couldn't reach.

Name: Shigeo Kageyama
Summary: Shigeo Kageyama, also known as Mob, is the protagonist of the manga/anime series Mob Psycho 100.

Name: Shihai Kuroiro (Vantablack)
Summary: Shihai Kuroiro (黒くろ色いろ支し配はい Kuroiro Shihai), also known as Vantablack (ベンタブラック Bentaburakku), is one of the students in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Shinichi Ozaki
Summary: Ensign Shinichi Ozaki (尾崎 真一) is a Mutant that was a member of M-Organization, which is part of the Earth Defense Force. He served under Captain Douglas Gordon aboard the Gotengo. He serves as the main protagonist of 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars.

Name: Shinji Nishiya (Kamui Woods)
Summary: Shinji Nishiya (西屋森児 Nishiya Shinji), also known by his hero name, Kamui Woods (シンリンカムイ Shinrin Kamui), is the No. 7 Pro Hero and member of The Lurkers.

Name: Shino Sosaki (Mandalay)
Summary: Shino Sosaki (送崎信乃 Sōsaki Shino), better known by her hero name, Mandalay (マンダレイ Mandarei) , is Pro Hero and member of the Wild Wild Pussycats alongside Tiger, Ragdoll, and Pixie-Bob. She is a calm and collected woman who doesn't hesitate to help someone in danger. Her Quirk, Telepath, allows her to advise and instruct anyone with her mind through mental transmissions.

Name: Shizuha Aki
Summary: Shizuha Aki is one of the two Aki goddesses of Autumn. Her job is to turn leaves red and make them fall from trees, although she does this by physically painting them red.

Name: Sho Suzuki
Summary: Sho Suzuki is the son of the leader of Claw. He led a direct resistance against his father's world domination plan.

Name: Shota Aizawa (Eraser Head)
Summary: Shota Aizawa (相澤消太 Aizawa Shōta), also known as Eraser Head (イレイザー・ヘッド Ireizā Heddo), is a Pro Hero and Class 1-A's Homeroom Teacher. Apathetic and stern at a glance, he nevertheless holds his class to incredibly high standards, going so far as to expel entire classes for failing to meet them.

Name: Shoto Todoroki (Shoto)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Shoto Todoroki (轟焦凍 Todoroki Shōto), also known as Shoto (ショート Shōto), is one of main protagonists of the My Hero Academia manga and anime series.

Name: Shroob
Summary: The Shroobs are a race of purple Toad-like aliens from the Shroob Planet, which was ruled by Princess Shroob and her older sister.

Name: Shuichi Iguchi (Spinner)
Summary: Shuichi Iguchi (伊口秀一 Iguchi Shūichi), also known as Spinner (スピナー Supinā), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He is obsessed with the ideals of the Hero Killer: Stain, and is determined to revive Stain's vision of society through himself. His group later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Shulker
Summary: The Shulker is a kind of monster found in the End, particularly in the End Cities. They camouflage themselves as blocks until a target comes nearby.

Name: Sienna Khan
Summary: Sienna Khan was a character in RWBY. The High Leader of the White Fang after Ghira Belladonna stepped down, she was a charismatic new leader, and with her rise came the use of violence and militarization as the fringe elements of the White Fang became the core, with members such as Adam Taurus embracing the philosophy of his new leader. However, after condemning Adam for his participation in the Fall of Beacon, she was killed by him, who usurped her role after covering up her murder.

Name: Skeleton (Minecraft)
Summary: The Skeleton is a hostile mob in Minecraft. It carries a bow and attacks players at long range.

Name: Slicer Brothers
Summary: The Slicer Brothers are a pair of serial killers who become one of the guardians of Laboratory 5 under the joint alias of Number 48 after being supposedly sentenced to execution, but instead being bound to a suit of armor, with one of them being the helmet and the other the rest of the armor.

Name: Slime (Minecraft)
Summary: A Slime is a hostile mob that spawns in caves underground or in swamps. It is squishy and can vary in sizes. The smallest of the slimes are harmless and deal no damage. However, the bigger the slime is, the more capable it is to harm a player.

Name: Sloth
Summary: Sloth (スロウス, Surōsu) is a Homunculus in the manga and the 2009 anime. Slow and dim-witted, he is used as a servant for menial and tiring tasks by Father, proving to be an infaticable worker despite his laziness.

Name: Sludge Villain
Summary: The Sludge Villain is a villain that appeared in the first chapter of My Hero Academia. It attempted to possess Deku, and later Dynamight's body. He was defeated by All Might on both occasions.

Name: Snake Jailbird
Summary: Chester Turley, better known as Snake Jailbird, is a recurring antagonist in the animated TV series The Simpsons and a minor antagonist in the 2007 theatrical film The Simpsons Movie. He is a recidivist criminal, always getting arrested, but rarely being kept locked up for long. He speaks with a "Valley Boy" accent and has a tattoo of a snake on his arm, which is presumably the source of his nickname.

Name: Sneed
Summary: Sneed is a farmer that appears in the episode E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt). He is the owner of the convenience store Sneed's Feed and Seed (Formerly Chuck's).

Name: Snipe (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Snipe (スナイプ Sunaipu) is the current No. 25 Pro Hero and a member of the teaching staff at U.A. High School. He is in charge of the third year students.

Name: Sniper
Summary: The Sniper is one of the support classes in Team Fortress 2. His job is to defend the base while also attacking enemy targets from afar. Half rugged outdoorsman, half alien observer, this taciturn strip of beef jerky has spent the better part of his life alone in the bush, slow baking under the Australian sun.

Name: Snowball 2
Summary: Snowball 2 is the black cat that The Simpsons family took in after their original cat, Snowball 1, was killed. Snowball 2 is often portrayed as fairly intelligent for an animal, understanding human english, and pulling off human activities such as dancing. Aside from her decent intelligence shown every now and then, she is your typical stereotypical cat. She lived as the Simpsons family cat for many years until being ran over and killed by Dr. Herbert in season 15.

Name: Snowball V
Summary: nan

Name: Soldier
Summary: I have personally killed 6,578 men in cold blood while looking them in the eye; jumped on 1,336 live grenades; and stuffed fourteen feet of my own intestine back into my stomach. If that doesn't scare you out of your frilly pink leotards, guess what: You are an idiot and you hate America.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Solid Snake
Summary: We can tell about other people about--having faith. What we had faith in. What we found important enough to fight for. It's not whether you were right or wrong, but how much faith you were willing to have, that decides the future.

Name: Solidus Snake
Summary: All I want is to be remembered. By other people, by history. The Patriots are trying to protect their power, their own interests, by controlling the digital flow of information. I want my memory, my existence to remain. Unlike an intron of history, I will be remembered as an exon. That will be my legacy, my mark on history. But the Patriots would deny us even that. I will triumph over the Patriots, and liberate us all. And we will become the Sons of Liberty!

Name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''Post-Muscle Tower''' | '''Post-Korin Training''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Post-Chōshinsui''' | '''23rd Budōkai'''
Summary: Son Goku (孫そん悟ご空くう, Son Gokū?) is the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball metaseries.

Name: Soundwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Soundwave, the Decepticon communications officer and one of Megatron's staunchest supporters, doesn't just master the frequencies that carry information across our planet, he revels in them. Stationed high in the upper atmosphere and capable of processing millions of data streams at once, he is fully capable of taking over communications on a planetary scale. Whether he uses this to direct civilization or destroy it remains to be seen.

Name: Sphinx (RWBY)
Summary: Sphinxes are large, flying feline Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in the episode "Argus Limited."

Name: Spike (Mario)
Summary: The Spike are a group of turtle-like creatures that inhabit the Mushroom Kingdom and a subspecies of Koopa.

Name: Spike the Devil Man
Summary: Spike the Devil Man, or just Devilman (アックマン, Akkuman?) is a devil from Hell and one of Fortuneteller Baba's fighters; he was once the strongest of all her fighters, and has won the World Martial Arts Tournament in the past, but he was bumped down one rank by Grandpa Gohan.

Name: Spike the Dragon
Key: '''Baby Dragon Form''' | '''Equestria Girls Dog Form''' | '''Adult Dragon Form ''' | '''Post Puberty'''
Summary: Spike the Dragon is a protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Spring Man (ARMS)
Summary: Spring Man is a playable fighter in ARMS. In the game, he is a young, enthusiastic fighter, and the newest contestant to join the Grand Prix. As his name implies, his visual appearance revolves around springs.

Name: Springtron
Summary: Springtron is a playable character in ARMS. He is a robotic ARMS Fighter, who resembles that of Spring Man, created by ARMS Labs, who interrupts the Grand Prix and acts as a boss battle. He is constantly learning and adapting in order to be the strongest, as well as provide more information on ARMS.

Name: Spy
Summary: This Spy has already breached our defenses... You've seen what he's done to our colleagues! And worst of all: He could be any one of us.

Name: Staff Officer Black
Summary: Staff Officer Black (ブラック参謀) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and in the anime Dragon Ball, also making short appearances in Dragon Ball GT. He is an assistant of Commander Red and is not given much of a role until the near end of the Commander Red Saga. He is a tall, soft-spoken and quick-witted person. Black carries out Commander Red's orders and informs Commander Red of the current situations with the remaining Red Ribbon Army officers.

Name: Star Sapphire (Touhou Project)
Summary: Star Sapphire (スターサファイア) is a fairy and one of the members of the Three Fairies of Light, along with Sunny Milk and Luna Child.

Name: Starscream (DS 2007 Game)
Summary: After the disappearance of Megatron nearly a million years ago, Starscream took over the Decepticons as their high commander. Arriving on Earth, he instructed Create-A-Bot to follow Barricade until he arrived. However, none of the other Decepticons would trust him, and he confided in Create-A-Bot a great number of secrets, including the location of the AllSpark and the identity of the lost Decepticon they were retrieving: Megatron. Starscream reasoned that he hid these things because revealing them would lead to a power struggle, but no one bought it except the naive rookie.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Stinger
Summary: Stinger (スティンガー, Sutingā) is the A-Class Rank 10 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Stygian
Summary: Tier: Unknown, likely 8-A | 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Subspace Bomb
Summary: The Subspace Bomb is a powerful weapon used in the Super Smash Bros. story mode. A large portion of the game is set to keep them from being set.

Name: Suguru Geto
Summary: An endless cycle of exorcism and consumption. Exorcise. Consume. It's a taste that nobody knows. The taste of a curse. Like ingesting a rag used to wipe up vomit. Exorcise. Consume. For whom? Ever since that day... It's been running through my head. What I saw was nothing out of the ordinary. A hideous evil known to everyone. Knowing that full well... I chose to protect them as a Jujutsu Sorcerer. Don't lose your way. Follow through with your duty as a Jujutsu Sorcerer... Monkeys...

Name: Sun Wukong (RWBY)
Summary: Sun Wukong is a Faunus from the kingdom of Vacuo, who later moved to Mistral and made his first appearance in "The Stray". His weapon is a collapsible staff that separates into two pairs of nunchucks made of guns called Ruyi Bang and Jingu Bang. In his first appearance, Sun is shown to be fun-loving and mischievous, with little regard for the law - stowing away on a ship, thanking the crew for the ride during his escape, throwing a banana peel in a detective's face, and stealing apples. He has a lot of self-confidence, referring to himself as a "great stowaway". He is also a bit of a flirt towards Blake. In conversation, Sun is very laid-back and casual. He is also kind and patient, willing to listen to Blake's story and waiting for her to do so for nearly two days, bearing with her "small talk and weird looks". He is not afraid to give his opinion and has a dislike for those who regard themselves as "holier than thou", or who "use force to get whatever they want", such as the White Fang. Sun also seems to be willing to help others, regardless of whether he is asked or not, even if he barely knows them. This quality is further demonstrated when he readily volunteers to help Team RWBY with their investigation, despite both Blake and Ruby stating their opposition to his involvement.

Name: Sunny Milk
Summary: Sunny Milk is the leader of the Three Fairies of Light, first appearing as one of the protagonists of Eastern and Little Nature Deity and later as one of the antagonists of Fairy Wars.

Name: Sweetie Belle
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A

Name: Swift Heart Rabbit
Summary: Swift Heart Rabbit is one of the Care Bear Cousins who has been a frequently recurring character since the first feature-length movie. True to her name, she is easily the fastest member of the Family, and she's not one to let people forget that. Her hubris and insistence to get things done as quickly as possible frequently lead to much needed lessons in humility. Despite her flaws, she's quick to get back up, and will always be there to lend her speed and a helping hand where she can.

Name: T-A.L.O.S.
Summary: T-A.L.O.S. was created to be a superior and controllable version of the Tyrant, and Umbrella North America's response to Umbrella Europe's Nemesis project.

Name: Takuma Ino
Summary: Takuma Ino (猪い野の 琢たく真ま, Ino Takuma?) is a supporting character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Ino is a grade 2 jujutsu sorcerer and a close associate of Kento Nanami who operates out of Tokyo Jujutsu High.

Name: Tamaki Amajiki (Suneater)
Summary: Tamaki Amajiki (天喰 環 Amajiki Tamaki), also known as Suneater (サンイーター San'ītā), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Tao Pai Pai
Summary: Mercenary Tao (桃白白 or タオパイパイ, Tao Pai Pai) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and the anime Dragon Ball, also making two filler appearances in Dragon Ball Z. He is a highly skilled assassin-for-hire, as well as the younger brother of Master Shen. He charges a hefty price for his expert services, as he normally charges ten billion Zeni per kill, but gave Commander Red a 20th anniversary discount of five billion Zeni (fifty million in the Japanese version).

Name: Tashigi
Summary: Tashigi was first introduced when the Straw Hat Pirates docked in Loguetown, where she was stationed. Smoker, her superior officer, seems to regard her as a protege; the two work very well together.

Name: Tasmanian Devil (Looney Tunes)
Summary: Page one: Aardvarks, Ants, Bears, Boars, Cats, Bats, Dogs, Hogs, Elephants, Antelopes, Pheasants, Ferrets, Giraffes, Gazelles, Stoats, Goats, Shoats, Ostriches, Lions, Jackals, Muskrats, Minks, Dingoes, Zebras, Foxes, Boxes, Octopus, Penguins, People, Warthogs, Yaks, Gnus, Newts, Walrus---Wildebeests.

Name: Team RWBY
Summary: Team RWBY (pronounced "Ruby") is a Huntress team of former Beacon Academy students, which is comprised of RWBY's main characters: team leader Ruby Rose, Weiss Schnee, Blake Belladonna, and Yang Xiao Long. Originally unable to even hold a proper conversation together, the team eventually develops a familial bond and grows into a tightly-knit group, willing to risk their futures and even their lives for each other. They have no qualms breaking the rules to do what they believe is right.

Name: Tenderheart Bear (Original)
Summary: Tenderheart Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared as an illustration on American Greetings greeting cards in August 1982. Exemplifying the very best qualities of the Care Bears, Tenderheart is usually considered the de facto leader of the gang. He frequently organizes their efforts to help spread love and care around the world, and keep their own home of Care-a-Lot in working shape. He is responsible for initiating new members into the Care Bear Family by bestowing their very own belly symbols, and has been directly involved in nearly every major event in their history.

Name: Tensei Iida (Ingenium)
Summary: Tensei Iida (飯いい田だ天てん晴せい Īda Tensei), also known as the Turbo Hero: Ingenium (ターボヒーロー・インゲニウム Tābo Hīrō Ingeniumu), is the older brother of Tenya Iida and a Pro Hero.

Name: Tenya Iida (Ingenium)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tenya Iida (飯田天哉 Īda Ten'ya), also known as Ingenium is the Class President of Class 1-A and a major character in My Hero Academia. Being born into a wealthy family of prestigious and esteemed heroes, he works tirelessly to uphold his family values and embody what it truly means to be a hero.

Name: Teru Momijiyama (Shy)
Key: '''Beginning of Series to Yuri Orphanage Arc''' | '''Tokyo Recapture arc'''
Summary: Teru Momijiyama (紅葉山テル, Momijiyama Teru), better known as Shy (シャイ Shai), is the main protagonist of the manga series SHY. Living in a world where every country has a hero to protect it. She is a middle school student and the successor to her older sister Mei Momijiyama, the previous Hero of Japan. After her passing, her Heart Shift Bracelets were given to her at her funeral. After which she chose to use the Bracelets to become Japan's new hero, and to live up to her sister's legacy. Even though she struggles with talking to crowds, or even just doing her job as a hero.

Name: Teruki Hanazawa
Summary: Teruki Hanazawa is a former antagonist and current ally of Mob. He used to be an arrogant and proud esper who believed he was the star protagonist of his life. This mainly stems from his belief that only he had the power of an esper to make his life easier. But his encounter with Mob did not just change his beliefs but also his hairstyle.

Name: Teryx
Summary: Teryxes are large Creatures of Grimm that take the appearance of a raptor-like dinosaur with pterosaur wings. They made their first appearance in the episode "As Above, So Below" of Volume 7.

Name: Tetsucabra
Summary: Tetsucabra is the first Amphibian fought in Monster Hunter 4. It is a large, frog-like monster.

Name: Tetsutetsu Tetsutetsu (Real Steel)
Summary: Tetsutetsu Tetsutetsu (鉄哲徹鐵), also known as Real Steel (リアルスティール Riaru Sutīru), is a student at U.A. training to become a Pro Hero. His similar hardening Quirk and attitude make him akin to a carbon copy of Red Riot.

Name: Tewi Inaba
Summary: Tewi Inaba is the leader of Gensokyo's rabbit youkai and one of the inhabitants of the hidden mansion of Eientei. She is implied to possibly be the White Hare of Inaba.

Name: The Boss (Metal Gear)
Summary: The Boss, also known as The Joy, The Mother of Special Forces, Mercury Lady and Voyevoda (Russian: Воевода, "Warlord"), was a renowned American female soldier, founder and leader of the Cobra Unit, the biological mother of Ocelot, and mentor and mother figure to Naked Snake. In June 1944, during World War II, she led the Cobra Unit to victory at the Battle of Normandy. Together with Naked Snake, she developed the technique of CQC.

Name: The Core (Amphibia)
Summary: The Core is the collective consciousness of the greatest minds of Amphibia and serves as the main antagonist throughout the later half of Amphibia. Being a collection of consciousness in a robotic shell it needs a host to properly interact with the outside world. As such The Core takes the body of Marcy and uses it for much of season 3.

Name: The Cube (Fortnite)
Summary: The Cube (Or Kevin) is a recurring object from Fortnite: Battle Royale. First appearing in Season 5 of Chapter 1, the Cube was a singular antagonistic device that traveled the map and created runes around it. It was later destroyed in the Butterfly Event, where it self destructed.

Name: The End (Metal Gear)
Summary: The End is a supporting antagonist of the 2004 video game; Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater, along with it's 2025 remake, Metal Gear Solid Δ: SNAKE EATER. He is a member of The Boss's Cobra Unit. He has an extensive lifespan and the ability to absorb solar energy after being infected by a parasite. He is also considered the greatest sniper in history. Like all members of the Cobra Unit, he bears the codename of an emotion he brings into battle: True Oblivion.

Name: The Fear
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheFearIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Fury (Metal Gear)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheFuryIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Hound (RWBY)
Summary: The Hound is a highly intelligent Creature of Grimm created by Salem that can adapt itself to its surroundings. It makes its first appearance in "Divide", when she commands it to hunt down the one who can show her how to use the Relic of Knowledge.

Name: The Hunter (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Hunters are the playable avatar of the Monster Hunter series.

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Looper (Lego)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the sub-game Lego Fortnite. The focus of the game is on long-term survival, crafting and online cooperation with friends.

Name: The Pain
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:ThePainIntroduction.ogg

Name: The Sorrow
Summary: The Sorrow was the "Spirit Medium Soldier" of the Cobra Unit. Gifted with the powers of a medium, he was able to summon the dead and assume their abilities by bringing their spirits into himself, along with being able to accurately predict the outcome of any fight by talking to the dead. Like the other Cobras, his codename reflected the emotion he brought to the battlefield, unending sadness.

Name: The Spirit (Care Bears)
Summary: The Spirit is the primary antagonist of the first Care Bears feature film. While Nicholas Cherrywood was cleaning out the old trunk which belonged to the magician, Mr. Fettuccine, he stumbled upon an ancient book of spells. The book spoke to him from within its pages and beckoned him to open it, offering the fame and notoriety he had been seeking all his life. Upon doing so, he met The Spirit. This would initiate their venture to render everyone in the world just as cold and uncaring as The Spirit herself.

Name: The Visitor (Fortnite)
Summary: The Visitor is a mysterious entity who had arrived to the planet via a meteorite in Season 3 of Fortnite: Battle Royale, responsible for having launched the rocket during Season 4 as well. Though nothing is known about their original intentions, it was through the launching of this rocket that a multitude of spatial and temporal rifts were opened up within the atmosphere, leading to the events in Seasons 4 - 6.

Name: Three-Eyed Ghost
Summary: Three-Eyed Ghost was a Tiger Level Monster that appeared in the office district. The negative emotions of the social workers gathered and it became the size of a building. The act of destroying the office building was due to a grudge against the company.

Name: Tigrex
Summary: Tigrex are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2.

Name: TNT (Minecraft)
Summary: The TNT block is an explosive in Minecraft, 9 of which are found as a trap in Desert Temples. 2 of these blocks can also be found in a rare secret room found in Woodland Mansions.

Name: Tobias Wilson
Summary: Tobias Wilson is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a student at Elmore Junior High. He claims to be popular with the ladies, but he is actually pretentious and is just good at projecting the persona of someone who is successful. Tobias frequently fails to impress his female classmates, yet continues to believe that he is the coolest person. He is overconfident in his social and physical capabilities, and enjoys boasting about his supposed status and accomplishments, much to the annoyance of others. Despite his shortcomings, Tobias does have plenty of friends anyway, and does actually come from a well-off family.

Name: Tock
Summary: Tock is a crocodile Faunus with a shaved head, dark-green mohawk and yellow eyes. She was part of a team of assassins sent to eliminate Maria Calavera, known as The Grimm Reaper. After a prolonged battle between the two, Tock manages to slash the Grimm Reaper's eyes, rendering her permanently blind and robbing her of the Silver Eyes technique. Before being dealt the killing blow, however, Maria manages to catch Tock off guard and decapitate her.

Name: Todd Ingram
Summary: Todd Ingram is Ramona Flowers's third ex-boyfriend. He is in a relationship with Envy Adams (cheating on Envy with Lynette Guycott) and the bass player for The Clash at Demonhead. He is also a Vegan, though known to cheat on both his vegan diet as well as his girlfriend, believing he can get away with mostly anything because he's a rock star.

Name: Togaru Kamakiri (Jack Mantis)
Summary: Togaru Kamakiri (鎌かま切きり尖とがる Kamakiri Togaru), also known as Jack Mantis (ジャックマンティス Jakku Mantisu), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Toge Inumaki
Summary: Run Away

Name: Toji Fushiguro
Summary: nan

Name: Tokiko
Summary: Tokiko is a minor youkai that appears in Curiosities of Lotus Asia, also known as the "book reading youkai".

Name: Tomura Shigaraki (Pre-Surgery)
Summary: Tomura Shigaraki (死柄木 弔 Shigaraki Tomura), original name Tenko Shimura (志村転弧 Shimura Tenko), was the protégé of All For One and the leader of the League of Villains. A dangerously unstable individual who looks up to his "Sensei" with the utmost awe and respect, Shigaraki plans on tearing down the society of heroes built up by All Might by any means necessary. His organization and the Meta Liberation Army later merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and he became its Grand Commander.

Name: Toridcless
Summary: Toridcless are mild mannered Bird Wyverns with control over electricity. They can be found living in the Gorge and Highland, and appear in the Bamboo Forest and Fortress Ruins.

Name: Toru Hagakure (Invisible Girl)
Summary: Toru Hagakure (葉隠透 Hagakure Tōru), also known as the Stealth Hero: Invisible Girl, is a student in Class 1-A at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero. She is a bubbly, cheery, and easygoing girl that does most things with an upbeat, positive attitude, even if she's been manipulated by her less reputable classmates.

Name: Tron (TRON)
Summary: Tron is one of the main protagonists of the TRON franchise. He is a security computer program written by Alan Bradley, and in 1982 was taken prisoner by the self-aware Master Control Program and forced to play on the Game Grid. His legendary skills and devotion to the users turned him into a formidable warrior and Disc Arena master.

Name: Truckasaurus
Summary: Truckasaurus is a giant mechanical truck/dinosaur first appearing in "Bart the Daredevil". It was inspired by the real life robotic dinosaur, Robosaurus.

Name: Tsukune Aono
Summary: Tsukune Aono (nicknamed Tsuki by his cousin Kyouko) is a former human and the main protagonist of the Rosario + Vampire series. He is mistakenly enrolled in Yokai Academy, a high school dedicated to teaching monsters to peacefully live alongside humans in disguise, where he meets and falls in love with Moka Akashiya, a vampire who takes a mutual interest in him and the sweet flavor of his blood. Tsukune becomes a member of the school’s Newspaper Club and eventually befriends several monster girls, including Kurumu Kurono, Yukari Sendo, Ruby Tojo, and Mizore Shirayuki—all of whom become obsessed with him—as well as Kokoa Shuzen, Moka’s younger half-sister. He also makes friends with several male monsters such as Ginei Morioka, Hokuto Kaneshiro, Fang-Fang Huang, and Haiji Miyamoto. They support Tsukune’s belief that monsters and humans can coexist and be more than just enemies, their friendship with him being a prime example of that sentiment.

Name: Tsunagu Hakamada (Best Jeanist)
Summary: Tsunagu Hakamata (袴田はかまだ維つなぐ Hakamata Tsunagu), also known as Fiber Hero: Best Jeanist (ファイバーヒーロー ベストジー二スト Faibā Hīrō Besuto Jīnisuto), is the formerly No. 4, now No. 3 Pro Hero and recipient of the "Best Jeanist" award for eight consecutive years.

Name: Tsuyu Asui (Froppy)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tsuyu Asui (蛙吹梅雨 Asui Tsuyu), also known as Froppy (フロッピー Furoppī), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. She's known for her stoic and unflappable attitude, being able to work well under pressure, contrasting heavily against her far more emotional classmates.

Name: Tyrian Callows
Summary: Tyrian Callows is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. A known serial killer, he is an associate of Salem and part of her inner circle. He first serves as a main antagonist in Volume 4, hunting down Ruby Rose on the order of Salem. He again serves as one in Volume 7 alongside Arthur Watts. Tyrian is described as being psychotic incarnate and someone who wants to see the world burn. He is a highly unstable, disturbed, maladjusted, manipulative, and outright sadistic individual. He frequently bursts into fits of uncontrollable, maniacal laughter and relishes in gruesome thoughts, such as the idea of removing one of Ruby's eyes in payment for her taking one of Cinder Fall's. His depravity is described in The World of RWBY: The Official Companion as someone who is irredeemable.

Name: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku
Summary: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku are Bird Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Tzveta Kooriskaya
Summary: Tzveta Kooriskaya (ツィベタ＝コオリスカヤ), formerly Letana Andreanova is a member of the villain group Amarariruku. She is the mother of the current hero of Russia, Spirits (Pepesha Andreanova). Born without her parents to take care of her she grew up in the Yuri Orphanage before leaving and having her own child. However, due to an economic recession which struck Russia at the time, she was struggling to provide for her daughter as a single mother. Often struggling to keep up with rent, having to choose between eating or keeping the apartment warm. This lead to her starting to believe her daughter would be happier if she wasn't the one raising her. Eventually she would fall to her death after a thief pushed her off a bridge. Afterwards she was resurrected by the leader of Amarariruku, Stigma but without her old memories. Now reborn with a new hatred for the world.

Name: Umber Gorgoneion
Summary: Umber Gorgoneion is a character from RWBY: Before the Dawn. She is a student hailing from Shade Academy who was assigned to Team FNDU after Theodore shuffled teams, and a secret agent of the Crown.

Name: Uragaan
Summary: Uragaans are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Urien
Summary: Urien is the younger brother of Gill, who bears an intense grudge against him, stemming from an inferiority complex. His inferiority stems mainly from his emotional instability. Being the second strongest member of the Illuminati, Urien originally holds the position of the Vice President of the organization during the tournament of Street Fighter III 2nd Impact, outranked only by Gill who serves as the President.

Name: Ursa (RWBY)
Summary: Ursai are large, bear-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "The Emerald Forest" in Volume 1. They have appeared in two varieties: the smaller, more common Ursa Minor, and the larger, better armored and more powerful Ursa Major.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Vamp
Summary: One of the members of the anti-terrorist squad Dead Cell's founding lineup, Vamp was orphaned in his youth when his church was bombed, forcing him to resort to feeding on the blood of his family to survive, giving him a taste for it. His codename was not gained from these vampiric traits, however, but from his bisexuality.

Name: Van Hohenheim
Summary: Van Hohenheim (ヴァン・ホーエンハイム, Ban Hōenhaimu) is the estranged father of Edward and Alphonse Elric. Previously, he had been known only as Slave No. 23. However, the Homunculus, grateful for the blood that brought him into the world and the unwavering friendship, bestowed upon the slave the gifts of a proper name, education, freedom, and ultimately, a body that never decays. Nevertheless, the freed slave, now known as Hohenheim, strongly condemned the gift of immortality that cost countless lives. Since then, Hohenheim has turned bitterly against Homunculus, sworn to end his agonizing immortality, and set free all the souls trapped within their bodies. Likewise, to prevent a similar tragedy from ever happening again.

Name: Varan
Summary: Varan (バラン) is a tri-phibian kaiju that first appeared in the 1958 Toho film, Varan, and later debuted in the Godzilla series in the 1968 film Destroy All Monsters.

Name: Velocidrome
Summary: Velocidromes are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Velvet Scarlatina
Summary: Velvet Scarlatina is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. Velvet is a very shy, quiet girl who tends to keep to herself, either by choice or because she is isolated by others for being a Faunus. Even when being picked on by others, she tends to act very reserved and refuses to fight back. One can say that she is very timid. However, despite her shy personality, she seems to get along with others, as seen with Team RWBY, and being an older student, she wishes them safety on their mission. Following the Fall of Beacon, she and her team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Venom Snake
Summary: Punished "Venom" Snake, also known as Big Boss, and formerly known as Ahab, V, Big Boss' phantom, or simply Snake, was a mercenary commander, formerly a combat medic for Militaires Sans Frontières (MSF). Big Boss made him lead the Diamond Dogs and Outer Heaven as his body double. Venom Snake served as a decoy to place all focus on him so that the real Big Boss could work under the radar. The phantom was killed by Solid Snake during the Outer Heaven Uprising, an operation directed by the real Big Boss.

Name: Vernal
Summary: Vernal is a character in RWBY and a member of the Branwen tribe, a group of bandits that operate in Mistral. In order to keep the identity of the Spring Maiden a secret, she took on the name "Vernal", posing as a decoy to fool others. As such, her true name is unknown. Her weapons of choice were crescent shaped blades combined into a gun.

Name: Vex
Summary: A Vex is an intangibile, flying, hostile mob that is summoned in small groups by the Evoker.

Name: Villagers (Minecraft)
Summary: The Villagers are the main civilization found in Minecraft. They are mainly found in isolated villages in biomes with flat terrains. The relationship between villages is unknown, but they are likely in somewhat friendly terms due to neighboring villages capable of easily fusing into one.Their lifestyle is passive, as they spend most of their times on local farms and shops. However, their access to Nether-exclusive goods and their possession of maps leading to faraway places such as the Water Temples seems to hint that some of them may be more adventurous than usual.

Name: Villain Bots
Summary: We exist... to serve humans' desires.

Name: Vindicator
Summary: The Vindicator is an enemy appearing in the Woodland Mansions and viciously attacks any trespassers. They, alongside Pillagers and Evokers raid and attack nearby villages, and only rarely failing if The Player or Iron Golems are there to protect it.

Name: Vine Zeki
Summary: Vine Zeki is a supporting character in RWBY. He is a member of the Ace Operatives Specialist team. He is described as calm and tranquil in both speech and temperament and is shown to be in control of himself, especially when compared to the rest of Ace-Ops. He is also shown to be easily exasperated by their comparatively more gung-ho approach. Vine believed self-improvement is the highest pursuit. At the end of Volume 8, he gave his life to protect Mantle from being blown up by a bomb, using his Semblance to contain the explosion.

Name: Viruses (Mario)
Summary: The Viruses are a group of germ-based enemies which became a duplicated problem during an experiment gone wrong in the Mushroom Kingdom Hospital's virus research lab. There are several types of viruses, but the classic three (Chill, Fever, and Weird) appears the most.

Name: Volgin
Summary: Yevgeny Borisovich Volgin was a Stalinist colonel who attempted to seize control of the Soviet Union by ousting Khrushchev and installing Brezhnev in his place. He was the son of Boris Volgin, a treasurer for the Philosophers. After his death, Volgin acquired their vast fortune, which his father had stolen, granting him access to what were practically limitless funds. With this money, Volgin constructed the Groznyj Grad fort and began building the Shagohod, a nuclear-armed tank designed by Nikolai Stepanovich Sokolov.

Name: Wakasagihime
Summary: Wakasagihime is a mermaid Youkai living in the Misty Lake. She is usually gentle and shy, although the release of magical energy from the Miracle Mallet made her aggressive in the events of Double Dealing Characters.

Name: Wapol
Summary: Wapol is the former monarch of the Drum Kingdom, originally named for the "Drum Peak" mountains which support Wapol's castle. He became a pirate after fleeing from his country when Blackbeard and his crew attacked Drum Island.

Name: Weiss Schnee
Summary: Weiss Schnee is the second member of Team RWBY. Her weapon is a Dust revolver/rapier named Myrtenaster, and her Semblance allows her to create glyphs in battle. At 17 years of age, she is the heiress to the Schnee Dust Company, a corporation famous for its sometimes shady business dealings, dangerous practices, and mistreatment of its Faunus laborers. Both the Schnee Dust Company and the Schnee family have been targets of the White Fang terrorist organization for years, leading to Weiss' inherent distrust of the Faunus. Weiss chose to become a Huntress over taking a job at SDC to restore her family's honor, as her father caused the company to decline. At the start of the show, she was shown as self-centered, standoffish, and an obnoxious know-it-all, but has matured somewhat throughout the show. She has a noticeable scar over her left eye, which she is assumed to have acquired in a fight against a living suit of armor in the 'White Trailer'. As of Volume 4, she is the former heiress of the Schnee Dust Company.

Name: White Fang Lieutenant
Summary: The White Fang Lieutenant is an officer in the White Fang and made his first appearance in the episode "Painting the Town..." at the White Fang Faction Meeting. As Adam Taurus' right hand Faunus, this hulking masked figure is a capable fighter with strength, speed, and toughness beyond even his most bestial peers. He has been seen leading many of the biggest White Fang Attacks in Remnant with his massive chainsaw. Yet none, know what kind of Faunus he is.

Name: Wile E. Coyote (Looney Tunes)
Summary: Wile E. Coyote is the persistent predator that chases the Roadrunner but often fails due to his own shortsightedness and hubris.

Name: Winter Schnee
Summary: Winter Schnee is a character in RWBY and the elder sister of Weiss Schnee. Despite being the eldest child, Winter's right to inherit the Schnee Dust Company was abdicated upon her decision to join the Atlas Military. At first glance, Winter appears to be cold, dignified, and distant, preferring to keep her emotions subdued and speaking in a very high-class, eloquent, almost robotic fashion. However, when interacting with Weiss, she smiles and shows that she cares about her younger sister's life and well-being. Although she strives to keep her emotions in check, she can be rather hot-headed at times. Once she becomes angry, she drops her dignified ladylike demeanor and loses all restraint. Winter consistently wrestles with her emotions, never letting them overpower her, yet still allowing them to guide her on what she believes to be a righteous path.

Name: Wish Bear (Original)
Summary: Wish Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. As one can infer from her name, she is tasked with making sure the wishes of everyone on Earth, and often even those of the Care Bear Family, come true. Sometimes this can be accomplished by her own supernatural wish granting abilities; other times she prefers to work towards seeing the wishes of others and even herself come to light.

Name: Wither Skeleton
Summary: The Wither Skeleton is a tall, black and withering skeleton found in the Nether. They roam the place aimlessly and viciously attack any intruders.

Name: Withered Sprout
Summary: Withered Sprout (やせ細りモヤツ, ) was a previously assumed Wolf-level threat that was later assumed to be a Dragon-level threat before finally being agreed upon to be a Tiger-level threat by the Hero Association, using his meek appearance he deceives people into letting their guard down before instantly freezing with the use of his powers. He acts as the main antagonist of the special chapter 'Disaster level'.

Name: Wolf (Minecraft)
Summary: The Wolf is a neutral mob in Minecraft that can be allied by the player.

Name: Wolfram (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Wolfram is a greedy and manipulative villain who will crush anything or anyone to get what he wants. He lusts for money and works as the leader of a company of thieves. They even posed as fake villains for hire to gain David Shield's trust just so they could steal his invention.

Name: Wriggle Nightbug
Summary: Wriggle Nightbug is a firefly with the ability to control other insects. She likes using her ability to direct concerted performances for her own amusement, as well as to attack humans who underestimate her significance or the importance of insects in general.

Name: Yamcha
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''23rd Budōkai''' | '''Saiyan Arc''' | '''Cell Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Yang Xiao Long
Summary: Yang Xiao Long is one of the main characters and the fifth character introduced in RWBY. A yellow-haired girl and Ruby Rose's older half-sister, she wields twin shotgun gauntlets called Ember Celica. Easily the most hotheaded member of the group, when she gets very angry or if her hair is damaged during battle, she completely loses her temper.

Name: Yatsuhashi Daichi
Summary: Yatsuhashi Daichi is a member of Team CFVY and a former student at Beacon Academy. He is first seen in the Volume 2 Opening, walking with his teammates and is later seen falling from the sky with other teams; he subsequently makes his first, albeit brief appearance in "Field Trip", before making a full-fledged appearance in "Breach". He is also one of the members of his team chosen to advance to the doubles round of the Vytal Festival Tournament, along with Coco Adel. Following the Fall of Beacon, he and his team transferred to Shade Academy.

Name: Yawara Chatora (Tiger)
Summary: Yawara Chatora (茶ちゃ虎とら柔やわら Chatora Yawara), also known as Tiger (虎とら Tora), is a Pro Hero and member of the Wild, Wild Pussycats.

Name: Yian Garuga
Summary: Yian Garugas are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom.

Name: Yian Kut-ku
Summary: Yian Kut-Kus are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Yo Shindo (Grand)
Key: '''Provisional Hero License Exam Arc''' | '''Dark Hero Arc'''
Summary: Yo Shindo (真堂しんどう揺よう Shindō Yō), also known as Grand (グランド Gurando), is a student at Ketsubutsu Academy High School.

Name: Yog
Summary: The Space Amoeba (宇宙生物) is an alien lifeform that serves as the antagonist of the 1970 Toho film, Space Amoeba. The entity's name is not spoken in American International Pictures' version of the film, although its title suggests it may be called Yog (ヨグ). According to producer Fumio Tanaka, this name may have been chosen as an homage to the works of H. P. Lovecraft.

Name: Yu Takeyama (Mount Lady)
Summary: Yu Takeyama (岳山優 Takeyama Yū), better known by her hero alias Mount Lady (Mt. レディ Maunto Redī), is a relatively new Pro Hero. She's in the business for fame and fortune, quickly becoming popular for her flirtatious nature and the raw power her Gigantification Quirk provides, but is nevertheless a kind person at heart. She is the No. 23 Pro Hero.

Name: Yuga Aoyama (Can't Stop Twinkling)
Summary: Yuga Aoyama (青山優雅 Aoyama Yūga), also known as Can't Stop Twinkling (キャント・ストップ・トゥインクリング Kyanto Sutoppu Tuinkuringu), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. He is flamboyant and loves the spotlight, but is prone to cracking under pressure and is somewhat cowardly. Nevertheless, he does pitch in when push comes to shove.

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die.
