I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Zampano
Summary: Zampano is a character in Fullmetal Alchemist. He is a soldier in the Amestrian State Military and one of the four Human Chimera commissioned to bodyguard and report to Solf J. Kimblee during the State Alchemist's mission to the northern area of Amestris.

Name: Zamtrios
Summary: Zamtrios are Amphibians introduced in Monster Hunter 4.

Name: Zenaserisu
Summary: Zenaserisu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z.

Name: Zeus (Fortnite)
Summary: nan

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Ziraph
Summary: Introduced in RWBY: After the Fall, Ziraphs are three-headed Grimm that resembles a giraffe. Their bodies are covered in red spots that bear resemblances to a leopard and each head has two horns. They are described as being five stories tall and having razor-like plates on their legs as well as long tongues they use to ensnare people and swallow them whole.

Name: Zoglin
Summary: The Zoglin is a large, zombified boar-like hostile mob that is created when a Hoglin is brought to the overworld. It is hostile to all other mobs and players except creepers, ghasts, and other zoglins.

Name: Zombie (Minecraft)
Summary: The Zombie is a hostile mob and the most common and basic enemy of the sandbox video game, Minecraft. They come out only at night, and attack local villages, killing Villagers and often turning them into Zombie Villagers.

Name: Zombified Piglin
Summary: The Zombie Pigman, or Zombified Piglin is a kind of monster found in the Nether. They don't indiscriminately attack living beings, unlike Zombies, although they will be merciless against those who dare to attack their brethren.

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Zurg (Buzz Lightyear of Star Command)
Summary: Zurg is Buzz Lightyear's arch-nemesis, and the biggest threat to Star Command and the Galactic Alliance. His main goal is to conquer them and rule over the galaxy. However, Team Lightyear continually thwarts his plans.

Name: Zwei (RWBY)
Summary: Zwei is the pet dog of Ruby Rose and Yang Xiao Long. He first appeared in the episode "Field Trip", when he was mailed to Beacon Academy from Patch by Taiyang Xiao Long along with a pile of canned dog food and a can opener. Taiyang sent Zwei to his daughters to take care of him temporarily due to him leaving Patch for undisclosed reasons.

Name: ZZ
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: ZZ (ズィー・ズィー Zī Zī) is a minor antagonist featured in Stardust Crusaders. ZZ is another of DIO's assassins who confronts the Joestar Group. He is a Stand User who drives his stand Wheel of Fortune.

Name: Abiorugu
Summary: Abiorugu are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.3.

Name: Agnaktor
Summary: Agnaktor is a large Leviathan which was first introduced in Monster Hunter 3 or Monster Hunter Tri.

Name: Albert Wesker
Summary: Albert Wesker is the main antagonist in the Resident Evil series. He was the leader of S.T.A.R.S. while secretly working for Umbrella Corporation as a Researcher. Later working for The 3rd Organization, H.C.F. (Hive/Host Capture Force), TriCell, he shifts allegiances at will to further his own goals of world domination. Wesker has been directly or indirectly responsible for the events of every game, and always seems to come out on top. Eventually, he would go on to pursue his megalomaniacal desires for world domination with the Uroboros virus, but was stopped by his arch-nemesis Chris Redfield and the BSAA.

Name: Ancient Leshen (Monster Hunter)
Summary: An old Leshen that arrived through a portal to assume control over the Ancient Forest. Sometimes revered as an indigenous deity. Dwelling deep inside the forest, this creature uses their innate magic to control all flora and fauna within their territory. Resulted from a crossover between Monster Hunter World and The Witcher 3.

Name: Angry Dad
Summary: Angry Dad is a fictional character made by Bart Simpson from The Simpsons. It is about a father who has extremely bad anger issues, throwing fits over the smallest problems he runs into. This show being based on his father, Homer Simpson, and his anger problems.

Name: Anjanath
Summary: Anjanath is a brute wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Anorupatisu
Summary: Anorupatisu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Astalos
Summary: Astalos is one of four flagships of Monster Hunter Generations/Monster Hunter X.

Name: Banbaro
Summary: Banbaro is a Brute Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter World: Iceborne.

Name: Barioth
Summary: Barioth is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Barroth
Summary: Barroth are Brute Wyverns uniquely adapted to living in arid desert environments. While normally docile, they will become territorial if disturbed and are capable of using their heavy head to smash through the environment. Unlike most Brute Wyverns, Barroth are insectivores and are known to attack Altaroth nests in order to devour their occupants.

Name: Baruragaru
Summary: Baruragaru are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G3.

Name: Basarios
Summary: Basarios are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter. Basarios is a small, rocky wyvern. It is the juvenile form of Gravios. Its hard, stone-like shell can be used for protection against other large wyverns, doubling up as effective camouflage when Basarios partially buries itself in the ground.

Name: Beck (TRON)
Summary: Beck is a young program who adopts the persona of Tron to free his home and friends from the reign of the villainous CLU and his henchman General Tesler. With training from Tron, the greatest warrior the Grid has ever come to know, he not only teaches Beck the fighting and lightcycle skills he needs to challenge this brutal military occupation, but becomes a guide and mentor to him as he grows beyond his youthful, impulsive nature into a courageous, powerful, strong leader.

Name: Beowolf
Summary: Beowolves are large werewolf-like Creatures of Grimm. They are the most basic and abundant type of Grimm on Remnant and are the first Grimm seen in the series.

Name: Blangonga
Summary: Blangonga is a Fanged Beast introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Blind Worm
Summary: Blind Worms are large worm-like Creatures of Grimm that appeared in RWBY: After the Fall. They are enormous worm-like Grimm capable of burrowing underground and through the sands of Vacuo. They have a singular red eye and a giant fanged mouth. These Worms can range from 6 feet to bigger than Flatback Sliders, which tower at over 100 feet in height, and are built to be far faster when traveling in sands. Like the King Taijitu, they have a head on each end of their body. Their defenses include bone plates, hooks and acidic blood. They attack with spiked teeth and are capable of spitting acid. According to Fox, when the Blind Worm is cut in half, the two halves will eventually regrow to each become individual Blind Worms.

Name: Bogabadorumu
Summary: Bogabadorumu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z Zenith.

Name: Brachydios
Summary: Brachydios is the Flagship Monster of Monster Hunter 3 Ultimate.

Name: Captain America's Shield (Fortnite)
Summary: Captain America’s Shield refers to the main weapon of Captain America in Fortnite: Battle Royale. Curiously, the shield that belongs to him during the events of Fortnite: Endgame is far superior to the shield he carried when he travelled to the Fortnite island in Chapter 2, Season 3, so it's likely he has multiple shields.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield. Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Creep (RWBY)
Summary: Creeps are subterranean Creatures of Grimm that resemble both lizards and birds. They were first encountered in "No Brakes".

Name: Creeper (Minecraft)
Summary: The Creeper is one of the primary and most iconic Minecraft monsters. Unlike others of their kind, Creepers cannot attack directly, instead having to blow themselves up to damage enemies.

Name: Devo the Cursed
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Devo the Cursed is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is given a Stand and hired by Dio Brando to kill the Joestars and allies. He appears in Singapore in an attempt to ambush Polnareff in a hotel room.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Disaster Wyvern
Summary: Disaster Wyvern is a Brute Wyvern, first introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Dracula Duck
Summary: Count Dracula Duck (Or in some cases, referred as Drake Von Vladstone) is a Disney character and provides the role as the Final Boss in the game, Ducktales for NES, later to be the Final Boss once more for its Remastered version for the Wii U, Ducktales Remastered.

Name: Dromedon
Summary: Dromedons are camel-like Grimm introduced in RWBY: After the Fall. They are native to Vacuo that can spit acidic venom. and are shown to have armored humps.

Name: Duramboros
Summary: Duramboros are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Ebirah (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: Ebirah returned 35 years later for the final entry in the Millennium series, Godzilla Final Wars, in which he was a mind-controlled pawn of the Xiliens. Ebirah was initially defeated by the Earth Defense Force's mutant soldiers at Tokai, and was deployed again to assist Hedorah against Godzilla in Tokyo Bay.

Name: Eminem (Fortnite)
Summary: Eminem is a former Boss/Event Character in Fortnite. He appears Spaghetti Grotto as a Boss, which sports Grenades and RG's Minigun and is a tough foe.[1] He also appears as a character in a Live Event as a large version of Marshall Never More that sings his song Godzilla.

Name: Enderman
Summary: The Enderman is a mob in Minecraft. It stands at 2.9 meters/blocks tall, one taller than The Player.

Name: Estrellian
Summary: Estrellian is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Evoker
Summary: The Evoker is a kind of Illager that lives in Woodland Mansions. They attack intruders using a variety of magic spells.

Name: Excella Gionne
Summary: Excella Gionne was the regional director of TRICELL's African division and a business partner of Albert Wesker.

Name: Fenton Crackshell
Summary: Fenton Crackshell is a Disney character and a protagonist that appears in the 1987 Disney cartoon Ducktales, later to be featured in Darkwing Duck as his superhero alter ego, Gizmoduck. In Ducktales, Fenton has the role of Scrooge McDuck's accountant due to his fast counting. Once portrayed as Gizmoduck, he then plays the role of Scrooge's personal security system. In Darkwing Duck, Gizmoduck and Darkwing seem to look at each other eye to eye in a rivalry.

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Gasurabazura
Summary: Gasurabazuras are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G8.

Name: Geist
Summary: Geists are Creatures of Grimm that resemble ghosts and are capable of "possessing" and controlling any inert object.

Name: General Blue
Summary: General Blue (ブルー将軍) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga and the anime Dragon Ball, and also makes an appearance in Dragon Ball GT. He is a powerful high-ranking officer in the Red Ribbon Army and is the leader of the Blue Corps. He also has powerful psychic abilities and is considered to be the strongest Red Ribbon soldier.

Name: General Tesler
Summary: General Tesler is the main antagonist of TRON: Uprising. He is one of CLU's generals and is both extremely ambitious and a coldly calculating sadist. Tesler rules over Argon City from his command ship.

Name: Giadrome
Summary: Giadrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2. It is physically very similar to the Velocidrome, the only key difference being the pale blue colouration and the presence of a frost sac.

Name: Giaorugu
Summary: Giaorugus are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Gideon Graves
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, 8-B with sword, Varies with subspace manipulation and The Glow

Name: Gigginox
Summary: Gigginox is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Glavenus
Summary: Glavenus are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Gobul
Summary: Gobuls are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Gore Magala
Key: '''Gore Magala''' | '''Chaotic Gore Magala''' | '''Shagaru Magala''' | '''Risen Shagaru Magala'''
Summary: Gore Magala debuted as the flagship monster of "Monster Hunter 4", being the main antagonist of the games low rank story.

Name: Grandpa Gohan
Summary: Grandpa Gohan is the elderly gentleman who found and raised the Saiyan Son Goku when he landed on Earth. A former disciple of Master Roshi, he taught Goku everything he knew. He died when Goku accidentally turned into an Oozaru and crushed him underneath his foot. He was brought back for a short time to spar against Goku in Fortuneteller Baba's tournament. Goku's son, Gohan, was named in honor of him.

Name: Gravios
Summary: nan

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Guardian (Minecraft)
Summary: Guardians are a kind of monster that dwells in the oceans. They gather around Ocean Monuments and guard it against any intruder, hence their names. The Elder Guardians are a larger, stronger and likely older version of the regular Guardian.

Name: Gurenzeburu
Summary: Gurenzeburu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 9.0.

Name: Halk
Summary: Halk, first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.2, is a Flying Wyvern-type creature that is able to help the Hunter in battle.

Name: Hiroshi Shibata
Summary: Hiroshi Shibata is a powerful esper and a former member of the terrorist organization Claw as a part of the Ultimate 5.

Name: Hoglin
Summary: The Hoglin is a large, boar-like hostile mob that spawn within Crimson Forests in herds.

Name: Hyujikiki
Summary: Hyujikiki is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G.

Name: Iodrome
Summary: Iodrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Ishiguro
Summary: Ishiguro is a minor antagonist appearing within Mob Psycho 100. He is the leader of Claw's Seventh Division and is a member of the organization's elite group of Scars, who have in one way or the other challenged the leader of the organization in combat.

Name: Jill Valentine
Summary: Jill Valentine is one of the main protagonists in the Resident Evil series. She appears in the first game, Resident Evil 3, the "End of Umbrella" scenario, Revelations, and the RE5 DLCs "Desperate Escape" and "Lost in Nightmares." She appears as a member of S.T.A.R.S. and then later fights zombies and bioterrorism. A senior member of S.T.A.R.S. belonging on the same team as Chris. Jill has also resigned from S.T.A.R.S. in Resident Evil 3 Nemesis and attempts to escape from the T-virus infested town, Raccoon City. She runs into Nemesis, a B.O.W. from Umbrella Corp. Nemesis relentlessly pursued Jill throughout the city. At some point, Nemesis managed to infect Jill with T-NE-virus. She also meets a member of the U.B.C.S. Carlos Olivera. In the end, Jill managed to kill Nemesis, and together with Carlos and Barry, escaped the city successfully.

Name: Khezu
Summary: Khezu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Knives Chau
Summary: Knives Chau is a protagonist in Scott Pilgrim graphic novel series. Introduced as a 17-year-old Chinese-Canadian student, she began dating Scott Pilgrim after the two encountered one another on a public transit bus. Originally a calm and kind girl, Knives quickly fell in love with Scott early into their relationship, which would escalate into pure obsession after he cheated on her with Ramona Flowers.

Name: Korin
Summary: Korin is a wise cat who is over 800 years old that lives atop Korin Tower. He is one of the martial arts teacher of Goku as well as Master Roshi. His teachings include anticipating the opponent's movements and reducing the needless movements of one's own body.

Name: Kuarusepusu
Summary: Kuarusepusu are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.4.

Name: Kyle and Ken Katayanagi
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C | At least High 8-C

Name: Lagiacrus
Summary: Lagiacrus are a variety of Leviathan introduced in Monster Hunter 3. They are feared by sailors as the "Lords of the Seas" and are the apex predators of their aquatic environment.

Name: Legiana
Summary: Legiana are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Leon S. Kennedy
Summary: Leon Scott Kennedy is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil horror media franchise by Capcom. He debuted as one of the two playable protagonists of the video game Resident Evil 2. Leon later returned as the main character of Resident Evil 4 and as one of the protagonists in Resident Evil Darkside Chronicles and Resident Evil 6.

Name: Ludroth
Summary: Ludroth are Leviathans introduced Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Midas (Fortnite)
Summary: Midas is a Legendary skin and main antagonist of Fortnite Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the leader of Ghost and a double agent for Shadow. He is based on the Greek mythology, King Midas. At the end of Chapter 2 Season 2, he becomes Cyclo, the Defiant to the Storm. At the start of Chapter 2 Season 3, he gets attacked by a shark and survived. Around Chapter 2 Season 4, he becomes Shadow Midas.

Name: Mizutsune
Summary: Mizutsune is a Leviathan first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Monoblos
Summary: Monoblos are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Mr. Chau
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C

Name: Muhammad Avdol
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Muhammad Avdol is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders.

Name: Musashi Goda
Summary: Musashi Goda (郷田武蕨, Gōda Musashi) is a student of Salt Middle School and the Body Improvement Club's President. He's a close friend of Mob.

Name: Mutants (Godzilla)
Summary: The Mutants are the genetic descendents of both humans and Xiliens. They were trained as a form of highly elite soldiers by the EDF under Commander Kumasaka. In Godzilla: Final Wars, all but Ozaki (and later Kazama) fell under the control of X. The most notable Mutant is Ozaki, who used his Keizer Energy to revive Godzilla.

Name: Nargacuga
Summary: Nargacuga are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Name: NegaScott
Summary: NegaScott, also known as Nega Scott, is Scott Pilgrim's alter ego and dark side, and represents his forgotten past mistakes. He has no lines, and has only appeared in a few panels of the comic. NegaScott is the manifestation of all of Scott's callousness, spite, faults, and flaws, and rather than accepting them and himself, he runs from them, thus creating this physical persona. Though NegaScott doesn't appear that often in the series, he can be considered a major character because of what he represents.

Name: Nibelsnarf
Summary: Nibelsnarf is a Leviathan introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Odogaron
Summary: Odogaron are Fanged Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Paolumu
Summary: Paolumu are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Pariapuria
Summary: Pariapuria are Flying Wyverns that was introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 5.0.

Name: Peely
Summary: Peely is one of many characters in Fortnite. Peely became a robot in Fortnite's Season X called P-1000. In Season 2, Chapter 2, he becomes an agent named, Agent Peely.

Name: Pet Shop
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Pet Shop is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is a trusted pet of Dio Brando and the guardian of his mansion.

Name: Piglin Brute
Summary: The Piglin Brute is a potent foe wandering and guarding the Bastion Remnant, although appearing rarely. They allow to spot the subtle differences of The Player with gold equipment, thus allowing them to eliminate The Player unlike the Piglin fellows.

Name: Pirate Robot
Summary: The Pirate Robot (海賊ロボ) is a powerful combat robot from Dragon Ball created by pirates to protect the lair where they keep their treasure.

Name: Pokaradon
Summary: Pokaradon are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G1.

Name: Pride
Summary: Pride (プライド, Puraido) was the first Homunculus that Father created, and resembles his original form. He masquerades as Selim Bradley (セリム・ブラッドレイ, Serimu Buraddorei), the adoptive son of King Bradley, and is the final one of the seven Homunculi to be revealed.

Name: Radobaan
Summary: Radobaans are Brute Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Ramona Flowers
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, weapons are higher against certain types of people, 8-B with the Power of Love, Varies with Subspace manipulation

Name: Rathalos
Key: '''Base/HC/Azure/HC Azure/Destruction Wyvern Rathalos''' | '''Flame Rathalos''' | '''Silver/HC Silver Rathalos''' | '''Dreadking Rathalos''' | '''Zenith Rathalos''' | '''Zerureusu'''
Summary: The flagship monster of the entire Monster Hunter series and one of only two monsters to have appeared in every game in the series. Rathalos is a type of monster known as a Flying Wyvern, and it uses the fire element as its primary weapon.

Name: Rathian
Key: '''Base/HC/Conflagration/Scorching Heat/Pink Rathian''' | '''HC Pink Rathian''' | '''Gold/HC Gold Rathian'''
Summary: Rathian is the female counterpart to Rathalos, and one of only two monsters, together with Rathalos, to appear in every game in the Monster Hunter franchise.

Name: Ravager (RWBY)
Summary: Ravagers are bat-like Creatures of Grimm that first appear in RWBY: After the Fall, where they are encountered by Team CFVY. They later appear in the main series at the end of "Worthy" attacking the refugees from Atlas and Mantle outside the main city of Vacuo.

Name: Rebecca Chambers
Summary: Dr. Rebecca Chambers is a former member of S.T.A.R.S., a special forces unit of the Raccoon Police Department. Despite her sweet and seemingly fragile appearance, she is a medical expert and a capable fighter. She is currently a professor at a university in Chicago, USA.

Name: Ritsu Kageyama
Summary: Ritsu Kageyama is the younger brother of Mob and a major supporting character in the anime/manga series Mob Psycho 100. While his brother is socially inept and lacking in motivation and accomplishment, Ritsu is a star student, with perfect grades and a place on the Student Council of Salt Middle School, and is generally amiable to his older brother. However, his drive to be a good brother towards Mob was discovered to be a front to his genuine fear and jealousy of his brother's power only striving to be a good sibling to avoid confronting the form that he observed his brother take when knocked out.

Name: Roxie Richter
Summary: Tier: At least High 8-C, at least High 8-C with Winifred Hailey Ninja Clones

Name: Ryo Shimazaki
Summary: Ryo Shimazaki is a minor antagonist in the World Domination Arc of Mob Psycho 100. He is an elite member of Scar, a terrorist organization bent on world domination and causing general destruction and chaos in order to leave a mark on the world. As one of its "Ultimate Five", he is easily one of the strongest members of the organization, who took the combined efforts of Claw's former Seventh Division, Teruki, Ritsu, and others before he was defeated.

Name: Scott Pilgrim
Summary: Scott William Pilgrim is the titular protagonist of the Scott Pilgrim media franchise.

Name: Seregios
Summary: Seregios are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate.

Name: Sheva Alomar
Summary: Sheva Alomar (シェバ・アローマ Sheba Arōma) is a fictional character in the Resident Evil horror video series by Capcom. She first appeared in Resident Evil 5 as one of the main characters. She was introduced in the E3 trailer and later on in E3 demo videos where she was a playable character that assists Chris Redfield throughout the game. She was introduced in 2009's Resident Evil 5 as a native African operative of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA) and a new partner of the series' veteran Chris Redfield. The character was met with mostly positive reception, but has yet not returned for any further installment of the series. Operating as part of its West African branch. She was assigned to the current mission to assist Chris Redfield, who was unfamiliar with the area. A versatile fighter with extensive experience, her ability to use firearms is on par with Chris. She is much smaller and more flexible than Chris, enabling her to perform certain maneuvers that Chris cannot. In turn, this allows Chris to throw her up to high ledges, or over large gaps in order to reach areas or objectives that a lone operative couldn't reach.

Name: Shigeo Kageyama
Summary: Shigeo Kageyama, also known as Mob, is the protagonist of the manga/anime series Mob Psycho 100.

Name: Shinichi Ozaki
Summary: Ensign Shinichi Ozaki (尾崎 真一) is a Mutant that was a member of M-Organization, which is part of the Earth Defense Force. He served under Captain Douglas Gordon aboard the Gotengo. He serves as the main protagonist of 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars.

Name: Sho Suzuki
Summary: Sho Suzuki is the son of the leader of Claw. He led a direct resistance against his father's world domination plan.

Name: Skeleton (Minecraft)
Summary: The Skeleton is a hostile mob in Minecraft. It carries a bow and attacks players at long range.

Name: Son Goku (Dragon Ball)
Key: '''Emperor Pilaf Arc''' | '''21st Budōkai''' | '''Post-Muscle Tower''' | '''Post-Korin Training''' | '''22nd Budōkai''' | '''Post-Chōshinsui''' | '''23rd Budōkai'''
Summary: Son Goku (孫そん悟ご空くう, Son Gokū?) is the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball metaseries.

Name: Staff Officer Black
Summary: Staff Officer Black (ブラック参謀) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and in the anime Dragon Ball, also making short appearances in Dragon Ball GT. He is an assistant of Commander Red and is not given much of a role until the near end of the Commander Red Saga. He is a tall, soft-spoken and quick-witted person. Black carries out Commander Red's orders and informs Commander Red of the current situations with the remaining Red Ribbon Army officers.

Name: Tao Pai Pai
Summary: Mercenary Tao (桃白白 or タオパイパイ, Tao Pai Pai) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and the anime Dragon Ball, also making two filler appearances in Dragon Ball Z. He is a highly skilled assassin-for-hire, as well as the younger brother of Master Shen. He charges a hefty price for his expert services, as he normally charges ten billion Zeni per kill, but gave Commander Red a 20th anniversary discount of five billion Zeni (fifty million in the Japanese version).

Name: Teruki Hanazawa
Summary: Teruki Hanazawa is a former antagonist and current ally of Mob. He used to be an arrogant and proud esper who believed he was the star protagonist of his life. This mainly stems from his belief that only he had the power of an esper to make his life easier. But his encounter with Mob did not just change his beliefs but also his hairstyle.

Name: Teryx
Summary: Teryxes are large Creatures of Grimm that take the appearance of a raptor-like dinosaur with pterosaur wings. They made their first appearance in the episode "As Above, So Below" of Volume 7.

Name: Tetsucabra
Summary: Tetsucabra is the first Amphibian fought in Monster Hunter 4. It is a large, frog-like monster.

Name: The Hunter (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Hunters are the playable avatar of the Monster Hunter series.

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Visitor (Fortnite)
Summary: The Visitor is a mysterious entity who had arrived to the planet via a meteorite in Season 3 of Fortnite: Battle Royale, responsible for having launched the rocket during Season 4 as well. Though nothing is known about their original intentions, it was through the launching of this rocket that a multitude of spatial and temporal rifts were opened up within the atmosphere, leading to the events in Seasons 4 - 6.

Name: Tigrex
Summary: Tigrex are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2.

Name: TNT (Minecraft)
Summary: The TNT block is an explosive in Minecraft, 9 of which are found as a trap in Desert Temples. 2 of these blocks can also be found in a rare secret room found in Woodland Mansions.

Name: Tron (TRON)
Summary: Tron is one of the main protagonists of the TRON franchise. He is a security computer program written by Alan Bradley, and in 1982 was taken prisoner by the self-aware Master Control Program and forced to play on the Game Grid. His legendary skills and devotion to the users turned him into a formidable warrior and Disc Arena master.

Name: Uragaan
Summary: Uragaans are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Ursa (RWBY)
Summary: Ursai are large, bear-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "The Emerald Forest" in Volume 1. They have appeared in two varieties: the smaller, more common Ursa Minor, and the larger, better armored and more powerful Ursa Major.

Name: Vex
Summary: A Vex is an intangibile, flying, hostile mob that is summoned in small groups by the Evoker.

Name: Vindicator
Summary: The Vindicator is an enemy appearing in the Woodland Mansions and viciously attacks any trespassers. They, alongside Pillagers and Evokers raid and attack nearby villages, and only rarely failing if The Player or Iron Golems are there to protect it.

Name: Yian Garuga
Summary: Yian Garugas are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom.

Name: Zamtrios
Summary: Zamtrios are Amphibians introduced in Monster Hunter 4.

Name: Zenaserisu
Summary: Zenaserisu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z.

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Ziraph
Summary: Introduced in RWBY: After the Fall, Ziraphs are three-headed Grimm that resembles a giraffe. Their bodies are covered in red spots that bear resemblances to a leopard and each head has two horns. They are described as being five stories tall and having razor-like plates on their legs as well as long tongues they use to ensnare people and swallow them whole.

Name: Zoglin
Summary: The Zoglin is a large, zombified boar-like hostile mob that is created when a Hoglin is brought to the overworld. It is hostile to all other mobs and players except creepers, ghasts, and other zoglins.
